    '{"id":"01KD3YFR3VAS8JVHJB2EQNKV1C","title":"Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **HubSpot Integration and CRM Data Flow**\n\nThe team aims to finalize field mappings between **HubSpot, Mulesoft, and Salesforce** to ensure smooth data transfer and automation by the end of January (09:52).\n\n- **Finalizing field approval and mapping** is critical to start sandbox development quickly, as noted by **Colin Costigan**; this will enable building email templates and workflows once compliance approves sensitive data handling (05:45).\n    - The goal is to map all necessary fields accurately, avoiding the transfer of unnecessary or sensitive data into Salesforce.\n    - **Christina Zanca** emphasized adding a \"masking needed\" column for sensitive fields to ensure proper data protection through Mulesoft.\n    - The masking approach will impact marketing’s ability to use certain data points, such as account numbers, influencing communication strategies.\n    - This setup will maintain compliance while enabling targeted marketing and lead generation.\n\n- **Customizing customer profiles** in HubSpot is confirmed feasible, allowing key fields like \"title\" to be placed prominently on contact records, supporting better user experience for retail staff (14:24).\n    - This customization ensures front-line teams see relevant information without exposing backend-only data.\n    - Permission controls can limit visibility to sensitive fields as needed.\n\n- The **API connection timeline depends on Mulesoft development updates**, which remain unclear; the team plans to clarify status in today’s meeting to keep the integration on track (40:22).\n    - Mulesoft development completion is a gating factor for enabling real-time lead creation from website forms.\n    - Once APIs are set, data flows from HubSpot form submissions through Mulesoft into Salesforce leads.\n\n- The website sitemap is designed for easy expansion to add new pages and products, supporting future growth and product launches like Zelle (42:12).\n    - This architecture allows quick updates without major rebuilds, maintaining agility in marketing content delivery.\n\n\n## **Marketing Collateral and Sales Enablement**\n\nThe team is refining a **two-sided laminated sales sheet** and related brochures to support retail and sales staff with clear, concise product information by early next quarter (17:25).\n\n- The current draft organizes products but needs restructuring into a **tree format showing primary products and associated cross-sell opportunities**, as suggested by **Christina Zanca** and supported by **Victor Garcia** (20:14).\n    - Grouping products by customer needs and linking secondary services will help staff guide customers more effectively.\n    - The format aims to fit consumer banking products on one side and business products on the other, balancing content density and readability.\n    - Color use will be muted for professionalism, and layout might be landscape to maximize space.\n\n- Differentiation between **consumer and business product sheets** is planned, with commercial mortgage and SBA lending products separated to avoid confusion in retail interactions (25:33).\n    - This distinction helps prevent sales staff from discussing products they are not licensed for.\n    - The materials will serve as quick reference tools rather than detailed marketing brochures, focusing on clarity and usability.\n\n- Compliance and branding standards guide the collateral design, including font choices and muted line drawings for a polished look (32:21).\n    - The new font is preferred and will be updated in brand guidelines.\n    - Design changes aim to maintain brand consistency and clear communication.\n\n- The **postcard marketing piece** is being redesigned to improve compliance copy spacing and layout, with the address and stamp placement aligned to postal requirements and visual clarity (33:13).\n    - Moving some copy to the front and reducing fluff like \"enjoy all benefits\" will streamline messaging.\n    - Social media logos will be added, and compliance-approved font sizes will be ensured.\n    - The postcard will highlight new branch openings and simple calls to action for local engagement.\n\n\n## **Automation and Chatbot Strategy**\n\nThe team is exploring **chatbot implementation** for the HubSpot site, balancing automation benefits with compliance requirements before proceeding (06:38).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** outlined three chatbot options: live person, AI knowledge base, or simple decision-tree logic to guide user interactions.\n    - Compliance sign-off is required to proceed, especially regarding data privacy and automated responses.\n    - The chatbot would trigger actions based on keyword detection and predefined pathways, improving customer self-service.\n\n- The decision on chatbot type will influence staffing needs, system complexity, and user experience.\n    - A live-person chatbot requires dedicated staff, while AI or limited logic bots reduce human resource demands but have different functional limits.\n    - This will impact response speed and quality of customer interactions.\n\n\n## **Project Timeline and Coordination**\n\nThe team targets **end of January for major milestones** such as field mapping finalization, API readiness, and sandbox configuration to enable HubSpot functionality (39:54).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** and **Victor Garcia** stressed the need for clear task ownership and deadlines from the GPS team to maintain momentum.\n    - Regular biweekly check-ins are suggested to track deliverables and address issues promptly.\n    - Clear communication protocols will reduce delays and confusion.\n\n- HubSpot can move quickly once fields and templates are approved, enabling fast deployment of marketing campaigns and website content (40:22).\n    - The team can adjust content and site structure as new products like Zelle launch.\n    - Feedback loops with compliance and marketing ensure content accuracy and regulatory adherence.\n\n- Social media campaign setup is pending budget approval but may start with small test promotions to validate system performance and ROI (43:33).\n    - Ad hoc campaigns can run as needed to maintain engagement.\n    - Training and onboarding for social tools will follow once setup is complete.\n\n\n## **Process Alignment and Compliance Considerations**\n\nThe team is focused on **ensuring data privacy and compliance** throughout integration, marketing, and customer engagement workflows (12:15).\n\n- Sensitive data fields will be masked in Mulesoft before reaching HubSpot or Salesforce, protecting Personally Identifiable Information (PII) (12:15).\n    - This masking maintains compliance while allowing marketing to use aggregated or anonymized data for analytics.\n    - Decisions on which fields to include or exclude depend on risk and business value.\n\n- Marketing collateral and customer communications will follow compliance guidance, including font sizes, disclaimers, and social media disclosures (38:57).\n    - Compliance reviews drive design iterations to avoid regulatory issues.\n    - The team will continue to coordinate with compliance to balance marketing goals and legal requirements.\n\n- **Christina Zanca** emphasized not limiting field mapping prematurely to avoid losing valuable data or marketing capabilities.\n    - Escalation processes will handle disputes or risk concerns to keep project progress smooth.\n    - This approach supports both innovation and caution in handling customer data.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Salesforce","Mulesoft","Brochure Design","Compliance","API Integration"],"overview":"- **HubSpot Integration Deadline:** Finalize mappings between HubSpot, Mulesoft, and Salesforce by end of January for smooth data transfer.\n\n- **Data Masking Implementation:** Add \"masking needed\" column for sensitive fields, ensuring compliance while protecting data in marketing.\n\n- **Custom Customer Profiles:** Customize HubSpot profiles to enhance user experience, showing relevant info while protecting sensitive backend data.\n\n- **Marketing Material Refinement:** Two-sided sales sheet and brochures to be completed early next quarter, emphasizing clarity and visual professionalism.\n\n- **Chatbot Options Evaluation:** Explore chatbot types for HubSpot site, balancing compliance and user experience before implementation.\n\n- **Timeline and Coordination:** Establish clear task ownership and regular check-ins to meet January milestones for integration and marketing readiness.","action_items":"\n**Victor Garcia**\nSend feedback regarding missing pages in sitemap to Colin for alignment (42:53)\nBring up account record CSV and Mulesoft integration status during GPS team meeting (30:55)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nPresent the data fields to GPS team for mapping and confirm their approach including masking needs for compliance (39:15)\nRework brochure designs into a tree hierarchy showing cross-sell opportunities and combine consumer and business content as feasible, adjusting layout to horizontal for better spacing (21:34)\nRevise postcard layout with copy redistribution to front and ensure postal compliance regarding stamp and address placement (33:13)\nUpdate brand guidelines and assets with new font choice (32:32)\nSchedule and lead GPS meeting to confirm API and Mulesoft development status and timelines (40:56)\nFinalize email template designs after stakeholder approval (39:54)\nCoordinate with printing vendors for postcard needs considering compliance feedback (33:13)\n\n**Christina Zanca**\nProvide final feedback on brochure and postcard content emphasizing compliance, simplicity, and usability for retail staff (22:04)\nReview product page content during copy editing phase and update as new products (e.g., Zelle) launch (42:53)\nParticipate in leading GPS meeting to set clear responsibilities, timelines, and deliverables (39:54)\nLead social media setup and training sessions once Jane returns; arrange for test campaign execution (43:33)\n"},"duration":44.91999816894531,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"victor garcia"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"christinazanca"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey Kyla, Good morning.","index":0,"end_time":186.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.67,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":1,"end_time":187.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was your Christmas?","index":2,"end_time":193.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.51,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It was good.","index":3,"end_time":195.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":194.629,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Family got a little sick but.","index":4,"end_time":198.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh my God, I have not met anybody that has not gotten sick within the month of December.","index":5,"end_time":208.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.39,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, everybody just got hit with some nonsense.","index":6,"end_time":212.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, I know the flu''s going around.","index":7,"end_time":214.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":212.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m hoping it''s just a cold but that''s what happens when spend Christmas with a bunch of little kids.","index":8,"end_time":220.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":214.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How many do you have?","index":9,"end_time":222.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.08,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Well, I just have one but then.","index":10,"end_time":223.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We went to my sister in law''s house, she''s got another two and then.","index":11,"end_time":227.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, family colds.","index":12,"end_time":229.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.2,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Aren''t they the best?","index":13,"end_time":230.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.4,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":14,"end_time":231.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":230.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about you?","index":15,"end_time":232.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was really good.","index":16,"end_time":234.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.7,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Refreshing to say the least.","index":17,"end_time":236.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.82,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I woke up today and I realized I''m like, what day is today?","index":18,"end_time":240.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.46,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Like, oh shit.","index":19,"end_time":241.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.98,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Oh, I work today.","index":20,"end_time":243.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.1,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":21,"end_time":244.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":243.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey guy, how''s it going?","index":22,"end_time":248.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":23,"end_time":248.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":248.18,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":24,"end_time":250.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":250.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Happy last Monday of the year.","index":25,"end_time":253.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":251.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Your hair looks fabulous by the way.","index":26,"end_time":255.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.34,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":27,"end_time":256.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":256.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just woke up like this must be nice.","index":28,"end_time":261.029,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":257.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We gotta comb.","index":29,"end_time":262.469,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.509,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We have to comb our hair as gentlemen.","index":30,"end_time":264.469,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.469,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s funny.","index":31,"end_time":269.749,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":268.789,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I assume Christina''s joining and then is Jane still out of office?","index":32,"end_time":275.349,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":271.749,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":33,"end_time":276.469,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.669,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"She had the pleasure of taking the last two weeks off of the year which was.","index":34,"end_time":280.869,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.469,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Sounds pretty amazing.","index":35,"end_time":282.709,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.509,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, let me, let me ping.","index":36,"end_time":285.869,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.789,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Christina, I know there''s a lot to go over, a ton to go over.","index":37,"end_time":292.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.869,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Did you receive that email from me this morning from the gps?","index":38,"end_time":296.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.54,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":39,"end_time":297.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.06,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, so honestly we might, it might.","index":40,"end_time":302.939,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":301.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not be an hour meeting later, but we will see.","index":41,"end_time":307.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.939,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds amazing.","index":42,"end_time":309.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.7,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All I know is that hopefully today we can kind of set the sentiment of what direction we want to go in because when I had the meeting with the GPS team, we already know what we would like to create and we already see how everything should be in the future.","index":43,"end_time":332.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.62,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The biggest thing is just getting the sign off from Christina and Betty to make sure that, you know, we''re all in alignment because we don''t have that authority yet.","index":44,"end_time":341.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.97,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, and as soon as like all the custom fields and everything are approved.","index":45,"end_time":348.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can build that out in the sandbox very quickly.","index":46,"end_time":351.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know the email templates and everything we shared, we can design those if.","index":47,"end_time":355.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''Re approved, all of that sort of stuff.","index":48,"end_time":356.569,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I was looking at, I was speaking with the customer rep from, from HubSpot.","index":49,"end_time":363.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.89,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Forgot the gentleman''s name.","index":50,"end_time":365.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.93,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I can find the email somewhere but he sent me a YouTube page called how to HubSpot and I''ve been kind of just digging through that whole thing how to develop landing pages, chatbots, how to work some of the automation stuff.","index":51,"end_time":379.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.05,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Just getting an overall feel for how the Software actually works, which is.","index":52,"end_time":383.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.59,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It''s pretty simple compared to like click funnels, go high level stuff like that.","index":53,"end_time":389.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.07,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So it''s just same.","index":54,"end_time":391.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":389.43,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Same systems just getting used to the different software.","index":55,"end_time":393.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.23,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":56,"end_time":396.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which by the way, did.","index":57,"end_time":399.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.24,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I don''t know if this was discussed, but are we looking to implement chatbots or any kind of automation?","index":58,"end_time":408.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.16,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":59,"end_time":409.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At all?","index":60,"end_time":410.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":409.92,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":61,"end_time":410.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I think a chatbot would be great.","index":62,"end_time":412.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":410.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The thing is just making sure that compliance has sign off on that.","index":63,"end_time":416.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":412.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":64,"end_time":417.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":416.56,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Because there''s a few different ways to approach chatbots.","index":65,"end_time":420.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":417.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can have like a live person if you have someone on your staff dedicated to it.","index":66,"end_time":423.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could do like a knowledge base where it''s AI and they can answer.","index":67,"end_time":427.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":423.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of questions if they have a documentation.","index":68,"end_time":429.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we can just do like very limited logic.","index":69,"end_time":432.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":429.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like they could only click a few buttons, you know, when the chatbot pops up and then it would go through that tree.","index":70,"end_time":438.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m assuming the chatbot would be based on, let''s say if it was just automation, AI.","index":71,"end_time":442.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.63,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I would assume that we would have to program that chatbot based on certain keywords that they would put in.","index":72,"end_time":447.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.47,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So it''s like if they said something along the lines of, you know, checking account, we can give them certain options depending on what we feed it.","index":73,"end_time":458.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.87,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Pretty much exactly.","index":74,"end_time":459.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":75,"end_time":459.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just have to pick which path.","index":76,"end_time":460.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":459.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to go.","index":77,"end_time":461.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So whether that''s a live person or a knowledge base that it works from.","index":78,"end_time":465.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or just a limited, like these are the only options you can click.","index":79,"end_time":469,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":80,"end_time":469.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.32,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":81,"end_time":470.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.96,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I still see that she''s in a meeting.","index":82,"end_time":476.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.88,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let me, let me give her a call.","index":83,"end_time":484.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.19,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let me see if she''ll answer.","index":84,"end_time":486.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.43,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"She didn''t answer.","index":85,"end_time":520.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.8,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let''s give it maybe two more minutes.","index":86,"end_time":523.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.6,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":87,"end_time":524.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Christina said the show joined in a few, but we can continue.","index":88,"end_time":564.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":89,"end_time":566.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know most of the design stuff.","index":90,"end_time":569.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":567.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I assume you''re just going to leave to Christina and Jane for feedback.","index":91,"end_time":573.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":92,"end_time":574.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":93,"end_time":575.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":575.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the main thing with me is just, you know, HubSpot, website, foundation type stuff.","index":94,"end_time":582.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.93,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yep.","index":95,"end_time":582.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":582.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":96,"end_time":583.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":582.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So pretty much where we''re at is we have the agenda today.","index":97,"end_time":587.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":583.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I believe you shared this with.","index":98,"end_time":590.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":589.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The GPS team as well.","index":99,"end_time":591.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":590.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":100,"end_time":593.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.55,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":101,"end_time":594.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, like I said, I mean it''s not a super lengthy agenda.","index":102,"end_time":597.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":594.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just wanted to have some good conversations and yeah, I saw that their responses came through on the other five questions that we asked.","index":103,"end_time":604.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":597.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re just gonna have to talk through like how we handle the account object.","index":104,"end_time":608.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then they said creating a lead from website forms and things like that.","index":105,"end_time":612.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":608.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would just need to.","index":106,"end_time":613.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":612.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It sounded like they were going to Set up a different flow inside of Mulesoft.","index":107,"end_time":617.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that website form fills when they''re captured in HubSpot, go into Mulesoft and.","index":108,"end_time":622.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then get sent out to Salesforce to create a lead record.","index":109,"end_time":625.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":622.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":110,"end_time":626.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.77,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So the biggest thing that they were also just kind of making sure was with all of the fields that Salesforce and HubSpot have to offer, are they looking to program every single field that you guys sent over in that Excel spreadsheet or are we taking out certain things?","index":111,"end_time":646.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, and that''s.","index":112,"end_time":648.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s kind of what the conversations are rooted around today as well.","index":113,"end_time":651.639,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":648.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So later in the agenda we have, you know, are there fields that we should avoid passing any information through?","index":114,"end_time":658.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":651.639,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we really just need to know like, you know, as we''ve had discussions around the marketing side of things, like it would be great to have this information on this person so we could send them XYZ communication.","index":115,"end_time":666.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":658.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If that''s something that they don''t want passed in HubSpot, then we will just.","index":116,"end_time":670.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":667.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Say we''re not going to create that field.","index":117,"end_time":672.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If there''s something missing, we can create that field.","index":118,"end_time":674.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":672.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But other than that, I think that, you know, we''ve got a lot in here.","index":119,"end_time":678.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":675.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, Colin, did you.","index":120,"end_time":680.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.1,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Did you mean to say passed into Salesforce?","index":121,"end_time":682.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.1,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":122,"end_time":684.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":683.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So between HubSpot and Salesforce.","index":123,"end_time":686.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":684.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re mapping the field so that.","index":124,"end_time":687.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":686.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They directly communicate well through mulesoft.","index":125,"end_time":690.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":687.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, because you said passed into HubSpot, but it should be the other way around where we''re taking the information from HubSpot into Mulesoft into Salesforce.","index":126,"end_time":698.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.54,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":127,"end_time":699.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":699.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":128,"end_time":700.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":699.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, what I meant by like passing fields is like all of these having the same labels and being mapped properly so that all the systems are.","index":129,"end_time":707.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":700.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Speaking the same language.","index":130,"end_time":708.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":131,"end_time":708.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.15,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":132,"end_time":708.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.63,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Just wanted to make sure.","index":133,"end_time":709.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yep.","index":134,"end_time":710.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":135,"end_time":711.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":710.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sorry I''m late.","index":136,"end_time":712.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":711.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just had to finish up a call.","index":137,"end_time":714.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":712.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"One thing I want to note, when we have the call leader with the.","index":138,"end_time":718.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":715.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The GPS team I want to kind of lead in with, these are the fields that we want mapped and have them give us like, how it.","index":139,"end_time":727.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":719.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How it gets done.","index":140,"end_time":728.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":727.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t want to give the.","index":141,"end_time":729.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":728.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t want to set the stage that they can kind of say yes or no.","index":142,"end_time":733.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":730.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They can choose.","index":143,"end_time":734.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":144,"end_time":735.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":735.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I think that''ll be limit.","index":145,"end_time":737.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":735.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Limiting us, you know, that there.","index":146,"end_time":739.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":737.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If.","index":147,"end_time":740.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":739.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If things are, let''s just say, a little bit more risky.","index":148,"end_time":742.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":740.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or for example, if like, like takes a little bit more work, I don''t want them just to kind of come in and say, hey, let''s just skip it.","index":149,"end_time":748.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":742.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, we''ll we''ll have a conversation around it.","index":150,"end_time":751.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":749.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If there''s an issue, then we''ll, you know, we''ll escalate.","index":151,"end_time":754.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":751.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But you know, I think these are a good, a good start.","index":152,"end_time":758.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":754.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The only thing that I think that you should do here is have a column that''ll kind of say masking needed or sensitive data.","index":153,"end_time":770.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":758.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So then they can indicate how that will be handled because that masking will have to happen probably through mulesoft.","index":154,"end_time":781.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":770.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it, the sensitive field is passed into mulesoft.","index":155,"end_time":786.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":781.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Mulestoff has I guess in some coding in it to say before it passes to HubSpot.","index":156,"end_time":792.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":786.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, you have to, you know, mass that, right?","index":157,"end_time":798.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":793.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":158,"end_time":798.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":798.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the pii.","index":159,"end_time":799.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":798.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":160,"end_time":800.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":799.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then how will the, will the masking, if any, impact our ability to use it as a kind of metric?","index":161,"end_time":809.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":800.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for example, like account number, like can we still from a marketing perspective use account number to kind of like make any, any business decisions?","index":162,"end_time":824.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":809.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like those are the conversations that we have also too, like as we go, like I don''t know if we necessarily need social and account number other than if we''re going to start to do emails where we say like account ending in the last four.","index":163,"end_time":843.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":824.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Although in my compliance research it doesn''t look like best practices to use HubSpot for kind of account related communication.","index":164,"end_time":854.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":843.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''ll have to kind of figure that out.","index":165,"end_time":856.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":854.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I think as long as it''s masked, we should be fine.","index":166,"end_time":861.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":858.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Mm, yeah.","index":167,"end_time":864.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":168,"end_time":864.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":864.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With a question.","index":169,"end_time":866.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":864.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":170,"end_time":867.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.93,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Just, just for when, when we create an account in Salesforce, would we have the ability to customize what is seen on the, on the customer''s profile based on, let''s say, specific need, for instance.","index":171,"end_time":886.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.57,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So a scenario that I bumped into with, with one of our managers is they would, they wanted to see certain information just on the first customer''s profile, but was not able to see that because it''s kind of like back end information.","index":172,"end_time":906.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Are we able to, you know, based on certain fields?","index":173,"end_time":910.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.18,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let''s just say they''re, let''s just use title, for instance.","index":174,"end_time":913.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let''s say title is not on the front customer profile.","index":175,"end_time":916.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":913.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Are we able to customize that so that we can take that information and put it on the forefront?","index":176,"end_time":920.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":916.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Are you talking about in HubSpot like viewing it from being able to see that information?","index":177,"end_time":924.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":921.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can customize.","index":178,"end_time":925.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":924.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like when you open a contact record, there''s a certain amount of fields that you can populate on the left side.","index":179,"end_time":930.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":925.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s before you view any property that''s associated with them.","index":180,"end_time":933.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":930.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can customize what that list is.","index":181,"end_time":935.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":933.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got it, okay, cool.","index":182,"end_time":938.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.21,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s it.","index":183,"end_time":939.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":938.45,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And, and every property you can just hit also view all properties and we can control who can see what, you.","index":184,"end_time":944.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":939.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Know, if we want limited vision on anything.","index":185,"end_time":946.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":186,"end_time":947.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.41,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Just making sure.","index":187,"end_time":947.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.17,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":188,"end_time":948.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":947.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Christina.","index":189,"end_time":951.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":950.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I hope you had a great holiday break.","index":190,"end_time":954.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":951.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, thank you.","index":191,"end_time":955.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":954.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I, I, I did.","index":192,"end_time":956.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":955.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How about you?","index":193,"end_time":957.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":956.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yep.","index":194,"end_time":958.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":957.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was just telling Victor, hanging out with kids over the holiday, definitely got.","index":195,"end_time":961.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":958.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A little cold or something, but what''s new?","index":196,"end_time":964.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":961.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I know.","index":197,"end_time":965.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":964.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That was, that was me a couple days before, you know, before Christmas, leading in.","index":198,"end_time":970.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":965.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And yesterday I sliced my hand open, my finger open.","index":199,"end_time":974.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":970.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s just like, why?","index":200,"end_time":976.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":974.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, you know, funny enough, I got a paper cut yesterday and I was like, I can''t remember the last time.","index":201,"end_time":981.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":977.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got a paper cut.","index":202,"end_time":982.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just, I don''t know.","index":203,"end_time":984.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":983.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The littlest pains hurt the most.","index":204,"end_time":986.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yes, yes.","index":205,"end_time":987.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":986.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I broke my husband''s new.","index":206,"end_time":989.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":987.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"He, my dad got him like the coolest Mets mug.","index":207,"end_time":993.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":989.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"He likes like a really like heavy mug for his coffee.","index":208,"end_time":996.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":993.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And you know, my, so my dad got him that as one of his, like little, you know, gag birthday presents and things like that.","index":209,"end_time":1003.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":997.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And he was, you know, using it, but it''s hand wash only and because of my bad hand, everything slips out, I have no grip and I was washing it and it just got slippery and it fell in the sink.","index":210,"end_time":1012.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1003.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It shattered and sliced.","index":211,"end_time":1014.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1012.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Literally.","index":212,"end_time":1015.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1014.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, I thought I was gonna have to go get stitches, but I just, I decided to just butterfly stitch it and hope for the best.","index":213,"end_time":1021.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1015.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, you did it yourself.","index":214,"end_time":1022.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1021.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":215,"end_time":1023.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1023.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''S what, that''s what moms do.","index":216,"end_time":1027.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1025.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m gonna need her for when a zombie apocalypse happens.","index":217,"end_time":1030.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1027.71,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I have all the disaster kind of backup medicine, stitching, you name it, go back, I''m a hypochondriac.","index":218,"end_time":1041.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1030.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then so Christina, I saw you send over the example.","index":219,"end_time":1048.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1045.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll, we''ll work that into the brochure or the double sided laminated document.","index":220,"end_time":1053.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1048.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we definitely need that to be just one sheet front and back.","index":221,"end_time":1058.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1054.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It can''t be multiple pages, right?","index":222,"end_time":1059.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":223,"end_time":1060.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1060.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, so, so there''s two, two parts of this kind of thing with the products, right.","index":224,"end_time":1064.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1060.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So one is a general brochure that kind of, you know, will be customer facing.","index":225,"end_time":1070.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1064.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":226,"end_time":1070.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1070.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s, it''s a, what we offer from a overview perspective.","index":227,"end_time":1074.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1070.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":228,"end_time":1075.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1074.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The sales, like tubes pager is more thinking about it from just that, the sales perspective.","index":229,"end_time":1084.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1076.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like what the internal team members could, you know, have at their desk as a quick reference guide, you know, for helping to identify kind of based off of the customer interaction, what do we have in a snapshot summary?","index":230,"end_time":1101.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1084.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I thought that that placement did a really good kind of, you know, overview of that.","index":231,"end_time":1107.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1101.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, I mean, obviously I know you guys were slated to get that, you know, sometime soon.","index":232,"end_time":1111.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1107.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, you know, don''t, don''t necessarily have to reinvent the wheel.","index":233,"end_time":1114.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1111.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But it could be a good, a good example, especially since that is an example that we''ll probably print and use on the cash management side because it''s basically the Fiserv team gives us those marketing assets.","index":234,"end_time":1130.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1114.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I thought like, hey, maybe it could be interesting to just make it look all uniform and consistent.","index":235,"end_time":1135.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1130.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So let me know there.","index":236,"end_time":1137.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1136.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The other thing, you know, that''s multiple pages, right.","index":237,"end_time":1141.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1137.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Depending on, you know, how you guys think about it.","index":238,"end_time":1143.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1141.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Although if we can get it into a, a trifold format, I think that that would be kind of the best case because printing will be, you know, low cost.","index":239,"end_time":1155.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1143.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":240,"end_time":1156.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1155.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":241,"end_time":1157.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1156.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And did you see the first draft that we sent over of the two sided document?","index":242,"end_time":1162.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1157.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think I did.","index":243,"end_time":1164.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1163.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Did I miss it?","index":244,"end_time":1165.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1164.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":245,"end_time":1166.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1165.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We sent over like it was like 20 things at once with all the social media and video and everything.","index":246,"end_time":1170.789,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1166.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know what, can you bring it up?","index":247,"end_time":1173.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1171.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe if you, if you don''t mind, because I''ve been cleaning out literally my inbox this whole week because I have just thousands of emails.","index":248,"end_time":1181.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1173.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m.","index":249,"end_time":1181.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1181.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m hoping I didn''t just grab something and put it into the, the file on the side like in the archives, thinking that like it was already addressed.","index":250,"end_time":1189.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1181.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Whoops, Sorry.","index":251,"end_time":1190.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1189.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, no worries.","index":252,"end_time":1191.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1190.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s.","index":253,"end_time":1196.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1196.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We could look at that.","index":254,"end_time":1197.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1196.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I had put some notes in the, the note thing for the 207.","index":255,"end_time":1205.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1197.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":256,"end_time":1205.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I wanted to go over that as well.","index":257,"end_time":1207.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Postcard.","index":258,"end_time":1207.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1207.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":259,"end_time":1208.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1207.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":260,"end_time":1208.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1208.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":261,"end_time":1215.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1214.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so this was our first pass at the two sided sales sheet.","index":262,"end_time":1223.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1218.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":263,"end_time":1224.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1223.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I like it.","index":264,"end_time":1224.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1224.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So obviously we have the print markers on here for color and everything, but.","index":265,"end_time":1229.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1225.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is actually nice.","index":266,"end_time":1235.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1233.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, look, I just sent over that other thing because I haven''t.","index":267,"end_time":1238.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1235.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I didn''t really see this, but this looks, this looks pretty good.","index":268,"end_time":1242.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1238.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What do you have there on the.","index":269,"end_time":1245.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1244.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we can change, you know, the header text or anything like that as well.","index":270,"end_time":1249.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1246.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it was pretty much just the.","index":271,"end_time":1253.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1252.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s why we reorganized the information that was in that sheet.","index":272,"end_time":1256.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1253.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just wanted to make sure before we went into design like that way that we were showing the information was fine.","index":273,"end_time":1261.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1256.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":274,"end_time":1263.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1262.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m wondering the only thing, like, do we.","index":275,"end_time":1267.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1264.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Do we set them up in more of like a tree format where it''s like, you know, what is the Leading product.","index":276,"end_time":1276.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1268.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like checking and then that''s the product.","index":277,"end_time":1279.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1276.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But then the ancillary services that would go with the checking account.","index":278,"end_time":1282.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1279.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So in other words, like you''d have to have one account to have the other.","index":279,"end_time":1285.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1282.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That might be a good, good thing to add.","index":280,"end_time":1292.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1287.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Can I make a suggestion in this case along with that?","index":281,"end_time":1297.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.71,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I think both of those things are perfect in this case because this lists out all of the products and services and the why in essence.","index":282,"end_time":1307.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1299.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And then having that what you just suggested as a second dairy that can kind of train the retail staff to know if somebody is interested in this product, then these other products can kind of lead to it.","index":283,"end_time":1320.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1307.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So I think that they both can work cohesively together.","index":284,"end_time":1323.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1320.39,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s, that''s what I mean.","index":285,"end_time":1325.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1324.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, like the goal is to have everything in like one view and, and it''ll.","index":286,"end_time":1330.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1325.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It could be up to 11 by 17 if you need to make it bigger to make, make more space.","index":287,"end_time":1335.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1330.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But it''s like maybe you have like product in a, in, in like bold and like the secondary services and not in bold.","index":288,"end_time":1349.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1335.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But then like you would have like maybe that the tree be marked as like possible cross sell opportunities.","index":289,"end_time":1358.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1349.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":290,"end_time":1358.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1358.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then you know, we can, we can go from there.","index":291,"end_time":1366.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1361.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Obviously like the, the teams will have to look at that and, and you know, make a, make a decision.","index":292,"end_time":1371.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1366.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think you can probably just say like retail, consumer banking, products and services and you know, you can get rid of description.","index":293,"end_time":1378.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1371.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":294,"end_time":1379.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1379.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":295,"end_time":1381.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1381.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll, we''ll take a stab at the tree logic.","index":296,"end_time":1384.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1381.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll definitely need to work with you guys on that.","index":297,"end_time":1386.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1384.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just of how every product intermingles.","index":298,"end_time":1388.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":299,"end_time":1389.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1388.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I''m just thinking like maybe mommy.","index":300,"end_time":1393.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1389.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"One second.","index":301,"end_time":1394.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1393.709,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe we don''t need so much color.","index":302,"end_time":1397.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1395.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe a little.","index":303,"end_time":1397.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1397.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Make a, a little bit more mute on the blue.","index":304,"end_time":1400.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1397.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think maybe a little bit too much.","index":305,"end_time":1402.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1400.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I, I think I like this is, this is the.","index":306,"end_time":1406,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1402.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":307,"end_time":1409.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1408.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m sorry, one second.","index":308,"end_time":1410.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1409.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No worries.","index":309,"end_time":1411.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1410.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh God.","index":310,"end_time":1420.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1419.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Santa brought this like big jug of like candy chocolates, lollipops and all that kind of stuff.","index":311,"end_time":1427.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1420.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s literally like I want to throw it across the room because that''s all they want to eat.","index":312,"end_time":1431.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1427.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1433.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1432.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Crazy.","index":314,"end_time":1434.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1433.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What was it gonna say?","index":315,"end_time":1437.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1435.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then just as far as like the design.","index":316,"end_time":1439.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1437.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I, I think it''s, it''s nice, it''s clean.","index":317,"end_time":1442.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1439.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is kind of just for the, your overall knowledge.","index":318,"end_time":1446.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1442.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is more like what I''m looking for.","index":319,"end_time":1447.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1446.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Things still be like kind of laid out, polished.","index":320,"end_time":1451.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1447.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like I like the background use of the, the line drawing with.","index":321,"end_time":1456.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1451.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Remember when I was saying like I Think a little bit more muted on the line drawing it would, it would still kind of bring it in but not be so much in your face.","index":322,"end_time":1464.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1456.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think that is a great way to balance it with the actual photography.","index":323,"end_time":1467.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1464.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just like you know, feedback.","index":324,"end_time":1470.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1467.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Overall I think that looks good.","index":325,"end_time":1473.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1470.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I''m wondering do we make it horizontal to give us a wider net for each row.","index":326,"end_time":1483.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1473.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So then you can kind of say maybe to Victor''s point for simply free checking you would have like the cross sell opportunities.","index":327,"end_time":1492.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1483.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You could also probably say like checking accounts and then like 1, 2, 3 options.","index":328,"end_time":1497.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1492.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because like let''s just say they''re interested in like lead with what their cut, their needs are.","index":329,"end_time":1504.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1498.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like maybe it''s like need, you know, operate, operation, account for something like that.","index":330,"end_time":1511.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1504.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":331,"end_time":1511.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1511.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Whatever we would call it or savings retirement.","index":332,"end_time":1515.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1512.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe start with the need, then lead into the product and the options and then you can lead into like the cr.","index":333,"end_time":1526.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1516.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The, the cross sells.","index":334,"end_time":1527.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1526.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":335,"end_time":1527.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1527.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":336,"end_time":1529.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1529.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":337,"end_time":1529.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1529.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One we were debating internally going landscape with this.","index":338,"end_time":1532.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1529.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":339,"end_time":1533.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1533.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So yeah, that would definitely free up some more space.","index":340,"end_time":1535.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1533.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":341,"end_time":1536.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1536.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think that that that is, is good.","index":342,"end_time":1539.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1536.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, obviously we would need one for business.","index":343,"end_time":1545.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1540.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe it''s.","index":344,"end_time":1546.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1545.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m trying to think like how.","index":345,"end_time":1550.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1548.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Do.","index":346,"end_time":1553.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1552.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do one kind of consumer banking and then one kind of can mortgage.","index":347,"end_time":1565.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1553.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I, I don''t know because kind of commercial is a little bit weird because they''re not going to have those interactions in, in branch.","index":348,"end_time":1573.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1566.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I have to kind of think about how we''re gonna.","index":349,"end_time":1576.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1574.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But at the same time too, if the retail team, you know, they, they, they''re having those conversations, at least they have something in front of them to start that conversation and then lead them to whoever it is that they need to have that conversation with.","index":350,"end_time":1592.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1579.56,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Say oh, I remember speaking with the banker about this product.","index":351,"end_time":1595.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1592.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"What is this?","index":352,"end_time":1596.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1595.53,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, no, you''re, you''re, you''re right.","index":353,"end_time":1599.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1597.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just want to make sure that it doesn''t lead the banker to have conversations that they''re not licensed to have with the, you know, with given some of the stuff.","index":354,"end_time":1606.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1599.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But no, but you''re right.","index":355,"end_time":1607.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1606.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like they should know what we, you know, what we offer.","index":356,"end_time":1611.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1607.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You can, you can almost probably make business.","index":357,"end_time":1619.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1616.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You can probably do residential mortgages and like the Prosper loans and all that on the consumer and probably the commercial mortgages and the.","index":358,"end_time":1633.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1622.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No.","index":359,"end_time":1637.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1637.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Prosper would be on the, the business.","index":360,"end_time":1639.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1637.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So commercials, the small business accounts, SBA lending, like those types of things on the business.","index":361,"end_time":1645.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1639.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"One your task I think and by making it horizontal is how do you fit all of consumer on one side and all of business on the other.","index":362,"end_time":1656.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1646.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe we just have to, you know, tighten up some of the, the bullets or by kind of lumping the products together, it might free up some rows.","index":363,"end_time":1673.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1659.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that would be my only honest feedback at this, at this point.","index":364,"end_time":1676.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1673.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if you could rework that, you know, I think that that would be a good pass to then send it off to the team.","index":365,"end_time":1683.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1676.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":366,"end_time":1684.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1684.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But overall, I think this looks really nice.","index":367,"end_time":1688.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1685.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":368,"end_time":1689.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1689.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this was, we had a two.","index":369,"end_time":1691.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1689.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had a front and back for business and then a front and back for consumers.","index":370,"end_time":1694.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1691.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll look for opportunities to consolidate to get that into one.","index":371,"end_time":1697.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1694.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And maybe you can''t.","index":372,"end_time":1698.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1697.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And maybe it''s just one, one for consumer and one for, you know, for, for business.","index":373,"end_time":1703.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1698.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And you know, let me, let me know in all honesty, if, like, if, if, if there''s just not enough room, maybe I could position it that we have two so.","index":374,"end_time":1713.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1703.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":375,"end_time":1714.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1713.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":376,"end_time":1714.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1714.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also had the trifold and so that was going through that as well.","index":377,"end_time":1723.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1714.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it sounds like we want this a little bit more customer facing instead of information.","index":378,"end_time":1728.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1724.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I, I, I, this is, this needs to be more.","index":379,"end_time":1735.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1731.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hold on one second.","index":380,"end_time":1738.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1737.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This needs to be more like in, in groups.","index":381,"end_time":1747.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1744.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Not, not you, you don''t need the, the benefits.","index":382,"end_time":1751.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1747.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The.","index":383,"end_time":1751.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1751.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Why, like who is this available for?","index":384,"end_time":1753.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1751.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, this is just like maybe a little bit about ponsse.","index":385,"end_time":1759.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1753.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The what we offer like a list out and maybe a few features and benefits and you can, you know, you can set it up in sections.","index":386,"end_time":1770.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1759.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe here you would have instead of description of products and services, you would just, you know, say, you know, onse bank, you know, products and services.","index":387,"end_time":1781.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1770.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Description is kind of redundant.","index":388,"end_time":1784.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1782.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yep.","index":389,"end_time":1785.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1784.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''m just gonna step away for one second.","index":390,"end_time":1787.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1785.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yep.","index":391,"end_time":1788.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1788.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I guess while Christine is away, as far as our timeline goes.","index":392,"end_time":1803.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1798.8,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let me, let me bring that up on my end.","index":393,"end_time":1806.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1804.8,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"What are we looking like for.","index":394,"end_time":1809.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1808.07,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We have the site map already that you guys sent us and we''re working on the configuration now for the sandbox and HubSpot.","index":395,"end_time":1818.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1810.63,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"What day do we have as the, as the test or the show?","index":396,"end_time":1823.349,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1819.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"For both.","index":397,"end_time":1824.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1823.35,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":398,"end_time":1825.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1824.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the things that we''re waiting on, I''m hoping will be just confirmed and finalized in our meeting today.","index":399,"end_time":1830.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1825.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that was just.","index":400,"end_time":1831.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1830.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There was mention of mulesoft development happening and we wanted to make sure that that was all taken care of so that the APIs can be set up.","index":401,"end_time":1838.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1831.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"By the GTS team.","index":402,"end_time":1840.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1838.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also that sample CSV and.","index":403,"end_time":1844.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1840.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I saw you included that in your email, but I didn''t see any response from them about that.","index":404,"end_time":1848.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1844.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that was The, So we''ll bring.","index":405,"end_time":1854.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1851.46,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Account record or something like that.","index":406,"end_time":1856.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1855.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":407,"end_time":1858.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1857.14,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":408,"end_time":1862.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1861.54,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll bring that up in today''s meeting.","index":409,"end_time":1863.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1862.23,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We''ll be.","index":410,"end_time":1864.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1863.55,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And then just any product or service.","index":411,"end_time":1867.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1865.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Collateral from the team so that we can draft all the website content and move into design and build.","index":412,"end_time":1871.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1867.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":413,"end_time":1873.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1872.39,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Sorry, guys.","index":414,"end_time":1901.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1900.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, no worries.","index":415,"end_time":1902.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1901.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Christina, I know that you weren''t able to join the meeting last week, but we did like Jane had asked, for example, showing like old font versus new font with the headline.","index":416,"end_time":1910.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1903.599,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have those examples and everything like that.","index":417,"end_time":1912.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1910.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then all of the different templates and everything we''ve built out as well.","index":418,"end_time":1915.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1912.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me go, go back to the first one.","index":419,"end_time":1921.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1919.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just the side by side comparison.","index":420,"end_time":1923.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1921.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"She was really focused, I think on.","index":421,"end_time":1927.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1925.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The line between the H. So this is the old font over here.","index":422,"end_time":1932.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1927.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Honestly, I mean, I, I, I, I like, I like the new, the new font.","index":423,"end_time":1938.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1932.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t like it when it''s in the ampersand.","index":424,"end_time":1940.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1938.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I saw that.","index":425,"end_time":1941.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1941.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":426,"end_time":1941.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1941.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And maybe the, so maybe just honestly go with the new font.","index":427,"end_time":1944.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1941.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, the, the old font, it''s, it''s like one of those, like it.","index":428,"end_time":1950.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1945.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is, that''s not worth the squeeze.","index":429,"end_time":1952.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1950.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, just, just go with that.","index":430,"end_time":1954.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1952.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The only thing that will need for you to do is just update the brand guideline with the new font then if you don''t mind.","index":431,"end_time":1959.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1954.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yep.","index":432,"end_time":1960.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1959.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And any of the, the assets.","index":433,"end_time":1962.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1960.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I, and I have to say I, I think I really, really like the line drawings when it''s a little bit more on the opac.","index":434,"end_time":1971.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1963.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"On the opacity.","index":435,"end_time":1972.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1971.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":436,"end_time":1972.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1972.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or yeah.","index":437,"end_time":1974.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1973.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When there''s like a fade in.","index":438,"end_time":1976.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1974.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":439,"end_time":1976.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1976.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that, I mean, I think that looks really nice combined.","index":440,"end_time":1979.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1976.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, these are starting to come together really nicely.","index":441,"end_time":1986.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1982.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, yeah, I''m excited to kind of see how we, we could take this a little bit further.","index":442,"end_time":1993.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1987.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I was out last few days, so I was going through the feedback on the postcard.","index":443,"end_time":1997.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1993.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m actually talking to new print vendors now because of the, with the long compliance copy, we''ll just need to kind of reshape and redesign a little bit.","index":444,"end_time":2007.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1997.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So where we''re going to have the address is going to be in this like bottom right and then a stamp up here.","index":445,"end_time":2014.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2007.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I''m thinking is taking one.","index":446,"end_time":2016.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2014.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of these and moving them to the front so that we have some more space for.","index":447,"end_time":2020.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2016.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because this is just very crowded.","index":448,"end_time":2022.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2020.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but, but don''t normal postcards have it like in the, in the middle, on the, on the right.","index":449,"end_time":2028.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2023.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":450,"end_time":2028.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2028.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like every, so I''m looking at like vistaprint, Tara Dell like everyone that the post office works with and they.","index":451,"end_time":2035.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2028.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All have it in different spots on their templates.","index":452,"end_time":2037.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2035.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, can we, can we pick one that has it in the middle?","index":453,"end_time":2041.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2038.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because then what I, I, I think it''s like, then you can take, Then.","index":454,"end_time":2045.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2041.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You want to do something like this.","index":455,"end_time":2046.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2045.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":456,"end_time":2047.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2047.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then, you know, you could then span, you know, you can span the top, you know, open a little bit.","index":457,"end_time":2055.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2047.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Whoops.","index":458,"end_time":2059.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2058.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"See, like also too, like, how do you maybe take some of the copy on the front and put it, I mean, the copy on this, this slide and put it on the front?","index":459,"end_time":2068.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2059.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I was thinking.","index":460,"end_time":2069.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2068.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, can you go to the front for a second?","index":461,"end_time":2074.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2069.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I, and I, I would even say, like, you don''t need, I don''t think you need Ponce bank in wood.","index":462,"end_time":2088.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2080.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We don''t really put any.","index":463,"end_time":2090.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2088.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I forgot to mention that we don''t really put the, you know, addresses, like under our logo.","index":464,"end_time":2095.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2090.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I would even say put the logo like literally as far up left as you can go and then right.","index":465,"end_time":2101.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2095.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then, you know, maybe even have the.","index":466,"end_time":2109.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2101.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, you''ll probably need an asterisk with near, like, you know, like, see terms and conditions on the other side.","index":467,"end_time":2124.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2116.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are you saying like a little tiny line of copy?","index":468,"end_time":2132.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2129.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":469,"end_time":2132.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2132.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"By the like 150.","index":470,"end_time":2133.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2132.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because it''s probably the.","index":471,"end_time":2134.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2133.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then are you, are you, is it too much blue?","index":472,"end_time":2143.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2137.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What you think would be better, but like with just like a, A smaller kind of vertical, I mean, horizontal kind of block across the, the, the photo.","index":473,"end_time":2151.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2143.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or what you can do is get some of the address details or, or some of the.","index":474,"end_time":2158.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2152.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I was thinking about moving like this copy to the front and redesigning it a little bit.","index":475,"end_time":2163.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2159,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we just have more space.","index":476,"end_time":2164.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2163.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So even if we do go and find someone that''s going to stamp it in the middle with the address and.","index":477,"end_time":2169.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2164.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can do this.","index":478,"end_time":2170.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2169.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is still like, if we''re able to spread these out a little bit more and move this to the front, I think it''ll look a lot cleaner.","index":479,"end_time":2175.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2170.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":480,"end_time":2177.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2176.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then another thing, like, I''m open to, like, maybe we just get rid of, enjoy all the benefits.","index":481,"end_time":2182.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2177.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because they''re like fluff anyway.","index":482,"end_time":2186.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2182.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like.","index":483,"end_time":2186.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2186.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":484,"end_time":2186.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2186.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, another, another thing you can do is.","index":485,"end_time":2193.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2188.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, how do you say, like now open in your neighborhood on the front and then stop by our inward location or just now open in, in wood.","index":486,"end_time":2210.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2198.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":487,"end_time":2210.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2210.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is like a header and like open a free checking.","index":488,"end_time":2213.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2210.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":489,"end_time":2214.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2213.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then so that takes the top whole section away.","index":490,"end_time":2217.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2214.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then, you know, maybe it''s stopped by our new location, you know, and speak with the banker today and then you have just that there.","index":491,"end_time":2234.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2221.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just rework it and, and see the.","index":492,"end_time":2236.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2234.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Potentially maybe getting rid of.","index":493,"end_time":2239.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2238.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Rid of the first section is better.","index":494,"end_time":2242.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2239.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Leave the, the benefits I would add though, like community, you know, community service, you know, like personalized service, stuff like that.","index":495,"end_time":2251.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2242.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":496,"end_time":2252.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2251.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I was, I just wanted to clarify on that comment because I saw that.","index":497,"end_time":2255.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2252.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the copy that you want that was to replace, stop by or new location today or to add into that.","index":498,"end_time":2259.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2255.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Section because you had said like product and service and support.","index":499,"end_time":2265.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2259.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s, I think that''s good.","index":500,"end_time":2268.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2266.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then we had reworked this copy as well.","index":501,"end_time":2270.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2269.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Try no monthly maintenance fees or minimum balances to like, you know, consolidate some of the, you know, free debit card, you know, or you can say free debit card and you know, digital, you know, digital banking tools.","index":502,"end_time":2291.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2270.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":503,"end_time":2292.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2291.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then you can say, you know, mobile banking with, you know.","index":504,"end_time":2297.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2293.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll.","index":505,"end_time":2297.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2297.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll figure out some ways to reorganize that.","index":506,"end_time":2300.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2297.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":507,"end_time":2301.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2300.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, yeah, we reworked this because it was speaking about the opening, which was inaccurate.","index":508,"end_time":2305.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2301.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just changed that copy.","index":509,"end_time":2307.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2305.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if we''re removing this or moving it to the front anyway, we''ll play around with some of that.","index":510,"end_time":2310.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2307.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":511,"end_time":2311.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2311.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, so I think that, you know, I think that that''s good.","index":512,"end_time":2315.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2312.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You can also maybe like just justify across the block all the compliance.","index":513,"end_time":2321.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2315.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s left justified.","index":514,"end_time":2322.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2321.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right, justified in.","index":515,"end_time":2323.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2322.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In a block to.","index":516,"end_time":2324.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2323.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To kind of make that.","index":517,"end_time":2326.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2324.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I think the member fdic, all those logos could be a little smaller if you needed to it to be.","index":518,"end_time":2332.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2326.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And the only thing I see is missing is the social.","index":519,"end_time":2334.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2332.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The social logos.","index":520,"end_time":2335.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2334.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":521,"end_time":2337.559,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2337,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we had large enlarged these because we had them at like nine point.","index":522,"end_time":2343.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2340.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then when we sent it to compliance they said that it was too small.","index":523,"end_time":2346.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2343.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I think that might have just been.","index":524,"end_time":2347.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2346.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe it was like instead of a PDF it was a PNG or something that was shared with them.","index":525,"end_time":2352.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2349.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it came through a little different.","index":526,"end_time":2353.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2352.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":527,"end_time":2355.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2353.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":528,"end_time":2356.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2355.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, we will rework.","index":529,"end_time":2357.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2356.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That sounds like we are good.","index":530,"end_time":2359.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2357.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, we''ll start with.","index":531,"end_time":2361.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2359.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In the conversation, Christina, to what you said of, you know, these are the fields that we would like to populate and have communicate between HubSpot, Mulesoft and Salesforce as that connection works and then just go through the rest of our questions and they answered a few of them already.","index":532,"end_time":2378.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2361.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that''ll speed this along.","index":533,"end_time":2380.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2378.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But pretty much what we''re at is if we''re approved to start building all of this out in the sandbox, you know, if they''re good with all the fields and everything, then we''re all good.","index":534,"end_time":2388.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2380.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also we sent over the email designs for review and approval and.","index":535,"end_time":2392.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2388.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can build those whenever they''re ready.","index":536,"end_time":2394.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2392.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that''s great.","index":537,"end_time":2396.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2394.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"A lot of good progress.","index":538,"end_time":2398.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2397.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think at this point.","index":539,"end_time":2399.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2398.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Today''s meeting hopefully will, you know, confirm a lot of, a lot of those things.","index":540,"end_time":2404.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2400.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think, you know, the only thing that we should do is make sure that the GPS team is clear on, you know, what their responsibilities are, what when they need to do things by when and what like the timeline is, because, you know, it''s already going to be, I feel like the end of January before we know it.","index":541,"end_time":2422.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2404.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I know.","index":542,"end_time":2424.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2422.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can move pretty quickly in HubSpot, so, you know, that''s good with me.","index":543,"end_time":2429.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2424.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And one thing I was asking, you know, in our conversations over the past month or two, there was mention of like mulesoft getting a development update.","index":544,"end_time":2438.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2430.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Has there been any update there that I, I don''t.","index":545,"end_time":2444.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2439.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, there was, there''s a mention of like a, an update happening to the development environment there and that was going to impact our API connection date essentially.","index":546,"end_time":2453.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2444.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can just ask them that.","index":547,"end_time":2454.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2453.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Today if anything''s happening there or.","index":548,"end_time":2456.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2454.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, honestly, on, on these types of conversations, I, I leave it to you guys to, to lead it and get as much information as, you know, you need from the team.","index":549,"end_time":2464.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2456.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, we''re just there as kind of the, the guide if anything get, you know, gets haywire or if we need any clarifications.","index":550,"end_time":2472.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2465.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But you know, I think that we should definitely have that alignment kind of, if not on the call by like the end of the, the week and then more clear touch bases with the team, maybe even bi weekly to, to go over like deliverables.","index":551,"end_time":2488.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2472.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is that because of the weather?","index":552,"end_time":2489.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2488.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Look, I''m in a meeting.","index":553,"end_time":2491.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2489.9,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"What was I going to say the last thing?","index":554,"end_time":2494.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2492.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just like, are we good?","index":555,"end_time":2497.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2496.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are we in a good place with the website as well?","index":556,"end_time":2500.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2497.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I was just showing that to Victor.","index":557,"end_time":2501.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2500.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re just waiting on any other information around products and we''re drafting the pages and then we can design and develop.","index":558,"end_time":2507.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2501.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if there''s any other.","index":559,"end_time":2509.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2508.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At this point, just consider that you have, you know, everything that was shared with us when we go through like the, you know, the copy editing phase.","index":560,"end_time":2518.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2509.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, obviously when Zelle comes out, we''ll have stuff to add.","index":561,"end_time":2521.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2518.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When, you know, with the team, when the team reviews their, their product pages, they''ll probably have stuff to add.","index":562,"end_time":2527.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2521.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, you know, we might have to, you know, to kind of just lightly configure that.","index":563,"end_time":2532.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2527.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":564,"end_time":2533.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2532.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m not sure if you saw the sitemap that we sent over, but the way that we built that is it''s positioned to just expand as we add new pages, new sections, new offers, everything like that.","index":565,"end_time":2541.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2533.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that, that, that''s great.","index":566,"end_time":2543.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2541.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Christina, really quick, there was a few things that was sent over to you.","index":567,"end_time":2548.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2544.4,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I didn''t know if you wanted to review it first before we send it over to mid, but it was a compliment on the site.","index":568,"end_time":2556.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2549.2,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Matt.","index":569,"end_time":2556.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2556.36,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"There were certain things that were missed because they''re not on the actual website itself.","index":570,"end_time":2562,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2556.72,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You kind of have to search through it or you have to give that link.","index":571,"end_time":2565.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2562.16,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Like cannabis, for instance.","index":572,"end_time":2568.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2566.89,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Cannabis.","index":573,"end_time":2568.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2568.17,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We created that webpage, but we didn''t put that on the website itself.","index":574,"end_time":2572.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2569.61,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So they''re like, they like those pages.","index":575,"end_time":2575.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2573.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t need to, I don''t need to review any of those.","index":576,"end_time":2578.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2575.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Send all that information over.","index":577,"end_time":2580.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2578.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When I review it is when we actually start to go through the review process of the content.","index":578,"end_time":2584.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2580.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, like if, you know, page hierarchy, that''s, that should be there.","index":579,"end_time":2588.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2585.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like the mission driven page and all that.","index":580,"end_time":2590.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2588.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yes.","index":581,"end_time":2590.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2590.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And okay, um, Colin, I''ll send that over to you right now within that same sitemap thread that you sent over so that we can keep everything in line.","index":582,"end_time":2600.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2590.49,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":583,"end_time":2601.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2600.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I know we''re 10 minutes over, so I appreciate you guys time.","index":584,"end_time":2606.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2603.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything that we didn''t cover today that.","index":585,"end_time":2609.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2608.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''Re hoping to chat through before we have our conversation later?","index":586,"end_time":2612.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2609.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think when Gene comes back, we''ll want to just have a dedicated kind of conversation around just the social setup and what training we need and you know, how to start to set some of those things up.","index":587,"end_time":2623.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2613.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I know our campaign, you know, retainer is kind of a little bit delayed because of the budget and we want to get things set up first.","index":588,"end_time":2631.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2624.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But you know, if we do need to run any like miscellaneous things, we''ll just do it as a, like an ad hoc basis.","index":589,"end_time":2637.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2631.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I, I was telling Betty that, you know, it could be interesting to maybe just run a test use case, even if it''s something small like we, we did ourselves in the beginning of the year upon Bank Direct, you know, CD promotion just to see how, you know, we''re, we''re start to show some results and some utilization of the system.","index":590,"end_time":2662.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2637.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yep.","index":591,"end_time":2663.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2663.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, and then if there''s anything else that we contracted for within HubSpot that we need to put on our radar in, in terms of getting up to speed and set up and using, just, just let us know.","index":592,"end_time":2677.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2664.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yep.","index":593,"end_time":2678.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2677.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll do.","index":594,"end_time":2678.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2678.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":595,"end_time":2680.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2679.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":596,"end_time":2680.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2680.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think that''s it.","index":597,"end_time":2681.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2680.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, well, we will see you guys in, like, an hour and a half.","index":598,"end_time":2684.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2681.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":599,"end_time":2685.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2685.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":600,"end_time":2685.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2685.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":601,"end_time":2686.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2685.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":602,"end_time":2687.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2686.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":603,"end_time":2687.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2687.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"}],"dateString":"2025-12-29T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85439302813?pwd=qMBHtkNo4lURIrnTCVFhLG0k15ZQca.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,jane.trachet@poncebank.net,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,victor.garcia@poncebank.net,rebecca.cruz@poncebank.net,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,christina.zanca@poncebank.net","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","jane.trachet@poncebank.net","victor.garcia@poncebank.net","rebecca.cruz@poncebank.net","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","christina.zanca@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KD3YFR3VAS8JVHJB2EQNKV1C","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Agreed to move forward with HubSpot custom fields pending Christina and Betty’s final approval.","Planned chatbot deployment variants discussed; compliance review will determine final implementation method.","Christina requested masking tagging for PII fields passed via Mulesoft to HubSpot and Salesforce.","Website sitemaps and materials finalized; teams aligned on page hierarchy and future content slots.","Sales collateral feedback collected; updates include layout shifts, simplified copy, and cross-sell mapping."],"highlights":[{"quote":"All I know is that hopefully today we can kind of set the sentiment of what direction we want to go in","speaker":"victor garcia"},{"quote":"A lot of good progress. I think at this point. Today''s meeting hopefully will confirm a lot of those things.","speaker":"christinazanca"},{"quote":"Pretty much what we''re at is if we''re approved to start building all of this out in the sandbox... then we''re all good.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["delivery","integration","collateral","website","automation"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-29T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **HubSpot Integration and CRM Data Flow**\n\nThe team aims to finalize field mappings between **HubSpot, Mulesoft, and Salesforce** to ensure smooth data transfer and automation by the end of January (09:52).\n\n- **Finalizing field approval and mapping** is critical to start sandbox development quickly, as noted by **Colin Costigan**; this will enable building email templates and workflows once compliance approves sensitive data handling (05:45).\n    - The goal is to map all necessary fields accurately, avoiding the transfer of unnecessary or sensitive data into Salesforce.\n    - **Christina Zanca** emphasized adding a \"masking needed\" column for sensitive fields to ensure proper data protection through Mulesoft.\n    - The masking approach will impact marketing’s ability to use certain data points, such as account numbers, influencing communication strategies.\n    - This setup will maintain compliance while enabling targeted marketing and lead generation.\n\n- **Customizing customer profiles** in HubSpot is confirmed feasible, allowing key fields like \"title\" to be placed prominently on contact records, supporting better user experience for retail staff (14:24).\n    - This customization ensures front-line teams see relevant information without exposing backend-only data.\n    - Permission controls can limit visibility to sensitive fields as needed.\n\n- The **API connection timeline depends on Mulesoft development updates**, which remain unclear; the team plans to clarify status in today’s meeting to keep the integration on track (40:22).\n    - Mulesoft development completion is a gating factor for enabling real-time lead creation from website forms.\n    - Once APIs are set, data flows from HubSpot form submissions through Mulesoft into Salesforce leads.\n\n- The website sitemap is designed for easy expansion to add new pages and products, supporting future growth and product launches like Zelle (42:12).\n    - This architecture allows quick updates without major rebuilds, maintaining agility in marketing content delivery.\n\n\n## **Marketing Collateral and Sales Enablement**\n\nThe team is refining a **two-sided laminated sales sheet** and related brochures to support retail and sales staff with clear, concise product information by early next quarter (17:25).\n\n- The current draft organizes products but needs restructuring into a **tree format showing primary products and associated cross-sell opportunities**, as suggested by **Christina Zanca** and supported by **Victor Garcia** (20:14).\n    - Grouping products by customer needs and linking secondary services will help staff guide customers more effectively.\n    - The format aims to fit consumer banking products on one side and business products on the other, balancing content density and readability.\n    - Color use will be muted for professionalism, and layout might be landscape to maximize space.\n\n- Differentiation between **consumer and business product sheets** is planned, with commercial mortgage and SBA lending products separated to avoid confusion in retail interactions (25:33).\n    - This distinction helps prevent sales staff from discussing products they are not licensed for.\n    - The materials will serve as quick reference tools rather than detailed marketing brochures, focusing on clarity and usability.\n\n- Compliance and branding standards guide the collateral design, including font choices and muted line drawings for a polished look (32:21).\n    - The new font is preferred and will be updated in brand guidelines.\n    - Design changes aim to maintain brand consistency and clear communication.\n\n- The **postcard marketing piece** is being redesigned to improve compliance copy spacing and layout, with the address and stamp placement aligned to postal requirements and visual clarity (33:13).\n    - Moving some copy to the front and reducing fluff like \"enjoy all benefits\" will streamline messaging.\n    - Social media logos will be added, and compliance-approved font sizes will be ensured.\n    - The postcard will highlight new branch openings and simple calls to action for local engagement.\n\n\n## **Automation and Chatbot Strategy**\n\nThe team is exploring **chatbot implementation** for the HubSpot site, balancing automation benefits with compliance requirements before proceeding (06:38).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** outlined three chatbot options: live person, AI knowledge base, or simple decision-tree logic to guide user interactions.\n    - Compliance sign-off is required to proceed, especially regarding data privacy and automated responses.\n    - The chatbot would trigger actions based on keyword detection and predefined pathways, improving customer self-service.\n\n- The decision on chatbot type will influence staffing needs, system complexity, and user experience.\n    - A live-person chatbot requires dedicated staff, while AI or limited logic bots reduce human resource demands but have different functional limits.\n    - This will impact response speed and quality of customer interactions.\n\n\n## **Project Timeline and Coordination**\n\nThe team targets **end of January for major milestones** such as field mapping finalization, API readiness, and sandbox configuration to enable HubSpot functionality (39:54).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** and **Victor Garcia** stressed the need for clear task ownership and deadlines from the GPS team to maintain momentum.\n    - Regular biweekly check-ins are suggested to track deliverables and address issues promptly.\n    - Clear communication protocols will reduce delays and confusion.\n\n- HubSpot can move quickly once fields and templates are approved, enabling fast deployment of marketing campaigns and website content (40:22).\n    - The team can adjust content and site structure as new products like Zelle launch.\n    - Feedback loops with compliance and marketing ensure content accuracy and regulatory adherence.\n\n- Social media campaign setup is pending budget approval but may start with small test promotions to validate system performance and ROI (43:33).\n    - Ad hoc campaigns can run as needed to maintain engagement.\n    - Training and onboarding for social tools will follow once setup is complete.\n\n\n## **Process Alignment and Compliance Considerations**\n\nThe team is focused on **ensuring data privacy and compliance** throughout integration, marketing, and customer engagement workflows (12:15).\n\n- Sensitive data fields will be masked in Mulesoft before reaching HubSpot or Salesforce, protecting Personally Identifiable Information (PII) (12:15).\n    - This masking maintains compliance while allowing marketing to use aggregated or anonymized data for analytics.\n    - Decisions on which fields to include or exclude depend on risk and business value.\n\n- Marketing collateral and customer communications will follow compliance guidance, including font sizes, disclaimers, and social media disclosures (38:57).\n    - Compliance reviews drive design iterations to avoid regulatory issues.\n    - The team will continue to coordinate with compliance to balance marketing goals and legal requirements.\n\n- **Christina Zanca** emphasized not limiting field mapping prematurely to avoid losing valuable data or marketing capabilities.\n    - Escalation processes will handle disputes or risk concerns to keep project progress smooth.\n    - This approach supports both innovation and caution in handling customer data.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Salesforce","Mulesoft","Brochure Design","Compliance","API Integration"],"overview":"- **HubSpot Integration Deadline:** Finalize mappings between HubSpot, Mulesoft, and Salesforce by end of January for smooth data transfer.\n\n- **Data Masking Implementation:** Add \"masking needed\" column for sensitive fields, ensuring compliance while protecting data in marketing.\n\n- **Custom Customer Profiles:** Customize HubSpot profiles to enhance user experience, showing relevant info while protecting sensitive backend data.\n\n- **Marketing Material Refinement:** Two-sided sales sheet and brochures to be completed early next quarter, emphasizing clarity and visual professionalism.\n\n- **Chatbot Options Evaluation:** Explore chatbot types for HubSpot site, balancing compliance and user experience before implementation.\n\n- **Timeline and Coordination:** Establish clear task ownership and regular check-ins to meet January milestones for integration and marketing readiness.","action_items":"\n**Victor Garcia**\nSend feedback regarding missing pages in sitemap to Colin for alignment (42:53)\nBring up account record CSV and Mulesoft integration status during GPS team meeting (30:55)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nPresent the data fields to GPS team for mapping and confirm their approach including masking needs for compliance (39:15)\nRework brochure designs into a tree hierarchy showing cross-sell opportunities and combine consumer and business content as feasible, adjusting layout to horizontal for better spacing (21:34)\nRevise postcard layout with copy redistribution to front and ensure postal compliance regarding stamp and address placement (33:13)\nUpdate brand guidelines and assets with new font choice (32:32)\nSchedule and lead GPS meeting to confirm API and Mulesoft development status and timelines (40:56)\nFinalize email template designs after stakeholder approval (39:54)\nCoordinate with printing vendors for postcard needs considering compliance feedback (33:13)\n\n**Christina Zanca**\nProvide final feedback on brochure and postcard content emphasizing compliance, simplicity, and usability for retail staff (22:04)\nReview product page content during copy editing phase and update as new products (e.g., Zelle) launch (42:53)\nParticipate in leading GPS meeting to set clear responsibilities, timelines, and deliverables (39:54)\nLead social media setup and training sessions once Jane returns; arrange for test campaign execution (43:33)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"fd2ec9b6-8771-43c7-8063-cf0fee89080e","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
