    '{"id":"01KD5SAAFFFFET5E6DZ7JZSX8S","title":"Ponce Bank // MiD: HubSpot & GPS Team","summary":{"notes":"## **Data Integration and Field Mapping**\n\nThe team agreed on a clear plan to map Salesforce account and contact data to HubSpot with precise transformation rules to ensure clean, consistent data flow (04:58).\n\n- **Salesforce account objects will be split into company and contact records in HubSpot**, differentiated by Salesforce record types to keep data organized and manageable (05:42).\n    - Contacts and companies will be linked logically in HubSpot to maintain relationship context.\n    - Gabriel explained that Mulesoft will handle most data transformations, especially for IDs, date-time fields, and picklist values, to align with HubSpot’s requirements.\n    - Christina emphasized the need to handle transformations both ways—from Salesforce to HubSpot and vice versa—for lead and campaign data sync.\n    - Data masking for sensitive fields like Social Security numbers will be applied via Mulesoft, per Christina and Gabriel, to comply with privacy needs.\n- The existing spreadsheet with **field mappings will be refined, color-coded, and scrubbed** to identify essential fields, questionable ones, and those needing masking, enabling a targeted data subset for marketing use (16:36).\n    - Betty highlighted the removal of sensitive fields like gender identity to avoid legal risks.\n    - Gabriel will review the list for any additional masking needs and provide descriptions for unclear fields.\n    - Christina and Victor will finalize field priorities and flag any outstanding questions.\n- The team confirmed **HubSpot supports custom identifiers and picklist options**, allowing smooth integration with Salesforce’s existing data structure (14:49).\n- Unique identification will primarily rely on **email addresses**, but including the **Clear Touch external ID** as a secondary unique key was recommended by Betty and Gabriel to improve matching accuracy across systems (24:17).\n- The **Encompass loan system fields** will be added to the integration scope since they populate the Salesforce Opportunity object, which aligns with HubSpot’s deal object, allowing future campaign personalization based on loan officer data (53:42).\n- Batch uploads will be supported for non-integrated data sources, enabling marketing to import lists from events or third-party systems as CSV files directly into HubSpot (42:38).\n\n## **Data Quality and Validation Processes**\n\nThe team recognized the critical need to address data quality before and during integration to avoid marketing and operational failures (29:00).\n\n- Christina raised concerns about **bad data quality from BI and existing systems**, including truncated business names and misspellings, which caused mail list errors previously (29:00).\n    - Betty suggested an internal audit of the **business analytics nightly batch files**, as they represent the most accurate source, to catch issues early before data reaches Salesforce or HubSpot.\n    - Victor agreed to resubmit access requests to business analytics for Christina’s team to perform this data review and cleaning (31:26).\n- A **regular data validation cadence** will be established post-integration, with weekly or monthly checks comparing record counts and balances across HubSpot and Salesforce to ensure sync integrity (50:56).\n    - Colin confirmed HubSpot performs weekly maintenance but emphasized the need for shared visibility with Salesforce and Mulesoft teams on data discrepancies and errors.\n    - Ashlie noted Encompass has its own error logs, which could complement HubSpot’s monitoring once connected.\n- Gabriel detailed that **Mulesoft triggers error cases within Salesforce on sync failures**, enabling issue tracking and resolution by the integration team (49:55).\n- The team agreed that removing backend automation fields and system flags from marketing sync would reduce clutter and improve clarity in HubSpot (18:35).\n\n## **Integration Timing and Real-time Sync Needs**\n\nThe group prioritized a hybrid approach to data sync frequency balancing real-time needs with nightly batch updates to optimize marketing responsiveness and system load (37:25).\n\n- Most data syncs will occur via **nightly batch uploads aligned with Clear Touch Salesforce schedules**, ensuring consistency with core system updates (37:54).\n    - Betty noted the importance of this timing for most data except for critical triggers like account booking or lead generation.\n- Real-time triggers will be implemented especially for **form submissions and account bookings** to enable immediate marketing actions such as welcome emails or lead notifications (38:47).\n    - Gabriel described leveraging Salesforce automation flows to push real-time updates through Mulesoft to HubSpot immediately upon account booking.\n- Christina emphasized the need for real-time data where possible to support **surveys, lead management, and customer engagement triggers**, with the goal of reducing delays in campaign responses (38:28).\n- Lead management processes will be redesigned so that **HubSpot becomes the primary system for initial lead capture and nurturing**, with qualified leads then routed to Salesforce for sales follow-up (39:56).\n    - Christina described plans to enhance forms with behavioral triggers and segmentation to improve lead scoring and routing.\n    - Colin agreed to build form templates with unique identifiers to support this flow.\n\n## **Cross-System Relationship and Householding Strategies**\n\nThe team focused on ensuring data relationships and householding are well represented and synchronized to avoid marketing errors and improve segmentation accuracy (23:14).\n\n- HubSpot will **store relationship context internally**, associating contacts with companies and households rather than mirroring Salesforce’s account structure directly (22:35).\n- Betty flagged the importance of a **bidirectional sync for householding** to keep contact center and branch engagement aligned with marketing data, preventing confusion over account roles and marketing eligibility (23:14).\n- Christina warned about the risk of incorrectly including beneficiaries or trust-listed individuals in marketing campaigns, emphasizing proper segmentation rules and awareness (27:26).\n- The team agreed to build **segmentation fields to distinguish direct customers from Ponzi Bank customers** to maintain separate brand streams in HubSpot for clearer marketing messaging (15:26).\n- Additional fields related to employee status and do-not-market flags will be carefully managed to avoid inadvertent marketing to internal staff (22:35).\n\n## **Operational Collaboration and Next Steps**\n\nClear roles, documentation, and communication plans were established to ensure smooth integration progress and issue resolution (52:24).\n\n- Colin and Gabriel will **collaborate asynchronously to update the field mapping spreadsheet**, including adding Encompass fields and clarifying masking needs (52:24).\n- A **sample CSV of contact records will be shared** before integration testing to validate field population and data flow accuracy (52:24).\n- Colin committed to sending **API documentation links and HubSpot developer resources** to Gabriel to facilitate integration development (56:31).\n- Victor and Christina will complete the **field review and prioritize marketing data needs**, escalating questions as needed to Gabriel and Colin (54:20).\n- The team will define a **timeline with clear milestones for completion and handoffs**, including when integration crosses over to email, social, and website teams to coordinate campaigns (55:36).\n- Regular communication channels will be maintained for error notifications, sync issues, and process updates, leveraging Mulesoft’s case creation in Salesforce and HubSpot error monitoring (49:52).\n- Christina will coordinate with cash management and Prosper teams to explore **API or batch upload options** for integrating those third-party data sources into HubSpot (36:18).","outline":null,"keywords":["Salesforce Integration","HubSpot Sync","Mulesoft Data Transformation","Data Masking","Lead Management","Marketing Automation"],"overview":"- **Data Mapping Agreement:** Salesforce account data will be organized in HubSpot as companies and contacts for consistency.\n\n- **Data Transformation Responsibilities:** Mulesoft to manage data transformations, including sensitive field masking for compliance purposes.\n\n- **Regular Data Validation:** Weekly checks post-integration will ensure data integrity between HubSpot and Salesforce.\n\n- **Sync Strategy Established:** Most data will sync nightly, with real-time triggers for lead generation and critical actions.\n\n- **Bi-directional Relationships:** HubSpot will maintain internal relationships and householding for accurate marketing segmentation and messaging.\n\n- **Collaborative Documentation:** Clear roles established for field mapping updates, integration testing, and communication plans.","action_items":"\n**Christina Zanca**\nCollaborate with Victor to review and scrub the Excel field mapping document and flag any questionable fields or missing info (54:20)\nFollow up with Victor on resubmitting access requests to Business Analytics to analyze and clean data before loading into HubSpot (32:00)\nInitiate calls with cash management and Prosper teams to explore available APIs or batch upload options for third-party product data integration (36:50)\nDeliver prioritized list of marketing fields to Gabe and Colin, including mortgage-centric fields like NMLS numbers (45:00)\nCoordinate internal discussions and training regarding lead management process changes and marketing tagging for inbound customer interactions (40:30)\nEnsure clear communication to call center and branch teams about marketing triggers and opt-out handling (44:00)\n\n**Gabriel Bencosme**\nProvide detailed descriptions of Salesforce fields in the mapping spreadsheet to clarify usage and exclude system/backend fields (18:30)\nShare list of Encompass fields (Opportunity object) currently integrated into Salesforce for evaluation of marketing relevance (53:45)\nReview and confirm which Salesforce fields require masking for PII before syncing to HubSpot (17:10)\nReview HubSpot API documentation and developer resources once links are provided by Colin (56:35)\nParticipate in asynchronous updates of field mapping document alongside Colin (52:15)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nSubmit ticket or resubmit access request for Christina to Business Analytics (32:00)\nAssist Christina with data review efforts related to source data quality and reporting issues (30:00)\nCollaborate with integration team on creation and testing of sample test records in sandbox environment (26:40)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare the latest version of the Excel field mapping spreadsheet with Gabriel and the team immediately after the meeting (53:20)\nProvide HubSpot API & developer documentation links to Gabriel for integration preparation (56:50)\nBuild sandbox environment incorporating agreed field mappings for Salesforce-HubSpot-MuleSoft syncs (52:00)\nCoordinate sharing of sample CSV test data for integration testing (52:15)\nDevelop clear timeline chart of deliverables and deadlines related to integrations and marketing streams for communication to wider team (55:30)\n\n**Ashlie Taska**\nAssist Victor and Christina with ongoing data review and validation tasks (30:00)\n\n**Betty Campiz**\nSupport discussions on householding strategy and ensure graduated roll-out with communications to marketing and sales (23:00)\nAdvise on sensitive field exclusions in data sync (gender identity etc.) for legal compliance (20:45)\nCoordinate team meetings with Cash Management and Prosper product SMEs for API integration discussions (36:45)\nProvide list of Encompass fields being currently integrated to assist marketing prioritization (47:50)\n"},"duration":57.560001373291016,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":1,"name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"id":4,"name":"bettycampiz"},{"id":5,"name":"victor garcia"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello again.","index":0,"end_time":24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":23.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I know.","index":1,"end_time":26.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just give it a minute.","index":2,"end_time":32.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think Betty''s going to join today just to, you know, provide some context.","index":3,"end_time":36.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, yeah, I''m just going to go on mute until she comes, so I have to grab something.","index":4,"end_time":42.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Give me one second.","index":5,"end_time":43.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Good afternoon.","index":6,"end_time":132.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.89,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Hey, how''s it going?","index":7,"end_time":134.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":133.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, how are you doing?","index":8,"end_time":136.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":9,"end_time":137.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good afternoon, guys.","index":10,"end_time":157.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":156.3,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Hey, how''s it going?","index":11,"end_time":158.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":157.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, just waiting for Betty.","index":12,"end_time":161.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''ll give her another minute, then we can get started.","index":13,"end_time":163.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":14,"end_time":165.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":164.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, you know what?","index":15,"end_time":203.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":202.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"He''s joining right now.","index":16,"end_time":204.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":203.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":17,"end_time":205.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":205.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":18,"end_time":206.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":205.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Nice.","index":19,"end_time":208,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll just let you kick it off then, Alan, and bring up the agenda and I know we have a lot to.","index":20,"end_time":215.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To cover.","index":21,"end_time":215.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":22,"end_time":216.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":216.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, Betty.","index":23,"end_time":217.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":216.96,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":24,"end_time":218.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":217.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going well.","index":25,"end_time":220.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How are you, Carmen?","index":26,"end_time":221.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":220.4,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":27,"end_time":222.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":221.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I will.","index":28,"end_time":226.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":224.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll bring up the agenda, but I don''t want to just share screen with a bunch of words on a document all day.","index":29,"end_time":230.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":226.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did share this agenda, so everyone has it and just feel like it''s a more productive conversation where we can just go through it.","index":30,"end_time":236.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":230.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll pull this up.","index":31,"end_time":238.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":236.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, thank you all for joining.","index":32,"end_time":241.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So today we want to get pretty focused.","index":33,"end_time":244.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":242.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not really revisiting the overall architecture of what we''re building inside of HubSpot and going through any work that we''ve documented already, but aligning on how Salesforce, Mulesoft and HubSpot all communicate with each other to ensure that there is everyone''s clear on responsibilities, there''s no remaining decisions, and that we can continue building the HubSpot sandbox and ultimately the HubSpot account without churn.","index":34,"end_time":267.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll go through each of the sections that we have outlined and you''ll notice that there are some updates that I made to this just based on the response that Victor, you forwarded over from Gabriel this morning.","index":35,"end_time":279.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions or anything before we dive into this?","index":36,"end_time":284.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":281.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope.","index":37,"end_time":288.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I''ll just mention Betty will share this document with you offline news so you can review it in more detail.","index":38,"end_time":294.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think it was circulated through email, but I''ll flip it to you again.","index":39,"end_time":298.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":40,"end_time":299.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":298.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so I will stop my share, but so it did share the spreadsheet.","index":41,"end_time":304.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":299.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Gabriel, I know that you mentioned in your email, you did go through that as well.","index":42,"end_time":308.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so with that mapping, it''s intentionally scoped at the contact level.","index":43,"end_time":312.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that was why one of our questions was around how are we going to use the accounts object inside of Salesforce and how that''s going to pass information through to Mulesoft and HubSpot and then Vice versa.","index":44,"end_time":322.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":312.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we want to confirm is just the exact payload that HubSpot should expect so that we can design every segmentation and property and automation cleanly.","index":45,"end_time":330.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":323.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know that you mentioned in your email they''ll come through as company information and contact information.","index":46,"end_time":336.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":330.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can we just dive into that a little bit further?","index":47,"end_time":338.779,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":336.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, so I guess the account object holds records for both company and contact.","index":48,"end_time":350.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":342.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So the only way we kind of separate that out is basically using what Salesforce is called record types.","index":49,"end_time":358.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":351.41,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We can actually use that as a differentiator between what we''re going to send over as a company.","index":50,"end_time":365.289,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":360.61,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And you know, I understand that some of the fields may be similar, but I think the Object itself within HubSpot is also different.","index":51,"end_time":372.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":365.289,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that is essentially what we''re going to use to kind of split that out.","index":52,"end_time":376.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":372.53,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":53,"end_time":377.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that aligns with our recommendation.","index":54,"end_time":379.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would like to have contacts as a record and then companies as a record.","index":55,"end_time":382.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":379.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so if we have that coming through from the account objects in Salesforce and we can just differentiate that based on record type, that will make it a lot cleaner in the data management.","index":56,"end_time":390.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":382.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we can associate contacts with companies as well when needed.","index":57,"end_time":394.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":390.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":58,"end_time":395.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":395.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We also, well, we in our side, we use what we is called connections.","index":59,"end_time":400.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":396.26,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s a different object.","index":60,"end_time":401.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":400.18,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So if something is linked, we may be able to leverage that as a flag to kind of bring it in as well.","index":61,"end_time":407.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":402.51,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And what is captured in that connection.","index":62,"end_time":411.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":408.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that is what we call beneficial ownership or the ownership structure more or less of what is.","index":63,"end_time":420.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":412.83,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"If it''s an individual connected to an individual, then it''ll say, okay, something like this person is an authorized signer of that nature.","index":64,"end_time":431.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":422.35,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So if it''s an individual connected to a business, it will actually display if it''s the title, if it''s a member, if it''s actually a president, if it''s a controlling individual, is an authorized individual, things of that nature.","index":65,"end_time":442.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":431.46,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":66,"end_time":443.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":442.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Victor, I know you mentioned this morning is that one of the bits of information that the team was looking to be able to see on a contact record as well, it varies depending.","index":67,"end_time":452.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":443.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On what specific things we''re capturing.","index":68,"end_time":456.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":452.26,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So you know that that kind of thing can change depending on the actual campaign.","index":69,"end_time":461.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":456.71,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":70,"end_time":462.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":71,"end_time":463.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So but we do want to be able to see that connection come through on the contact record so that we can discern all of the information.","index":72,"end_time":468.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":463.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":73,"end_time":469.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, because that''ll give us cross sell, you know, when we look to do the cross sell campaigns, you know that that could be helpful.","index":74,"end_time":475.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":75,"end_time":476.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":476.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And with that you had mentioned creating some flows within mulesoft and things like that.","index":76,"end_time":482.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So which fields do you see as requiring transformation?","index":77,"end_time":484.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, going through mulesoft before they are past the HubSpot or vice versa?","index":78,"end_time":489.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":485.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, one of the things that most likely we are going to have to transform is basically anything that has with an ID.","index":79,"end_time":497.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":490.47,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m not sure, I''m not entirely sure how HubSpot handles IDs or unique identifiers.","index":80,"end_time":503.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":497.83,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s probably one that we, we might have to update.","index":81,"end_time":507.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":503.91,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Also I haven''t had the.","index":82,"end_time":510.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":509.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m not sure how.","index":83,"end_time":511.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":510.96,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Let me see.","index":84,"end_time":512.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":511.92,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Actually, let me put up this sheet right now.","index":85,"end_time":513.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":512.44,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because date fields in Salesforce can be a little tricky.","index":86,"end_time":516.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":513.84,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I''m.","index":87,"end_time":517.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":517.04,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Some of them may have date time fields which is adding all the extra hour, minutes, seconds on that, on that, on that field.","index":88,"end_time":526.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":518.32,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But I''m.","index":89,"end_time":527.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":526.96,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So those are the kind of ones.","index":90,"end_time":531.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":529.44,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Anything that''s kind of like a string of Boolean, that''s something that kind of matches.","index":91,"end_time":534.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":531.48,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But besides dates, anything else, for example, express interest could be a pick list on your side.","index":92,"end_time":542.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":534.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"While we would need to actually transform our values into what is.","index":93,"end_time":548.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":543.1,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Into what exactly goes into your pick list values for to match the exact names of the pick list values.","index":94,"end_time":553.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":548.38,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Those are the places where most likely we will have to do some data mapping.","index":95,"end_time":558.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":553.62,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, question Colin.","index":96,"end_time":560.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When you talk about transform, are we also capturing transform from our side back to Salesforce as well?","index":97,"end_time":567.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":560.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because right now we set up campaigns.","index":98,"end_time":570.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We just started that testing within the Salesforce system.","index":99,"end_time":574.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But we''ll want to as we import leads that into HubSpot that are not in.","index":100,"end_time":581.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In Salesforce, we''ll want them track back to Salesforce and be categorized or transformed.","index":101,"end_time":586.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Gabe, just for your reference, we''ll also need to think about the incoming data.","index":102,"end_time":594.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":586.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Data.","index":103,"end_time":595.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s fine.","index":104,"end_time":597.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":596.81,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I mean as long I''m.","index":105,"end_time":598.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":597.57,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m not sure if in HubSpot colon, are you able to, you know, add the pickless values with the same names as we have them in Salesforce.","index":106,"end_time":608.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":598.53,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That, that could be one route that we can take.","index":107,"end_time":609.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":608.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But if something is limited and where we need to kind of, you know, make transformations, that''s not a problem.","index":108,"end_time":615.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":610.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And of course transformations are going to happen both ways.","index":109,"end_time":618.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":615.49,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Most likely Milsoft will throw an error if he doesn''t find a specific pick list or if it''s a restricted pick list as well.","index":110,"end_time":624.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":618.89,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So essentially, Christina, this is something that we most likely are going to have to do with MuleSoft.","index":111,"end_time":633.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":626.73,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":112,"end_time":634.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Data transformation is going to happen across the board.","index":113,"end_time":636.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":634.41,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":114,"end_time":638.009,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Most likely that''s one of the things that mulesoft does specifically Level this is basically rearrange the data so that it can actually be imported the way.","index":115,"end_time":649.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":640.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":116,"end_time":651.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":651.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then that''s where you''ll do like the data masking and all that for the PII that is that considered transformation as well.","index":117,"end_time":658.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":651.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We don''t have to bring that in.","index":118,"end_time":660.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":658.8,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"If any PII information, we don''t have to bring that in on the payload.","index":119,"end_time":663.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":660.12,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We don''t have to include it as part of the field.","index":120,"end_time":665.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":663.96,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So when, when you talk about mealsoft, one of the things that we can do is we can once we create a trigger, for example and it triggers, it calls out to salesforce.","index":121,"end_time":676.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":665.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We can specify the number of fields that we want to bring in.","index":122,"end_time":681.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":676.89,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we don''t have to bring in the PI data if it''s not needed.","index":123,"end_time":684.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":681.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll bring in some.","index":124,"end_time":686.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":684.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But we talked in the IT committee the team being comfortable with that as long as we mask it because we''ll use some of it for householding, we''ll use some of it for down the line like operations, comms and then unless we need it for HubSpot.","index":125,"end_time":708.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"HubSpot for householding, we could probably avoid, you know, the sensitive one like Social Security.","index":126,"end_time":713.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t think that we''ll have a marketing use case for that.","index":127,"end_time":717.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But when customers have multiple, you know, account types, having the account number always helps because then it helps us segment it a little bit further.","index":128,"end_time":726.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":129,"end_time":728.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''ll talk about that.","index":130,"end_time":730.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Pretty much everything on that spreadsheet that Colin just brought up is what we are hoping that you guys could work towards for data integration.","index":131,"end_time":739.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Colin, I''m not sure if you actually shared that spreadsheet out yet with the team but we should kind of go through offline and make sure that we have a plan to incorporate for each of these and if there''s any concerns we can kind of make a note for it.","index":132,"end_time":756.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The one thing that I wanted to make sure because I remember when we were talking, talking about the email opt out process in the Salesforce marketing cloud.","index":133,"end_time":767.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When we had it, it was a little bit cumbersome and wasn''t necessarily being tracked appropriately.","index":134,"end_time":772.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we just want to make sure that if there''s any changes that we need to make, even Betty, including possibly on the retail side when a customer comes in and makes an opt out or either in the call center, we''ll just flagging that because we have to, we have to have the a clear opt out for the can spam.","index":135,"end_time":791.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":772.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":136,"end_time":795.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":794.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes Victor.","index":137,"end_time":795.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":795.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for when we transfer data over from Salesforce over to constant contact just for the email side of things it does give us a.","index":138,"end_time":805.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":796.89,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It does let us know who subscribe, who unsubscribed as of recently.","index":139,"end_time":808.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":805.53,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So I don''t know if that information can help you with this type of thing, but a lot of the time when we transfer just regular records over from Salesforce to Constant Contact, it lets us know already who unsubscribed.","index":140,"end_time":823.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":809.53,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":141,"end_time":824.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that.","index":142,"end_time":824.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that''s from the actual like email.","index":143,"end_time":826.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What I''m talking about is like typically there''s other methods to unsubscribe.","index":144,"end_time":831.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":827.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So there''s the branches, there''s a call center, you know, so the system typically tracks that.","index":145,"end_time":837.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I remember Jen saying that we didn''t necessarily have that properly set up or weren''t able to get that, so we could talk about that a little bit offline.","index":146,"end_time":846.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":837.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I just saw the email opt out, so it made me remember to raise that.","index":147,"end_time":850.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Colin, just make a note of that to make sure that we''re testing that and capturing all the fields that manage opt out.","index":148,"end_time":857.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And you know, if we need to have any training on that, we can talk about that if we.","index":149,"end_time":862.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, and HubSpot''s got strict requirements around it.","index":150,"end_time":865.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":863.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, every form, everything needs to have the option to opt out.","index":151,"end_time":868.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":865.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it all goes back into a single field.","index":152,"end_time":870.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":868.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can also create an extra field that''ll tell us like source of opt out.","index":153,"end_time":874.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":870.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if they clicked it in an email or if they sold someone at a branch, then developing the process for that to get back to the HubSpot record.","index":154,"end_time":880.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guys, before we move forward, is that list.","index":155,"end_time":882.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":881.18,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Can you scroll down on this list?","index":156,"end_time":884.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":882.94,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Is it the complete list that you guys saw send us before?","index":157,"end_time":889.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":884.1,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, this is the list that we sent over before.","index":158,"end_time":891.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":889.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did add one column after talking with Christina earlier of just is masking needed in a checkbox?","index":159,"end_time":896.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":160,"end_time":897.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":896.7,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And this is contact based and so we can get the.","index":161,"end_time":899.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":897.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I mean with accounts being similar with the companies, then we''re in a good spot.","index":162,"end_time":905.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":900.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Gabriel, to answer your point from earlier, HubSpot does do custom fields with custom identifiers and we can do any content inside of dropdown or pick list options.","index":163,"end_time":917.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":906.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":164,"end_time":918.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":918.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So if it''s easier that we just match the options, if you guys are set with those in Salesforce and you like those for any field, then we can copy that.","index":165,"end_time":926.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":918.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":166,"end_time":926.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"One question.","index":167,"end_time":928.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How are we.","index":168,"end_time":929.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is there a field to the segment, a direct customer versus Ponzi Bank?","index":169,"end_time":935.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We do not have one right now.","index":170,"end_time":939.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we typically would do there is either like a.","index":171,"end_time":942.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":939.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A brand label or a company association label.","index":172,"end_time":945.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":942.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":173,"end_time":946.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":945.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":174,"end_time":946.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''ll Just have to make sure that, you know, if.","index":175,"end_time":948.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If it''s a direct only customer, that we''re.","index":176,"end_time":951.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":948.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That we''re categorizing that appropriately.","index":177,"end_time":953.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":951.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because, Betty, just for your knowledge, we''re going to keep the two brand streams in hubsp.","index":178,"end_time":958.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When I was doing research, especially on the national marketing, it''s going to get.","index":179,"end_time":963.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":960.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s going to get confusing with some of the language.","index":180,"end_time":966.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":963.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t necessarily recommend that we get rid of Ponzi Bank Direct in its entirety from like a marketing perspective.","index":181,"end_time":976.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":966.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s going to be built out as like a microsite and a separate brand stream in HubSpot.","index":182,"end_time":981.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":976.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I mean, that was my expectation.","index":183,"end_time":984.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":981.85,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"And it also is not connected to GPS today, so that.","index":184,"end_time":990.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":984.65,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"That would have been another factor anyway.","index":185,"end_time":992.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":990.71,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":186,"end_time":993.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":187,"end_time":995.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Gabriel, is there any other fields that we need to be aware of for masking as far as any attributes or anything that we don''t want to pass through?","index":188,"end_time":1004.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":996.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that in the sheet, as Christina mentioned, like this is.","index":189,"end_time":1007.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1004.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are the fields that we want to be able to use from a marketing perspective.","index":190,"end_time":1010.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1007.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, you know, Social Security, things like that that maybe aren''t completely necessary.","index":191,"end_time":1015.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1011.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anything else that you see as you were going through the list that you would want to pull out?","index":192,"end_time":1020.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1015.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m looking at the list right now.","index":193,"end_time":1024.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1022.26,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Nothing comes up to mind, but I keep that.","index":194,"end_time":1026.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1024.34,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''ll note that up to see if there''s anything that needs to be masked.","index":195,"end_time":1030.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1026.94,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"For 87 individual ideas that''s specific to the kind of idea that Gabe was talking about or like actual idea of the person.","index":196,"end_time":1044.869,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1031.62,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So this is the field inside of Salesforce.","index":197,"end_time":1048.789,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1046.229,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You have the individual ID name and it looks like it''s just.","index":198,"end_time":1052.789,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1049.749,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the Salesforce label is individual id.","index":199,"end_time":1056.309,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1054.229,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Looks like it''s just a text token.","index":200,"end_time":1059.109,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.509,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Gabriel, what is that currently being used for inside of Salesforce?","index":201,"end_time":1062.949,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1059.989,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that is the actual ID type.","index":202,"end_time":1065.909,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1063.749,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And that''s why I''m asking, because why would you guys need that?","index":203,"end_time":1070.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1066.6,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah, we can remove that from the list.","index":204,"end_time":1072.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1070.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, anything like that that removes kind of that layer of security concern should come out.","index":205,"end_time":1079.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1073.24,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":206,"end_time":1080.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1079.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And this was just the exercise to like match up like, like terms.","index":207,"end_time":1084.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1080.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So there''s definitely a little bit of scrubbing that that has to.","index":208,"end_time":1088.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1085.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That has to happen.","index":209,"end_time":1089.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1088.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like is deleted ID validated?","index":210,"end_time":1095.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, I guess all those could kind of come out as part of it.","index":211,"end_time":1098.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t know what is deleted is and Jigsaw key.","index":212,"end_time":1102.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1098.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe what we could do is, Gabe, we can add a column and you could kind of give a little bit of a Description for some of the ones that are not necessarily like.","index":213,"end_time":1113.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1103.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Understood that we provided a whole list of fields that were related to the contact or I mean to the least to the account object.","index":214,"end_time":1122.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1115.35,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Those fields you guys are not going to need, for example that is deleted is a system field when a record gets deleted.","index":215,"end_time":1128.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1123.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So it kind of puts it in the trash bin and it kind of marks that as a record that has been deleted.","index":216,"end_time":1134.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1128.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m seeing a couple of things here.","index":217,"end_time":1137.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1135.51,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m not going to say I''m not sure if anything is email bounce or if we''re going to need that.","index":218,"end_time":1144.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1137.99,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Anything with a triple Z most likely something that we deprecated before.","index":219,"end_time":1149.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1145.75,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So most likely we''re not using anymore or any automation that might have triggered or updated.","index":220,"end_time":1154.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1149.47,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I feel we''ve kind of removed it the field itself.","index":221,"end_time":1157.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1154.36,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I guess just trying to figure out what would be the best route for us to.","index":222,"end_time":1164.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1157.8,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because you know, the.","index":223,"end_time":1165.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1164.6,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Our contact or at least our account object contains a lot of fields that are.","index":224,"end_time":1171.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1165.8,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Some of them are just basically used for backend automation and I don''t want to send that over because you guys are not going to be needed needing that at all.","index":225,"end_time":1177.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1171.08,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So.","index":226,"end_time":1178.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1177.93,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I mean, I think, you know, for, for your purposes, anything that is.","index":227,"end_time":1184.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1178.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is to your point, like a field that helps do something in the background for, for Salesforce.","index":228,"end_time":1190.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1184.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t think that, you know, will, will necessarily need it.","index":229,"end_time":1194.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1190.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What I think that, you know, Colin, we should color code this like green is absolutely necessary.","index":230,"end_time":1201.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1195.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It has to go in top priority and then, you know, maybe leave all of the ones that are questionable white so we can kind of just look at them and make a decision and then anything that''s, you know, pii you just check off the masking.","index":231,"end_time":1218.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1201.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if we could just clean this up a little bit to help us drive the, you know, the final subset of data.","index":232,"end_time":1224.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1219,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because what I want to do after today is just align on who''s going to be responsible, how we start to set this up and a timeline so we make sure that we''re, you know, we''re smooth sailing because you know, we.","index":233,"end_time":1238.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1224.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"January is going to come and before we know it it''ll.","index":234,"end_time":1241.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1238.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''ll be March and April.","index":235,"end_time":1243.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1241.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I, I do want to call out not to go too much into this because to your point, you had that.","index":236,"end_time":1248.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1244.04,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"I think just that exercise is going to be very valuable.","index":237,"end_time":1251.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1248.28,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"But something like gender identity absolutely should not be there because we shouldn''t be getting into that territory of communicating in any way, shape or form that''s like specific to gender identity and then get sued for how we''re, you know, communicating.","index":238,"end_time":1268.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1251.04,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So, yeah, that should be kept in mind as these fields are being assessed wherever we can avoid those potential issues.","index":239,"end_time":1275.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1268.61,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":240,"end_time":1277.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1276.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":241,"end_time":1277.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1277.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And then for a field like IS deleted, you know, there''s.","index":242,"end_time":1279.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1277.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s two trains of thought to that.","index":243,"end_time":1281.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1279.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if a.","index":244,"end_time":1282.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1281.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Someone fills out a form on the website, for example, and we''re trying to determine after their record is created in HubSpot, do they already exist in Salesforce or do we have an is deleted key?","index":245,"end_time":1291.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1282.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or if we''re just searching based on email address, for example, then that would be the alternate route.","index":246,"end_time":1295.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1291.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why a field like that was included initially.","index":247,"end_time":1297.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1295.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":248,"end_time":1298.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1298.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we can, you know, we can keep it there as a.","index":249,"end_time":1301.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1298.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"As a way to say, hey, it might have been scrubbed off.","index":250,"end_time":1303.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1301.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe there was a touch point, some case, you know, in the past, and it could be.","index":251,"end_time":1308.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1303.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe even put in a warm lead category.","index":252,"end_time":1311.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think that that''s.","index":253,"end_time":1312.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":254,"end_time":1313.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Another thing like Equifax frozen file code, I don''t know that maybe we''ll.","index":255,"end_time":1319.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1314.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We have to figure out what would be the use case for there.","index":256,"end_time":1322.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1320.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe like a do not market for credit.","index":257,"end_time":1324.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1322.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But again, we''ll have to maybe ask a little bit more.","index":258,"end_time":1327.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1324.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Employee notes, employee birth dates, like those things.","index":259,"end_time":1334.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1328.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m not sure we may necessarily need.","index":260,"end_time":1337.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1334.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I want to definitely categorize employees differently because they''re typically scrubbed from marketing components.","index":261,"end_time":1344.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, you know, that''s that.","index":262,"end_time":1347.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1345.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":263,"end_time":1356.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1355.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":264,"end_time":1357.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1356.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So definitely go through the exercise of cleaning this list up and working hand in hand with that, being cognizant of time.","index":265,"end_time":1364.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1357.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So talking through the accounts section.","index":266,"end_time":1367.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1364.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So understanding that Salesforce is storing accounts and business data in that object, HubSpot''s going to split that, as we said.","index":267,"end_time":1373.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1367.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we don''t want to mirror Salesforce''s setup.","index":268,"end_time":1376.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1373.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Betty, that is to your point that you made a few months ago of building HubSpot to the best standards.","index":269,"end_time":1380.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1376.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re going to store the relationship context and that''ll be associating those contact records with any businesses that they are associated with.","index":270,"end_time":1388.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1381.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I don''t really think we have many questions there.","index":271,"end_time":1393.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1390.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do have one quick comment, Colin, and maybe you guys have already discussed this, but it''s important for.","index":272,"end_time":1400.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1394.4,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"For me to call it out just in case.","index":273,"end_time":1402.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1401.23,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So I heard Christina call out householding, and obviously I know that''s going to be kind of a different setup as it exists today.","index":274,"end_time":1413.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1403.23,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Right, In Salesforce versus what you guys are building in HubSpot.","index":275,"end_time":1417.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1413.59,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"It''ll be interesting and important to understand also how we create some sort of I guess bidirectional of whatever''s happening on the HubSpot end.","index":276,"end_time":1428.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1417.55,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Because my concern would be in terms of how that exercise plays out, that since the householding wouldn''t necessarily look the same when there''s engagement either at the contact center level or branch level, people are going to be confused.","index":277,"end_time":1444.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1428.59,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So just again, food for thought as you guys work on that for you and Gabriel, I guess.","index":278,"end_time":1450.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1444.91,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":279,"end_time":1452.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1451.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you for bringing that up, Eddie.","index":280,"end_time":1453.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1452.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Victor, did you.","index":281,"end_time":1454.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1453.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":282,"end_time":1457.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1457.07,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Just out of curiosity, just so that I know, what is our unique identifier?","index":283,"end_time":1460.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1457.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So that when we, when you do sync over, I know, you know, is it email?","index":284,"end_time":1465.55,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1460.43,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Is it something other than email?","index":285,"end_time":1467.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1465.63,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"What are we using as that consistent thing across the board?","index":286,"end_time":1470.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1467.71,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":287,"end_time":1470.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1470.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So HubSpot''s default unique identifier is email address.","index":288,"end_time":1473.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1470.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":289,"end_time":1474.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1474.03,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Cool.","index":290,"end_time":1475.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1474.63,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":291,"end_time":1476.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1475.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that we''ll have to discuss too because you know, we''re going to want to keep all of the, the records, you know, within, within HubSpot.","index":292,"end_time":1486.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1476.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I''m assuming there''s several customers that don''t have updated, you know, email addresses.","index":293,"end_time":1491.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1486.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''ll have to figure out, you know, maybe Betty, like a campaign to get those records updated in branch when they come in or what have you.","index":294,"end_time":1499.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1491.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I know, been there, done that.","index":295,"end_time":1502.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1499.15,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Listen, we, we should absolutely do it.","index":296,"end_time":1505.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1503.07,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"I''m not discouraging it.","index":297,"end_time":1507.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1505.63,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"I did just want to call out in terms of that unique identifier that although HubSpot is going to use, you know, emails, because so much can go wrong with emails and we''ve seen that happen even like on other efforts that we have, we should, if we''re able to include the, the viscode.","index":298,"end_time":1528.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1507.87,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Gabe and Ashley, like the, the unique identifier that goes all the way back to the core level.","index":299,"end_time":1534.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1528.8,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Like that''s the unique identifier assigned by Clear Touch.","index":300,"end_time":1538.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1534.88,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Because push comes to shove, that''s going to be kind of the one clear indicator that is tied to each individual.","index":301,"end_time":1546.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1538.4,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So we should consider pulling that in even if it''s not being utilized.","index":302,"end_time":1550.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1546.19,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah, that was my approach and when I kind of spoke about when I sent the email, that''s why I, when we do, I guess an original input, it''ll be safe to kind of add that field because we can have mulesoft update the records based not necessarily on email, but on that external id, we want to call it that.","index":303,"end_time":1572.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1551.07,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So just curious to see if.","index":304,"end_time":1575.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1572.22,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Does that.","index":305,"end_time":1576.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1575.58,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Is that type of field supported in any way in HubSpot?","index":306,"end_time":1579.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1576.18,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Colin?","index":307,"end_time":1580.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1579.98,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":308,"end_time":1581.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1580.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is the field just.","index":309,"end_time":1581.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1581.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it like a, like a text or number chain?","index":310,"end_time":1584.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1581.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''ll be.","index":311,"end_time":1584.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1584.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it will have numeric values.","index":312,"end_time":1588.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1586.86,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1589.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1588.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we can absolutely do that.","index":314,"end_time":1590.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1589.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I go right back into what we discussed earlier, Colin, about the test records that we could potentially use.","index":315,"end_time":1595.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1590.54,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Gabe, I know that we discussed it briefly and Ashley, are there any test records that we can send from Salesforce over to HubSpot or how do we want to do test records from the sandbox?","index":316,"end_time":1607.34,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1597.1,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Well, if we wanted to.","index":317,"end_time":1610.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1608.62,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I haven''t still created any type of connectivity between.","index":318,"end_time":1613.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1610.38,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I haven''t done that yet.","index":319,"end_time":1616.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1615.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I haven''t looked at the API documentation for HubSpot.","index":320,"end_time":1619.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1616.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But need a test customers.","index":321,"end_time":1623.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1621.58,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"They can just be created.","index":322,"end_time":1627.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1623.84,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"We have test customers like for example, that we just create for the DAO implementation.","index":323,"end_time":1635.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1629.04,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"They''re brand new but, you know, if we''re testing out different things, we can just create new test customers.","index":324,"end_time":1644,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1635.68,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"It''s.","index":325,"end_time":1644.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1644,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"It''s going to be in our sandbox, so it''s fine.","index":326,"end_time":1646.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1644.36,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay.","index":327,"end_time":1647.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1646.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, we had some time to talk about, you know, the testing, I think, but, but just, I want to.","index":328,"end_time":1653.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1648.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because we''re short on time, I want to just raise the two things.","index":329,"end_time":1656.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So one, when we think about email, we are going to want to run a report to see if we have customers with duplicate email addresses because we''re going to have to figure out how we handle those.","index":330,"end_time":1669.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1657.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I want to make sure that when we are householding, we properly identify those customers that are just beneficiaries or listed on trusts accounts or anything of that nature so we don''t incorrectly pull them into a household where they''re not supposed to be marketed to because they don''t really have awareness to the.","index":331,"end_time":1693.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1670.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That account per se.","index":332,"end_time":1694.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1693.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s just they''re on it.","index":333,"end_time":1695.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1694.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ve ran into some issues in, in the past where organizations would send out, you know, notices and like a beneficiary be like, oh, I didn''t know I had, you know, I, I''m a beneficiary on account and like the account holder would get mad so that, you know, that could be a problem.","index":334,"end_time":1710.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1696.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then the other thing I want to make sure that we start to think about is that when we start to think about like the data validation process, we''re going to want to have a standard report that is our go to where, I don''t know, weekly, monthly, whatever.","index":335,"end_time":1728.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1711.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Once we start the syncs, we can always say, okay, like HubSpot has 13,000 records, Salesforce has 13,000 records.","index":336,"end_time":1734.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1728.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And make sure that we''re always kind of putting things in the right place.","index":337,"end_time":1738.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1734.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so there''s nothing that''s broken.","index":338,"end_time":1739.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1738.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then.","index":339,"end_time":1741.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1740.94,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I don''t know if we''re gonna have an issue with some of the data.","index":340,"end_time":1748.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1743.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I''ll just throw this example out there.","index":341,"end_time":1751.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1749.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I tried to do a mailing and we pulled the, we pulled the data.","index":342,"end_time":1756.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1751.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think it was from BI or I forget exactly where it came from.","index":343,"end_time":1760.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1756.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But the data wasn''t great.","index":344,"end_time":1764.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1760.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It had words cut off.","index":345,"end_time":1766.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1764.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it was leading to just a lot of errors on our mail list.","index":346,"end_time":1770.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1766.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so what I, I''m just, I guess going to ask is, is there going to be a need because we''re using MuleSoft to have to kind of data validate and clean up data or are you, are you thinking that we''re gonna be okay from that perspective?","index":347,"end_time":1784.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1770.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I just don''t want to put bad data into the system and run into those same problems where we have to like look at every single line item to make sure that, you know, there''s no misspellings or missing apartments or for example, like association, the last part of association cut off where it''s addressing to something we don''t want to note.","index":348,"end_time":1804.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1784.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Gabe, before you even jump in, I just want to suggest that maybe, Christina, you have an exercise, like an internal exercise of actually seeing the business analytics files that bring in this type of information, that nightly batch, because at the end of the day that''s the most accurate system of record.","index":349,"end_time":1831.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1806.01,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"And if Salesforce goes down, that''s what''s pulling from the core.","index":350,"end_time":1835.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1831.54,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"We want to make sure that that''s where you''re identifying those potential issues rather than have Gabriel doing kind of work on the Salesforce side to address those versus in business analytics.","index":351,"end_time":1851.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1837.38,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Maybe that''s an exercise you should do before.","index":352,"end_time":1853.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1851.4,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, I''m gonna need help there then because I, I, we''ve asked for access a couple times and it was just always denied because of the whole data upgrade snowflake thing, whatever was going on.","index":353,"end_time":1865.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1854.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t know if there''s, you know, a go to person or reports that I could download to look at, but that slightly makes me concerned because we got, we got the data from, like I said, from BI and it was, you know, you Betty, it was all cut off and there was character limitations and things that were causing us not to capture all of the business name.","index":354,"end_time":1886.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1865.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And yeah, that is pretty common with the core itself.","index":355,"end_time":1891.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1886.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"The core uses a lot of codes rather than actual big words or, you know, the complete word itself.","index":356,"end_time":1898.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1892.02,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we even encounter those kind of limitations when we push in data into the core.","index":357,"end_time":1902.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1898.5,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So yeah, that is definitely something to think about.","index":358,"end_time":1905.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1902.86,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But just to let you know that the business analytics integration has been completed.","index":359,"end_time":1910.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1905.86,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we are allowed to create users at this point?","index":360,"end_time":1913.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1910.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yes, it can actually create that access.","index":361,"end_time":1915.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1913.55,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I don''t think it is actually the one creating them.","index":362,"end_time":1919.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1917.31,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I think they have to submit a ticket for you to Pfizer themselves.","index":363,"end_time":1922.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1919.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, all right, so Victor, maybe take that, take that back and put, put resubmit your access to business analytics so we can start to look at that.","index":364,"end_time":1932.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1922.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I just want to get ahead of that because you know, we identified big issues with, you know, bad data in.","index":365,"end_time":1939.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1932.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re gonna have to identify a plan to, you know, to scrub and clean some of that data because that''s gonna be a, a hurdle for, for us from a marketing perspective because the, the, the best use case of the system is automation.","index":366,"end_time":1953.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1939.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so if I have to, you know, get in there and manually like update, you know, names and addresses and cross reference things, I mean, Victor was going through it for two days I think to just do a, a 200 person mail list and it was just nightmare.","index":367,"end_time":1969.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1953.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And plus, you know, when you''re doing manual updates, then you lose kind of that integrity that, you know, I, I don''t want to get into the weeds of having to do that.","index":368,"end_time":1979.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1969.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Victor, just put that on a lit on the list of things to do in HubSpot and put your ticket in and then I''ll follow up on, you know, what that would look like.","index":369,"end_time":1989.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1979.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":370,"end_time":1992.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1992.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When is that fiscal field that you''re referring to?","index":371,"end_time":1996.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1993.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When is that created?","index":372,"end_time":1997.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1996.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As soon as an account is booked.","index":373,"end_time":2000.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1999.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":374,"end_time":2001.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2001.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for example, if we were to have a form on the website and it''s a HubSpot form, so they would be created initially directly in HubSpot and then pass through Mulesoft back to Salesforce.","index":375,"end_time":2011.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2001.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would a code be created then or only if they are a customer?","index":376,"end_time":2016.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2011.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It would like find an associate.","index":377,"end_time":2017.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2016.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s the only time that they would be created essentially when they become a customer.","index":378,"end_time":2022.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2018.36,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":379,"end_time":2023.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2022.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":380,"end_time":2023.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2023.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there any, any accounts that are not living within the systems that we''re pulling from that we need to take account take into account?","index":381,"end_time":2036.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2025.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m just thinking more broadly, like loans, you know, the whole Prosper thing.","index":382,"end_time":2042.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2036.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Anything on the, on that side of the house.","index":383,"end_time":2045.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2043.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What I vaguely heard.","index":384,"end_time":2048.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2047.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well, what was your question again?","index":385,"end_time":2050.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2049.04,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"I''m sorry, I only caught half of it because.","index":386,"end_time":2052.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2050.48,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"No, no, that''s okay.","index":387,"end_time":2053.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2052.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m just trying to think outside of the box and capture anything that potentially maybe not be booked on the core, you know, any type of loan account.","index":388,"end_time":2061.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2053.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Prosper.","index":389,"end_time":2062.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2061.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is there anything that we may be missing that we would have to get another data set from?","index":390,"end_time":2067.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2062.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I thought I heard no, like Lions Mortgages and in Clear Touch now.","index":391,"end_time":2074.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2068.48,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So that''s a non issue.","index":392,"end_time":2075.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2074.2,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Prosper is the only one right now that comes to mind that isn''t getting booked because even the mortgage world, even when we''re selling them, they still get booked to Clear Touch.","index":393,"end_time":2086.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2077,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":394,"end_time":2087.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2086.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For that purpose.","index":395,"end_time":2088.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2087.24,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So it''s really going to be Prosper DCI and Clear Touch.","index":396,"end_time":2095.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2088.44,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"What about the cash management too?","index":397,"end_time":2098.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2096.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is is in there or is it that.","index":398,"end_time":2100.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2098.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It depends on what you''re looking for in terms of cash management because that''s all obviously tying back to the account in the core, but you''re not going to have indicators or specific type of information within the core depending on what you''re looking for.","index":399,"end_time":2115.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2101.64,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So.","index":400,"end_time":2116.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2115.72,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Okay, because like if I was looking for like what type of cash management service they had or what type of machine or what have you, you know, when we look to think about doing more cross sell campaigns, we have separate.","index":401,"end_time":2130.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2116.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Separate sites that the team has to access for, for things like positive pay and, and all those other things.","index":402,"end_time":2138.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2130.9,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So, so would we still be able to get that in through a different area or does that, would that still come through Mulesoft?","index":403,"end_time":2147.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2138.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean that wouldn''t be Mulesoft at this point.","index":404,"end_time":2151.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2149.3,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"And, and Ash and Gabe, don''t let me miss.","index":405,"end_time":2154.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2151.62,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"No, you''re right.","index":406,"end_time":2155.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2154.39,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":407,"end_time":2156.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2155.51,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"We haven''t done much on that front in the past in terms of integration to these cash management sites precisely because they''re like separate.","index":408,"end_time":2166.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2156.15,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"They''re not, it''s not coming from the core.","index":409,"end_time":2168.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2166.39,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Okay, okay, so then Colin, when we look at like the products and stuff, we may have to think about.","index":410,"end_time":2176.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2168.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You.","index":411,"end_time":2178.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2178.44,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Know, maybe like a batch upload if we get from other, you know, sites.","index":412,"end_time":2183.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2178.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m sure, you know, there''s reports and things that, you know, you could download from these third parties or maybe I can even get calls with their reps to see if they have like direct APIs, you know.","index":413,"end_time":2194.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2183.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But just make a note of that.","index":414,"end_time":2196.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2194.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because we can schedule, or you can schedule a call with Ting and Maria.","index":415,"end_time":2203.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2196.64,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah, but Ting is the one that would know all the sites so you can meet with her.","index":416,"end_time":2208.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2203.48,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah, and they''re, they''re working on the Prosper now too.","index":417,"end_time":2210.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2208.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''ll uncover two birds, one song.","index":418,"end_time":2213.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2210.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, so Victor, just put that on the to dos call with the cash management and in Prosper.","index":419,"end_time":2222.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2213.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I definitely know because I was building a report for one of our meetings that we have the ability to put those reports together.","index":420,"end_time":2230.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2222.179,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"What I can''t confirm because I''m new to the, to the portal is whether we can automate the delivery of the file that needs to be looked into.","index":421,"end_time":2240.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2232.18,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"But definitely the reporting in Prosper is easy enough.","index":422,"end_time":2245.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2240.69,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":423,"end_time":2245.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2245.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"As far as the.","index":424,"end_time":2249.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2248.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The cycle and the.","index":425,"end_time":2252.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2250.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The bidirectional sync, what is that frequency?","index":426,"end_time":2256.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2252.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is it going to be real time or daily batch upload?","index":427,"end_time":2260.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2256.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How does that work?","index":428,"end_time":2263.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2262.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or is that not something that we could kind of identify at this time?","index":429,"end_time":2267.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2263.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":430,"end_time":2268.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2268.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So within HubSpot you can set different frequencies.","index":431,"end_time":2270.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2268.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it depend on what you would want Mulesoft to communicate at.","index":432,"end_time":2274.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2270.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, it''s a nightly upload on the.","index":433,"end_time":2278.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2274.69,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"On the clear touch Salesforce side.","index":434,"end_time":2280.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2278.53,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So you probably want to align with that.","index":435,"end_time":2283.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2280.69,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Unless you''re specifically looking at data that may come in in terms of like an account being booked today and you want to send something out today versus Tomor, then that''s the only time where I would see alignment with Salesforce directly would be beneficial.","index":436,"end_time":2300.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2285.17,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Just like, let''s say we''re going to send a welcome email, you might want to send it when the customer is walking out the branch after opening their account.","index":437,"end_time":2308.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2301.47,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Right, that''s what I was thinking.","index":438,"end_time":2311.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2308.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like more real time.","index":439,"end_time":2312.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2311.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Especially when we get into some of the surveys that the teams were interested in doing.","index":440,"end_time":2316.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2312.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, you know, rather than waiting 24 hours, you just have them be triggered.","index":441,"end_time":2323.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2317.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, if this happens, you know that.","index":442,"end_time":2326.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2323.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That happens.","index":443,"end_time":2327.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2326.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, it could happen.","index":444,"end_time":2328.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2327.7,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But I think essentially what we can do is leverage that same automation that triggers me also when the account is booked and, you know, push it in both directions and then push it.","index":445,"end_time":2339.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2328.74,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":446,"end_time":2340.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2339.38,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Create a flow that kind of.","index":447,"end_time":2341.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2340.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Once.","index":448,"end_time":2341.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2341.42,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Once it completes the booking process, then go to that other flow and just send that information over.","index":449,"end_time":2346.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2341.7,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":450,"end_time":2347.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2347.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To Hopspot.","index":451,"end_time":2349.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2348.35,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":452,"end_time":2350.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2349.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that kind of aligns with the next question I had.","index":453,"end_time":2352.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2350.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Gabriel, in your email, you kind of responded to this as well, of, you know, someone submits a form on the website, it''s.","index":454,"end_time":2358.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2352.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s either general inquiry or there''s, you know, I''m a hot lead.","index":455,"end_time":2361.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2358.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so it sounds like we want to create a lead object inside of Salesforce.","index":456,"end_time":2365.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2361.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would we want to do that right away or is that going to occur in the nightly sync?","index":457,"end_time":2371.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2367.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It can happen either way.","index":458,"end_time":2374.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2373.88,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I mean, it depends on Christina, I guess, the marketing team.","index":459,"end_time":2378.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2374.88,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"What would you want to do?","index":460,"end_time":2380.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2379.56,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Would you like that information to flow over right away or is that something that you want to have it when it becomes a hot, hot lead so that when it comes into Salesforce, we can create automation so that the bankers automatically.","index":461,"end_time":2392.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2380.8,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, we got.","index":462,"end_time":2393,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2392.28,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We received the lead now, so let''s operate on it.","index":463,"end_time":2395.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2393.4,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, I would say, you know, certain things real time and this would be, you know, one of them.","index":464,"end_time":2401.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2396.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We also have to think about the whole, the lead management process in general because right now everything flows through to Salesforce.","index":465,"end_time":2409.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2401.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I would, I would suggest that we have to reconfigure that so it flows to HubSpot from, you know, from HubSpot to, to Salesforce and then, you know, kind of communicates back and forth and then even taking it a step further, like tagging customer contact records for marketing activities.","index":466,"end_time":2430.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2409.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So when they, you know, come into the branch or call the call center, they have that, you know, information there.","index":467,"end_time":2436.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2430.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But that would require some maybe slight training.","index":468,"end_time":2440.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2436.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe not a go live thing, but that would be my wish list.","index":469,"end_time":2443.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2440.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, and what is, or is there existing criteria right now for?","index":470,"end_time":2450.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2445.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is just, you know, a form fill that we got.","index":471,"end_time":2452.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2450.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is someone that wants to talk to someone at a bank right now to open an account.","index":472,"end_time":2457.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2452.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there a criteria that''s automatically flowing or is it a lead object created for all of them?","index":473,"end_time":2460.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2457.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have to talk about that process.","index":474,"end_time":2464.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2462.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We started to think about it a little bit right now.","index":475,"end_time":2466.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2464.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The forms are very basic, right.","index":476,"end_time":2468.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2466.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And anybody that, you know, fills a form would go directly, you know, to the, the rep.","index":477,"end_time":2473.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2468.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In my mind, it should be a little bit of, kind of customer driven, but also data driven.","index":478,"end_time":2481.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2474.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s like we can create leads based off of repeat website traffic behavior and that would funnel them into marketing automated campaigns.","index":479,"end_time":2489.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2481.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hey, like, almost like you abandoned your, your cart type of thing in a retail store.","index":480,"end_time":2493.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2489.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But when you think about the different products we''re have, we''re going to have to expand on the information.","index":481,"end_time":2498.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2494.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We kind of ask the customer to, to an extent because you don''t want to make the form too big because then it''ll abandon it.","index":482,"end_time":2503.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2498.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But it''s like on the mortgage side, for example, like you might ask a question like, you know, what stage of the home buying process are you in?","index":483,"end_time":2509.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2504.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are you just looking?","index":484,"end_time":2510.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2509.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are you ready to buy?","index":485,"end_time":2511.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2510.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Do you, you know, because then that would say if they''re ready to buy, that''s an automatic go to the, you know, the, the loan officer.","index":486,"end_time":2517.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2511.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But if they''re just looking, it''s not, you know, they''re not ready.","index":487,"end_time":2521.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2517.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":488,"end_time":2521.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2521.21,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Home buying cycle could be, you know, six months, you know, and they''re not going to, you know, call them.","index":489,"end_time":2527.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2521.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But then as they go through the marketing, you know, cycle will come up with different triggers that would say, okay, like what''s the turning point to then say they''re ready now for the sales team?","index":490,"end_time":2537.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2527.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":491,"end_time":2538.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2538.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":492,"end_time":2539.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2538.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s something we have to kind of build Out Colin.","index":493,"end_time":2541.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2539.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So you might want to, you know, start to put that template together because we''ll have to get approval on that from the team.","index":494,"end_time":2547.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2541.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, and we''ll utilize FormLogic as well and then have unique identifiers on the form so that we say, you know, this is what they were searching for, etc.","index":495,"end_time":2553.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2547.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":496,"end_time":2555.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2554.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":497,"end_time":2557.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2556.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":498,"end_time":2558.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2557.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":499,"end_time":2558.439,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2558.2,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And we can continue to get into the weeds in this in our other meetings, Christina and Victor.","index":500,"end_time":2562.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2558.439,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But right now it sounds like the main triggers for contact creation is going to be obviously the integration between the systems and then form fills from the website and then any batch like file CSV uploads.","index":501,"end_time":2575.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2562.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, if you were to hold an event or say, you know, you''re just talking about this other system that may not be integrated at first.","index":502,"end_time":2581.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2575.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we wanted to do batch uploads, then we could just do that through HubSpot as well.","index":503,"end_time":2585.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2581.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One question.","index":504,"end_time":2587.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2586.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, Betty, and maybe I could have a conversation with, with Ingress, but I''m just thinking like when a customer calls and there''s certain information that, you know, that they need, you know, rather than kind of, you know, walking them through it, they might be able to just say, hey, what''s your email address?","index":505,"end_time":2606.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2588.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll send you maybe like a how to guide or some type of resource.","index":506,"end_time":2609.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2606.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":507,"end_time":2609.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2609.23,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Is there a way where we could track GPS cases so they could almost like maybe assign something to trigger a marketing activity and not be something that we capture from.","index":508,"end_time":2622.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2609.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"From Salesforce.","index":509,"end_time":2623.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2622.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I would like it to be a little bit more engaging between the call center teams, the branch teams and the sales teams for them to trigger, even on the, you know, the loan side, like they.","index":510,"end_time":2633.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2623.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Something in their loses might trigger a marketing activity to happen based off of them selecting like, you know, a survey or something.","index":511,"end_time":2640.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2633.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think you just have to narrow down or be very targeted in terms of what it is you would ask that team to request.","index":512,"end_time":2649.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2641.84,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Because obviously, given that you''re speaking to someone over the phone, we are cautious in terms of what is being collected and entered by one of our own versus the customer being present and, you know, certain ID being validated.","index":513,"end_time":2666.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2649.64,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So I think as long as you have that alignment with her, that that''s absolutely doable.","index":514,"end_time":2671.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2666.47,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"And she''s, she''s very much on board with, with trying to help the sales efforts overall.","index":515,"end_time":2680.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2671.91,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I think that, I think that would be great because then it would give us an opportunity to, you know, if the customer just calls to request more information about our products, we could just send them, you know, an email or something like that one other thing I forgot that I didn''t see it in the data list.","index":516,"end_time":2696.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2680.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But is NMLS numbers in the.","index":517,"end_time":2698.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2696.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The criteria list?","index":518,"end_time":2701.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2699.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because when we do Mark, it''s not.","index":519,"end_time":2704.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2701.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Do we.","index":520,"end_time":2704.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2704.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Can we get that?","index":521,"end_time":2705.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2704.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I said I don''t.","index":522,"end_time":2706.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2705.55,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":523,"end_time":2706.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2706.23,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":524,"end_time":2707.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2706.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You can''t read lives, Christina.","index":525,"end_time":2710.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2709.43,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"No, no, I stink at that.","index":526,"end_time":2713.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2711.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But only because when we go to do like mortgage, you know, marketing emails, eventually I would like to build out different workflows to have emails be signed from like the mortgage loan officer or the branch manager.","index":527,"end_time":2733.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2716.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we would want to capture like their information from the employee profile, like their, their home base, their title, their NMLs, stuff like that.","index":528,"end_time":2743.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2733.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":529,"end_time":2744.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2743.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some of that data may.","index":530,"end_time":2746.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2744.63,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"If it really isn''t in.","index":531,"end_time":2748.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2746.95,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"In Salesforce, it''s probably an encompass and it might be information that we can surface through the, through the connector that we''re leveraging.","index":532,"end_time":2761.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2749.67,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So.","index":533,"end_time":2762.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2761.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":534,"end_time":2763.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2762.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think there are avenues to explore if that type of information isn''t there.","index":535,"end_time":2767.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2763.24,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":536,"end_time":2768.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2767.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To the information related to the actual users that are.","index":537,"end_time":2775.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2772.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":538,"end_time":2777.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2777,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, it depends on what we have collected for the users.","index":539,"end_time":2782.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2779,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Like are you trying to get title or positions of things of that nature, Christina, or.","index":540,"end_time":2787.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2782.6,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because some of the stuff that does live in Salesforce.","index":541,"end_time":2789.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2787.4,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, sometimes we, you know, sometimes I think there''s better, you know, engagement if we have a communication be from a direct sales rep or from a branch manager when we do more targeted campaigns like by branch.","index":542,"end_time":2805.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2790.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so sometimes rather than, you know, sending it out from Ponzi bank management, you know, we can create like a lookup field and pull in the branch manager, mortgage loan, you know, banker''s name.","index":543,"end_time":2819.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2806.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But there would be certain fields that we would need, you know, especially on the loan side.","index":544,"end_time":2824.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2820.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if we can get that, then just.","index":545,"end_time":2826.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2824.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We have to make sure they''re put on that.","index":546,"end_time":2827.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2826.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That sheet.","index":547,"end_time":2828.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2827.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":548,"end_time":2832.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2832.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because that lives in a different.","index":549,"end_time":2833.549,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2832.55,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Different object itself is not necessarily on the contact as a separate database that we got to look at, but we can, we can bring in some of that information of the person that worked.","index":550,"end_time":2843.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2833.95,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"For example, if you booked on account, you booked an account, you would like the contact of the person who booked the account as well or something of that nature.","index":551,"end_time":2853.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2844.81,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":552,"end_time":2853.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2853.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And I would say, Gabe, if you''re able to just give them the list of fields that we''re pulling in from encompass the same way that you did for the course side, that might be helpful in terms of then kind of going through that and saying this is valuable data versus not.","index":553,"end_time":2875.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2855.77,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah, I know that would be.","index":554,"end_time":2879.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2878.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That would be helpful.","index":555,"end_time":2880.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2879.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I think the only Other thing where I don''t think, you know, you guys, Gabe and Ashley are going to necessarily have access to, but I would eventually want to think about those other third party systems where we would have to have an API.","index":556,"end_time":2895.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2881.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for example, we''re going to be building out the Careers page.","index":557,"end_time":2900.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2895.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Eventually we''ll want to be able to track applications to actual hire.","index":558,"end_time":2906.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2900.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And there''s a gap right now when somebody clicks on a.","index":559,"end_time":2909.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2906.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"An ad, a careers page and then applies.","index":560,"end_time":2912.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2909.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We don''t know like what the decisioning is.","index":561,"end_time":2914.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2912.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so if we can get that done, just let me know how I would go about that, Colin, if that''s possible.","index":562,"end_time":2921.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2914.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because then I can bring in Melissa and it would be the same thing on the LOS side with the approved loans and things like that.","index":563,"end_time":2928.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2921.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If we can''t get that from the core.","index":564,"end_time":2931.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2929.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":565,"end_time":2931.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2931.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What platform are you utilizing right now to manage, like when people submit a resume?","index":566,"end_time":2936.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2931.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not 100% sure the name Kronos is like our HR management system, but I think there''s another system for recruiting.","index":567,"end_time":2943.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2937.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Not using Kronos for that.","index":568,"end_time":2945.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2944.4,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Like Kronos is when the person is hired.","index":569,"end_time":2947.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2945.88,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, it might be ADP, but I''m not 100% sure.","index":570,"end_time":2952.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2947.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I forget what I applied through.","index":571,"end_time":2953.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2952.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I have to look.","index":572,"end_time":2954.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2953.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":573,"end_time":2955.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2955.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it would depend on the system.","index":574,"end_time":2956.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2955.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we could likely also build a custom app inside of HubSpot for that.","index":575,"end_time":2960.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2956.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":576,"end_time":2964.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2962.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":577,"end_time":2965.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2964.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, as you guys know, we work in all sorts of shapes and flavors of who handles what on the integration side.","index":578,"end_time":2972.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2965.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sometimes we own things holistically.","index":579,"end_time":2974.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2973.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In this arrangement, you guys are handling the integration with the systems as well.","index":580,"end_time":2978.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2974.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing that we just want to understand on our side is currently when something fails, is there an alert message that is sent to specific members of the team?","index":581,"end_time":2987.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2978.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is the course of action?","index":582,"end_time":2988.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2987.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it sent directly from mulesoft to Salesforce?","index":583,"end_time":2991.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2989.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Populate an error.","index":584,"end_time":2992.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2991.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What.","index":585,"end_time":2992.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2992.66,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"What''s going on with that right now?","index":586,"end_time":2994.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2992.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, we usually get the notifications out.","index":587,"end_time":2999.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2995.5,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It created kind of creates a case for us and then we can see the notification cases.","index":588,"end_time":3002.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2999.02,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It kind of triggers a notification on the case that opens up.","index":589,"end_time":3007.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3003.74,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So if something fails, we''ll definitely.","index":590,"end_time":3009.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3007.1,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"If any automation fails within mulesoft.","index":591,"end_time":3012.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3010.48,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We do have a case creation in Salesforce, so we can see that.","index":592,"end_time":3016.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3012.68,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":593,"end_time":3017.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3016.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So with that then we would likely just need open lines of communication.","index":594,"end_time":3021.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3019.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys see an error come through on the mulesoft side that we are not, that we don''t have visibility into.","index":595,"end_time":3026.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3021.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If it''s anything that we need to correct in HubSpot, let us know.","index":596,"end_time":3028.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3026.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If HubSpot because HubSpot will let us know of errors.","index":597,"end_time":3031.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3028.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if it''s happening in the mulesoft side, it may not.","index":598,"end_time":3034.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3032.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, typically when on the API level, I''m not sure if it''ll reply back.","index":599,"end_time":3041.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3035.26,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It depends on the error handler that we set up.","index":600,"end_time":3044.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3041.42,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"If we actually stop the transaction, most likely your system is going to get updated with that as well.","index":601,"end_time":3049.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3045.5,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But that''s something that we can test out as we build.","index":602,"end_time":3054.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3051.34,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We can go through those routes.","index":603,"end_time":3056.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3054.62,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, and that''s why I said we should have a cadence for doing a data validation back to almost that we used to do it back to the data like we would look at.","index":604,"end_time":3066.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3056.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":605,"end_time":3067.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3066.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We have a hundred, 100 accounts.","index":606,"end_time":3068.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3067.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The balances are this, like we would match everything to make sure that both systems, you know, were accurate, even like by the product type.","index":607,"end_time":3075.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3068.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":608,"end_time":3076.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3075.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that might be a little bit overkill because we, you.","index":609,"end_time":3079.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3077.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We were doing that for the CRM more specifically.","index":610,"end_time":3082.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3079.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But you know, it can''t hurt to set like a standard list of like a checklist of things that we''re going to validate every month.","index":611,"end_time":3088.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3082.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t think it''s overkill at all.","index":612,"end_time":3090.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3089.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Especially when it comes to data.","index":613,"end_time":3091.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3090.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You want to make sure that everything is clean and all systems are communicating the same way.","index":614,"end_time":3094.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3091.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We typically do a weekly maintenance of HubSpot, but with the lack of visibility in other systems we would just be sending, like, here''s the standpoint, like, here''s how many contacts we have, accounts we have things like that to be validated on your end from, you know, soft and Salesforce standpoint.","index":615,"end_time":3111.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3096.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So as of, as of right now, for example, another connector that we have is Encompass.","index":616,"end_time":3119.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3114.06,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And Encompass actually has its own section within Salesforce that it can sort of be managed.","index":617,"end_time":3128.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3120.06,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So like system connections or the inbound data sync or error log.","index":618,"end_time":3132.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3128.1,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So not sure if HubSpot will also have something like this.","index":619,"end_time":3136.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3133.02,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I guess we''ll know more once we plug it in.","index":620,"end_time":3139.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3136.98,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"But that might also be a good tool for the team to go into and review.","index":621,"end_time":3143.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3139.02,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":622,"end_time":3145.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3144.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":623,"end_time":3147.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3147.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So with eight minutes left, just want to be clear on next steps and everything.","index":624,"end_time":3151.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3148.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the spreadsheet we''ll go through and Gabe, you and I will work asynchronously to make sure that is updated with any fields that need to be mapped, do not need to be included in data syncs and anything that we are missing from what Betty''s point was of the Encompass fields that would be nice to have in there so that we can have visibility on those.","index":625,"end_time":3168.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3151.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then if we are all set there we will build all of that into the sandbox and then let you guys know when the integration is ready to connect.","index":626,"end_time":3178,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3170.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Before then, it would be great to have like just a sample CSV of a few contact records with the fields that you are usually seeing populated so that we can make sure that when we test these integrations, everything is communicating appropriately.","index":627,"end_time":3190.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3178.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so can you do me a favor?","index":628,"end_time":3193.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3191.97,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I don''t think that I have access to the, to the Excel sheet that you were looking at before.","index":629,"end_time":3198.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3193.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I was.","index":630,"end_time":3200.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3198.93,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I was looking actually at the other one that Victor provided to us that had all the HubSpot.","index":631,"end_time":3205.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3200.21,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":632,"end_time":3207.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3206.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I can share that.","index":633,"end_time":3208.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3207.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No problem.","index":634,"end_time":3208.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3208.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Objects in it.","index":635,"end_time":3209.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3208.45,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So can you share that?","index":636,"end_time":3210.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3209.37,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that way we can.","index":637,"end_time":3211.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3210.17,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"If it''s in.","index":638,"end_time":3211.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3211.31,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"In a SharePoint, we can.","index":639,"end_time":3214.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3212.75,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We can both make updates to it with no problems.","index":640,"end_time":3217.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3214.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, no.","index":641,"end_time":3218.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3217.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No problem at all.","index":642,"end_time":3219.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3218.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can send that right after this meeting.","index":643,"end_time":3220.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3219.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can take.","index":644,"end_time":3223.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3222.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So you want me to provide as well the list of fields that are coming from Encompass, right?","index":645,"end_time":3227.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3223.31,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be great.","index":646,"end_time":3228.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3227.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just to give you information.","index":647,"end_time":3229.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3228.91,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I don''t think they necessarily populate the account object, they actually populate the Opportunity object, so.","index":648,"end_time":3237.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3229.87,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But I''ll provide those as well.","index":649,"end_time":3240.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3239.63,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":650,"end_time":3241.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3241.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''ll be good to get visibility into that and then we can make a decision.","index":651,"end_time":3244.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3241.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because if that''s populating Opportunity object, the most similar to that inside of HubSpot is a deal object.","index":652,"end_time":3250.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3244.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can determine what path we want for those systems to communicate.","index":653,"end_time":3255.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3251.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":654,"end_time":3258.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3255.47,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":655,"end_time":3259.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3259.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":656,"end_time":3260.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3260.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And for the Excel is, I don''t know, Victor or Christina, are you going to go through those fields and kind of let us know which fields you need additional information on to determine if that''s a field that you want to bring in or not?","index":657,"end_time":3275.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3260.39,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"There may be a lot of those fields.","index":658,"end_time":3278.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3277.09,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Is there more fields than what we looked at in that Excel, doc?","index":659,"end_time":3284.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3281.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well, no, I''m talking about the fields in that Excel document.","index":660,"end_time":3288.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3285.65,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah, we scrubbed.","index":661,"end_time":3290.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3289.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We scrubbed some of it.","index":662,"end_time":3291.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3290.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Some of them were added in there because we really didn''t know what they were.","index":663,"end_time":3294.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3291.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So slash, they were like, questionable.","index":664,"end_time":3296.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3294.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think we''re okay for now.","index":665,"end_time":3299.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3296.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Victor and I will go through it.","index":666,"end_time":3301.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3300.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If we have any, like, glaring questions, we''ll.","index":667,"end_time":3303.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3301.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''ll we''ll raise it and then when Gabe goes through it with Colin, he can further explain, but I think that, that we''re okay.","index":668,"end_time":3310.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3303.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":669,"end_time":3313.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3312.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, super excited, very excited to get into actually building this out and, and making these communications work between these systems.","index":670,"end_time":3322.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3315.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Really appreciate you guys time.","index":671,"end_time":3324.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3323.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy that we could get this call on the calendar and if any Questions.","index":672,"end_time":3329.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3324.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, if you guys have anything, any questions, anything, please feel free to email us.","index":673,"end_time":3333.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3329.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re typically very quick to respond.","index":674,"end_time":3335.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3334.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":675,"end_time":3336.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3335.82,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"One thing, Colin, before we go, I think in your, in your email, just if you could clearly just define out for the team, like what, what we would have to complete by.","index":676,"end_time":3346.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3336.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When clear card dates to.","index":677,"end_time":3349.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3346.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To work against, and then any of the deliverables, that would be great.","index":678,"end_time":3353.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3349.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just put that in a chart.","index":679,"end_time":3355.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3353.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then at what point is this going to cross over into the other streams, the email, the social, and the.","index":680,"end_time":3362.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3355.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The website?","index":681,"end_time":3364.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3363.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because there''s a couple things that we''ll have to do for those and there are different teams.","index":682,"end_time":3368.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3364.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":683,"end_time":3370.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3369.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":684,"end_time":3371.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3370.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":685,"end_time":3373.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3372.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else that we didn''t cover that anyone was hoping to chat through or any questions?","index":686,"end_time":3377.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3373.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Colin, I have a small question.","index":687,"end_time":3380,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3378.44,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s related to that API documentation.","index":688,"end_time":3382.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3380,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I believe Victor provided a couple of links.","index":689,"end_time":3384.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3382.04,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"They''re related to HubSpot developers.","index":690,"end_time":3386.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3384.92,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Is that where I''m the best way for me to get all the information that I need related to the APIs?","index":691,"end_time":3391.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3386.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":692,"end_time":3392.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3391.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"HubSpot also has a marketplace that you can check out that has a lot of information with any APIs that they have just direct integrations with.","index":693,"end_time":3398.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3392.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the other place would be in the developer library because that is where we would build like a custom connected app.","index":694,"end_time":3404.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3398.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you.","index":695,"end_time":3405.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3405.29,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Can you do me a favor?","index":696,"end_time":3406.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3405.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Can you actually send me the links to those?","index":697,"end_time":3408.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3406.93,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, that I could actually start reviewing that and just putting pieces together so that I, you know.","index":698,"end_time":3414.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3408.57,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem at all.","index":699,"end_time":3416.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3415.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Be the best route of.","index":700,"end_time":3418.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3417.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Of us, because I''m pretty sure there''s several ways to connect to the hotspot, so just want to start taking a look at that.","index":701,"end_time":3426.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3418.25,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":702,"end_time":3427.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3426.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":703,"end_time":3429.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3428.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you, everyone for your time.","index":704,"end_time":3432.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3430.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hopefully.","index":705,"end_time":3432.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3432.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hope you all had a great holiday break last week and are ready for the new year.","index":706,"end_time":3437.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3432.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":707,"end_time":3438.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3438.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":708,"end_time":3439.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3438.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Friends are still on break.","index":709,"end_time":3440.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3439.18,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":710,"end_time":3440.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3440.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right, all right.","index":711,"end_time":3443.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3441.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"}],"dateString":"2025-12-29T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81885319336?pwd=R0wzhJrHbAF636Q1j9Eo4Jc7P4W2a3.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net,christina.zanca@poncebank.net,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,ashlie.taska@poncebank.net,betty.campiz@poncebank.net,victor.garcia@poncebank.net","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net","christina.zanca@poncebank.net","ashlie.taska@poncebank.net","betty.campiz@poncebank.net","victor.garcia@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KD5SAAFFFFET5E6DZ7JZSX8S","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Confirmed use of Mulesoft for bidirectional data syncs between HubSpot and Salesforce.","Aligned on transformation for fields like IDs, dates, and picklists between platforms.","Identified PII fields to mask; Betty flagged gender identity as a compliance concern.","Discussed adding ClearTouch ID as stable identifier beyond HubSpot’s default email key.","Agreed on regular data validation and shared responsibility for system error monitoring."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Something like gender identity absolutely should not be there because we shouldn''t be getting into that territory.","speaker":"bettycampiz"},{"quote":"Before then, it would be great to have like just a sample CSV of a few contact records.","speaker":"colincostigan"},{"quote":"We should have a cadence for doing a data validation back to... make sure that both systems... were accurate.","speaker":"christinazanca"}],"topics":["integration","data","privacy","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-29T22:51:33Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Data Integration and Field Mapping**\n\nThe team agreed on a clear plan to map Salesforce account and contact data to HubSpot with precise transformation rules to ensure clean, consistent data flow (04:58).\n\n- **Salesforce account objects will be split into company and contact records in HubSpot**, differentiated by Salesforce record types to keep data organized and manageable (05:42).\n    - Contacts and companies will be linked logically in HubSpot to maintain relationship context.\n    - Gabriel explained that Mulesoft will handle most data transformations, especially for IDs, date-time fields, and picklist values, to align with HubSpot’s requirements.\n    - Christina emphasized the need to handle transformations both ways—from Salesforce to HubSpot and vice versa—for lead and campaign data sync.\n    - Data masking for sensitive fields like Social Security numbers will be applied via Mulesoft, per Christina and Gabriel, to comply with privacy needs.\n- The existing spreadsheet with **field mappings will be refined, color-coded, and scrubbed** to identify essential fields, questionable ones, and those needing masking, enabling a targeted data subset for marketing use (16:36).\n    - Betty highlighted the removal of sensitive fields like gender identity to avoid legal risks.\n    - Gabriel will review the list for any additional masking needs and provide descriptions for unclear fields.\n    - Christina and Victor will finalize field priorities and flag any outstanding questions.\n- The team confirmed **HubSpot supports custom identifiers and picklist options**, allowing smooth integration with Salesforce’s existing data structure (14:49).\n- Unique identification will primarily rely on **email addresses**, but including the **Clear Touch external ID** as a secondary unique key was recommended by Betty and Gabriel to improve matching accuracy across systems (24:17).\n- The **Encompass loan system fields** will be added to the integration scope since they populate the Salesforce Opportunity object, which aligns with HubSpot’s deal object, allowing future campaign personalization based on loan officer data (53:42).\n- Batch uploads will be supported for non-integrated data sources, enabling marketing to import lists from events or third-party systems as CSV files directly into HubSpot (42:38).\n\n## **Data Quality and Validation Processes**\n\nThe team recognized the critical need to address data quality before and during integration to avoid marketing and operational failures (29:00).\n\n- Christina raised concerns about **bad data quality from BI and existing systems**, including truncated business names and misspellings, which caused mail list errors previously (29:00).\n    - Betty suggested an internal audit of the **business analytics nightly batch files**, as they represent the most accurate source, to catch issues early before data reaches Salesforce or HubSpot.\n    - Victor agreed to resubmit access requests to business analytics for Christina’s team to perform this data review and cleaning (31:26).\n- A **regular data validation cadence** will be established post-integration, with weekly or monthly checks comparing record counts and balances across HubSpot and Salesforce to ensure sync integrity (50:56).\n    - Colin confirmed HubSpot performs weekly maintenance but emphasized the need for shared visibility with Salesforce and Mulesoft teams on data discrepancies and errors.\n    - Ashlie noted Encompass has its own error logs, which could complement HubSpot’s monitoring once connected.\n- Gabriel detailed that **Mulesoft triggers error cases within Salesforce on sync failures**, enabling issue tracking and resolution by the integration team (49:55).\n- The team agreed that removing backend automation fields and system flags from marketing sync would reduce clutter and improve clarity in HubSpot (18:35).\n\n## **Integration Timing and Real-time Sync Needs**\n\nThe group prioritized a hybrid approach to data sync frequency balancing real-time needs with nightly batch updates to optimize marketing responsiveness and system load (37:25).\n\n- Most data syncs will occur via **nightly batch uploads aligned with Clear Touch Salesforce schedules**, ensuring consistency with core system updates (37:54).\n    - Betty noted the importance of this timing for most data except for critical triggers like account booking or lead generation.\n- Real-time triggers will be implemented especially for **form submissions and account bookings** to enable immediate marketing actions such as welcome emails or lead notifications (38:47).\n    - Gabriel described leveraging Salesforce automation flows to push real-time updates through Mulesoft to HubSpot immediately upon account booking.\n- Christina emphasized the need for real-time data where possible to support **surveys, lead management, and customer engagement triggers**, with the goal of reducing delays in campaign responses (38:28).\n- Lead management processes will be redesigned so that **HubSpot becomes the primary system for initial lead capture and nurturing**, with qualified leads then routed to Salesforce for sales follow-up (39:56).\n    - Christina described plans to enhance forms with behavioral triggers and segmentation to improve lead scoring and routing.\n    - Colin agreed to build form templates with unique identifiers to support this flow.\n\n## **Cross-System Relationship and Householding Strategies**\n\nThe team focused on ensuring data relationships and householding are well represented and synchronized to avoid marketing errors and improve segmentation accuracy (23:14).\n\n- HubSpot will **store relationship context internally**, associating contacts with companies and households rather than mirroring Salesforce’s account structure directly (22:35).\n- Betty flagged the importance of a **bidirectional sync for householding** to keep contact center and branch engagement aligned with marketing data, preventing confusion over account roles and marketing eligibility (23:14).\n- Christina warned about the risk of incorrectly including beneficiaries or trust-listed individuals in marketing campaigns, emphasizing proper segmentation rules and awareness (27:26).\n- The team agreed to build **segmentation fields to distinguish direct customers from Ponzi Bank customers** to maintain separate brand streams in HubSpot for clearer marketing messaging (15:26).\n- Additional fields related to employee status and do-not-market flags will be carefully managed to avoid inadvertent marketing to internal staff (22:35).\n\n## **Operational Collaboration and Next Steps**\n\nClear roles, documentation, and communication plans were established to ensure smooth integration progress and issue resolution (52:24).\n\n- Colin and Gabriel will **collaborate asynchronously to update the field mapping spreadsheet**, including adding Encompass fields and clarifying masking needs (52:24).\n- A **sample CSV of contact records will be shared** before integration testing to validate field population and data flow accuracy (52:24).\n- Colin committed to sending **API documentation links and HubSpot developer resources** to Gabriel to facilitate integration development (56:31).\n- Victor and Christina will complete the **field review and prioritize marketing data needs**, escalating questions as needed to Gabriel and Colin (54:20).\n- The team will define a **timeline with clear milestones for completion and handoffs**, including when integration crosses over to email, social, and website teams to coordinate campaigns (55:36).\n- Regular communication channels will be maintained for error notifications, sync issues, and process updates, leveraging Mulesoft’s case creation in Salesforce and HubSpot error monitoring (49:52).\n- Christina will coordinate with cash management and Prosper teams to explore **API or batch upload options** for integrating those third-party data sources into HubSpot (36:18).","outline":null,"keywords":["Salesforce Integration","HubSpot Sync","Mulesoft Data Transformation","Data Masking","Lead Management","Marketing Automation"],"overview":"- **Data Mapping Agreement:** Salesforce account data will be organized in HubSpot as companies and contacts for consistency.\n\n- **Data Transformation Responsibilities:** Mulesoft to manage data transformations, including sensitive field masking for compliance purposes.\n\n- **Regular Data Validation:** Weekly checks post-integration will ensure data integrity between HubSpot and Salesforce.\n\n- **Sync Strategy Established:** Most data will sync nightly, with real-time triggers for lead generation and critical actions.\n\n- **Bi-directional Relationships:** HubSpot will maintain internal relationships and householding for accurate marketing segmentation and messaging.\n\n- **Collaborative Documentation:** Clear roles established for field mapping updates, integration testing, and communication plans.","action_items":"\n**Christina Zanca**\nCollaborate with Victor to review and scrub the Excel field mapping document and flag any questionable fields or missing info (54:20)\nFollow up with Victor on resubmitting access requests to Business Analytics to analyze and clean data before loading into HubSpot (32:00)\nInitiate calls with cash management and Prosper teams to explore available APIs or batch upload options for third-party product data integration (36:50)\nDeliver prioritized list of marketing fields to Gabe and Colin, including mortgage-centric fields like NMLS numbers (45:00)\nCoordinate internal discussions and training regarding lead management process changes and marketing tagging for inbound customer interactions (40:30)\nEnsure clear communication to call center and branch teams about marketing triggers and opt-out handling (44:00)\n\n**Gabriel Bencosme**\nProvide detailed descriptions of Salesforce fields in the mapping spreadsheet to clarify usage and exclude system/backend fields (18:30)\nShare list of Encompass fields (Opportunity object) currently integrated into Salesforce for evaluation of marketing relevance (53:45)\nReview and confirm which Salesforce fields require masking for PII before syncing to HubSpot (17:10)\nReview HubSpot API documentation and developer resources once links are provided by Colin (56:35)\nParticipate in asynchronous updates of field mapping document alongside Colin (52:15)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nSubmit ticket or resubmit access request for Christina to Business Analytics (32:00)\nAssist Christina with data review efforts related to source data quality and reporting issues (30:00)\nCollaborate with integration team on creation and testing of sample test records in sandbox environment (26:40)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare the latest version of the Excel field mapping spreadsheet with Gabriel and the team immediately after the meeting (53:20)\nProvide HubSpot API & developer documentation links to Gabriel for integration preparation (56:50)\nBuild sandbox environment incorporating agreed field mappings for Salesforce-HubSpot-MuleSoft syncs (52:00)\nCoordinate sharing of sample CSV test data for integration testing (52:15)\nDevelop clear timeline chart of deliverables and deadlines related to integrations and marketing streams for communication to wider team (55:30)\n\n**Ashlie Taska**\nAssist Victor and Christina with ongoing data review and validation tasks (30:00)\n\n**Betty Campiz**\nSupport discussions on householding strategy and ensure graduated roll-out with communications to marketing and sales (23:00)\nAdvise on sensitive field exclusions in data sync (gender identity etc.) for legal compliance (20:45)\nCoordinate team meetings with Cash Management and Prosper product SMEs for API integration discussions (36:45)\nProvide list of Encompass fields being currently integrated to assist marketing prioritization (47:50)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"4ddeac69-be61-4178-ae72-4482ee91bf49","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
    '2025-12-29 23:41:18.660926+00',
