-- Meeting: PTO Exchange Weekly (2025-12-29 20:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '3f032f15-833e-4d7d-9347-381febf6d953',
    '2025-12-29 20:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KD5SAACN3ECPYM34RZ6Z9TT1',
    'PTO Exchange Weekly',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Josh Reinhard"}'::text[],
    853,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86093865913?pwd=ajXSuerDGmcROjfezSWYYGsa7iPOWd.1',
    '{"id":"01KD5SAACN3ECPYM34RZ6Z9TT1","title":"PTO Exchange Weekly","summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Generation and Campaign Performance**\n\nThe new LinkedIn ad campaigns launched in mid-December are delivering **strong lead quality** with relevant contacts from notable companies (07:48).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** confirmed that leads are now assigned to **Steph** and **Dan**, with Steph officially starting today to manage these tasks (08:20).\n- The LinkedIn lead forms auto-fill company information, helping identify contacts like a head of HR at **PI Health** despite personal email addresses (08:30).\n- The team decided not to build an automatic data enrichment tool for leads since manual verification via **ZoomInfo** is sufficient and simpler, as per Josh Reinhard’s input (09:13).\n- Early campaign results include leads from companies such as **Carta** and **American Hm**, indicating strong targeting and promising pipeline quality (10:36).\n\n## **Team Structure and Role Transitions**\n\nThe team is adjusting to **Sam’s departure** and seeking continuity in leadership and communication (06:01).\n\n- Josh Reinhard explained they are **backfilling Sam’s role** but currently have no immediate needs for Colin’s team (06:01).\n- To maintain coordination, Dan and Steph may join weekly calls as secondary attendees to stay informed and provide input as needed, starting next week (06:10).\n- Meeting schedules will be flexible during the transition, with some sessions postponed to accommodate personal commitments, such as Josh’s family visit on the 31st (07:11).\n- Colin remains available despite planned time off midweek, ensuring ongoing support during the transition period (12:31).\n\n## **Process and Tool Access**\n\nAccess to design tools and shared resources remains critical for collaboration and handoff (11:04).\n\n- Colin noted that Sam promised to provide **Figma access** but had not yet done so; Josh plans to follow up to ensure this happens promptly (11:19).\n- Gaining Figma access will enable Colin’s team to take on more design-related tasks and reduce limitations on what Josh can do alone (11:40).\n- This tool access aligns with the broader goal of smooth operational handoff and clear division of responsibilities during the staffing change (11:50).\n\n## **Lead Assignment and Workflow Updates**\n\nLead routing is stabilizing to ensure clear ownership and responsiveness (12:02).\n\n- Josh confirmed he should no longer receive leads except for a small residual flow due to recent connection requests, which will taper off over the next few weeks (12:02).\n- Colin clarified that leads will now funnel directly to Steph or Dan based on territory, ensuring quicker follow-up and reducing confusion (08:10).\n- This updated workflow supports improved sales efficiency by connecting leads immediately to the right contacts (10:12).\n- The team will continue monitoring campaign performance and lead quality to adjust processes as needed (10:46).\n\n## **Campaign and Website Optimization Plans**\n\nOngoing tweaks and content updates aim to sustain and improve campaign results (10:46).\n\n- Colin is focusing on refining website content to better support lead generation and conversion efforts (10:46).\n- Performance of current campaigns is being tracked closely, with plans to adjust based on data rather than relying solely on one campaign’s success (10:50).\n- This iterative approach reflects a pragmatic marketing philosophy that balances multiple tactics and avoids overdependence on a single channel (10:50).\n- The team intends to maintain this approach while keeping an eye on future opportunities to enhance engagement and pipeline growth (10:50).","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn lead gen","campaign performance","sales team integration","Figma access","lead assignment","team transition"],"overview":"- **Lead Quality Improvement:** New LinkedIn campaigns are performing well, bringing leads from companies like Carta and American Hm.  \n- **Lead Assignment Changes:** Leads are now assigned to Steph and Dan for better management and quicker follow-up.  \n- **Team Transition Strategy:** Adjustments are made post-Sam''s departure, with Dan and Steph joining calls for continuity.  \n- **Tool Access Needed:** Figma access is essential for better design tasks; follow-up is necessary to secure it.  \n- **Efficient Lead Routing:** Leads will now go directly to specified team members to enhance sales efficiency.  \n- **Ongoing Campaign Optimization:** Website content is being refined to boost lead generation and track performance closely for adjustments.","action_items":"\n**Josh Reinhard**\nEnsure Colin Costigan receives Figma access from Sam to facilitate design collaboration (11:04)\nMonitor lead assignment transition and verify no leads are sent to Josh after existing connection request follow-ups end (11:50)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nContinue monitoring and tweaking LinkedIn ad campaigns for performance, focusing on quality lead generation and task assignments to Steph and Dan (07:48)\nMaintain ongoing work on website content updates to support campaign effectiveness and user engagement (10:46)\nBe available as needed for communication despite planned days off, balancing work with family care (12:24)\n\n**Unassigned**\nAdd Dan and Steph to weekly calls starting next week for secondary meeting participation and sales input (coordination led by Josh and Colin) (06:48)\n"},"duration":14.210000038146973,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Josh Reinhard"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Josh.","index":0,"end_time":242.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":246.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What''s up, Colin?","index":2,"end_time":247.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":3,"end_time":247.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":4,"end_time":248.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about you?","index":5,"end_time":248.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":248.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not too bad.","index":6,"end_time":249.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"After Christmas, it was good, but being around, having my kid around, other family''s kids.","index":7,"end_time":259.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":250.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re all sick, Unfortunately.","index":8,"end_time":262.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, like, 50% of the people I talk to today, that''s been the case.","index":9,"end_time":267.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Something''s going around, too, especially.","index":10,"end_time":270.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Especially when there''s kids involved.","index":11,"end_time":272.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":270.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Different types of germs and not what they''re used to.","index":12,"end_time":275.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, unfortunately, I feel like this is going to be the next few years of my life.","index":13,"end_time":279.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, we went.","index":14,"end_time":281.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, it was funny because we did that.","index":15,"end_time":283.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then, like, the next kid would get old enough that they would be in daycare and then they would bring stuff home.","index":16,"end_time":289.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":17,"end_time":290.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The kids were bringing stuff home from school.","index":18,"end_time":291.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It was like.","index":19,"end_time":292.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":291.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It felt like we were, like, in this all directions.","index":20,"end_time":294.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":21,"end_time":295.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Really.","index":22,"end_time":296.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Finally on the other side of it now, it feels like, for the most part.","index":23,"end_time":298.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":296.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":24,"end_time":299.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":25,"end_time":300.529,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.049,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sorry to hear that.","index":26,"end_time":302.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, all good.","index":27,"end_time":303.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was your Christmas?","index":28,"end_time":305.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was good.","index":29,"end_time":306.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, we don''t have a huge family, so it''s pretty low key compared to, like, where I grew, grew up with.","index":30,"end_time":316.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There was always a ton of people, like, yeah, three siblings.","index":31,"end_time":320.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"My dad had three siblings.","index":32,"end_time":322.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":321.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So all the aunts and uncles, all the cousins, all the grandparents, you know, it was like, nuts.","index":33,"end_time":328.089,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":322.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then here in Seattle, it''s my family, and my wife''s sister lives close to us, and she doesn''t have any aunts or uncles.","index":34,"end_time":337.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.089,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Her mom''s here.","index":35,"end_time":339.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Her dad passed away.","index":36,"end_time":340.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There''s like, you know, when we''re all together, there''s like 11 of us.","index":37,"end_time":345.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":38,"end_time":345.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Loki is nice.","index":39,"end_time":347.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":40,"end_time":347.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s not.","index":41,"end_time":348.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, it''s not the worst thing in the world.","index":42,"end_time":349.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":43,"end_time":350.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":44,"end_time":352.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I don''t know if you wanted to start.","index":45,"end_time":354.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you had anything to share out of you and Sam and Rob connecting on.","index":46,"end_time":358.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything for us.","index":47,"end_time":359.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re still kind of up in the air on all that stuff.","index":48,"end_time":363.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Today''s the first day without Sam.","index":49,"end_time":365.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think we''re trying to figure out kind of like, where.","index":50,"end_time":367.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Where everything lands right now.","index":51,"end_time":369.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":368.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":52,"end_time":370.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I don''t think we have any immediate needs for you guys, but one thing that I do think might change a little bit.","index":53,"end_time":378.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we''re in the process of trying to backfill Sam''s role, but in the interim, and maybe ongoing, if it''s not too much, we might have Dan and Steph join our weekly calls.","index":54,"end_time":388.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":378.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":55,"end_time":389.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Just so they know what''s going on and can have a little bit of input when.","index":56,"end_time":395.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, this would be a secondary meeting for them.","index":57,"end_time":397.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So if they have Customer meetings or, you know.","index":58,"end_time":400.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, that''ll take prospect stuff.","index":59,"end_time":401.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That would take brighter, but.","index":60,"end_time":402.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But if they''re around.","index":61,"end_time":403.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Dan particularly was like, you know, expressing interest on just being involved, which.","index":62,"end_time":408.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":63,"end_time":409.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":408.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":64,"end_time":410.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":409.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I really also.","index":65,"end_time":412.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do like being able to talk to salespeople too, just to like see how things close on the other side of the loop of delivering some leads, so.","index":66,"end_time":419.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be great.","index":67,"end_time":420.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":419.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":420.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":69,"end_time":421.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So Dan''s on PTO today and then the next call we have was what''s Mondays and Thursdays?","index":70,"end_time":428.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":71,"end_time":428.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So Thursday''s the first, so it''ll probably just start next week.","index":72,"end_time":431.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":73,"end_time":432.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you in on Thursday?","index":74,"end_time":434.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I am not.","index":75,"end_time":435.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":434.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not.","index":76,"end_time":435.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":77,"end_time":436.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you want to move that meeting to Friday or go it for this week?","index":78,"end_time":440.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, forego it for this week.","index":79,"end_time":441.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"My brother''s coming into town actually for the first time in like seven or eight years and he''s getting here on the 31st.","index":80,"end_time":446.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I''m trying to not do anything on Friday, Friday if I can.","index":81,"end_time":449.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m like, yep, only responding to things.","index":82,"end_time":452.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I would rather if we can just punt that till next week.","index":83,"end_time":456.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":84,"end_time":456.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":456.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":85,"end_time":457.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":456.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just took that off and then.","index":86,"end_time":459.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know.","index":87,"end_time":460.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I knew we were having this meeting, but, you know, did the ads that we launched in the middle of December have been doing much better on performance.","index":88,"end_time":467.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":89,"end_time":469.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":468.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And so we''ve added several.","index":90,"end_time":471.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we made the updates to get Steph assigned as the contact owner and get tasks assigned to her.","index":91,"end_time":477.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like even this Stacy who filled it out with her personal email address, she is like the head of human resources at, what was it, PI Health in New Jersey.","index":92,"end_time":488.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":478.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":93,"end_time":489.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":489.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, yeah, I mean, we''re getting some, some good quality leads coming in and the tasks are going straight to Steph for those or Dan if they''re in his territory.","index":94,"end_time":498.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Steph starting as of today?","index":95,"end_time":500.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yes.","index":96,"end_time":501.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":97,"end_time":503,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How are you figuring out that that''s where she is and where she works?","index":98,"end_time":509.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":504.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s coming through on the LinkedIn form that they fill out.","index":99,"end_time":513.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the cool thing about LinkedIn lead gen forms is they don''t have to fill out all their information.","index":100,"end_time":517.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":513.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It comes pre filled.","index":101,"end_time":518.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":102,"end_time":519.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have like company HQ in there as a field and it''s grabbing that from their profile.","index":103,"end_time":524.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So even though she''s putting her Comcast email.","index":104,"end_time":527.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So yeah, this is the email that she signed up with for LinkedIn.","index":105,"end_time":531.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":528.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why it''s collecting that I could run an enrichment and try and get her.","index":106,"end_time":536.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was about to say it doesn''t automatically run an enrichment through whatever like zoom info or whatever.","index":107,"end_time":544.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, it doesn''t currently, but I could build something like that.","index":108,"end_time":548.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":544.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Don''t worry about it for now.","index":109,"end_time":554.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":553.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Let me see what the team thinks.","index":110,"end_time":556.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":554.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because if they see that and they say it''s a comcast email, but it''s showing her title and her job and stuff, I mean they can just go into zoom info and just.","index":111,"end_time":565.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or you know, pulling the info from zoom info because it''s going to be in there anyway.","index":112,"end_time":570.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a head of human resources at PI Health.","index":113,"end_time":572.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s been there for I don''t want to.","index":114,"end_time":574.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t want you and a half years build something that''s not that difficult for them to do.","index":115,"end_time":578.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, but yeah, this one looked good.","index":116,"end_time":582.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean all the titles that have been coming through on the.","index":117,"end_time":585.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry if I''m cutting out.","index":118,"end_time":587.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":586.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry, I heard you on not building it until.","index":119,"end_time":590.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unless they say that they need it.","index":120,"end_time":592.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":590.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you hear me?","index":121,"end_time":596.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, can you hear me now?","index":122,"end_time":598.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":597.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yes.","index":123,"end_time":598.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, I seemed like I was cutting out there.","index":124,"end_time":600.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":598.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Oh, good.","index":125,"end_time":601.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you said just don''t build it until.","index":126,"end_time":603.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":601.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unless they say they really need it.","index":127,"end_time":605.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean I don''t know how difficult it is to build but it just seems like an easy thing for them to do.","index":128,"end_time":609.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":605.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So yeah, I think you don''t need to worry about it.","index":129,"end_time":612,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":130,"end_time":612.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds good.","index":131,"end_time":613.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, I mean the titles have been great.","index":132,"end_time":616.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Coming through.","index":133,"end_time":616.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So another resources.","index":134,"end_time":618.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the new ads are performing well.","index":135,"end_time":621.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So excited to see that.","index":136,"end_time":624.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":621.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":137,"end_time":624.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":624.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just so there will be task.","index":138,"end_time":627.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":624.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looks like you took care of a task on this one, so that''s good.","index":139,"end_time":630.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":627.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m a little bit behind on task.","index":140,"end_time":632.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I got you to get through.","index":141,"end_time":634.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":632.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, no worries.","index":142,"end_time":636.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":634.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But yeah, a lot of good companies.","index":143,"end_time":638.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":636.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Carta, big one American.","index":144,"end_time":639.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hm.","index":145,"end_time":640.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So definitely some good ones coming in.","index":146,"end_time":643.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":147,"end_time":644.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":643.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":148,"end_time":644.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":644.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Other than that I don''t really have too many updates.","index":149,"end_time":648.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just going to keep tweaking on things and working on the website content.","index":150,"end_time":653.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we get all of that taken care of and published and just going to keep looking at performance of the campaigns and seeing what improvements we can make.","index":151,"end_time":661.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":653.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously the last one took but I don''t put all my eggs in that basket, so.","index":152,"end_time":664.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":153,"end_time":666.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then I was going to ask you something.","index":154,"end_time":670.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So when.","index":155,"end_time":671.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"When you were working with Sam on stuff, did he give you access to figma?","index":156,"end_time":678.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"He did not.","index":157,"end_time":679.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He mentioned he was going to give me access to Figma when the three of us met last week, but I never saw an email come through.","index":158,"end_time":684.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":159,"end_time":685.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I have like something else to talk to him about so I might just ask him about that because I want to make sure you Guys do have access to it because there''s some things I can do in figma, but I''m like, limited.","index":160,"end_time":695.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And if we need stuff, it would be good to know that we could potentially throw it over to you guys.","index":161,"end_time":700.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":695.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":162,"end_time":701.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let me.","index":163,"end_time":702.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":701.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"When I talk to him, I''ll just make sure he sends you access to that.","index":164,"end_time":707.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":703.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":165,"end_time":708,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''d be great.","index":166,"end_time":708.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":167,"end_time":710.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":708.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Other than that, is there anything else you need from me?","index":168,"end_time":712.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":169,"end_time":716.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":715.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So going forward, I should not be getting any leads coming to me.","index":170,"end_time":720.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":716.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Correct.","index":171,"end_time":721.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":720.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So the only way that that would happen is if, like, in the last few weeks you sent a connection request, or we did on your behalf, and then someone accepts it.","index":172,"end_time":729.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":722.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like next week.","index":173,"end_time":730.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would be the only thing.","index":174,"end_time":732.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But like.","index":175,"end_time":732.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, virtually, you know, in the next few weeks you will see if any.","index":176,"end_time":737.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''ll be very little.","index":177,"end_time":738.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":737.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then after that, zero.","index":178,"end_time":739.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''ll be gone.","index":179,"end_time":740.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":180,"end_time":740.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":181,"end_time":741.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":182,"end_time":743.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":742.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":183,"end_time":745.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":744.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, if you need anything, reach out.","index":184,"end_time":746.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s your.","index":185,"end_time":749.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your schedule is.","index":186,"end_time":750.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":749.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You''re working?","index":187,"end_time":751.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We are.","index":188,"end_time":752.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m actually out Wednesday and Thursday this week.","index":189,"end_time":754.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":190,"end_time":755.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":755.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But, you know, as always, you''ve.","index":191,"end_time":758.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":756.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''ve noticed I am always online and available, so.","index":192,"end_time":762.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t want you to be for stuff like this because you take some time, especially if you''re compromised.","index":193,"end_time":769.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You gotta rest up.","index":194,"end_time":770.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":769.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, well, I''ll focus on the baby right now.","index":195,"end_time":772.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":196,"end_time":773.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":772.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It sucks seeing a little baby sick.","index":197,"end_time":775.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":773.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":198,"end_time":775.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What''s.","index":199,"end_time":776.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Does she have any, like, anything real bad going on?","index":200,"end_time":778.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":776.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, just.","index":201,"end_time":779.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just a cold so far.","index":202,"end_time":780.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like today.","index":203,"end_time":780.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just like heard it in her sleep last night and she woke up and it''s just boogers everywhere, so, you know, fever and stuff like that.","index":204,"end_time":787.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":205,"end_time":788.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just trying to take care of her.","index":206,"end_time":789.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How old is she again?","index":207,"end_time":789.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":789.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like nine months or something.","index":208,"end_time":790.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":789.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"She just turned 11 months yesterday.","index":209,"end_time":792.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, she''ll be one year next month.","index":210,"end_time":795.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, nice.","index":211,"end_time":797.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":795.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"My brother, just like two weeks ago or something, he went to go visit his wife''s family and they have little kids and his wife ended up getting Covid and his daughter got rsv, which I don''t know if you''ve had to deal with that yet.","index":212,"end_time":812.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":797.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That is a tough one.","index":213,"end_time":814.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":813.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, no, we have luckily not had two, but I''m gonna knock on all.","index":214,"end_time":817.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The wood I can find right now.","index":215,"end_time":819.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a tough one.","index":216,"end_time":820.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":819.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So they thought she was gonna have to spend the night in the hospital.","index":217,"end_time":822.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Then she was in for a few hours and then they released her.","index":218,"end_time":825.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But that''s one where you''re like, oh, I want that.","index":219,"end_time":828.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"My nephew had that, and it was when they were on vacation in Florida, so they had to spend, like, an extra few days at the hospital.","index":220,"end_time":833.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Brutal.","index":221,"end_time":835.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":835.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, well, get healthy.","index":222,"end_time":838.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":835.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Happy Happy New Year.","index":223,"end_time":840.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":839.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":224,"end_time":841.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":841.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll just ping you if I need anything, but I doubt I will this week.","index":225,"end_time":844.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s pretty quiet.","index":226,"end_time":844.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":227,"end_time":846.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":228,"end_time":846.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks for everything, Josh.","index":229,"end_time":847.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":230,"end_time":847.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":847.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Talk to you soon.","index":231,"end_time":848.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":847.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"}],"dateString":"2025-12-29T20:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86093865913?pwd=ajXSuerDGmcROjfezSWYYGsa7iPOWd.1","participants":["josh@ptoexchange.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,sam@ptoexchange.com","josh@ptoexchange.com","sam@ptoexchange.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KD5SAACN3ECPYM34RZ6Z9TT1","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.87,"bullets":["Confirmed Steph and Dan may join weekly calls to provide sales insight during Sam''s absence.","Validated new LinkedIn ads launched mid-December are performing well, generating quality leads.","Rerouted all new tasks to Steph or Dan; Josh confirmed no longer receiving inbound leads.","Colin updated ownership and task assignments in CRM; Steph officially onboarded as of today.","Deferred Thursday meeting due to holidays; next sync will resume after New Year."],"highlights":[{"quote":"The ads that we launched in the middle of December have been doing much better on performance.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Going forward, I should not be getting any leads coming to me. Correct.","speaker":"Josh Reinhard"}],"topics":["handoff","lead routing","ads","sales alignment"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-29T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Generation and Campaign Performance**\n\nThe new LinkedIn ad campaigns launched in mid-December are delivering **strong lead quality** with relevant contacts from notable companies (07:48).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** confirmed that leads are now assigned to **Steph** and **Dan**, with Steph officially starting today to manage these tasks (08:20).\n- The LinkedIn lead forms auto-fill company information, helping identify contacts like a head of HR at **PI Health** despite personal email addresses (08:30).\n- The team decided not to build an automatic data enrichment tool for leads since manual verification via **ZoomInfo** is sufficient and simpler, as per Josh Reinhard’s input (09:13).\n- Early campaign results include leads from companies such as **Carta** and **American Hm**, indicating strong targeting and promising pipeline quality (10:36).\n\n## **Team Structure and Role Transitions**\n\nThe team is adjusting to **Sam’s departure** and seeking continuity in leadership and communication (06:01).\n\n- Josh Reinhard explained they are **backfilling Sam’s role** but currently have no immediate needs for Colin’s team (06:01).\n- To maintain coordination, Dan and Steph may join weekly calls as secondary attendees to stay informed and provide input as needed, starting next week (06:10).\n- Meeting schedules will be flexible during the transition, with some sessions postponed to accommodate personal commitments, such as Josh’s family visit on the 31st (07:11).\n- Colin remains available despite planned time off midweek, ensuring ongoing support during the transition period (12:31).\n\n## **Process and Tool Access**\n\nAccess to design tools and shared resources remains critical for collaboration and handoff (11:04).\n\n- Colin noted that Sam promised to provide **Figma access** but had not yet done so; Josh plans to follow up to ensure this happens promptly (11:19).\n- Gaining Figma access will enable Colin’s team to take on more design-related tasks and reduce limitations on what Josh can do alone (11:40).\n- This tool access aligns with the broader goal of smooth operational handoff and clear division of responsibilities during the staffing change (11:50).\n\n## **Lead Assignment and Workflow Updates**\n\nLead routing is stabilizing to ensure clear ownership and responsiveness (12:02).\n\n- Josh confirmed he should no longer receive leads except for a small residual flow due to recent connection requests, which will taper off over the next few weeks (12:02).\n- Colin clarified that leads will now funnel directly to Steph or Dan based on territory, ensuring quicker follow-up and reducing confusion (08:10).\n- This updated workflow supports improved sales efficiency by connecting leads immediately to the right contacts (10:12).\n- The team will continue monitoring campaign performance and lead quality to adjust processes as needed (10:46).\n\n## **Campaign and Website Optimization Plans**\n\nOngoing tweaks and content updates aim to sustain and improve campaign results (10:46).\n\n- Colin is focusing on refining website content to better support lead generation and conversion efforts (10:46).\n- Performance of current campaigns is being tracked closely, with plans to adjust based on data rather than relying solely on one campaign’s success (10:50).\n- This iterative approach reflects a pragmatic marketing philosophy that balances multiple tactics and avoids overdependence on a single channel (10:50).\n- The team intends to maintain this approach while keeping an eye on future opportunities to enhance engagement and pipeline growth (10:50).","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn lead gen","campaign performance","sales team integration","Figma access","lead assignment","team transition"],"overview":"- **Lead Quality Improvement:** New LinkedIn campaigns are performing well, bringing leads from companies like Carta and American Hm.  \n- **Lead Assignment Changes:** Leads are now assigned to Steph and Dan for better management and quicker follow-up.  \n- **Team Transition Strategy:** Adjustments are made post-Sam''s departure, with Dan and Steph joining calls for continuity.  \n- **Tool Access Needed:** Figma access is essential for better design tasks; follow-up is necessary to secure it.  \n- **Efficient Lead Routing:** Leads will now go directly to specified team members to enhance sales efficiency.  \n- **Ongoing Campaign Optimization:** Website content is being refined to boost lead generation and track performance closely for adjustments.","action_items":"\n**Josh Reinhard**\nEnsure Colin Costigan receives Figma access from Sam to facilitate design collaboration (11:04)\nMonitor lead assignment transition and verify no leads are sent to Josh after existing connection request follow-ups end (11:50)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nContinue monitoring and tweaking LinkedIn ad campaigns for performance, focusing on quality lead generation and task assignments to Steph and Dan (07:48)\nMaintain ongoing work on website content updates to support campaign effectiveness and user engagement (10:46)\nBe available as needed for communication despite planned days off, balancing work with family care (12:24)\n\n**Unassigned**\nAdd Dan and Steph to weekly calls starting next week for secondary meeting participation and sales input (coordination led by Josh and Colin) (06:48)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"10afd0eb-6ddf-4966-956c-c203dc7bbc49","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
