ce the site goes live we were going to use the KTC search.","index":560,"end_time":1652.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1647.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So what he''s going to probably do over the next week or so is the.","index":561,"end_time":1656.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1652.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"The email that like Kristen has and most of the team has the Kirsten Talent capitalsplural co She''s.","index":562,"end_time":1662.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1656.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"He''s gonna transition everybody over to that KTC search.","index":563,"end_time":1665.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1662.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I told him not to mess with any of our other domain stuff because once you guys move stuff, either I give you access, you take care of it, or I can hook you up with him and you guys take it from there.","index":564,"end_time":1674.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1665.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":565,"end_time":1675.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1674.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, and we do prefer if Ryan''s okay with it.","index":566,"end_time":1678.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1675.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do prefer just having control of the environment.","index":567,"end_time":1680.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1678.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":568,"end_time":1681.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1680.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope, I want you guys to have telephone.","index":569,"end_time":1682.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1681.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep, that''s what I told him.","index":570,"end_time":1683.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1682.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I said I''m assuming they will take care of it itself.","index":571,"end_time":1685.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1683.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But you know, you guys just tell him what you want and then you guys take admin consult control on that.","index":572,"end_time":1690.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1685.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys control.","index":573,"end_time":1691.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1690.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":574,"end_time":1691.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1691.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":575,"end_time":1692.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1691.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, sounds great stuff.","index":576,"end_time":1694.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1692.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, thank you guys very much.","index":577,"end_time":1695.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1694.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Talk soon.","index":578,"end_time":1696.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1696.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Bye.","index":579,"end_time":1697.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1696.67,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"}],"dateString":"2025-12-23T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83519004309?pwd=JvKSZR6BzSlyNxK5WTgZHYayMsLSKi.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,michael@kerstentalentcapital.com,kristen@kerstentalentcapitals.co,kristen.baller@richeymay.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","michael@kerstentalentcapital.com","kristen@kerstentalentcapitals.co","kristen.baller@richeymay.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KCMJGQH85T45QFRTS6R3ZQVC","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Presented 30-page ABM strategy to drive targeted engagement across email, LinkedIn, and ads.","Michael confirmed outbound campaigns and paid ads are aligned for January rollout.","Colin committed to facilitating Clay subscription through their existing rep due to access issues.","Website redesign progressing; stakeholders will provide feedback via interactive Markup tool.","Preliminary content calendar populated with guests and topics; production readiness planned post-launch."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I want to make sure the site''s done...so that way they have a brand.","speaker":"Michael Kersten"},{"quote":"Everything that we do is backed by data...we''re going to review the performance.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I want to make sure we''re working towards stuff versus we have a list.","speaker":"Kristen Baller"}],"topics":["launch","outbound","content","branding","integration"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-23T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy and Outbound Campaign**\n\nThe team agreed on launching a focused ABM campaign targeting private equity (PE) operating partners and portfolio company leaders to build a predictable pipeline beyond referrals.\n\n- **Colin Costigan** presented a detailed **30+ page ABM plan** emphasizing a narrow focus on PE operators and portfolio companies to turn KTC’s referral momentum into a consistent pipeline (07:00)  \n    - The strategy layers email sequences, LinkedIn outreach, retargeted ads, and podcast content to build brand awareness and top-of-mind recall for hiring needs.  \n    - The campaign aims for quality engagement over volume, starting with **four emails** and refining weekly based on open rates and website visits, avoiding a fixed email count upfront.  \n    - Paid ads are included with a recommended starting budget of **$3,000**, to be regularly reviewed and adjusted based on performance metrics.  \n    - This multi-touch approach is designed to keep KTC visible until prospects are ready to engage actively.  \n\n- **Michael Kersten** raised interest in integrating contact data and CRM workflows with tools like **Clay** and HubSpot to improve outbound efficiency (09:30)  \n    - Colin confirmed the team will help broker Clay access due to recent changes from self-serve to rep-driven sales, addressing Michael’s difficulty getting direct support.  \n    - The integration will support clean data flow and allow tracking of leads alongside HubSpot records, enabling marketing and sales alignment.  \n    - Colin explained they will build a **custom dashboard (\"data box\")** linking campaign metrics, HubSpot data, and website activity for transparent, real-time tracking accessible by KTC (24:30).  \n    - This dashboard will include engagement signals to guide timely outreach, such as website visit frequency and email interactions.  \n\n## **Website Development and SEO Optimization**\n\nThe website redesign is progressing with multiple pages designed and content rewritten to improve keyword rankings and support the ABM strategy.\n\n- The team reviewed pages including **Executive, Resources, Contingent Hiring, and Services**, all integrated into a feedback tool called **Markup** for easy commenting and edits (12:20)  \n    - Michael emphasized the importance of highlighting both **contingent and retained search** terms to improve search engine visibility for common client queries (13:00).  \n    - Colin confirmed SEO is a key focus in the new content, aiming to maintain and enhance current keyword rankings without losing momentum.  \n    - A keyword table outlining targeted phrases per page will be shared for transparency and approval.  \n\n- Logo and branding updates are underway based on feedback to increase green tones and explore gradient effects while preserving a professional look (19:20)  \n    - Michael suggested subtle color blends to align with parent company **Richie May** branding for future integration, aiming for seamless visual cohesion by Q1 or Q2 2024.  \n    - Colin confirmed the team will prepare logo versions reflecting potential co-branding as an RM Talent Solutions affiliate, ready for deployment when needed (21:40).  \n    - Email signatures, letterhead, and other collateral will be updated accordingly after final logo approval.  \n\n## **Content Marketing and Podcast Development**\n\nA structured content calendar and podcast framework will drive thought leadership and client engagement using internal and external guests.\n\n- Colin shared a **living content calendar** with Michael and Kristen to track topics, guests, publish dates, and URLs, allowing dynamic collaboration and updates (14:00)  \n    - Michael confirmed **Darren Pitre, EVP Sales at Sunbelt Solomon**, is ready to participate as a guest, signaling early content momentum.  \n    - The team will provide guests with a flexible framework and talking points to simplify participation and maintain consistent messaging.  \n\n- Michael proposed leveraging high-energy external voices like **Felicia, CMO of Richie May**, and potential interviews with **Alex (PE firm principal)** and placed CROs to diversify content and testimonials (16:00)  \n    - Colin agreed to build interview frameworks and research guest backgrounds to maximize relevance and audience interest.  \n    - Some interviews may be recorded in Q1 2024 depending on availability, supporting a staggered content rollout aligned with the website launch and campaign schedules.  \n\n- Kristen emphasized the importance of scheduling and deadline management to ensure content production aligns with Q1 goals and avoids delays (18:20).  \n\n## **Operational and Technical Integrations**\n\nThe team is aligning systems and workflows to support marketing automation, tracking, and domain management for a smooth launch and ongoing operations.\n\n- Michael noted the need for seamless **HubSpot integration and dashboard setup** to monitor campaigns and manage leads, with Colin confirming their ability to develop and maintain this infrastructure (24:00)  \n    - The HubSpot dashboard will enable both internal and client-side visibility into lead flow and campaign effectiveness.  \n\n- Domain and email management will transition to KTC branding, with **Google account admin access** handed over to the marketing team for control and alignment (27:40)  \n    - Michael assigned Brian, the Google admin, to coordinate this transition without disrupting existing domains or email services.  \n    - Colin stressed the preference for full admin control to streamline future changes and reduce dependencies.  \n\n- Meeting cadence was confirmed to resume on **January 6th**, with flexibility around Michael’s travel in mid-January, ensuring timely reviews of content and website progress (26:30).  \n\n## **Strategic Market Positioning and Future Planning**\n\nThe overall strategy focuses on evolving KTC from a referral-based firm to a data-driven, visible market leader in PE search, with layered content and branding supporting long-term growth.\n\n- Colin framed the ABM plan as a way to shift from unpredictable referrals to a controlled, repeatable pipeline driven by targeted multi-channel contact (07:10)  \n    - This approach positions KTC as a **“senior speed first” alternative** to competitors like Korn Ferry, focusing on rapid, clear hiring processes.  \n    - The plan emphasizes consistent brand exposure across channels to become the default option when clients decide to hire.  \n\n- Michael highlighted the need for brand cohesion with Richie May to prepare for future integration without disrupting current identity, reflecting a phased approach to corporate alignment (20:50)  \n    - This foresight aims to reduce friction and maintain client confidence during eventual co-branding or acquisition transitions.  \n\n- The content strategy, including podcasts and guest interviews, supports thought leadership and client engagement, helping differentiate KTC in a competitive market (16:20)  \n    - By using client testimonials and expert voices, KTC plans to build trust and showcase unique value propositions.  \n\n- Kristen’s focus on deadlines and scheduling reinforces the importance of execution discipline to realize strategic goals within Q1 2024.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","Website Development","Content Calendar","Paid Advertising","Lead Data Integration","Branding Strategy"],"overview":"- **Launch of ABM Campaign:** Focus on private equity leaders to create a predictable pipeline using emails, ads, and podcasts.  \n- **Integration with CRM:** Enhance efficiency through Clay and HubSpot integration to improve lead tracking and data flow.  \n- **Website Redesign Progress:** Multiple pages are being developed with SEO focus to boost keyword rankings and support ABM.  \n- **Content Calendar Establishment:** Structured plan to include guest interviews and maintain engagement aligned with launch strategies.  \n- **Branding Updates:** Logo redesign incorporating green tones and co-branding with Richie May to ensure cohesive identity.  \n- **Operational Workflow Alignment:** HubSpot dashboard and domain management will facilitate campaign monitoring and secure brand transition.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare the detailed ABM plan document and provide access to Markup tool for website feedback (07:16)\nContact Clay representative to facilitate Michael Kersten’s Clay subscription acquisition and resolve lack of direct support (10:55)\nDevelop a data dashboard (“data box”) linked with HubSpot for exportable front-of-funnel marketing performance metrics, accessible via Pulse portal (24:30)\n\n**Marketing Team**\nContinue developing and refining the website content, focusing on SEO keywords including ''contingent'' and ''retained'' hiring terms (12:50)\nProduce various logo iterations incorporating more green and potential Richie May co-branded versions, including email signature and letterhead templates (19:45)\n\n**Michael Kersten**\nProvide LinkedIn profiles for potential podcast guests such as Darren Pitre, Felicia (CMO Richie May), Alex (F3 Principal), and Randy (CRO EMC) to aid framework and research for interviews (17:10)\nCoordinate with Brian (Google admin) on transitioning staff emails to KTC Search domain, then hand over control to marketing for environment management (27:45)\n\n**Kristen Baller**\nCoordinate a one-on-one for scheduling content recordings and establishing deadlines (18:25)\n\n**All participants**\nPrepare for January 6th meeting and adjust schedules around Michael’s travel on January 14-16, keeping January 13th meeting slot confirmed (26:30)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"1f4ec69d-1576-4385-b9c9-a2e3e39d3b07","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
