WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '059db008-bde9-43e2-b5ea-2d8080194a92',
    '2025-12-22 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KCHEN272FVPTPTFPYFC1MBA3',
    'Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync',
    '{"victor garcia","Colin Costigan","Colin Costigan","Guille Santana"}'::text[],
    1090,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85439302813?pwd=qMBHtkNo4lURIrnTCVFhLG0k15ZQca.1',
    '{"id":"01KCHEN272FVPTPTFPYFC1MBA3","title":"Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Integration and Data Management**\n\nThe team is focused on finalizing system integration details and ensuring data flows smoothly between platforms.\n\n- **The sandbox environment inside HubSpot has been built and is ready for testing** with integration mapping documents pending final confirmation from the GPS team (06:19)  \n    - The team is awaiting answers on integration fields and property mapping to link Salesforce, Mulesoft, and ClearTouch systems  \n    - Colin explained that verifying these connections is crucial to ensure all systems communicate and share data effectively  \n    - Once confirmed, the team will populate the sandbox with sample data to validate workflows and integration accuracy  \n    - This step is critical to avoid delays in setup and ensure clean, secure data transfer through the pipelines  \n    - The GPS team’s input is essential as they handle data masking and PII concerns  \n\n- **Questions remain about how Salesforce objects like accounts and leads will align with HubSpot’s contact and company models** (13:03)  \n    - Victor noted this is primarily a conversation for Christina and Betty, as they hold the context for data flow and lead priming  \n    - Colin suggested compiling outstanding questions for Betty and Christina to clarify before proceeding further  \n    - This alignment affects how leads are created and tracked, impacting sales workflows and reporting accuracy  \n    - Victor will confirm Betty’s availability and update the team on decisions that will guide integration adjustments  \n\n- **Sample data for sandbox testing is needed, but the team currently only has field definitions, not example records** (11:14)  \n    - Victor will ask the GPS team for sample or dummy data to simulate realistic records in HubSpot  \n    - If unavailable, the team may create randomized data internally to ensure testing can continue without delay  \n    - This approach helps verify system behavior before going live and avoids using any real customer data  \n\n## **Website and Content Strategy**\n\nThe website structure is designed to support a large, multi-faceted banking platform with clear navigation and location-based content.\n\n- **A comprehensive sitemap has been developed covering personal, business, community banking, and branch location pages** (07:16)  \n    - Colin described grouping branch locations by city with dedicated pages to improve user navigation  \n    - Victor confirmed the current location tool contract will end soon (expected in April), so the team must build a new solution internally  \n    - The new approach aims to replace the Ubero-based location listing with a custom-built page matching existing data  \n    - This transition is critical to maintaining user experience and ensuring location information is accurate and easy to update  \n\n- **Brand asset delivery was completed last week, but no feedback has been received yet** (08:56)  \n    - Colin highlighted the need for direction on font choices, showing differences between the old and new fonts with implications for brand consistency  \n    - Victor flagged that final font decisions will come from Christina’s team, and communication on this should be included in the next email round  \n    - The brand guideline updates and design assets depend heavily on this decision to maintain consistency across all materials  \n    - The team also prepared print-ready laminate documents for review, aiming for cleaner versions than previous drafts  \n\n## **Project Coordination and Communication**\n\nClear communication between internal teams and GPS is essential to keep the project on track amid key personnel absences.\n\n- **Key personnel absences include Christina (out sick) and Jane (out for the rest of the year), impacting decision-making capacity** (04:22)  \n    - Victor and Colin agreed on the importance of capturing outstanding questions now to avoid wasting GPS team time on unclear issues  \n    - Victor is monitoring Betty’s availability, as her input is critical for Salesforce-HubSpot integration decisions  \n    - The team prefers asynchronous communication for simpler questions to keep progress moving despite scheduling challenges  \n    - Colin suggested preparing a list of questions to send to Victor for discussion with Christina and Betty, minimizing meeting delays  \n\n- **The immediate next meeting with the GPS team may be shortened or rescheduled due to pending clarifications and availability** (14:07)  \n    - Victor recommended waiting for Betty’s participation before deep technical discussions to avoid unproductive calls  \n    - This cautious approach aims to respect everyone’s time and ensure meetings drive clear outcomes rather than confusion  \n    - The team will adjust the agenda and timing based on Betty’s response and ongoing email updates  \n\n## **Technical Development and Timelines**\n\nThe technical build is progressing but requires clarity on Mulesoft development and data handling to finalize schedules.\n\n- **Mulesoft development status is unclear, with GPS team mentioning ongoing changes that have not been fully communicated** (10:12)  \n    - Victor was unaware of recent system changes and plans to raise this at the next GPS meeting for clarity  \n    - Colin recalled that Betty may have brought up these changes during kickoff meetings, highlighting the need for cross-team alignment  \n    - Understanding Mulesoft’s completion timeline is essential to coordinate integration and avoid bottlenecks  \n\n- **The data model and custom fields have been delivered for review, with property mapping efforts ongoing** (06:50)  \n    - The team is verifying field alignment across Salesforce, HubSpot, Mulesoft, and ClearTouch to maintain consistent data definitions  \n    - This work supports seamless data flow and accurate reporting across business units  \n    - Timely completion of this mapping is vital to meet downstream project milestones and launch targets  \n\n## **Next Steps and Follow-up**\n\nThe team is focused on consolidating questions, confirming personnel availability, and preparing deliverables for review.\n\n- **Victor will send updates via email after consulting with Christina and Betty to clarify outstanding integration questions** (16:30)  \n    - Colin requested the team send any additional questions to Victor to ensure they are addressed comprehensively  \n    - This approach helps keep asynchronous progress steady while key decision makers are unavailable  \n    - The team is prepared to support communications via email or smaller meetings to avoid delays  \n\n- **Deliverables such as the sitemap, brand assets, and laminate documents will be packaged and sent for review promptly** (08:56)  \n    - The team aims to incorporate feedback quickly to maintain momentum on design and content finalization  \n    - Clear deadlines and feedback loops will be established to avoid stalling progress due to personnel absences  \n    - This aligns with the broader goal of launching the website and integrations on schedule with consistent branding and functionality","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot integration","Salesforce account objects","Mulesoft development","Brand assets and fonts","Website sitemap","GPS team collaboration"],"overview":"- **Integration Progress:** Sandbox in HubSpot ready for testing; waiting on GPS team for integration field confirmations.  \n- **Data Alignment:** Need clarity on how Salesforce objects connect to HubSpot, affects lead tracking and workflows.  \n- **Sample Data Request:** Victor to ask GPS for test records; if not available, team may create dummy data internally.  \n- **Website Navigation:** Comprehensive sitemap developed; new custom location tool needed due to current contract ending in April.  \n- **Brand Asset Feedback:** Delivery completed but awaiting feedback on font decisions; essential for brand consistency across materials.  \n- **Personnel Absences:** Key decisions impacted by Christina''s and Jane''s absences; need to gather questions to streamline communication with GPS.","action_items":"\n**Victor Garcia**\nVerify with GPS team regarding availability of sample data to populate HubSpot sandbox and share with Colin (12:28)\nConfirm status and decisions from Christina and Betty on Salesforce account objects, integration flows, and any outstanding questions; provide updates to Colin and team via email (16:30)\nForward all collected questions from Colin and team to Christina to facilitate clarifications or arrange further meetings as necessary (16:56)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nCompile and send any integration or technical questions to Victor for follow-up with GPS team and Christina (16:56)\nPackage and send site map and double-sided laminate brand documents, along with font comparison, to Christina and GPS for review and feedback (08:54)\n"},"duration":18.15999984741211,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"victor garcia"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Guille Santana"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, tristan.","index":0,"end_time":215.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.88,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":1,"end_time":215.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215.44,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Hey, Victor.","index":2,"end_time":223.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":3,"end_time":224.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.92,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":4,"end_time":224.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.48,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":5,"end_time":225.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.88,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":6,"end_time":226.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":7,"end_time":227.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.8,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"How was your weekend?","index":8,"end_time":228.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.16,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Not too bad.","index":9,"end_time":230,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Flew by, but got a lot of household chores done.","index":10,"end_time":233.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":230,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Definitely.","index":11,"end_time":235.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":235.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Definitely agree with you.","index":12,"end_time":237.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":236.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m saying, same here.","index":13,"end_time":238.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.17,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You, like, catch up on laundry and.","index":14,"end_time":242.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All the fun stuff, and you''re like, oh, cool.","index":15,"end_time":244.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I guess it''s time to go to bed.","index":16,"end_time":245.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":17,"end_time":248.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.77,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I literally just cleaned out my gear closet, so now it''s nice and prepared for me to mess it up again.","index":18,"end_time":255.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":249.37,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"There you go.","index":19,"end_time":256.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you know if we''ll have everyone today, Christina.","index":20,"end_time":262.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It will not be joining us.","index":21,"end_time":264.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.66,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"She is sick, and Jane is out for the remainder of the year.","index":22,"end_time":267.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.02,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":23,"end_time":268.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":24,"end_time":269.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, we''ll go through some things.","index":25,"end_time":270.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Might not need the whole 30 minutes.","index":26,"end_time":272.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":271.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I do want to just also pull up the agenda for the.","index":27,"end_time":276.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Meeting after this and just make sure we''re all good there.","index":28,"end_time":278.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":29,"end_time":279.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.74,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The only thing that Christina asked me to mention for you guys is the.","index":30,"end_time":289.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.94,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The documents look good.","index":31,"end_time":290.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.39,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I asked them to strip out the data and tech stuff into a doc so that we could share with the GPS team.","index":32,"end_time":294.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.51,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That was the only thing.","index":33,"end_time":295.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.87,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":34,"end_time":296.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":296.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s kind of the agenda that I.","index":35,"end_time":298.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":296.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That we put together for this.","index":36,"end_time":299.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just some, like, any last questions?","index":37,"end_time":302.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":300.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Making sure.","index":38,"end_time":303.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if you forwarded that to the GPS team or if you need us to or if that''s what she''s referring to.","index":39,"end_time":308.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Making a different version of the document.","index":40,"end_time":310.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":41,"end_time":310.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.41,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":42,"end_time":311.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":43,"end_time":311.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can make that.","index":44,"end_time":312.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just give me one moment.","index":45,"end_time":319.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.73,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''ll be right back.","index":46,"end_time":320.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem.","index":47,"end_time":321.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, guy.","index":48,"end_time":324.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Kirsten.","index":49,"end_time":325.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.89,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":50,"end_time":326.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":51,"end_time":328.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":328.25,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Hello.","index":52,"end_time":330.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":329.93,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Victor was just sharing with me.","index":53,"end_time":332.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":331.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''ll be right back.","index":54,"end_time":333.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":332.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He was just sharing that Christina''s out.","index":55,"end_time":335.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":333.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sick today and Jane is out for the rest of the year.","index":56,"end_time":337.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we''ll go through the.","index":57,"end_time":341.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Items in the agenda quickly, and then we''ll probably just spend most of our time going through the agenda for the meeting after this.","index":58,"end_time":347.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Victor said Christina asked us to basically take the data out.","index":59,"end_time":354.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":348.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, Victor, now that you''re back, maybe.","index":60,"end_time":355.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":354.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can just restate that again.","index":61,"end_time":357.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Take the data out of the documents.","index":62,"end_time":358.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":357.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We sent so that the GPS team.","index":63,"end_time":359.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can look at it.","index":64,"end_time":360.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":359.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":65,"end_time":361.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Strip out the data tech stuff into a doc so that we can share with the GPS team.","index":66,"end_time":365.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":362.38,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Cool.","index":67,"end_time":366.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.89,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Quote unquote.","index":68,"end_time":366.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":366.11,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":69,"end_time":367.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, definitely want to dive in a.","index":70,"end_time":370.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Little bit more into that.","index":71,"end_time":371.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll get through some of the housekeeping items, though.","index":72,"end_time":374.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''m ready whenever you guys are.","index":73,"end_time":378.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":74,"end_time":379.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":379.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So taking a look at Pulse, there''s just a Few things that we''re waiting on.","index":75,"end_time":384.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":379.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re really ready to set up the environment.","index":76,"end_time":387.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just down to these last questions with the GPS team of the integrations and fields and all the mapping documents and everything that we''ve sent.","index":77,"end_time":395.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So hoping that, you know, with this call after this meeting, we can have.","index":78,"end_time":400.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":396.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of those details ironed out and we can just put the finishing touches.","index":79,"end_time":403.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we did build the sandbox inside.","index":80,"end_time":404.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":403.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of HubSpot, so that''s all ready as well.","index":81,"end_time":406.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that was what they were requesting last time and I told them that you guys were working on that.","index":82,"end_time":410.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.07,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So.","index":83,"end_time":410.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.59,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":84,"end_time":411.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the sandbox is built and then we sent over like the postcard and.","index":85,"end_time":416.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":411.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Things like that for review.","index":86,"end_time":418.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So any feedback there?","index":87,"end_time":419.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":88,"end_time":421.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then same thing with the data.","index":89,"end_time":423.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":421.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Model and custom fields.","index":90,"end_time":425.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":423.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s just property mapping to make sure that Salesforce, mulesoft, cleartouch, whatever systems.","index":91,"end_time":430.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are, you know, locked in and in.","index":92,"end_time":431.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":430.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Place that they''re all communicating effectively.","index":93,"end_time":433.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":94,"end_time":434.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.89,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We have developed a site map for the entire website as well.","index":95,"end_time":439.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":436.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I won''t make you go blind.","index":96,"end_time":441.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is obviously a big website, so we have a lot of different pieces in here.","index":97,"end_time":445.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":441.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ponte Bank Direct is an aspect business banking, personal banking, community.","index":98,"end_time":450.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":445.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we even were taking an approach of having location pages for the branches.","index":99,"end_time":456.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":450.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can even just group these.","index":100,"end_time":458.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":457.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"By like city and have them listed on one page.","index":101,"end_time":461.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But just a place for someone to go to to understand, you know, the branches and ATMs that are near them.","index":102,"end_time":466.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":461.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you guys have another tool.","index":103,"end_time":467.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For that in place.","index":104,"end_time":468.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So do you know what the plan is with that other tool?","index":105,"end_time":472.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":106,"end_time":473.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So we have to build that out ourselves.","index":107,"end_time":474.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We''re getting rid of that contract soon, so we need to, we need to build that up.","index":108,"end_time":479.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":474.71,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I believe in April that.","index":109,"end_time":481.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.79,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And do you have.","index":110,"end_time":481.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":481.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there like a lit.","index":111,"end_time":483.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t really seen, like the back end of that page that lists out all your locations.","index":112,"end_time":488.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":483.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there like a document that it''s working from of all of the different.","index":113,"end_time":491.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":488.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Branches or how is that set up?","index":114,"end_time":493.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":491.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, it''s literally just.","index":115,"end_time":496.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.38,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It''s a locations page.","index":116,"end_time":498.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":497.26,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But the, the, the biggest thing that they use is.","index":117,"end_time":501.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.58,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Damn it, I forgot what the name.","index":118,"end_time":502.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":501.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Of the software was.","index":119,"end_time":503.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":502.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ubero, I believe it''s called.","index":120,"end_time":505.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.06,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So it''s literally just a webpage of all of our locations.","index":121,"end_time":509.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.3,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So that''s as simple as us building that ourselves.","index":122,"end_time":514.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.14,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":123,"end_time":515.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":514.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":124,"end_time":516.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":515.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can go through and just make sure that we have the same.","index":125,"end_time":518.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":516.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"List that they''re working with as well then about and careers and resources.","index":126,"end_time":523.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":518.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all of that built into here.","index":127,"end_time":525.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With pages that branch off of them for more information.","index":128,"end_time":528.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":526.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But this has been built out.","index":129,"end_time":530.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":529.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s nice.","index":130,"end_time":531.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.92,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Have you shared that with Christina yet?","index":131,"end_time":534.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.68,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We have not.","index":132,"end_time":534.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were planning to go through it today.","index":133,"end_time":535.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":134,"end_time":536.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.04,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But yeah, we can.","index":135,"end_time":537,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can package this up and send it, please.","index":136,"end_time":538.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":137,"end_time":540.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also shared all of the brand assets last week.","index":138,"end_time":543.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We haven''t seen any feedback, but that is.","index":139,"end_time":545.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure when Jade''s vacation started.","index":140,"end_time":546.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s probably a part of it.","index":141,"end_time":548.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably must have.","index":142,"end_time":550.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.06,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And she had asked for just a side by side comparison of the old font versus the new font.","index":143,"end_time":555.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":551.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is the old font over here.","index":144,"end_time":557.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can see just a subtle difference in the header.","index":145,"end_time":559.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":557.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Whereas this is just a little bit.","index":146,"end_time":561.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":560.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"More of the sans style.","index":147,"end_time":564.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the sans serif.","index":148,"end_time":566.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just a little bit more playful in the old one.","index":149,"end_time":568.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know she mentioned like the line thickness and the H''s.","index":150,"end_time":571.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":568.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if the decision is to switch back to the old font, we just need to know.","index":151,"end_time":576.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":571.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can update all the brand guidelines documentation and then all of the.","index":152,"end_time":579.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":576.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Designs that we''ve made so far.","index":153,"end_time":580.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":154,"end_time":581.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":580.76,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s definitely a conversation for them at that point.","index":155,"end_time":585.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.32,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So if you could just include that in the email when you send.","index":156,"end_time":588.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.8,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Of course.","index":157,"end_time":589.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":589.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Guille and I are reviewing, but we do have a few versions of that double sided laminate document that Christina was looking for.","index":158,"end_time":597.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":590.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we even have like the print.","index":159,"end_time":599.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":598.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rules and everything over here for getting those printed out.","index":160,"end_time":601.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we do have the first two versions of this.","index":161,"end_time":604.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":162,"end_time":604.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.43,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Hopefully this is a little bit cleaner than.","index":163,"end_time":608.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure what the team''s currently been working from.","index":164,"end_time":610.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":608.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nothing.","index":165,"end_time":611.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":611.23,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":166,"end_time":613.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":167,"end_time":614.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so we''ll send that over for review as well.","index":168,"end_time":616.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we were just waiting on.","index":169,"end_time":619.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":617.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There was conversations of Mulesoft development completion date.","index":170,"end_time":624.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When we were going through all of the kickoff meetings that we had.","index":171,"end_time":627.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":624.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was just changes that they were making to the system.","index":172,"end_time":631.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":628.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then that''s where like Clear Touch and other things got brought into the conversation.","index":173,"end_time":636.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just wanted to check in and.","index":174,"end_time":638.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":636.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kind of just talk about what''s going on there.","index":175,"end_time":640.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I am not even aware of that.","index":176,"end_time":642.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":640.48,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Funny enough, Christina was the one that mentioned that.","index":177,"end_time":646.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.88,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Or the GPS team were the ones that mentioned that.","index":178,"end_time":648.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.4,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I believe it was the GPS team, if my memory served me correctly.","index":179,"end_time":651.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":648.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was in like the series of meetings that we had.","index":180,"end_time":653.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":651.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll bring that up to them on this next meeting.","index":181,"end_time":657.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.29,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Because I wasn''t even aware of any.","index":182,"end_time":661.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.05,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Any other things outside of what we were doing.","index":183,"end_time":664.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":184,"end_time":665.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":664.61,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It may even have been Betty that brought it up.","index":185,"end_time":666.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just talking about, like changes that the team was making.","index":186,"end_time":670.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, not sure.","index":187,"end_time":672.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.57,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So we''ll bring that up in the next meeting.","index":188,"end_time":674.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.89,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":189,"end_time":675.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":674.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also we just talked about a sample CSV file of, you know, like records that you would typically have.","index":190,"end_time":681.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":675.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or information you would typically have for a record so that we could use that for the sandbox just to make sure everything is flowing as you guys expect.","index":191,"end_time":687.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":681.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I believe I''ve sent that over to you guys with all of the records that the GPS team were using.","index":192,"end_time":693.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.85,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So there was like sample context?","index":193,"end_time":695.849,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":694.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not sample context.","index":194,"end_time":698.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":697.69,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m sorry, it was just the.","index":195,"end_time":700.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.77,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All of the records or not all of the records.","index":196,"end_time":703.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.81,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m sorry.","index":197,"end_time":703.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":703.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of the, the fields that they use.","index":198,"end_time":706.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.77,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":199,"end_time":706.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":706.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have the fields document and that''s.","index":200,"end_time":709.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":706.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":201,"end_time":710.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":709.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we wanted.","index":202,"end_time":710.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We talked about having just a few sample records that we could populate.","index":203,"end_time":714.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, so not real customers of Ponte bank, but just some sample data from the team so that we could say like, okay, cool, we pass this into HubSpot and then we set up the integration between the systems or the.","index":204,"end_time":724.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":714.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your team goes in and sets up the integration.","index":205,"end_time":727.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":725.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we make sure that those are communicating.","index":206,"end_time":730.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":728.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got you.","index":207,"end_time":731.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":730.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":208,"end_time":732.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.51,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let''s ask the GPS team if they''re able to actually send us over some type of sample data or anything like that.","index":209,"end_time":739.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.55,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"If anything, I don''t see why we can''t just fill in some random data, but let''s see if they have anything that we could potentially use.","index":210,"end_time":748.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":739.23,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":211,"end_time":748.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":748.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it was more to see because we have the properties and the types of fields that they are.","index":212,"end_time":753.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":748.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just wanted to see the actual.","index":213,"end_time":754.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Information that goes in there.","index":214,"end_time":755.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":215,"end_time":756.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.47,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":216,"end_time":756.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":756.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I just have like a preview of our agenda for the call.","index":217,"end_time":761.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":757.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So really just trying to answer a few questions, you know, is there.","index":218,"end_time":767,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From all the HubSpot fields and everything that we''ve sent over.","index":219,"end_time":770.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":767.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to make sure that they''re able to make the system communicate with the integration.","index":220,"end_time":776.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":771.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I know that the team would be handling that per the PII and.","index":221,"end_time":780.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":776.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everything like that and data masking.","index":222,"end_time":781.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":780.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":223,"end_time":783.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":782.6,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So making sure they''re confident with that.","index":224,"end_time":784.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then really a big pivotal part is just understanding are we using account objects at all out of Salesforce?","index":225,"end_time":793,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":786.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because HubSpot is much more contact and company based versus what you guys had.","index":226,"end_time":797.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":793.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In Salesforce of contacts versus leads versus accounts.","index":227,"end_time":800.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":797.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just need to understand, you know, exactly how we want that data to flow.","index":228,"end_time":804.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m saying that''s the tough part.","index":229,"end_time":807.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.45,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":230,"end_time":808.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.61,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s more of a Christina thing for me.","index":231,"end_time":809.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m sorry, I Can''t be more help in this case because my.","index":232,"end_time":815.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.73,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"My thought process with this would definitely be that, you know, we get the information from into HubSpot and then transfer it over once the lead is ready to be primed, I guess by the sales team.","index":233,"end_time":829.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.49,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But I''m not sure if there was any closed off conversations or at least just conversations had between Betty and Christina at that point so that we know exactly what it is that we want to do.","index":234,"end_time":841.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.62,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And I don''t want to speak out of term.","index":235,"end_time":842.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":841.06,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":236,"end_time":843.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":842.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, damn.","index":237,"end_time":845.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.1,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Now I''m kind of just like.","index":238,"end_time":846.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.63,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So it might even be a conversation where we.","index":239,"end_time":850.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":847.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We even just leave with a list of things we need to confirm with.","index":240,"end_time":853.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":850.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With Betty and Christina.","index":241,"end_time":855.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":853.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":242,"end_time":856.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":855.55,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":243,"end_time":856.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":856.43,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I would even say maybe even reschedule.","index":244,"end_time":859.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.55,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But I know that there''s certain things that we can get out of this next meeting that we can continue pushing.","index":245,"end_time":863.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.67,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So.","index":246,"end_time":863.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.47,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we can.","index":247,"end_time":865.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":864.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tristan, do you have a thought there?","index":248,"end_time":867.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":865.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you think still valuable to have the.","index":249,"end_time":869.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":867.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The call after this or.","index":250,"end_time":870.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":869.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It seems like we still have maybe some questions of conversations that happen between.","index":251,"end_time":876.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":872.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Betty and Christina that not everyone is privy to of handling account records and things like that.","index":252,"end_time":880.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":876.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Victor, I mean, I leave it up to you all, but I mean, the questions we''re going to ask will probably rely upon some of those decisions.","index":253,"end_time":889.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":881.71,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So I just want to make sure we''re.","index":254,"end_time":891.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":889.31,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That folks don''t feel like we''re wasting their time.","index":255,"end_time":894.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":892.91,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Right, right, right.","index":256,"end_time":895.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":895.07,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":257,"end_time":896.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":895.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Give me one second.","index":258,"end_time":896.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":896.23,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let me actually see if Betty is.","index":259,"end_time":898.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":896.95,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Is even in today.","index":260,"end_time":899.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.43,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I know that she was.","index":261,"end_time":901.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":901.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She had a loss in the family too, so I''m not sure.","index":262,"end_time":904.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":901.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":263,"end_time":906.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.82,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I do see that she is in a meeting right now, so.","index":264,"end_time":909.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.3,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Hey, just.","index":265,"end_time":913.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.9,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, so then, you know what?","index":266,"end_time":927.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.55,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I think it''s best that we could probably just cut.","index":267,"end_time":929.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.55,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I mean, if there''s anything else that we need to go over, we could probably cut this meeting short.","index":268,"end_time":932.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.59,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Unless, like I said, unless there''s anything else.","index":269,"end_time":936.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.87,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But I''m confirming with Betty right now to see if she will be joining.","index":270,"end_time":939.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.95,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And if she does, then she''ll have the most say in how we''re going to maneuver in this case.","index":271,"end_time":946.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":940.79,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":272,"end_time":947.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":947.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":273,"end_time":948.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":947.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so it''s like the account records, understanding relationships with households or companies.","index":274,"end_time":954.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":948.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How much of the.","index":275,"end_time":958.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":957.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The website.","index":276,"end_time":958.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":958.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we were imagining was that the only contacts that would be originally created in HubSpot is a form filled from the website.","index":277,"end_time":965.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":958.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just confirming that and making sure that.","index":278,"end_time":971.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":965.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''S no other reason that we would.","index":279,"end_time":972.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":971.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Create a HubSpot record or a record.","index":280,"end_time":973.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":972.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In HubSpot originally versus them being created in another platform and being synced to HubSpot.","index":281,"end_time":979.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":973.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, that''s pretty much it.","index":282,"end_time":982.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, I don''t know if you''re going to meet with her or communicate with her.","index":283,"end_time":986.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":982.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you just want to send me.","index":284,"end_time":986.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":986.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"An email of what the status is of the meeting when you can.","index":285,"end_time":990.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":986.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it doesn''t seem like she''ll be joining this meeting, so.","index":286,"end_time":997.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":990.64,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, let me.","index":287,"end_time":1001.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1000.08,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let me get back to you guys, and I will send you an email once I have some type of direction from her.","index":288,"end_time":1006.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1001.6,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And, yeah, sounds good.","index":289,"end_time":1009.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But all the questions that you guys do potentially have, if you could just forward that to me in an email so that I can have that conversation with Christina tomorrow, and if we need to have a separate meeting with the GPS team just to get some of those answers, at least we can forward that to you so that it''s not a complete waste.","index":290,"end_time":1025.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1009.57,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":291,"end_time":1026.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":292,"end_time":1027.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1026.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, you know, we''re happy to have conversations with anyone or if anyone is more comfortable moving async and just, you know, answering any easy questions via email.","index":293,"end_time":1035.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1027.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or anything, we can do that, too.","index":294,"end_time":1036.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1035.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":295,"end_time":1037.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1036.75,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":296,"end_time":1038.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1037.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, thank you, Victor.","index":297,"end_time":1039.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1038.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, guys, have a good one.","index":298,"end_time":1040.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1039.15,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You too.","index":299,"end_time":1040.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1040.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sam.","index":300,"end_time":1084.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1062.28,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"}],"dateString":"2025-12-22T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85439302813?pwd=qMBHtkNo4lURIrnTCVFhLG0k15ZQca.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,jane.trachet@poncebank.net,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,victor.garcia@poncebank.net,rebecca.cruz@poncebank.net,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,christina.zanca@poncebank.net","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","jane.trachet@poncebank.net","victor.garcia@poncebank.net","rebecca.cruz@poncebank.net","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","christina.zanca@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KCHEN272FVPTPTFPYFC1MBA3","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.78,"bullets":["Confirmed sandbox environment and sitemap are ready; feedback pending from GPS and Christina.","Prepared stripped data/tech doc version for GPS team per Christina’s earlier request.","Awaiting clarification on Salesforce account object usage to shape HubSpot integration flow.","Requested sample data records to validate field mapping and test HubSpot sync functionality.","Pending decisions from Betty and Christina blocked deeper integration planning and next steps."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Yeah, I''m saying that''s the tough part... That''s more of a Christina thing for me.","speaker":"victor garcia"},{"quote":"We just need to understand, you know, exactly how we want that data to flow.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I just want to make sure... that folks don''t feel like we''re wasting their time.","speaker":"Guille Santana"}],"topics":["delivery","integration","data","process"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-22T20:32:05Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Integration and Data Management**\n\nThe team is focused on finalizing system integration details and ensuring data flows smoothly between platforms.\n\n- **The sandbox environment inside HubSpot has been built and is ready for testing** with integration mapping documents pending final confirmation from the GPS team (06:19)  \n    - The team is awaiting answers on integration fields and property mapping to link Salesforce, Mulesoft, and ClearTouch systems  \n    - Colin explained that verifying these connections is crucial to ensure all systems communicate and share data effectively  \n    - Once confirmed, the team will populate the sandbox with sample data to validate workflows and integration accuracy  \n    - This step is critical to avoid delays in setup and ensure clean, secure data transfer through the pipelines  \n    - The GPS team’s input is essential as they handle data masking and PII concerns  \n\n- **Questions remain about how Salesforce objects like accounts and leads will align with HubSpot’s contact and company models** (13:03)  \n    - Victor noted this is primarily a conversation for Christina and Betty, as they hold the context for data flow and lead priming  \n    - Colin suggested compiling outstanding questions for Betty and Christina to clarify before proceeding further  \n    - This alignment affects how leads are created and tracked, impacting sales workflows and reporting accuracy  \n    - Victor will confirm Betty’s availability and update the team on decisions that will guide integration adjustments  \n\n- **Sample data for sandbox testing is needed, but the team currently only has field definitions, not example records** (11:14)  \n    - Victor will ask the GPS team for sample or dummy data to simulate realistic records in HubSpot  \n    - If unavailable, the team may create randomized data internally to ensure testing can continue without delay  \n    - This approach helps verify system behavior before going live and avoids using any real customer data  \n\n## **Website and Content Strategy**\n\nThe website structure is designed to support a large, multi-faceted banking platform with clear navigation and location-based content.\n\n- **A comprehensive sitemap has been developed covering personal, business, community banking, and branch location pages** (07:16)  \n    - Colin described grouping branch locations by city with dedicated pages to improve user navigation  \n    - Victor confirmed the current location tool contract will end soon (expected in April), so the team must build a new solution internally  \n    - The new approach aims to replace the Ubero-based location listing with a custom-built page matching existing data  \n    - This transition is critical to maintaining user experience and ensuring location information is accurate and easy to update  \n\n- **Brand asset delivery was completed last week, but no feedback has been received yet** (08:56)  \n    - Colin highlighted the need for direction on font choices, showing differences between the old and new fonts with implications for brand consistency  \n    - Victor flagged that final font decisions will come from Christina’s team, and communication on this should be included in the next email round  \n    - The brand guideline updates and design assets depend heavily on this decision to maintain consistency across all materials  \n    - The team also prepared print-ready laminate documents for review, aiming for cleaner versions than previous drafts  \n\n## **Project Coordination and Communication**\n\nClear communication between internal teams and GPS is essential to keep the project on track amid key personnel absences.\n\n- **Key personnel absences include Christina (out sick) and Jane (out for the rest of the year), impacting decision-making capacity** (04:22)  \n    - Victor and Colin agreed on the importance of capturing outstanding questions now to avoid wasting GPS team time on unclear issues  \n    - Victor is monitoring Betty’s availability, as her input is critical for Salesforce-HubSpot integration decisions  \n    - The team prefers asynchronous communication for simpler questions to keep progress moving despite scheduling challenges  \n    - Colin suggested preparing a list of questions to send to Victor for discussion with Christina and Betty, minimizing meeting delays  \n\n- **The immediate next meeting with the GPS team may be shortened or rescheduled due to pending clarifications and availability** (14:07)  \n    - Victor recommended waiting for Betty’s participation before deep technical discussions to avoid unproductive calls  \n    - This cautious approach aims to respect everyone’s time and ensure meetings drive clear outcomes rather than confusion  \n    - The team will adjust the agenda and timing based on Betty’s response and ongoing email updates  \n\n## **Technical Development and Timelines**\n\nThe technical build is progressing but requires clarity on Mulesoft development and data handling to finalize schedules.\n\n- **Mulesoft development status is unclear, with GPS team mentioning ongoing changes that have not been fully communicated** (10:12)  \n    - Victor was unaware of recent system changes and plans to raise this at the next GPS meeting for clarity  \n    - Colin recalled that Betty may have brought up these changes during kickoff meetings, highlighting the need for cross-team alignment  \n    - Understanding Mulesoft’s completion timeline is essential to coordinate integration and avoid bottlenecks  \n\n- **The data model and custom fields have been delivered for review, with property mapping efforts ongoing** (06:50)  \n    - The team is verifying field alignment across Salesforce, HubSpot, Mulesoft, and ClearTouch to maintain consistent data definitions  \n    - This work supports seamless data flow and accurate reporting across business units  \n    - Timely completion of this mapping is vital to meet downstream project milestones and launch targets  \n\n## **Next Steps and Follow-up**\n\nThe team is focused on consolidating questions, confirming personnel availability, and preparing deliverables for review.\n\n- **Victor will send updates via email after consulting with Christina and Betty to clarify outstanding integration questions** (16:30)  \n    - Colin requested the team send any additional questions to Victor to ensure they are addressed comprehensively  \n    - This approach helps keep asynchronous progress steady while key decision makers are unavailable  \n    - The team is prepared to support communications via email or smaller meetings to avoid delays  \n\n- **Deliverables such as the sitemap, brand assets, and laminate documents will be packaged and sent for review promptly** (08:56)  \n    - The team aims to incorporate feedback quickly to maintain momentum on design and content finalization  \n    - Clear deadlines and feedback loops will be established to avoid stalling progress due to personnel absences  \n    - This aligns with the broader goal of launching the website and integrations on schedule with consistent branding and functionality","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot integration","Salesforce account objects","Mulesoft development","Brand assets and fonts","Website sitemap","GPS team collaboration"],"overview":"- **Integration Progress:** Sandbox in HubSpot ready for testing; waiting on GPS team for integration field confirmations.  \n- **Data Alignment:** Need clarity on how Salesforce objects connect to HubSpot, affects lead tracking and workflows.  \n- **Sample Data Request:** Victor to ask GPS for test records; if not available, team may create dummy data internally.  \n- **Website Navigation:** Comprehensive sitemap developed; new custom location tool needed due to current contract ending in April.  \n- **Brand Asset Feedback:** Delivery completed but awaiting feedback on font decisions; essential for brand consistency across materials.  \n- **Personnel Absences:** Key decisions impacted by Christina''s and Jane''s absences; need to gather questions to streamline communication with GPS.","action_items":"\n**Victor Garcia**\nVerify with GPS team regarding availability of sample data to populate HubSpot sandbox and share with Colin (12:28)\nConfirm status and decisions from Christina and Betty on Salesforce account objects, integration flows, and any outstanding questions; provide updates to Colin and team via email (16:30)\nForward all collected questions from Colin and team to Christina to facilitate clarifications or arrange further meetings as necessary (16:56)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nCompile and send any integration or technical questions to Victor for follow-up with GPS team and Christina (16:56)\nPackage and send site map and double-sided laminate brand documents, along with font comparison, to Christina and GPS for review and feedback (08:54)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"37799bd0-4406-4bc2-9058-ecb3ff07a654","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
