INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync',
  '## **Integration and Data Management**

The team is focused on finalizing system integration details and ensuring data flows smoothly between platforms.

- **The sandbox environment inside HubSpot has been built and is ready for testing** with integration mapping documents pending final confirmation from the GPS team (06:19)  
    - The team is awaiting answers on integration fields and property mapping to link Salesforce, Mulesoft, and ClearTouch systems  
    - Colin explained that verifying these connections is crucial to ensure all systems communicate and share data effectively  
    - Once confirmed, the team will populate the sandbox with sample data to validate workflows and integration accuracy  
    - This step is critical to avoid delays in setup and ensure clean, secure data transfer through the pipelines  
    - The GPS team’s input is essential as they handle data masking and PII concerns  

- **Questions remain about how Salesforce objects like accounts and leads will align with HubSpot’s contact and company models** (13:03)  
    - Victor noted this is primarily a conversation for Christina and Betty, as they hold the context for data flow and lead priming  
    - Colin suggested compiling outstanding questions for Betty and Christina to clarify before proceeding further  
    - This alignment affects how leads are created and tracked, impacting sales workflows and reporting accuracy  
    - Victor will confirm Betty’s availability and update the team on decisions that will guide integration adjustments  

- **Sample data for sandbox testing is needed, but the team currently only has field definitions, not example records** (11:14)  
    - Victor will ask the GPS team for sample or dummy data to simulate realistic records in HubSpot  
    - If unavailable, the team may create randomized data internally to ensure testing can continue without delay  
    - This approach helps verify system behavior before going live and avoids using any real customer data  

## **Website and Content Strategy**

The website structure is designed to support a large, multi-faceted banking platform with clear navigation and location-based content.

- **A comprehensive sitemap has been developed covering personal, business, community banking, and branch location pages** (07:16)  
    - Colin described grouping branch locations by city with dedicated pages to improve user navigation  
    - Victor confirmed the current location tool contract will end soon (expected in April), so the team must build a new solution internally  
    - The new approach aims to replace the Ubero-based location listing with a custom-built page matching existing data  
    - This transition is critical to maintaining user experience and ensuring location information is accurate and easy to update  

- **Brand asset delivery was completed last week, but no feedback has been received yet** (08:56)  
    - Colin highlighted the need for direction on font choices, showing differences between the old and new fonts with implications for brand consistency  
    - Victor flagged that final font decisions will come from Christina’s team, and communication on this should be included in the next email round  
    - The brand guideline updates and design assets depend heavily on this decision to maintain consistency across all materials  
    - The team also prepared print-ready laminate documents for review, aiming for cleaner versions than previous drafts  

## **Project Coordination and Communication**

Clear communication between internal teams and GPS is essential to keep the project on track amid key personnel absences.

- **Key personnel absences include Christina (out sick) and Jane (out for the rest of the year), impacting decision-making capacity** (04:22)  
    - Victor and Colin agreed on the importance of capturing outstanding questions now to avoid wasting GPS team time on unclear issues  
    - Victor is monitoring Betty’s availability, as her input is critical for Salesforce-HubSpot integration decisions  
    - The team prefers asynchronous communication for simpler questions to keep progress moving despite scheduling challenges  
    - Colin suggested preparing a list of questions to send to Victor for discussion with Christina and Betty, minimizing meeting delays  

- **The immediate next meeting with the GPS team may be shortened or rescheduled due to pending clarifications and availability** (14:07)  
    - Victor recommended waiting for Betty’s participation before deep technical discussions to avoid unproductive calls  
    - This cautious approach aims to respect everyone’s time and ensure meetings drive clear outcomes rather than confusion  
    - The team will adjust the agenda and timing based on Betty’s response and ongoing email updates  

## **Technical Development and Timelines**

The technical build is progressing but requires clarity on Mulesoft development and data handling to finalize schedules.

- **Mulesoft development status is unclear, with GPS team mentioning ongoing changes that have not been fully communicated** (10:12)  
    - Victor was unaware of recent system changes and plans to raise this at the next GPS meeting for clarity  
    - Colin recalled that Betty may have brought up these changes during kickoff meetings, highlighting the need for cross-team alignment  
    - Understanding Mulesoft’s completion timeline is essential to coordinate integration and avoid bottlenecks  

- **The data model and custom fields have been delivered for review, with property mapping efforts ongoing** (06:50)  
    - The team is verifying field alignment across Salesforce, HubSpot, Mulesoft, and ClearTouch to maintain consistent data definitions  
    - This work supports seamless data flow and accurate reporting across business units  
    - Timely completion of this mapping is vital to meet downstream project milestones and launch targets  

## **Next Steps and Follow-up**

The team is focused on consolidating questions, confirming personnel availability, and preparing deliverables for review.

- **Victor will send updates via email after consulting with Christina and Betty to clarify outstanding integration questions** (16:30)  
    - Colin requested the team send any additional questions to Victor to ensure they are addressed comprehensively  
    - This approach helps keep asynchronous progress steady while key decision makers are unavailable  
    - The team is prepared to support communications via email or smaller meetings to avoid delays  

- **Deliverables such as the sitemap, brand assets, and laminate documents will be packaged and sent for review promptly** (08:56)  
    - The team aims to incorporate feedback quickly to maintain momentum on design and content finalization  
    - Clear deadlines and feedback loops will be established to avoid stalling progress due to personnel absences  
    - This aligns with the broader goal of launching the website and integrations on schedule with consistent branding and functionality',
  '2025-12-22 16:00:00+00',
