-- Meeting: Decidalo // MiD: Customer Data and Tools (2025-12-22 15:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'e50afe94-037e-49d6-8f2e-8c05ac7e3294',
    '2025-12-22 15:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KCT3VMQWR0EE3N2345MDH0PD',
    'Decidalo // MiD: Customer Data and Tools',
    '{"MaximilianRabeler","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    1747,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82101665141?pwd=ejjaLBMLaY6b5HbYEMa3AQFfr3Kgzx.1',
    '{"id":"01KCT3VMQWR0EE3N2345MDH0PD","title":"Decidalo // MiD: Customer Data and Tools","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Technology Infrastructure**\n\nThe campaign uses a multi-tool tech stack to identify, engage, and track target accounts efficiently.\n\n- **Clay software** identifies companies using criteria like **revenue ranges, location, and technology stacks** to build target lists (02:11)  \n    - Job titles are selected per company, and contacts are enriched with **LinkedIn URLs and work emails only** to ensure compliance  \n    - Communication flows through **Heyreach for LinkedIn automation** and **Smart Lead for personalized emails** sent from alternate domains to protect the main domain reputation  \n    - Ads run on **LinkedIn and AdRoll retargeting pixels** placed on relevant websites to keep the brand top of mind across channels  \n    - Website traffic is analyzed with **Factors AI** for GDPR-compliant, account-level visitor insights, anticipating 2026 regulatory changes that may simplify cookie consent  \n\n- **N8N automation** manages event workflows by routing data into a **Supabase database** and applying **OpenAI sentiment analysis** to prioritize leads before syncing with CRM systems (06:14)  \n    - A **$9/month HubSpot account** is used to house marketing contacts and track message engagement to avoid disrupting the long-standing Dynamics data  \n    - Sales handoff is manual, with interested contacts flagged in Teams and then added by Eli and Axel to Dynamics for follow-up  \n\n## **Target Audience Definition and Segmentation**\n\nTargeting precision is focused on key industries and roles where the product demonstrates the strongest fit and competitive edge.\n\n- The primary targets are **SAP consulting companies, Microsoft technology stacks, IT and public consulting firms**, identified as high potential due to market familiarity and product integration strength (15:06)  \n    - SAP companies in Germany are especially attractive, as the product aligns well with their complex needs and the market is well connected  \n    - Public consulting firms working on **Request for Proposal (RFP)** processes and IT consulting firms needing **skill and CV management** are also key targets due to clear pain points and lack of competition  \n\n- Targeted job titles include **operations, resource management**, and potentially **HR roles**, as these are the users who benefit most from features like availability tracking and resource allocation (17:14)  \n    - Messaging is personalized based on tech stack usage and recent job changes to increase relevance and engagement (24:39)  \n    - Historical campaigns involved manual review of target lists by Axel, ensuring all contacts and companies were a good fit before purchase  \n\n## **Product Positioning and Messaging Strategy**\n\nThe messaging focuses tightly on clear pain points and feature benefits rather than broad product overviews to improve conversion.\n\n- The **Request for Proposal (RFP) search feature** has received the best feedback from larger clients and is seen as a flagship offering that saves significant manual work (18:29)  \n    - Marketing will promote RFP and resource management features as primary hooks, emphasizing time saved and ease of use compared to manual methods like spreadsheets or Gantt charts (19:29)  \n    - AI capabilities are acknowledged as important but remain in beta, with plans to integrate them subtly in messaging to avoid early skepticism, especially in conservative German markets (19:42)  \n    - Emails will focus on pain points and resolutions, avoiding overwhelming prospects with full feature lists in initial outreach (21:26)  \n\n- The product’s competitive advantage includes **unified availability, skills, and CV management** that simplifies workflows compared to fragmented or manual competitor solutions (22:05)  \n    - Ease of use and integration with existing systems like Microsoft stacks are highlighted to encourage adoption and reduce friction (16:15)  \n\n## **Campaign Measurement and Adaptation**\n\nTracking and iterative improvement underpin the campaign’s effectiveness despite limited budget for advanced tools.\n\n- Campaigns are measured via responses, website visits, and email engagement tracked through the current toolset without high-cost platforms like Dream Data (11:37)  \n    - A typical sequence starts with a **four-email outreach** and a few LinkedIn messages, allowing quick A/B testing and message refinement based on open and conversion rates (12:09)  \n    - Colin emphasized the importance of sharing engagement insights with product teams to prioritize feature development, such as increased clicks on RFP-related ads signaling higher demand (12:24)  \n\n- Data from Dynamics is manually reviewed to identify reasons for lost deals, with plans to develop a campaign targeting previously engaged but non-converting contacts once Bettina returns from vacation on **January 5th** (27:25)  \n    - Maximilian highlighted limitations in CRM data usability due to inconsistent field usage and free-text notes, so manual summaries or structured extraction would be needed for meaningful insights (27:25)  \n\n## **Collaboration and Documentation Commitments**\n\nClear communication and documentation are priorities to align teams and support campaign refinement.\n\n- Colin committed to sharing an updated, detailed **ABM plan and configuration guide**, including webhook and automation setup, to ensure full transparency and enable collaboration (09:39)  \n    - The documentation will cover targeting segmentation, messaging flows, and technical details of data integration through N8N and Supabase (10:05)  \n    - Maximilian expressed intent to review materials closely next week and provide feedback or questions as they arise (26:46)  \n\n- Regular syncs and open communication channels were agreed upon, with Colin available for questions and follow-ups to refine targeting and campaign approaches (28:38)  \n    - Coordination with Bettina on CRM data and feedback loops will be critical for ongoing campaign optimization once she returns  \n\n## **Market Context and Strategic Insights**\n\nThe campaign strategy reflects a pragmatic approach to market realities, regulatory changes, and customer behavior.\n\n- Awareness that **LinkedIn targeting is limited to profiles present on the platform**, so email and retargeting ads fill gaps for those without active LinkedIn accounts (07:15)  \n    - German data privacy attitudes may challenge cookie-based tracking despite anticipated regulatory easing in 2026, requiring vigilance and adaptation (08:10)  \n    - Conservative client attitudes toward AI tools necessitate nuanced messaging, presenting AI features as part of broader benefits rather than standalone selling points (20:27)  \n\n- The market is at an inflection point regarding AI adoption, with companies deciding between full embrace or strict governance, influencing how AI features are introduced to prospects (20:47)  \n    - Targeting “power users” who directly benefit from features like RFP search is essential for adoption and internal advocacy within client companies (18:30)  \n    - The ecosystem approach of omnichannel outreach aims to maintain constant brand presence and increase conversion likelihood by reinforcing messaging across multiple touchpoints (10:56)","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","LinkedIn Outreach","GDPR Compliance","SAP Consulting","RFP Campaign","Campaign Automation"],"overview":"- **Campaign Tech Stack:** Multi-tool stack for tracking, engaging, and identifying target accounts efficiently across platforms.  \n- **Target Audience Focus:** Primarily SAP consulting and public consulting firms, identifying key job titles for personalized messaging.  \n- **Messaging Strategy:** Emphasize RFP feature''s time-saving benefits; avoid overwhelming prospects with full feature lists initially.  \n- **Campaign Measurement:** Track responses and engagement with streamlined tools; plan targeted outreach for non-converting contacts post-holidays.  \n- **Documentation Commitment:** Update ABM plan to ensure transparency; regular syncs established for ongoing campaign optimization and feedback.  \n- **Market Context Awareness:** Adapt messaging due to regulatory changes in Germany; consider client attitudes towards AI in outreach strategies.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated ABM documentation and configuration guides including webhook details and targeting parameters to Maximilian and team (10:00)\nMaintain open availability for questions and potentially arrange follow-up sync meetings as needed (28:40)\n\n**Axel**\nProvide previous campaign company and contact lists for review and approval prior to new list purchases (26:01)\n\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nReview CRM data fields and consult with Bettina once she returns from vacation on January 5 for insights on closed-lost deals and reasons for losses (26:56)\nReview detailed documentation next week and provide additional questions or feedback for campaign refinement (26:46)\n"},"duration":29.1200008392334,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sa.","index":0,"end_time":0.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":28.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.77,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Hey.","index":2,"end_time":29.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":3,"end_time":29.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, good.","index":4,"end_time":31.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.73,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"You doing all right?","index":5,"end_time":32.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":31.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have a good weekend?","index":6,"end_time":33.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, definitely.","index":7,"end_time":36.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":35.13,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":8,"end_time":37.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was you guys holiday party, was that.","index":9,"end_time":41.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":39.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Last week or is that this week, the Christmas party?","index":10,"end_time":44.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.37,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, it was on Friday.","index":11,"end_time":45.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.53,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Nice.","index":12,"end_time":46.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":45.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was that fun?","index":13,"end_time":47.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was that fun?","index":14,"end_time":49.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":51.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.65,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yes.","index":16,"end_time":51.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":51.48,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Good dinner.","index":17,"end_time":53.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.44,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"That''s a good thing.","index":18,"end_time":55.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.52,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":19,"end_time":56.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.88,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"All right, well, I want to make the best use of your time, so I figured it might be helpful just to walk you through a little bit of like the technology infrastructure that we have in place.","index":20,"end_time":65.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I don''t know if we need to hop into Dynamics on this call at all, but I just kind of wanted to give you the parameters of what I''m looking for as we''re setting up this campaign.","index":21,"end_time":75.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so let me zoom into this document a little bit and I''ll share my screen.","index":22,"end_time":80.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is an ABM plan document.","index":23,"end_time":86.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I''ll be creating a new version of this for our targeting.","index":24,"end_time":90.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the version from our US campaign.","index":25,"end_time":92.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I just wanted to zoom in on this technology infrastructure that we have in place.","index":26,"end_time":96.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":92.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we use clay to identify lists.","index":27,"end_time":100.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":97.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we build parameters of companies and say they''re within this revenue range, this is their location.","index":28,"end_time":106.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This may be some technology that they''re currently using, Everything like that.","index":29,"end_time":109.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":106.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then from that list of companies we say, okay, these are the job titles that we want to target and we want to pick a certain amount of people from each of those companies.","index":30,"end_time":117.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We then enrich them and get their LinkedIn profile URL, their email address, a work email, never a personal email, so that we can remain compliant.","index":31,"end_time":126.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":117.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then that kind of filters into a few main platforms.","index":32,"end_time":131.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":128.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one that we don''t have pictured here, but is in use is called heyreach.","index":33,"end_time":135.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that is a tool that we use to connect to.","index":34,"end_time":138.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":135.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In this case, it''s going to be Bettina''s LinkedIn profile.","index":35,"end_time":142.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we will basically put this list of people in.","index":36,"end_time":146.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":143.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll have set messages that we''ll send over to you guys for translation and make sure that we''re all set.","index":37,"end_time":150.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":146.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then they go through a flow that sends a connection request to that person and then sends them a few messages.","index":38,"end_time":156.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":151.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At any point, if they respond, the automation stops and.","index":39,"end_time":159.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that is handed off from us to the sales process.","index":40,"end_time":162.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":159.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are also simultaneously sending emails through a tool called Smart Lead.","index":41,"end_time":168.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, personalized emails talking about the pain points that they''re dealing with, things like that.","index":42,"end_time":173.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":168.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that is coming from domains that we''ve set up that are not desi dollo.com but things like try desidollo.com or getdesidalo.com or desidalo psa.com things like that.","index":43,"end_time":185.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":173.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they all redirect to the main desidollo.com website.","index":44,"end_time":189.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":186.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do that so that if anyone unsubscribes which we have a link to in every email to remain compliant, then that does not hurt your guy''s actual domain.","index":45,"end_time":200.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":190.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s no danger of blacklist or anything like that.","index":46,"end_time":202.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are also targeting with ads via LinkedIn.","index":47,"end_time":207.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":204.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So uploading the audience that we are sending email communication to, but also tapping into LinkedIn''s targeting natively and saying we want to talk to people at these types of companies, these job titles, et cetera.","index":48,"end_time":219.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":208.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we run those in two separate campaigns.","index":49,"end_time":221.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have a really hyper targeted who we''re communicating with via email and everything else.","index":50,"end_time":225.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":221.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also just an ad campaign dedicated to LinkedIn''s audience as well as AdRoll which is a retargeting pixel that we have placed on the website.","index":51,"end_time":234.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so then if someone goes to SAP.com, or Wall Street Journal or something, they will see that ad and likely go back to the dusty dollar website.","index":52,"end_time":244.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":234.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re trying to create basically an ecosystem where we''re constantly back of mind of this person.","index":53,"end_time":249.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then the next time they get a message or an email or see an ad, they''re more likely to convert.","index":54,"end_time":253.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Another tool that we use is called Factors AI and this is GDPR compliant because it is only account based de anonymization of your website traffic.","index":55,"end_time":264.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing that is actually changing or was announced to be in the plans to change in 2026 is the way that GDPR compliance is handled.","index":56,"end_time":275.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it is likely moving in a direction that you will no longer need cookie banner on your website.","index":57,"end_time":282.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''ll actually be something that someone agrees to in their browser across all websites.","index":58,"end_time":287.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that will help a lot with just understanding traffic and who actually is visiting the website.","index":59,"end_time":293.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But this is another tool that we can tap into.","index":60,"end_time":295.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once they agree to cookies, they never have to agree to it again.","index":61,"end_time":298.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":296.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s just account level de anonymization.","index":62,"end_time":301.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":299.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can say this company has visited the website 10 times in the last month.","index":63,"end_time":305.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, they''re showing interest.","index":64,"end_time":306.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe let''s send them a personal email or let''s send them something to download or a video walkthrough of the tool.","index":65,"end_time":313.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of this automation is being handled in N8N which we''re using as an event manager.","index":66,"end_time":320.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So basically just I don''t know if you''ve used like make.com or if you''ve used N8N but just an automation workflow sequence builder.","index":67,"end_time":327.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So basically it says anytime a webhook is coming in from any of these channels, pull it in, understand the data and route it into a table that we have in Supabase, which is just basically a massive spreadsheet.","index":68,"end_time":341.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is then understanding that data through OpenAI sentiment analysis and then discerning where to pass that through.","index":69,"end_time":348.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because when we initially talked to axel, there''s over 15 years of data in Microsoft Dynamics, so we didn''t want to mess anything up.","index":70,"end_time":357.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":350.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we did was create a free HubSpot account.","index":71,"end_time":360.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s actually, it''s $9 a month.","index":72,"end_time":362.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":360.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we get forms with no branding, but that is basically housing all of the marketing contacts that we are sending communications to.","index":73,"end_time":371.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s tracking the messages that they''re receiving and sending.","index":74,"end_time":374.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And as soon as they show interest, we then let you guys know when our teams chat.","index":75,"end_time":378.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":374.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Eli and Axel have been adding them manually to Dynamics.","index":76,"end_time":382.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":378.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know I went through that pretty fast, so I want to take a beat for any questions.","index":77,"end_time":389.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so I think the most important part or the part where you automated the least is the first part, like who you are targeting.","index":78,"end_time":404.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":389.77,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So that''s the part you need to do manually.","index":79,"end_time":405.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":404.13,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I would take that part for some more minutes, maybe to the end and then like.","index":80,"end_time":415.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.01,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":81,"end_time":415.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.56,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"For ad platforms, I mean for LinkedIn it''s kind of easy.","index":82,"end_time":418.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.88,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like you have the job position, you have basically all the information you need.","index":83,"end_time":422.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.96,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yep.","index":84,"end_time":423.039,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But is there any more targeting you do or is it really that hard?","index":85,"end_time":429.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.12,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like, I mean it sounded like there''s a really big LinkedIn focus.","index":86,"end_time":432.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":430.08,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s a big LinkedIn focus on.","index":87,"end_time":435.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"LinkedIn, we can basically not target them.","index":88,"end_time":437.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.39,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I''m sorry, so if someone is not on LinkedIn for whatever reason, we cannot target them basically.","index":89,"end_time":445.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.79,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Well, we can still send them emails even if they don''t have a LinkedIn profile and if they visit the website, they would still get hit with a retargeting pixel.","index":90,"end_time":453.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, But I mean we have no idea how to figure out that they are the correct person to target.","index":91,"end_time":459.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.91,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":92,"end_time":461.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":461.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re able to.","index":93,"end_time":463.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":462.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With Clay, it''s Not only using LinkedIn''s audience, it taps into tools like Zoom Info and other list building aggregators that.","index":94,"end_time":471.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Won''T work in Germany.","index":95,"end_time":472.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.9,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, Info is I think only us, right?","index":96,"end_time":475.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.38,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":97,"end_time":477.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, Zoom Info has data on people all over the world.","index":98,"end_time":480.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just more accurate in the us, more updated.","index":99,"end_time":482.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":480.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":100,"end_time":483.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":483.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so if we can''t find any communication channels for them, then they wouldn''t be in the list.","index":101,"end_time":488.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":483.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re correct.","index":102,"end_time":489.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean it''s just wanted to check whether I overlooked something here.","index":103,"end_time":494.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.8,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay then.","index":104,"end_time":498.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.96,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":105,"end_time":499,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.6,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean I get this with the automated.","index":106,"end_time":501.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":107,"end_time":502.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":502.24,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Message from patina and stuff that''s kind of clear.","index":108,"end_time":507.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.6,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And 8N is for automation, I think spots for the rest.","index":109,"end_time":515.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":509.36,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":110,"end_time":516.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":516.33,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean you said it might help with the cookies.","index":111,"end_time":519.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":516.73,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I actually think the exact opposite.","index":112,"end_time":524.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.93,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I think when people can manage easier to turn off cookies everywhere, they will do it in Germany at least.","index":113,"end_time":531.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.53,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like I think that makes things way more difficult.","index":114,"end_time":535.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.97,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean definitely something that we''ll see how it goes.","index":115,"end_time":539.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":116,"end_time":541.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.73,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But because I think it''s.","index":117,"end_time":543.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.49,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It''s the most important resource is time and when you have to click five times, you.","index":118,"end_time":549.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":543.05,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, you take the option with one click even it''s if it is, even if it allows cookies and you don''t want that.","index":119,"end_time":558.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.41,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So still you go for the quicker version.","index":120,"end_time":560.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.97,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean that''s how we build our software as well.","index":121,"end_time":563.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.85,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like make the least clicks to achieve what you want.","index":122,"end_time":567.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.85,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So.","index":123,"end_time":568.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.94,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I think maybe we will see how it goes.","index":124,"end_time":572.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.22,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yep.","index":125,"end_time":573.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":572.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, go on.","index":126,"end_time":577.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.9,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":127,"end_time":579.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then basically everything else in this document and like I said, we''ll be sending an updated version for the docs region, but it goes over how we define our target audience, how we segment them, the communications that we''re sending, everything is in here.","index":128,"end_time":593.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we also create a configuration guide and this is the detail I was saying of even down to the web hooks that we''re using to send all of this data across the board.","index":129,"end_time":601.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s also in the pool thing.","index":130,"end_time":604.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.16,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yes.","index":131,"end_time":606.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":605.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":132,"end_time":606.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That this all works in through N8N.","index":133,"end_time":608.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, this is a configuration document that we''ll share with you guys.","index":134,"end_time":612.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re completely transparent about everything that we''re doing all the time.","index":135,"end_time":615.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, good, good.","index":136,"end_time":616.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.44,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s good to know.","index":137,"end_time":618.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":617.44,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay, so maybe I think it more or less.","index":138,"end_time":625.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":621.92,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay, wait, so you, you do this with like showing ads in on LinkedIn and probably also on, I don''t know, SAP.com so is there any.","index":139,"end_time":640.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.85,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean you don''t have to show me, but I just want to know do you have any, I don''t know, statistics or something from the past that you do that because it works and you know it works or do you have any other evidence there?","index":140,"end_time":655.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.37,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean I can pull up metrics from various campaigns, but essentially the way that we approach this account based marketing campaign is through Omnichannel.","index":141,"end_time":664.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re trying to hit them in multiple places at once.","index":142,"end_time":667.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can''t guarantee that someone''s going to be checking their email, but they''re likely going to be either checking their email, checking LinkedIn, surfing online.","index":143,"end_time":676.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":667.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re trying to be present in all those locations.","index":144,"end_time":679.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And just one thing, you know, to be completely transparent with.","index":145,"end_time":683.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":680.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unless you guys have a budget to spend $100,000 a year on a tool like Dream Data that can, like, piece together all of these different things happening, this is like the tool stack that we have to put in place to be able to track as much as possible.","index":146,"end_time":696.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":684.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so you have some sort of.","index":147,"end_time":701.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":697.25,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"That would have been the next question.","index":148,"end_time":702.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":701.05,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"You track what you do and you.","index":149,"end_time":703.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.49,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Somehow I''m missing the English word here.","index":150,"end_time":708.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.89,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We report on it, if that''s what you''re looking for.","index":151,"end_time":711.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":152,"end_time":712.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.98,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like, we report on the metrics and like, we say, like, these are the people that have responded, or these are the people that have been browsing the website from our campaign.","index":153,"end_time":718.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":712.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that what you''re referring to?","index":154,"end_time":720.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":718.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you.","index":155,"end_time":721.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.26,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean, you track it and then you look at what you tracked and try to improve your campaign.","index":156,"end_time":729.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.94,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":157,"end_time":730.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":729.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":158,"end_time":730.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":730.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we start with a four email sequence and just a few messages.","index":159,"end_time":733.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":730.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way we can quickly change things if we''re seeing, hey, this email is.","index":160,"end_time":738.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m getting a lot more opens or conversions.","index":161,"end_time":741.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":738.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s do that and toss in a new AB test.","index":162,"end_time":744.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, it''s.","index":163,"end_time":745.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":744.52,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I''m coming from the product development view here.","index":164,"end_time":750.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":746.28,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like, okay, for example, all the RFP ads are getting clicked more, for example.","index":165,"end_time":758.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.44,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So, I mean, for me, that would mean, okay, I need to push that internally more.","index":166,"end_time":763.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We just end up those features faster or prioritize them higher.","index":167,"end_time":767.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.32,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So that''s where I come from here.","index":168,"end_time":769.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.75,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And that''s what I would like to know then, when it started.","index":169,"end_time":772.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":769.75,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And.","index":170,"end_time":773.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":773.03,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, and that''s where I''m really excited for us to work together.","index":171,"end_time":775.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because then you and I can talk and say, hey, is there like a.","index":172,"end_time":779.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A document or something that we can generate that shows someone some insight to using the tool for RFP purposes?","index":173,"end_time":786.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":780.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then that way, like, they don''t even have to talk to someone.","index":174,"end_time":789.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":787.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They could download that and circle it around their company.","index":175,"end_time":791.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":789.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then all of a sudden, desi$, is just getting more and more popular within their company.","index":176,"end_time":795.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":791.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":797.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":796.86,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean, yeah, and as Axel said, I''m the.","index":178,"end_time":800.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.38,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I''m the guy who is building the dashboard with customer statistics here.","index":179,"end_time":805.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":800.06,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So that''s exactly where I come from and what I want to improve.","index":180,"end_time":810.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.74,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":181,"end_time":811.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":182,"end_time":812.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":811.98,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I would like to focus on the first part now.","index":183,"end_time":816.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.18,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like, what are the target groups?","index":184,"end_time":820.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.3,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"How can you.","index":185,"end_time":820.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.2,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"How do you target the right people?","index":186,"end_time":823.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.76,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, so that was in.","index":187,"end_time":826.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me just stop my share real quick.","index":188,"end_time":827.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":826.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was in the document that we went over on Friday.","index":189,"end_time":830.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":827.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you joined.","index":190,"end_time":832.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, you ran that call the whole time.","index":191,"end_time":834.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":832.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You joined the Tuesday one late.","index":192,"end_time":836.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":834.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":193,"end_time":840.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":840.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was this slide where we basically develop parameters for the company so employee ranges, revenue ranges, industry and location.","index":194,"end_time":854.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":845.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then from that data we also get like a description of what the company does.","index":195,"end_time":859.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":855.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can tap into a tech stack that they''re using for example so we can even have personalization of you know.","index":196,"end_time":864.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":859.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you using Microsoft Dynamics as a CRM?","index":197,"end_time":867.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":864.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s integrations that we have with those systems.","index":198,"end_time":870.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":867.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":199,"end_time":871.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":871.1,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I think for that like the target.","index":200,"end_time":874.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":871.66,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"The target company.","index":201,"end_time":876.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.82,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I think we have some.","index":202,"end_time":879.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":877.9,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We have like one, two, maybe three to four main targets here.","index":203,"end_time":885.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":879.42,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like okay the.","index":204,"end_time":887.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":886.46,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We know it works for sa so GCD works well for SAP consulting companies.","index":205,"end_time":893.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":888.06,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I don''t know how popular SAP is in America, but in Germany it''s a German company.","index":206,"end_time":900.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.78,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, many German companies are using it even though it''s hella complicated.","index":207,"end_time":906.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.7,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But yeah, we''ve worked with a few SAP companies in or SAP consultants in Germany and so got to get familiar with you know Hana and a bunch of different features there.","index":208,"end_time":919.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I mean the great thing here is SAP companies are all the same and they all know each other.","index":209,"end_time":924.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.48,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":210,"end_time":925.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":924.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There are more than.","index":211,"end_time":928.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.64,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean we got the biggest ones already I guess I did not research that but I mean Axel said it and I just believe it.","index":212,"end_time":935.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean he can''t be that much wrong at least So I mean we got all for one in chair and these are the two biggest ones definitely in Germany.","index":213,"end_time":942.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.97,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":214,"end_time":943.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Montana is not fully SAP I guess so yeah we got the biggest ones so that''s definitely a thing.","index":215,"end_time":952.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.77,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"SAP companies are the same.","index":216,"end_time":954.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.77,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We know it works easy target in my opinion also yeah Microsoft stacks are good because it''s.","index":217,"end_time":963.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.13,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We have a good auto can fit in there to a landscape.","index":218,"end_time":970.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":964.58,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Really good.","index":219,"end_time":971.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":970.9,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m missing the word again.","index":220,"end_time":974.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.62,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Integrations.","index":221,"end_time":976.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Integrate.","index":222,"end_time":976.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":976.18,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":223,"end_time":977.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":976.82,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We have good integrations.","index":224,"end_time":979.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.02,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So but a part of that I mean consulting companies especially IT consulting and probably strategy consulting.","index":225,"end_time":987.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.98,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Strategy maybe not even that much and developing with this RFP things public.","index":226,"end_time":993.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.51,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Public consulting is I think there we have a lot of potential as well.","index":227,"end_time":999.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.47,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":228,"end_time":999.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":999.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean if it''s about getting more leads I think those public.","index":229,"end_time":1004.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":999.75,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"This public stuff and again they know each other because they are competing and all those public.","index":230,"end_time":1011.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1005.03,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, the request for proposal.","index":231,"end_time":1016.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":232,"end_time":1018.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The contract bidding status.","index":233,"end_time":1019.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1018.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah yeah, absolutely.","index":234,"end_time":1021.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":235,"end_time":1023.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then within those companies targeting job titles with operations or resource management.","index":236,"end_time":1028.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1023.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But then you guys also brought up HR could be something interesting worth tapping into as well.","index":237,"end_time":1033.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1028.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean as I said, I mainly know about the positive like the, the opportunity opportunities we won in the end.","index":238,"end_time":1046.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1034.5,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But I mean what I definitely know is that for RFPs, for example, we had a huge, not really rollout, but we had a lot of demos like a year ago, maybe one and a half years ago where we really pushed that topic and had a lot of demos with a lot of figma files and hey, because we didn''t have it back then and I mean we built it and then we could show something we built and something we want to build and people, I don''t know, they liked it but in the end nobody really bought it.","index":239,"end_time":1079.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1046.86,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean we didn''t develop for, I don''t know how good, you know, our software like this marketplace thing, we didn''t develop it further.","index":240,"end_time":1088.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1081.04,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So probably we targeted the wrong audience.","index":241,"end_time":1093.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1091.2,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like the one who did the demos is.","index":242,"end_time":1099.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1094.26,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"He said like maybe we were not targeting the people which would use the.","index":243,"end_time":1105.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1100.02,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"With the main benefit of our software.","index":244,"end_time":1109.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1105.78,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, the power users.","index":245,"end_time":1110.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, maybe some power users which use things where we have a good, where we have good competition.","index":246,"end_time":1117.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.46,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I mean that''s also if when you have seen this, we call it the RFP search, like where you have this result matrix, this is maybe the, the main flagship tool here.","index":247,"end_time":1134.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1118.9,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"That''s something where we got the by far best feedback from bigger companies for.","index":248,"end_time":1140.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1135.44,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":249,"end_time":1141.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1141.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":250,"end_time":1142.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1141.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":251,"end_time":1142.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1142.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because that''s something they would need to do by hand.","index":252,"end_time":1146.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1142.6,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":253,"end_time":1147.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that would take a lot of time and they immediately understand the benefit of that.","index":254,"end_time":1153.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1148.06,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":255,"end_time":1154.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1153.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And in my opinion the marketing needs to talk at least for FPS, needs to target those people and maybe even for usual skill, resource skill, CV and resource management as well.","index":256,"end_time":1169.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1154.62,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we want to talk about all of those things.","index":257,"end_time":1172.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1169.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to talk about also the AI.","index":258,"end_time":1175.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1172.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that that''s still in beta, but definitely a huge feature and a very evolving conversation in Germany as well.","index":259,"end_time":1181.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1175.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think like, okay, I''m not that convinced with like using the chatbot that early in sales because like we have many clients which are using the application and I mean they could know that there''s a lot of AI involved but sometimes they say yeah, we are using a tool but we are not using the AI there.","index":260,"end_time":1207.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.51,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We are just using it for this and this.","index":261,"end_time":1209.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1207.8,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And while they are saying it, I already know five places where they use AI without knowing it.","index":262,"end_time":1214.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1210.2,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, but the many German companies are still really conservative.","index":263,"end_time":1220.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1215.08,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I don''t know if you said as well.","index":264,"end_time":1222.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1220.88,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":265,"end_time":1222.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1222.44,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Regarding AI and New development there.","index":266,"end_time":1227.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1223.72,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":267,"end_time":1228.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1227.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our conversation on Tuesday and Friday, Axel was mentioning it''s.","index":268,"end_time":1231.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1228.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s kind of we''re coming to a point where companies kind of need to make a decision on are we going to go all in on AI or are we going to develop very strict governance on how we use AI?","index":269,"end_time":1242.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1233.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So definitely a strong inflection point in the market.","index":270,"end_time":1246.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1243.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":271,"end_time":1247.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.36,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But I think we can.","index":272,"end_time":1248.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.68,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"There is.","index":273,"end_time":1250.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1250,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"In most companies I think there is an angle if we target the right audience.","index":274,"end_time":1256.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1252.56,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But we can, we should show them what they can get out of it and if we, if we label it directly with what it is, in the end it might get harder.","index":275,"end_time":1273.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1257.44,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I think the chatbot or I just got a chatbot, I think you know what I mean?","index":276,"end_time":1277.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1273.23,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Maybe not what I would show in those ads.","index":277,"end_time":1282.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1278.11,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It''s more like the result metrics or something like that.","index":278,"end_time":1285.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1282.43,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, it was the way that I was thinking of it was more of a component of the other platform features.","index":279,"end_time":1291.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1286.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you think we have a few emails and I don''t want to hit them with like a huge feature list in the first email, like I kind of want to go like Pain point and our resolution with this feature.","index":280,"end_time":1300.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pain Point and R resolution.","index":281,"end_time":1301.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1300.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they can see a couple different use cases and even forward the email to other team members, you know, to get their company talking about it.","index":282,"end_time":1307.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":283,"end_time":1309.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.12,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And then maybe.","index":284,"end_time":1311.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1310.17,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean that''s the search.","index":285,"end_time":1314.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.93,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean it''s also the, the availability is also included there.","index":286,"end_time":1320.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1314.37,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So find the right person at the right time is really easy with this.","index":287,"end_time":1325.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1320.69,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":288,"end_time":1325.529,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1325.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s.","index":289,"end_time":1326.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.529,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean usually you can target everyone with that but I mean it''s about people who search for others.","index":290,"end_time":1333.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1327.37,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And the second thing is.","index":291,"end_time":1335.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.69,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Well the.","index":292,"end_time":1337.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.02,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Where I think the sales process can be really easy in the end is for skill and CV customers which are again growing really fast and not having proceed processes.","index":293,"end_time":1352.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1338.86,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So.","index":294,"end_time":1353.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1352.78,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And there we have.","index":295,"end_time":1353.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.06,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean the customer said there is basically no competition for like good skill and CV management.","index":296,"end_time":1359.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.86,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":297,"end_time":1360.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1359.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because it''s just basically just consulting, maybe even just IT consulting which really needs that and nobody focuses on that.","index":298,"end_time":1370.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1360.22,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So there I am many cl.","index":299,"end_time":1373.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1370.71,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Well many is hard to say but I know a few clients which just hit a sharepoint with Word documents before and I think that''s the main competition here for us.","index":300,"end_time":1385.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1373.35,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"You just need to be better than a SharePoint with Word documents.","index":301,"end_time":1388.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.67,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yep.","index":302,"end_time":1389.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1388.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s basically also a thing.","index":303,"end_time":1394.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1390.22,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":304,"end_time":1395.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1394.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I imagine some of the toughest competition is like if a company has made a Gantt chart with their availability.","index":305,"end_time":1400.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1395.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s probably as close as some of them are Getting.","index":306,"end_time":1402.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1400.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but I think availability, like resource management tools, there are a few more.","index":307,"end_time":1407.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1403.5,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like it''s easier to find a resource management tool, but then usually people are then swapping over to us because it''s easier.","index":308,"end_time":1418.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1408.94,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":309,"end_time":1419.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1418.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"People just need to learn one tool instead of two.","index":310,"end_time":1421.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1419.75,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":311,"end_time":1422.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1422.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s connected.","index":312,"end_time":1428.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1423.83,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1429.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1429.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":314,"end_time":1430.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1429.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And one place to go to see availability skills, even formatting resumes all in the same style so they could respond to things quicker.","index":315,"end_time":1438.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1430.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, definitely.","index":316,"end_time":1442.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.23,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":317,"end_time":1444.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1444.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any other questions around, like how we''re putting this together?","index":318,"end_time":1448.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1446.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like I said, I''ll be following up this week with a lot of documentation around this.","index":319,"end_time":1452.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1449.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good.","index":320,"end_time":1454.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1453.28,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":321,"end_time":1455.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1454.88,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean it''s still mainly about hitting the right audience.","index":322,"end_time":1458.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1455.2,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like I told you some things.","index":323,"end_time":1462.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1459.2,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Now what.","index":324,"end_time":1463.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1462.2,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"What are you doing with this?","index":325,"end_time":1465.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1463.92,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like, I mean, in my head is not.","index":326,"end_time":1467.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1465.84,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":327,"end_time":1468.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1467.74,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"What could I tell you additionally or what can I tell you next time?","index":328,"end_time":1473.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1468.94,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":329,"end_time":1473.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1473.26,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"What do you need to know?","index":330,"end_time":1474.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1473.82,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like what are you doing with those information and how do you make sure you target the right audience for this?","index":331,"end_time":1479.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1474.78,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":332,"end_time":1480.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1479.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So once we go into Clay and put in the parameters and identify, you know, basically at the widest scope of job titles within companies that are a fit, we then break it down into, okay, well, you know, if they''re using this technology and they have this job title, they likely have this pain point.","index":333,"end_time":1498.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1480.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we change our messaging based on that.","index":334,"end_time":1500.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1498.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have a lot of personalization baked into all of it.","index":335,"end_time":1503.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1500.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also tapping into, even get information, you know, if their job history.","index":336,"end_time":1507.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1503.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if they''ve recently moved to a new company, we can tap into that.","index":337,"end_time":1510.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1507.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, have you been exploring the.","index":338,"end_time":1512.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1510.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The tech stack at your new company and you''re looking for areas for improvement?","index":339,"end_time":1515.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1512.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, there''s a lot of different angles that we can tap into based on the data that we get once we enrich their profile files.","index":340,"end_time":1522.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1516.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s how I''m using the information you''re giving me right now.","index":341,"end_time":1525.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1522.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":342,"end_time":1526.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1526.36,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":343,"end_time":1527.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1526.8,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And for example, I don''t know, like people who are searching for fitting people.","index":344,"end_time":1536.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1527.24,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It''s not only resource manager or it''s not always resource managers.","index":345,"end_time":1540.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1536.68,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Do you just know like other job positions or do you not use any.","index":346,"end_time":1546.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1540.84,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Any evidence?","index":347,"end_time":1547.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1546.52,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":348,"end_time":1548.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1548.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we, we had developed a list with Axle in our first campaign and so we are going to use that and we send everything over before we, you know, buy the contact information or anything like that too, just to make sure that we''re completely aligned.","index":349,"end_time":1560.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1548.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":350,"end_time":1561.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1561.28,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So we sent over the list of all the contacts we were reaching out to to Axel beforehand.","index":351,"end_time":1565.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1561.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":352,"end_time":1568.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1567.76,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So that''s basically manually created before.","index":353,"end_time":1571.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1568.4,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean it''s.","index":354,"end_time":1572.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1571.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We, we.","index":355,"end_time":1573.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1572.72,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It''s a very large spreadsheet that we create through clay which has a bunch of automation enrichments.","index":356,"end_time":1578.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1573.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Axel went through and I don''t think there was any companies that he pulled out of it.","index":357,"end_time":1584.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1579.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He said, he said everyone, all the contacts and companies were a good fit based on our research.","index":358,"end_time":1588.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1584.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so you already have a company list and people list.","index":359,"end_time":1593.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1589.03,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Well, that was for the US campaign so now we''re switching and we''ll be sending new one.","index":360,"end_time":1596.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1593.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":361,"end_time":1597.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1596.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":362,"end_time":1597.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1597.59,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":363,"end_time":1598.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1597.99,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":364,"end_time":1598.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1598.27,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":365,"end_time":1600.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.51,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":366,"end_time":1601.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1601.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any other questions around the infrastructure or anything?","index":367,"end_time":1605.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1602.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean I will have a closer look when I got some time next week or something.","index":368,"end_time":1611.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1606.48,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe then I have more questions.","index":369,"end_time":1615.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1613.6,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, and I''m always open for questions and hopping on and syncing.","index":370,"end_time":1619.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1615.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what would be helpful?","index":371,"end_time":1622,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1620.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think you mentioned that maybe Bettina is the person to grab this but just extracting closed lost out of Dynamics and if there''s any information on, you know, was it a timing issue, was it a budget issue?","index":372,"end_time":1633.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1622,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If there''s any insight we have like that.","index":373,"end_time":1635.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1633.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would like to also take this time to develop a campaign for those that are more familiar with Desi Dollo have already had a conversation but maybe it just didn''t work at that time.","index":374,"end_time":1644.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1635.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":375,"end_time":1646.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1645.39,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like, I mean I can, I can also read the CRM, but I don''t know, I don''t think it''s effective since I don''t know how, which fields are used for what and if, if there is any, I don''t know, statistic evidence or something.","index":376,"end_time":1663.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1646.27,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like if it''s a free text field and there''s something in.","index":377,"end_time":1667.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.54,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":378,"end_time":1669.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1668.82,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And also like from what I said that''s not mainly written down somewhere like I''m making a list and then ticking things off when something is, it''s just, I mean I just, it came from my memory what I said.","index":379,"end_time":1684.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1669.34,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I gotcha.","index":380,"end_time":1685.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1684.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":381,"end_time":1686.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1685.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just seeing.","index":382,"end_time":1686.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1686.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can do that as well.","index":383,"end_time":1688.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1687.38,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And it''s like for her than two minutes.","index":384,"end_time":1690.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1688.3,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"What is 200 minutes for me?","index":385,"end_time":1692.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1690.65,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I gotcha.","index":386,"end_time":1693.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1692.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":387,"end_time":1693.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1693.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just anything that she has, you know, would be helpful for at least us to just see, you know, what data is available.","index":388,"end_time":1699.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1693.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean she''s on vacation until the 5th of January, so.","index":389,"end_time":1703.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1700.57,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay, okay, no problem.","index":390,"end_time":1705.009,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1703.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then next two weeks there won''t be anything.","index":391,"end_time":1707.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1705.009,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, no problem.","index":392,"end_time":1708.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1707.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":393,"end_time":1711.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1710.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well we are, we''re pretty much at time.","index":394,"end_time":1713.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1711.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there any last minute question you wanted me to answer before we hop off?","index":395,"end_time":1716.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1713.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":396,"end_time":1718.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1717.85,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":397,"end_time":1719.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1718.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I know there''s a lot of information to digest and everything like that.","index":398,"end_time":1722.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1719.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like I said, we''ll be sending over very in depth documentation, but if you need anything in the meantime, you know, please feel free to just reach out to me.","index":399,"end_time":1729.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1722.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m.","index":400,"end_time":1729.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1729.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m typically quick to respond unless I''m back to back in meetings.","index":401,"end_time":1733.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1729.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s.","index":402,"end_time":1733.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1733.41,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"That''s the only time I delay.","index":403,"end_time":1735.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1733.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":404,"end_time":1736.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1735.77,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":405,"end_time":1736.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1736.29,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Great.","index":406,"end_time":1736.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1736.65,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":407,"end_time":1737.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1736.97,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you very much.","index":408,"end_time":1738.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1737.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":409,"end_time":1740.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1740.33,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"}],"dateString":"2025-12-22T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82101665141?pwd=ejjaLBMLaY6b5HbYEMa3AQFfr3Kgzx.1","participants":["rabeler@data-assessment.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","rabeler@data-assessment.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KCT3VMQWR0EE3N2345MDH0PD","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Outlined ABM campaign using Clay, LinkedIn, Smartlead, and retargeting across multiple platforms.","Confirmed manual validation of targeting lists by Axel before outreach begins.","Discussed tailoring messaging based on tech stack, job title, and company context.","Flagged SAP consulting firms and Microsoft stack users as top-priority customer segments.","Agreed to track conversions and iteratively improve messaging using platform analytics."],"highlights":[{"quote":"SAP companies are the same. We know it works — easy target in my opinion.","speaker":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"quote":"We report on the metrics... these are the people that have responded.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"We''re completely transparent about everything that we''re doing all the time.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["targeting","delivery","analytics","campaign","segmenting"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-22T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Technology Infrastructure**\n\nThe campaign uses a multi-tool tech stack to identify, engage, and track target accounts efficiently.\n\n- **Clay software** identifies companies using criteria like **revenue ranges, location, and technology stacks** to build target lists (02:11)  \n    - Job titles are selected per company, and contacts are enriched with **LinkedIn URLs and work emails only** to ensure compliance  \n    - Communication flows through **Heyreach for LinkedIn automation** and **Smart Lead for personalized emails** sent from alternate domains to protect the main domain reputation  \n    - Ads run on **LinkedIn and AdRoll retargeting pixels** placed on relevant websites to keep the brand top of mind across channels  \n    - Website traffic is analyzed with **Factors AI** for GDPR-compliant, account-level visitor insights, anticipating 2026 regulatory changes that may simplify cookie consent  \n\n- **N8N automation** manages event workflows by routing data into a **Supabase database** and applying **OpenAI sentiment analysis** to prioritize leads before syncing with CRM systems (06:14)  \n    - A **$9/month HubSpot account** is used to house marketing contacts and track message engagement to avoid disrupting the long-standing Dynamics data  \n    - Sales handoff is manual, with interested contacts flagged in Teams and then added by Eli and Axel to Dynamics for follow-up  \n\n## **Target Audience Definition and Segmentation**\n\nTargeting precision is focused on key industries and roles where the product demonstrates the strongest fit and competitive edge.\n\n- The primary targets are **SAP consulting companies, Microsoft technology stacks, IT and public consulting firms**, identified as high potential due to market familiarity and product integration strength (15:06)  \n    - SAP companies in Germany are especially attractive, as the product aligns well with their complex needs and the market is well connected  \n    - Public consulting firms working on **Request for Proposal (RFP)** processes and IT consulting firms needing **skill and CV management** are also key targets due to clear pain points and lack of competition  \n\n- Targeted job titles include **operations, resource management**, and potentially **HR roles**, as these are the users who benefit most from features like availability tracking and resource allocation (17:14)  \n    - Messaging is personalized based on tech stack usage and recent job changes to increase relevance and engagement (24:39)  \n    - Historical campaigns involved manual review of target lists by Axel, ensuring all contacts and companies were a good fit before purchase  \n\n## **Product Positioning and Messaging Strategy**\n\nThe messaging focuses tightly on clear pain points and feature benefits rather than broad product overviews to improve conversion.\n\n- The **Request for Proposal (RFP) search feature** has received the best feedback from larger clients and is seen as a flagship offering that saves significant manual work (18:29)  \n    - Marketing will promote RFP and resource management features as primary hooks, emphasizing time saved and ease of use compared to manual methods like spreadsheets or Gantt charts (19:29)  \n    - AI capabilities are acknowledged as important but remain in beta, with plans to integrate them subtly in messaging to avoid early skepticism, especially in conservative German markets (19:42)  \n    - Emails will focus on pain points and resolutions, avoiding overwhelming prospects with full feature lists in initial outreach (21:26)  \n\n- The product’s competitive advantage includes **unified availability, skills, and CV management** that simplifies workflows compared to fragmented or manual competitor solutions (22:05)  \n    - Ease of use and integration with existing systems like Microsoft stacks are highlighted to encourage adoption and reduce friction (16:15)  \n\n## **Campaign Measurement and Adaptation**\n\nTracking and iterative improvement underpin the campaign’s effectiveness despite limited budget for advanced tools.\n\n- Campaigns are measured via responses, website visits, and email engagement tracked through the current toolset without high-cost platforms like Dream Data (11:37)  \n    - A typical sequence starts with a **four-email outreach** and a few LinkedIn messages, allowing quick A/B testing and message refinement based on open and conversion rates (12:09)  \n    - Colin emphasized the importance of sharing engagement insights with product teams to prioritize feature development, such as increased clicks on RFP-related ads signaling higher demand (12:24)  \n\n- Data from Dynamics is manually reviewed to identify reasons for lost deals, with plans to develop a campaign targeting previously engaged but non-converting contacts once Bettina returns from vacation on **January 5th** (27:25)  \n    - Maximilian highlighted limitations in CRM data usability due to inconsistent field usage and free-text notes, so manual summaries or structured extraction would be needed for meaningful insights (27:25)  \n\n## **Collaboration and Documentation Commitments**\n\nClear communication and documentation are priorities to align teams and support campaign refinement.\n\n- Colin committed to sharing an updated, detailed **ABM plan and configuration guide**, including webhook and automation setup, to ensure full transparency and enable collaboration (09:39)  \n    - The documentation will cover targeting segmentation, messaging flows, and technical details of data integration through N8N and Supabase (10:05)  \n    - Maximilian expressed intent to review materials closely next week and provide feedback or questions as they arise (26:46)  \n\n- Regular syncs and open communication channels were agreed upon, with Colin available for questions and follow-ups to refine targeting and campaign approaches (28:38)  \n    - Coordination with Bettina on CRM data and feedback loops will be critical for ongoing campaign optimization once she returns  \n\n## **Market Context and Strategic Insights**\n\nThe campaign strategy reflects a pragmatic approach to market realities, regulatory changes, and customer behavior.\n\n- Awareness that **LinkedIn targeting is limited to profiles present on the platform**, so email and retargeting ads fill gaps for those without active LinkedIn accounts (07:15)  \n    - German data privacy attitudes may challenge cookie-based tracking despite anticipated regulatory easing in 2026, requiring vigilance and adaptation (08:10)  \n    - Conservative client attitudes toward AI tools necessitate nuanced messaging, presenting AI features as part of broader benefits rather than standalone selling points (20:27)  \n\n- The market is at an inflection point regarding AI adoption, with companies deciding between full embrace or strict governance, influencing how AI features are introduced to prospects (20:47)  \n    - Targeting “power users” who directly benefit from features like RFP search is essential for adoption and internal advocacy within client companies (18:30)  \n    - The ecosystem approach of omnichannel outreach aims to maintain constant brand presence and increase conversion likelihood by reinforcing messaging across multiple touchpoints (10:56)","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","LinkedIn Outreach","GDPR Compliance","SAP Consulting","RFP Campaign","Campaign Automation"],"overview":"- **Campaign Tech Stack:** Multi-tool stack for tracking, engaging, and identifying target accounts efficiently across platforms.  \n- **Target Audience Focus:** Primarily SAP consulting and public consulting firms, identifying key job titles for personalized messaging.  \n- **Messaging Strategy:** Emphasize RFP feature''s time-saving benefits; avoid overwhelming prospects with full feature lists initially.  \n- **Campaign Measurement:** Track responses and engagement with streamlined tools; plan targeted outreach for non-converting contacts post-holidays.  \n- **Documentation Commitment:** Update ABM plan to ensure transparency; regular syncs established for ongoing campaign optimization and feedback.  \n- **Market Context Awareness:** Adapt messaging due to regulatory changes in Germany; consider client attitudes towards AI in outreach strategies.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated ABM documentation and configuration guides including webhook details and targeting parameters to Maximilian and team (10:00)\nMaintain open availability for questions and potentially arrange follow-up sync meetings as needed (28:40)\n\n**Axel**\nProvide previous campaign company and contact lists for review and approval prior to new list purchases (26:01)\n\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nReview CRM data fields and consult with Bettina once she returns from vacation on January 5 for insights on closed-lost deals and reasons for losses (26:56)\nReview detailed documentation next week and provide additional questions or feedback for campaign refinement (26:46)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"82901be6-0ff9-4239-9950-3c2ca61c3862","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
