    '01KCPJEKJF7HDZ55T539DKR2FC',
    'Discuss Encamp, timelines, next steps, etc.',
    '{"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"}'::text[],
    1584,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86729959306?pwd=UC87qHDQx0heP0NFfGFcB4nw9Kuo2L.1',
    '{"id":"01KCPJEKJF7HDZ55T539DKR2FC","title":"Discuss Encamp, timelines, next steps, etc.","summary":{"notes":"## **Project Scope and Resourcing**\n\nThe team clarified the project scope and adjusted roles to improve efficiency and accountability.\n\n- **Bailey was assigned as the new account director for the NCAMP website project** to provide focused leadership and support for Nina, replacing the original lead who is stepping back (00:00)  \n    - The shift aims to bring more hands-on management as the website work ramps up  \n    - Nina continues to handle brand-related tasks, while Bailey focuses on project coordination and delivery  \n    - This change addresses previous bottlenecks and unclear ownership in the workflow  \n    - Introducing Bailey allows for better client communication and internal coordination  \n\n- **The scope was narrowed to exclude copywriting and several design deliverables like PowerPoint and social media templates** after multiple out-of-scope requests and scope creep issues (01:40)  \n    - NCAMP agreed to provide all website copy, with the internal copywriter delivering Google Docs for design  \n    - The team will deliver Figma design files and two ebooks, plus finalize brand guidelines  \n    - Additional requests will be pushed back or handled as separate work beyond current agreements  \n    - This redefinition ensures proper resource allocation and prevents uncontrolled project growth  \n\n## **Content Delivery and Timeline Management**\n\nThe team established clear content delivery deadlines and a timeline framework to meet critical milestones.\n\n- **NCAMP committed to delivering all website copy and product assets by January 2nd to meet the January 12th board meeting deadline** (06:54)  \n    - Only three pages of copy have been produced in six weeks, highlighting content delays  \n    - Nina and Bailey emphasized that design approval must precede development to avoid rework  \n    - A timeline with key milestones including copy delivery, design approval, development, testing, and content migration is being created to set realistic expectations  \n    - This schedule will be presented to NCAMP with clear assumptions and boundaries to prevent scope creep  \n\n- **The timeline will include assumptions such as limited revision rounds and no scope expansion beyond approved deliverables** to enforce discipline (10:59)  \n    - Nina stressed the importance of defining how many revisions per page are acceptable to manage feedback flow  \n    - The timeline will also cover template development for simpler pages like blogs, privacy notices, and terms  \n    - Content migration from the existing WordPress site will be automated with Demir’s support, reducing manual tasks and speeding up delivery  \n    - AI tools will assist in cleaning and formatting migrated content for faster turnaround  \n\n## **Client Communication and Workflow Improvements**\n\nImproving communication channels and workflows was prioritized to reduce delays and clarify expectations.\n\n- **A Slack channel will be set up to enable real-time communication and faster feedback loops with NCAMP’s team** (15:58)  \n    - This replaces slow email chains and long meeting lead times, which have delayed progress  \n    - Bailey will handle introductions and ongoing communication to smooth collaboration  \n    - The Slack channel will be the primary hub for updates, questions, and task status alongside Pulse for task tracking  \n    - This change aims to accelerate approvals and reduce the typical one to two-week turnaround for responses  \n\n- **Weekly meetings with the copywriter Kylie have fallen off due to slow progress on copy and unclear priorities** (18:57)  \n    - Kylie’s requests for out-of-scope deliverables caused confusion and required firm pushback to reset expectations  \n    - Bailey and Nina clarified that only two ebooks and the website are in scope, with no additional templates or materials  \n    - Kylie’s inconsistent adherence to original copy and formatting standards added quality control challenges  \n    - This communication reset was crucial to align all parties on project boundaries and deliverables  \n\n## **Quality Control and Design Finalization**\n\nThe team reinforced brand guidelines and quality checks to avoid rework and maintain consistency.\n\n- **Brand guidelines are finalized and frozen to prevent ongoing changes that delay design and QA** (16:37)  \n    - Nina highlighted that repeated modifications forced multiple rounds of design and quality assessments  \n    - Lou and Georgia have been involved in thorough quality checks to ensure compliance with brand standards  \n    - This freeze enables the design team to focus on website pages and ebook layouts without shifting requirements  \n    - The final guidelines serve as a baseline for all creative assets to maintain consistency across deliverables  \n\n- **AI-assisted content generation is used cautiously due to quality issues and client reluctance** (21:40)  \n    - Bailey noted that although AI can speed up copywriting, inconsistent formatting and errors require significant manual fixes  \n    - The client prefers human-written copy but struggles with timely delivery, creating a tension between quality and speed  \n    - Clear communication with the client about these trade-offs is necessary to set realistic expectations  \n    - The team remains open to AI tools but will maintain rigorous review processes to uphold standards  \n\n## **Next Steps and Deliverable Management**\n\nConcrete plans were set to finalize deliverables and ensure smooth project handoff.\n\n- **Nina will draft a high-level timeline and assumptions document using an existing kitchen sink template, targeting delivery by tomorrow** (23:25)  \n    - The template provides a ready-made structure for milestones and presentation styles, speeding up preparation  \n    - The timeline will incorporate phased content delivery assumptions, allowing for progressive design and development  \n    - Bailey will coordinate sharing the timeline and team introductions via Slack to facilitate immediate feedback  \n    - This documentation will serve as the foundation for managing client expectations and internal workflows  \n\n- **Bailey will manage ongoing communications and help transition leadership as the original project lead reduces involvement** (15:58)  \n    - The team anticipates smoother progress with more hands involved and clearer accountability  \n    - Emphasis remains on limiting scope creep and ensuring timely delivery of copy, design, and development milestones  \n    - Continuous monitoring of client responsiveness and quality will be necessary to maintain momentum  \n    - The approach aims to deliver the website and ebooks on schedule for the January 12th board meeting with minimal surprises","outline":null,"keywords":["Encamp","website copy","brand guidelines","project timeline","scope management","client communication"],"overview":"- **Project Leadership Updates:** Bailey will be the new account director for better management of the NCAMP website project.\n\n- **Scope Adjustments:** Project scope revised to exclude copywriting and certain design deliverables after discussions on scope creep.\n\n- **Content Deadlines Set:** NCAMP to provide website copy by January 2nd for the January 12th board meeting; current progress is slow.\n\n- **Improved Communication Channels:** A Slack channel will replace email for real-time updates, aiming to speed up feedback loops.\n\n- **Quality Control Measures:** Brand guidelines finalized to avoid delays; AI tools will be used cautiously to maintain quality standards.\n\n- **Actionable Next Steps:** Nina to draft a timeline document for deliverables, with Bailey coordinating ongoing communications for clarity.","action_items":"\n**Nina Belina**\nBuild detailed website project timeline slides including key milestones, assumptions (e.g., revision limits, scope boundaries), and dependencies based on copy delivery by January 2 (00:09)\nUse provided kitchen sink template as a starting point to format timeline and milestone presentation slides (00:25)\nFollow up with Kylie regarding status and delivery plan of copy for second ebook and remaining web pages to confirm drip-feed schedule (00:06)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nSet up Slack channel for Encamp project team and client stakeholders; introduce Bailey and connect agency and client teams for streamlined communications (00:15)\nSend the timeline and assumptions slide deck through Slack to client team once completed (00:17)\nManage scope creep by communicating clearly with client on out-of-scope items such as PowerPoint/social media templates, reinforce brand guidelines finality (00:05)\n\n**Bailey Gunnell**\nEngage closely with Nina and client’s Jenny B. and Kylie for project continuity and account management transition (00:01)\n\n**Nina Belina & Tristan Pelligrino**\nCoordinate with client’s content migration lead (Demir) to plan content export/import for blogs and knowledge articles using programmatic methods, assisted by AI tools (00:12)\n"},"duration":26.399999618530273,"speakers":[],"sentences":[{"text":"Update you all.","index":0,"end_time":0.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But then also, I don''t know, Bailey.","index":1,"end_time":5.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If Nina knows, but we''re going to.","index":2,"end_time":8.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Nina, for your information, Bailey, I''m going to slide out more and be less involved on.","index":3,"end_time":19.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"On this.","index":4,"end_time":20.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So you''ll get cut out for a second.","index":5,"end_time":23.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":24.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":23.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"On the most important part.","index":7,"end_time":26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":24.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Can you hear me now?","index":8,"end_time":27.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, it did say my Internet connection was on stale.","index":9,"end_time":30.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Must have just popped out for a second.","index":10,"end_time":32.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, yeah, I wanted to say, you know, that I''ll recap yesterday''s meeting with the NCAMP folks, and then Bailey''s going.","index":11,"end_time":42.339,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"To be the account director on End Camp.","index":12,"end_time":44.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.339,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Now we''ll get some more hands on.","index":13,"end_time":46.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"This project as it ramps up on the website side.","index":14,"end_time":49.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then, Nina, you''ll have, you know, more support and stuff versus, you know, going through me, which, I mean, you''re.","index":15,"end_time":59.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Doing a good job of not even.","index":16,"end_time":60.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Really going through me at all and getting stuff done.","index":17,"end_time":63.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But Bailey will be a good partner on that side.","index":18,"end_time":66.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So more traditional account director and strategist role on the project.","index":19,"end_time":72.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I think that''ll help out things.","index":20,"end_time":74.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s why we have Bailey here.","index":21,"end_time":77.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And Bailey''s pretty new to ncamp.","index":22,"end_time":79.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bailey, I''m not sure if you know too much of what''s going on there, but.","index":23,"end_time":83.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":79.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, we''ll.","index":24,"end_time":84.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ll get you up to speed here.","index":25,"end_time":86.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think.","index":26,"end_time":89.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"From yesterday''s call, I want.","index":27,"end_time":94.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":91.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"To give you all an update, but.","index":28,"end_time":96.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":94.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Essentially, big picture, we have a brand.","index":29,"end_time":100.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Activation project that''s going on, and we''ve got the brand guidelines updated and sent over.","index":30,"end_time":108.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":100.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right, Nina, those got packaged up.","index":31,"end_time":110.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":108.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Those should be final.","index":32,"end_time":112.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":111.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then we''re working through the website now as well.","index":33,"end_time":118.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":113.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So the web plans all been done.","index":34,"end_time":120.589,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":118.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have the.","index":35,"end_time":121.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The site maps been created.","index":36,"end_time":123.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Now we''re just going basically page by page.","index":37,"end_time":126.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":123.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And Bailey, this is more for you.","index":38,"end_time":128.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, the big.","index":39,"end_time":129.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":128.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Kind of.","index":40,"end_time":132.789,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.309,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Negotiation or deal that we made is we were going to.","index":41,"end_time":138.789,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134.789,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We were supposed to write all the copy for the website and do the.","index":42,"end_time":141.549,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.789,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Design and everything, but they had us completely rebuild their brand and we start over.","index":43,"end_time":146.869,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.549,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We started over many times.","index":44,"end_time":148.389,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.949,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we went through so many rounds of even concepts before we.","index":45,"end_time":153.509,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":148.869,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And.","index":46,"end_time":154.069,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":153.669,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then Nina''s been working on, I don''t know, three to four different versions of the brand guidelines, even after they''ve been approved, I think.","index":47,"end_time":162.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.149,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''s going through a lot.","index":48,"end_time":164.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That said, so based on that, you.","index":49,"end_time":170.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":166.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Know, I had to talk to them and just say, hey, you know, things.","index":50,"end_time":172.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Are out of scope.","index":51,"end_time":173.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We need to figure out, like, how we''re going to work together and get this done.","index":52,"end_time":176.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so they agreed to write the.","index":53,"end_time":178.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":176.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Copy for for the website.","index":54,"end_time":180.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So either we are using an existing web page and its content and just like redesigning it in the new format or they''re giving us the brand new.","index":55,"end_time":190.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":180.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Copy and, and the, you know, for all the different sections and then we''re designing it from there.","index":56,"end_time":195.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we''re not really in charge of any copy at all.","index":57,"end_time":198.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so what has been going on now is we''re leaning on a copywriter.","index":58,"end_time":206.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Internally at NCAMP to produce, you know, essentially Google Docs for each page that we are going to then design.","index":59,"end_time":212.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":206.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She has produced how many so far, Nina?","index":60,"end_time":217.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":214.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"3.","index":61,"end_time":218.382,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"2.","index":62,"end_time":218.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.478,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean with the ebook, it''s two pages and an ebook.","index":63,"end_time":222.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":219.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":64,"end_time":223.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So ever compliance.","index":65,"end_time":225.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We do have chemicals, epra though.","index":66,"end_time":236.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":67,"end_time":237.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So how many do you have?","index":68,"end_time":243.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The waste page, the homepage and the ebook.","index":69,"end_time":247.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":70,"end_time":254.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Just make sure those are.","index":71,"end_time":257.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Chemicals.","index":72,"end_time":265.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Chemicals.","index":73,"end_time":267.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":266.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t know if that''s the waste page, then that would be.","index":74,"end_time":270.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, I think this is a third page.","index":75,"end_time":273.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We, we didn''t discuss it in the channel.","index":76,"end_time":277.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":274.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, here''s the.","index":77,"end_time":279.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let me show this one.","index":78,"end_time":281.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":79,"end_time":285.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Can you see my email?","index":80,"end_time":286.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep.","index":81,"end_time":290.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":289.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So this is from Monday?","index":82,"end_time":292.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":295.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She said, I have copy ready for another web page, epcra.","index":84,"end_time":299.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":85,"end_time":300.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I was like, I need to talk about maybe that.","index":86,"end_time":306.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s why I was like, yeah, because.","index":87,"end_time":308.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There was so much more.","index":88,"end_time":309.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":89,"end_time":310.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So this one, Nina, we can get into the workflow.","index":90,"end_time":312.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, so we have three pages effectively.","index":91,"end_time":317.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s, that''s all we have, Bailey.","index":92,"end_time":319.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"For a website that probably has over 150.","index":93,"end_time":321.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s, that''s where we are.","index":94,"end_time":324.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":322.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That includes like knowledge based articles and.","index":95,"end_time":326.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Blog posts and things like that.","index":96,"end_time":327.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So yesterday I talked to them, they agreed that we are just going to give them the Figma files, Nina, that.","index":97,"end_time":340.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''Ve produced and just focus on the ebooks and then we need to make.","index":98,"end_time":345.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sure we do get those into InDesign.","index":99,"end_time":347.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But they''re not going to have us do PowerPoint templates or social media templates.","index":100,"end_time":351.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or any of that stuff.","index":101,"end_time":352.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They, they didn''t want to pay for any of it.","index":102,"end_time":354.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":352.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And their team''s going to take our.","index":103,"end_time":356.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Figma files and try to, you know, do what they can internally.","index":104,"end_time":360.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t think they have additional budget to support it.","index":105,"end_time":362.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So effectively, Nina, we have to produce two ebooks, wrap up the brand guidelines.","index":106,"end_time":368.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then the website.","index":107,"end_time":369.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So anything beyond that, let me know.","index":108,"end_time":371.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because it''s going to be out of scope.","index":109,"end_time":374.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So.","index":110,"end_time":375.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And do we have the copy for the second eBook?","index":111,"end_time":379.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We do not.","index":112,"end_time":381.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And it''s okay to follow up with Kylie to understand, like when.","index":113,"end_time":389.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because they.","index":114,"end_time":390.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":390.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We also had a issue for the waste page, where in the meeting they had an idea which was new for the carousel on the web waste page, but they never sent the product, like, footage or information that would go for the carousel.","index":115,"end_time":407.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":390.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So now we left it as a, you know, a mockup of how it would look like.","index":116,"end_time":412.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But they still need to give us that information.","index":117,"end_time":413.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":412.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But from what I also noticed that they, you know, they comment on something and then they want to see it so they can, you know, elaborate further.","index":118,"end_time":422.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":414.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, yeah, so those are the things we''ll have to work through and.","index":119,"end_time":428.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s where we need to, like, push back on them, because that''s been the problem.","index":120,"end_time":436.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That was part of the conversation I had yesterday.","index":121,"end_time":438.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So what we have to do now.","index":122,"end_time":440.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":438.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So they got on the phone, they were like, okay, cool, let''s figure out.","index":123,"end_time":443.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We know we''ve taken a long time.","index":124,"end_time":446.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":444.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"On the content, which I knew that it would take a long time, and.","index":125,"end_time":450.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We got pushed to do a lot.","index":126,"end_time":451.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And this person''s written two pages basically in about six weeks.","index":127,"end_time":456.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I knew yesterday''s conversation would happen.","index":128,"end_time":459.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So they jump on.","index":129,"end_time":460.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They''re like, well, we would love to.","index":130,"end_time":461.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Have the website available for the board meeting on January 12th.","index":131,"end_time":467.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And.","index":132,"end_time":467.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I''m like, well, we have three pages written so far.","index":133,"end_time":472.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''m like, everything.","index":134,"end_time":475.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":473.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I told him on the call, I was like, everything probably should have.","index":135,"end_time":478.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Been finalized and sent our way by last Friday for us to hit the deadline.","index":136,"end_time":483.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":478.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I was like, we got to be able to.","index":137,"end_time":484.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because I said, you have to remember, we are designing some of these pages.","index":138,"end_time":488.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":485.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"First in figma, sending those FIGMA files to you for approval before we develop.","index":139,"end_time":493.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":488.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So there is a round of review there.","index":140,"end_time":496.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We can''t just go off and code the pages that you haven''t viewed from a design standpoint.","index":141,"end_time":502.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":496.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And they asked to change the brand guidelines while working on the pages.","index":142,"end_time":506.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Exactly.","index":143,"end_time":507.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.819,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so I said, if.","index":144,"end_time":511.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":508.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If you can get us, you know, copy by.","index":145,"end_time":518.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think.","index":146,"end_time":518.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":518.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think.","index":147,"end_time":519.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":518.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Were they committed to giving us all.","index":148,"end_time":521.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The copy by January 2nd?","index":149,"end_time":523.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then what they asked me to do was put together a timeline from there as to when we could deliver the website.","index":150,"end_time":530.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because I said, it''s just.","index":151,"end_time":532.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s hard for me to give you a deadline, you know, when only three pages have been produced to this point in six weeks.","index":152,"end_time":539.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.559,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, I can''t commit to a whole entire freaking website to be done and.","index":153,"end_time":543.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Tested and everything and rolled out, knowing.","index":154,"end_time":546.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":543.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The revisions and feedback that you have.","index":155,"end_time":549.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s what we need to build today.","index":156,"end_time":553.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":551.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I told them I would put together basically two slides.","index":157,"end_time":556.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":553.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like a slide that has like a Gantt chart essentially like just showing the.","index":158,"end_time":561.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":556.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Key milestones.","index":159,"end_time":562.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":561.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Of, of the website project we have left.","index":160,"end_time":567.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So testing you know, final development, content migration, you know, for, for pages that they are not developing new copy for and then kind of you know, a mark in the sand where there are no design changes and you know, effectively what date we can commit to.","index":161,"end_time":588.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s what I want to talk to you all about.","index":162,"end_time":592.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":589.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If, if they, they committed to giving.","index":163,"end_time":596.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":594.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All the copy by January 2nd.","index":164,"end_time":598.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":596.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so that''s kind of the milestone that we''ll build on from there.","index":165,"end_time":603.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":599.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Do you.","index":166,"end_time":605.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s probably more towards.","index":167,"end_time":607.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Nina, do you want me to build.","index":168,"end_time":609.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"A high level schedule and send that to you or is that something you want to think about based on what.","index":169,"end_time":615.009,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have in the web plan and just build out like the key dates.","index":170,"end_time":618.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.009,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What are you thinking there?","index":171,"end_time":619.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I would like to build out the key dates but also to kind of make them aware that it''s not you know, I do understand like the team effort that they put in to each page but we cannot have a meeting with something already done and then you know, get more into what can be added and whatnot.","index":172,"end_time":638.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like if, if it''s done, it''s done.","index":173,"end_time":640.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":638.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s you know, maybe, maybe if we can, with each state they say okay, we can have one revision or you know, just to give them a number of how many times they can change something.","index":174,"end_time":651.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":640.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, so what I''m thinking, and I totally agree Nina, we need to put.","index":175,"end_time":655.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":652.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Those key assumptions in this document because.","index":176,"end_time":658.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":655.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I, I basically want to use a.","index":177,"end_time":660.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":658.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Two page slide deck.","index":178,"end_time":661.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Say here''s the key milestones and dates.","index":179,"end_time":664.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":662.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then have like a second page that has like the key assumptions like you know, we''re not going to have everything that you''re saying, you know, additional revisions after designs approved, you know, no, no scope creep on the technical side, blah blah blah.","index":180,"end_time":681.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So those are things that we need to, to document there.","index":181,"end_time":684.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":681.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so I think we do need to draw a line in the sand so copies done.","index":182,"end_time":689.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think the next key phase is design is all approved for the key pages that require like custom designs.","index":183,"end_time":697.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then we''ll have to need to.","index":184,"end_time":700.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Develop like template pages like for the blog and like knowledge based articles.","index":185,"end_time":705.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ll have to design some of those pages just where with existing content there.","index":186,"end_time":712.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Are some simple pages too like you.","index":187,"end_time":714.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":712.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Know privacy and, and privacy notice and then also like just terms and conditions, you know just like regular pages like.","index":188,"end_time":725.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That we''ll have to craft.","index":189,"end_time":726.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But yeah, I mean there, so there''s design that has to get approved and then there''s development and then we need a whole like content migration phase too where we will have to work with Demir to figure out the best way to get their existing blog content over because we don''t want people manually adding each of those pages.","index":190,"end_time":749.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Probably we can do it programmatically.","index":191,"end_time":751.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ll just need to get Demir to work on the best route to take there.","index":192,"end_time":756.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I''ve worked with Demir on that before where I''ve exported the data out of the existing WordPress environment.","index":193,"end_time":764.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"AI is great for that because it can take the existing code and strip out a lot of the garbage and just give you the content in kind of newly formatted HTML.","index":194,"end_time":775.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":765.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I used AI heavily when we did the.","index":195,"end_time":779.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It was like the new New north blog migration or whatever and AI is a lot better now than what it was then.","index":196,"end_time":785.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So.","index":197,"end_time":785.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":785.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s the piece there.","index":198,"end_time":790.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.949,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":199,"end_time":792.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":792.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I mean I just said by the end of today or tomorrow morning we would have like, you know, a couple slides that just outline the key.","index":200,"end_time":799.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":792.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Dates and the assumptions that we''re working from and see how they feel about that.","index":201,"end_time":805.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I also told them.","index":202,"end_time":806.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":805.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I was on the phone with, with both Jenny.","index":203,"end_time":810.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":807.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So Kylie was not on that call.","index":204,"end_time":813.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":810.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She''s the copywriter.","index":205,"end_time":814.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":813.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think they kind of just kicked her out because she''s asking for a lot of things that it''s not in scope, like she doesn''t understand what they bought.","index":206,"end_time":822.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so just Jenny Vance and Jenny Brighthall or whatever, they.","index":207,"end_time":831.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They were the only ones on the phone.","index":208,"end_time":832.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, so Bailey just.","index":209,"end_time":834.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":832.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And Nina for just like the hierarchy.","index":210,"end_time":839.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Of their team has, has changed a little bit.","index":211,"end_time":841.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":839.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They''ve hired, they hired Kylie, which is the copywriter.","index":212,"end_time":844.779,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":841.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They hired her in like the summer.","index":213,"end_time":847.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.779,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Jenny B.","index":214,"end_time":850.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is what they call her.","index":215,"end_time":852.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She is the product marketer but she.","index":216,"end_time":853.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":852.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Got promoted so she''s like running product marketing.","index":217,"end_time":857.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":853.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She''s in charge of the website and she''s really like the key person on that project.","index":218,"end_time":863.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so I feel like Nina, you''ll.","index":219,"end_time":867.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":864.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Work mostly with Jenny B.","index":220,"end_time":870.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And Kylie, you know, that''s who you''ve been working with with the most part.","index":221,"end_time":874.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They also just hired Demand Generation, head of Demand Gen.","index":222,"end_time":881.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I believe I got introduced to her yesterday.","index":223,"end_time":884.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She''s going to probably have some questions.","index":224,"end_time":887.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":884.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"About like the forms that we add and like, you know, things like that.","index":225,"end_time":891.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Just to make sure things are going in the HubSpot because they''re also doing a HubSpot migration that we''re not a part of.","index":226,"end_time":897.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":891.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So some of that will also be.","index":227,"end_time":899.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":897.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"New that will have to get in place.","index":228,"end_time":902.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":899.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so what I said is, great, your team has changed, you know, on your side.","index":229,"end_time":909.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then we''re going to have some.","index":230,"end_time":911.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":909.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Changes on our side.","index":231,"end_time":912.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That way we all have like, you know, some more hands involved.","index":232,"end_time":915.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I was like, Bailey will shift.","index":233,"end_time":919.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":916.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"More into this role so we get some hands there.","index":234,"end_time":921.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I was like, she''s account director and I explained that whole process.","index":235,"end_time":926.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So they introduced me through email to Christina and I said, you know, I''m.","index":236,"end_time":931.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Happy to chat with her.","index":237,"end_time":933,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":931.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I gave her my calendar to sync up with her.","index":238,"end_time":935.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And.","index":239,"end_time":935.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then what I''m going to do is introduce Bailey, you all to their team.","index":240,"end_time":942.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''m going to do that through a.","index":241,"end_time":944.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Slack channel because I said we would get a Slack channel set up so that it just allows you all to work more freely back and forth versus, you know, that''s the other problem.","index":242,"end_time":955.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":944.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have to set up a meeting.","index":243,"end_time":956.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It takes three days to set up a meeting.","index":244,"end_time":958.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":956.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They''re not prepared and then they take another three to four days to get us stuff.","index":245,"end_time":962.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So every, everything we ask for always takes like one to two weeks.","index":246,"end_time":965.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I was like, we''re just not going to be able to work that way if we need to get some, some quick feedback from you all.","index":247,"end_time":971.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So the things I''m going to do or I need to send them by.","index":248,"end_time":977.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":972.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"End of today or early tomorrow morning is like a one to two page set of slides that covers the overall timeline and then the assumptions and then get a Slack channel set up where everyone gets introduced and we''re all working together there.","index":249,"end_time":994.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So those are the, the two things, so long winded way to get there.","index":250,"end_time":999.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But that''s what we''re, that''s what we''re all looking for.","index":251,"end_time":1002.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":999.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But what kind of what comes to mind from you all?","index":252,"end_time":1007.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1004.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like questions and things you''re thinking about?","index":253,"end_time":1009.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1007.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"For me, I think that it''s much easier to do it like this where we know the whole scope of like they know what they''re asking from us and we also know like what''s going to be like the average timeline for each page.","index":254,"end_time":1023.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1010.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And also I think it''s easier now that we''ve, you know, officially made it clear that the brand guidelines are, you know, finalized and nobody can ask anything additional because that was, I mean, for this two pages and the ebook, that was like the biggest challenge both for the designers and then for the quality assessment because I gave it all to, you know, both Lou and for Georgia to check additional times that everything is correct.","index":255,"end_time":1049.979,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1023.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I mean they know that they cannot change like the basic stuff that we need to Follow.","index":256,"end_time":1056.699,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1050.699,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because then all of the pages would need to be changed and.","index":257,"end_time":1060.459,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1056.699,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, I totally agree.","index":258,"end_time":1062.779,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1060.459,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":259,"end_time":1065.339,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1064.779,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, Nina, do you want to take a shot at putting together the timeline.","index":260,"end_time":1070.779,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1065.419,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, based on that dependency?","index":261,"end_time":1073.019,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.859,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Well, they will give us all copy by January 2nd.","index":262,"end_time":1077.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.019,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep.","index":263,"end_time":1078.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1077.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And also all product shots and anything they want to use, like in carousels or.","index":264,"end_time":1082.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1078.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, put that in there.","index":265,"end_time":1085.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1084.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I love it.","index":266,"end_time":1086.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1085.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then I will get the Slack channel set up.","index":267,"end_time":1092.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1088.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ll wait probably till this afternoon because I would like to probably set the.","index":268,"end_time":1098.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Slack channel up and then send these.","index":269,"end_time":1100.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1098.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Slides to through Slack.","index":270,"end_time":1102.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1100.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s like, hey, here''s the team.","index":271,"end_time":1104.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1103.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Here''s what we.","index":272,"end_time":1105.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1104.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We all put together.","index":273,"end_time":1106.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1105.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, let us know how this looks, blah, blah, blah.","index":274,"end_time":1110.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1107.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then I''m just gonna say, you know, over the next few weeks, and.","index":275,"end_time":1113.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"This is help, like me transition out.","index":276,"end_time":1116.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1113.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Just, you know, have a lot of time off the next few weeks.","index":277,"end_time":1119.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Please communicate in Slack.","index":278,"end_time":1120.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1119.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''ll help things progress.","index":279,"end_time":1121.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1120.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And, you know, you have pulse for the status of the tasks and everything.","index":280,"end_time":1127.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1124.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then you have Slack for us.","index":281,"end_time":1129.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1127.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, that''s probably the best way for us to keep moving.","index":282,"end_time":1131.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So do we have any meetings booked with them right now or are they mostly ad hoc?","index":283,"end_time":1138.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I was doing a weekly meeting with.","index":284,"end_time":1142.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1141.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Kylie and then she canceled one and then that''s fallen off the board probably.","index":285,"end_time":1149.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1142.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because, I mean, it''s hard to show.","index":286,"end_time":1151.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1149.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Up when you''ve done two pages.","index":287,"end_time":1154.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1151.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":288,"end_time":1154.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1154.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like every week.","index":289,"end_time":1155.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1154.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s just what''s happened.","index":290,"end_time":1157.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1155.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then she.","index":291,"end_time":1160.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She does like to gaslight a bit in email.","index":292,"end_time":1164.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1161.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s also why I had to talk with him.","index":293,"end_time":1166.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1164.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, she just.","index":294,"end_time":1167.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She had a long.","index":295,"end_time":1168.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1167.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean.","index":296,"end_time":1168.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1168.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Here, I''ll just share.","index":297,"end_time":1169.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bailey.","index":298,"end_time":1170.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1169.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, she just put together.","index":299,"end_time":1172.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1170.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You see this email?","index":300,"end_time":1174.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1173.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Not yet.","index":301,"end_time":1176.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Oh, there it is.","index":302,"end_time":1178.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1177.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":303,"end_time":1179.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So in progress.","index":304,"end_time":1180.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1179.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, she said, like, PowerPoint slide templates, one pager layouts, social media template.","index":305,"end_time":1190.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1181.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, these are.","index":306,"end_time":1192.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1190.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She''s like, these are in progress.","index":307,"end_time":1193.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1192.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I want to know the stat.","index":308,"end_time":1194.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''m like, never.","index":309,"end_time":1196.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1194.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"This is all out of scope.","index":310,"end_time":1198.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1196.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"These are.","index":311,"end_time":1198.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1198.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"These are not in progress.","index":312,"end_time":1200.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1198.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, I''m sure they''re in progress in your head, but not.","index":313,"end_time":1203.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1200.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Not anywhere in the scope of the project.","index":314,"end_time":1206.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1204.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so I told them also, she.","index":315,"end_time":1209.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1207.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sometimes doesn''t really keep to her original copy when she asks for changes, which.","index":316,"end_time":1214.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1209.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s a little bit like.","index":317,"end_time":1215.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1214.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, we can change it.","index":318,"end_time":1217.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1216.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s not a problem.","index":319,"end_time":1218.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1217.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But, like, if she''s asking us to stick to the original copy, then she should also do it for headers, for subheaders and things like that.","index":320,"end_time":1227.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1218.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, 100% I mean, this is just crazy.","index":321,"end_time":1230.839,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1227.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Baby, look.","index":322,"end_time":1231.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1230.839,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"20 slide layout options.","index":323,"end_time":1233.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1231.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, she just.","index":324,"end_time":1234.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1233.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She''s just throwing a bunch of things that she would like to have.","index":325,"end_time":1237.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1234.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And.","index":326,"end_time":1237.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I was like, this is crazy.","index":327,"end_time":1240,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1238.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, yeah, I don''t even know what you''re saying, but I mean, she said that she.","index":328,"end_time":1243.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1240.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She''s like, this is in progress.","index":329,"end_time":1244.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1243.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I want the status.","index":330,"end_time":1245.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1244.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, where are these things?","index":331,"end_time":1246.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And like, what are you even talking about?","index":332,"end_time":1249.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1246.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So anyway, so that got cleared up.","index":333,"end_time":1253.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1250.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yesterday and none of that stuff is on us.","index":334,"end_time":1256.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1253.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I just want to want you.","index":335,"end_time":1257.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1256.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All to know that too.","index":336,"end_time":1258.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1257.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, we have two ebooks and.","index":337,"end_time":1260.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1258.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Then we have to get the website done.","index":338,"end_time":1261.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1260.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That is.","index":339,"end_time":1262.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1261.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That is it on this project.","index":340,"end_time":1264.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Anything beyond that is, you know, you can kick to me and we can figure out what they want to do.","index":341,"end_time":1270.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s a very easy.","index":342,"end_time":1271.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1270.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, they did add for the ebook, so that was a.","index":343,"end_time":1275.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1272.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"An addendum.","index":344,"end_time":1276.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1275.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We can do that.","index":345,"end_time":1278.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1277.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ve mentioned multiple times there are ways we can help.","index":346,"end_time":1282.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1278.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But they just, you know, they''re looking to hire internal people, so it''s fine.","index":347,"end_time":1289.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1282.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They keep adding headcount and stuff and.","index":348,"end_time":1291.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1289.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And it''s the route they want to go.","index":349,"end_time":1293.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So what''s going to happen is they''ll have Kylie who, you know, they''ll find out.","index":350,"end_time":1299.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There''s no way she hits January 2nd, by the way.","index":351,"end_time":1301.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1299.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But that will be impossible for her to do.","index":352,"end_time":1305.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1303.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Even if she hits that date, she''s.","index":353,"end_time":1309.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1307.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Going to pass over probably a lot of Google Docs that are incomplete.","index":354,"end_time":1313.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1309.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She''ll be like, hey, here''s all I need is like these, these 10 things, but it''s done.","index":355,"end_time":1318.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1313.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, we''ll get some stuff like that probably, but we''ll see.","index":356,"end_time":1321.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1318.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ll see.","index":357,"end_time":1322.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1321.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hopefully.","index":358,"end_time":1322.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1322.38,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And also, like, they don''t want, like they don''t want to see AI, but all of the copies AI.","index":359,"end_time":1328.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1322.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, it''s.","index":360,"end_time":1329.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Oh.","index":361,"end_time":1331.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1331.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Oh.","index":362,"end_time":1331.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I. I was on the call, Nina.","index":363,"end_time":1334.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1331.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"With Jenny and Kylie, and I even.","index":364,"end_time":1338.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1334.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Mentioned, you know, a lot of the copywriting we can.","index":365,"end_time":1341.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1338.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We can do.","index":366,"end_time":1342.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ve mentioned AI, blah, blah, blah.","index":367,"end_time":1344.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then she''s like, yeah, you know.","index":368,"end_time":1345.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1344.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Kylie, I know you''re working with a.","index":369,"end_time":1346.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1345.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Lot of the prompts and maybe you.","index":370,"end_time":1348.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1346.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Can use that to help generate a lot of this.","index":371,"end_time":1350.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1348.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It was just insane.","index":372,"end_time":1352.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1350.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, it was not okay for us to go in that direction.","index":373,"end_time":1355.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1352.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But then on the flip side, I''m like, if that''s the route you''re going, why does it take a week and a half to do one page?","index":374,"end_time":1363.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1356.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, now I''m really confused.","index":375,"end_time":1365.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":376,"end_time":1366.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1366.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I don''t know.","index":377,"end_time":1368.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.469,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, that''s The.","index":378,"end_time":1371.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1370.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The route to go, if you want to have speed involved, you know, like, definitely.","index":379,"end_time":1377.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1371.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And it''s not like she writes the AI copy and it''s, you know, then she proofreads it and everything''s correct, but, like, her headlines are not consistent.","index":380,"end_time":1387.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1377.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, she uses a dot on some of them, on some of them not.","index":381,"end_time":1390.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1387.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, some of them are all caps, some of them are not.","index":382,"end_time":1393.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1390.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And it''s.","index":383,"end_time":1395.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1394.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Oh, yeah, it takes, like, a lot of subtle adjustments that, like, she won''t mind because she knows that it''s incorrect and like, to do it that way.","index":384,"end_time":1405.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1395.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But.","index":385,"end_time":1406.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1405.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, but that.","index":386,"end_time":1409.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That is kind of some of the.","index":387,"end_time":1410.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1409.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Detail we''ll need on our side.","index":388,"end_time":1411.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1410.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I think that''s.","index":389,"end_time":1413.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s where we are.","index":390,"end_time":1414.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1413.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, Nina, are you comfortable getting, you know, those bullet points and timelines in place?","index":391,"end_time":1420.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1414.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":392,"end_time":1420.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1420.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And would you mind putting that into.","index":393,"end_time":1423.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1421.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have a kitchen sink template that I think you can use.","index":394,"end_time":1429.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1425.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let me.","index":395,"end_time":1430.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1430.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let me find that real quick for you.","index":396,"end_time":1434.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1432.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So is Kylie going to, like, drip feed us copy by the.","index":397,"end_time":1443.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1438.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"By January 2nd, or does she plan to do everything and then deliver it to January 2?","index":398,"end_time":1449.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1443.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hopefully drip.","index":399,"end_time":1452,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1450.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Drip feed it to us so that we can design and dev.","index":400,"end_time":1455.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1452,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think that''s a key assumption, though, Nina, that.","index":401,"end_time":1459.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1456.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think that would be a line.","index":402,"end_time":1460.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1459.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Item that, you know, January 2nd assumes.","index":403,"end_time":1463.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1460.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That we will progressively get, you know, pages delivered to us so that we can get those into design and dev.","index":404,"end_time":1471.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1463.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because if we do wait for just a.","index":405,"end_time":1474.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1471.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All these pages to come over on January 2nd, then we''re not going to be able to design and get everything approved in a short amount of time.","index":406,"end_time":1483.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1474.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, we''ll need to spread that out.","index":407,"end_time":1485.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1483.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So.","index":408,"end_time":1485.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1485.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"One thing.","index":409,"end_time":1488.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So.","index":410,"end_time":1489.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1489.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So Nina, we just.","index":411,"end_time":1497.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1495.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bailey had a good idea.","index":412,"end_time":1499.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1498.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have this.","index":413,"end_time":1500.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, we call it the kitchen sink template.","index":414,"end_time":1506.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1502.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And so this is the ver.","index":415,"end_time":1511.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1508.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You can copy this, but it gives you, like, a lot of different cover pages styles to use.","index":416,"end_time":1516.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1511.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then these are just like, different.","index":417,"end_time":1519.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1516.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Types of layouts for a page.","index":418,"end_time":1521.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1519.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like if you have a table, an image you want to reference, a document, if you need a large table.","index":419,"end_time":1528.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1522.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So just like, different ways to present information that everyone.","index":420,"end_time":1532.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1529.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s kind of already formatted.","index":421,"end_time":1534.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1532.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So you can use this as a starting point.","index":422,"end_time":1536.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1534.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You can just, you know, end camp.","index":423,"end_time":1539.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1536.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You could do, like, website milestones or something like that, and then probably use, you know, like maybe this type of image or slide or something.","index":424,"end_time":1551.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1539.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ll let you kind of work through that.","index":425,"end_time":1553.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1551.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But this is just good to have.","index":426,"end_time":1555.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1553.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"A couple different layouts to choose from.","index":427,"end_time":1558.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1555.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Does that work?","index":428,"end_time":1561.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1561.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep.","index":429,"end_time":1562.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1562.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":430,"end_time":1564.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1564.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Well, I think that is everything I have Anything else you all can think of?","index":431,"end_time":1568.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1565.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, thanks.","index":432,"end_time":1569.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1569.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":433,"end_time":1571.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1571.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Well, thank you very much.","index":434,"end_time":1573.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1571.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ll keep moving along.","index":435,"end_time":1574.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1573.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":436,"end_time":1575.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1575.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Talk to you.","index":437,"end_time":1576.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1575.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Thank you.","index":438,"end_time":1577.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1576.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bye.","index":439,"end_time":1577.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1577.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bye.","index":440,"end_time":1578.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1577.91,"speaker_name":null}],"dateString":"2025-12-18T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86729959306?pwd=UC87qHDQx0heP0NFfGFcB4nw9Kuo2L.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KCPJEKJF7HDZ55T539DKR2FC","organizer_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"negative","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Escalated scope creep resolved; NCAMP confirmed brand guidelines, site copy, and ebook scope only.","Only 3 of 150+ website pages drafted; client now aims for full site by January 12.","Team to deliver two-slide timeline with firm assumptions, page limits, and cutoff dates.","Nina tasked with creating project timeline; copy handoff deadline set for January 2.","Slack channel to replace slow meeting cadence and accelerate feedback turnaround."],"highlights":[{"quote":"They jump on. They''re like, well, we would love to have the website available for the board meeting on January 12th.","speaker":"Unknown"},{"quote":"This person''s written two pages basically in about six weeks.","speaker":"Unknown"},{"quote":"She''s just throwing a bunch of things that she would like to have... this is crazy.","speaker":"Unknown"}],"topics":["scope","delivery","risk","timeline","client"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-22T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Project Scope and Resourcing**\n\nThe team clarified the project scope and adjusted roles to improve efficiency and accountability.\n\n- **Bailey was assigned as the new account director for the NCAMP website project** to provide focused leadership and support for Nina, replacing the original lead who is stepping back (00:00)  \n    - The shift aims to bring more hands-on management as the website work ramps up  \n    - Nina continues to handle brand-related tasks, while Bailey focuses on project coordination and delivery  \n    - This change addresses previous bottlenecks and unclear ownership in the workflow  \n    - Introducing Bailey allows for better client communication and internal coordination  \n\n- **The scope was narrowed to exclude copywriting and several design deliverables like PowerPoint and social media templates** after multiple out-of-scope requests and scope creep issues (01:40)  \n    - NCAMP agreed to provide all website copy, with the internal copywriter delivering Google Docs for design  \n    - The team will deliver Figma design files and two ebooks, plus finalize brand guidelines  \n    - Additional requests will be pushed back or handled as separate work beyond current agreements  \n    - This redefinition ensures proper resource allocation and prevents uncontrolled project growth  \n\n## **Content Delivery and Timeline Management**\n\nThe team established clear content delivery deadlines and a timeline framework to meet critical milestones.\n\n- **NCAMP committed to delivering all website copy and product assets by January 2nd to meet the January 12th board meeting deadline** (06:54)  \n    - Only three pages of copy have been produced in six weeks, highlighting content delays  \n    - Nina and Bailey emphasized that design approval must precede development to avoid rework  \n    - A timeline with key milestones including copy delivery, design approval, development, testing, and content migration is being created to set realistic expectations  \n    - This schedule will be presented to NCAMP with clear assumptions and boundaries to prevent scope creep  \n\n- **The timeline will include assumptions such as limited revision rounds and no scope expansion beyond approved deliverables** to enforce discipline (10:59)  \n    - Nina stressed the importance of defining how many revisions per page are acceptable to manage feedback flow  \n    - The timeline will also cover template development for simpler pages like blogs, privacy notices, and terms  \n    - Content migration from the existing WordPress site will be automated with Demir’s support, reducing manual tasks and speeding up delivery  \n    - AI tools will assist in cleaning and formatting migrated content for faster turnaround  \n\n## **Client Communication and Workflow Improvements**\n\nImproving communication channels and workflows was prioritized to reduce delays and clarify expectations.\n\n- **A Slack channel will be set up to enable real-time communication and faster feedback loops with NCAMP’s team** (15:58)  \n    - This replaces slow email chains and long meeting lead times, which have delayed progress  \n    - Bailey will handle introductions and ongoing communication to smooth collaboration  \n    - The Slack channel will be the primary hub for updates, questions, and task status alongside Pulse for task tracking  \n    - This change aims to accelerate approvals and reduce the typical one to two-week turnaround for responses  \n\n- **Weekly meetings with the copywriter Kylie have fallen off due to slow progress on copy and unclear priorities** (18:57)  \n    - Kylie’s requests for out-of-scope deliverables caused confusion and required firm pushback to reset expectations  \n    - Bailey and Nina clarified that only two ebooks and the website are in scope, with no additional templates or materials  \n    - Kylie’s inconsistent adherence to original copy and formatting standards added quality control challenges  \n    - This communication reset was crucial to align all parties on project boundaries and deliverables  \n\n## **Quality Control and Design Finalization**\n\nThe team reinforced brand guidelines and quality checks to avoid rework and maintain consistency.\n\n- **Brand guidelines are finalized and frozen to prevent ongoing changes that delay design and QA** (16:37)  \n    - Nina highlighted that repeated modifications forced multiple rounds of design and quality assessments  \n    - Lou and Georgia have been involved in thorough quality checks to ensure compliance with brand standards  \n    - This freeze enables the design team to focus on website pages and ebook layouts without shifting requirements  \n    - The final guidelines serve as a baseline for all creative assets to maintain consistency across deliverables  \n\n- **AI-assisted content generation is used cautiously due to quality issues and client reluctance** (21:40)  \n    - Bailey noted that although AI can speed up copywriting, inconsistent formatting and errors require significant manual fixes  \n    - The client prefers human-written copy but struggles with timely delivery, creating a tension between quality and speed  \n    - Clear communication with the client about these trade-offs is necessary to set realistic expectations  \n    - The team remains open to AI tools but will maintain rigorous review processes to uphold standards  \n\n## **Next Steps and Deliverable Management**\n\nConcrete plans were set to finalize deliverables and ensure smooth project handoff.\n\n- **Nina will draft a high-level timeline and assumptions document using an existing kitchen sink template, targeting delivery by tomorrow** (23:25)  \n    - The template provides a ready-made structure for milestones and presentation styles, speeding up preparation  \n    - The timeline will incorporate phased content delivery assumptions, allowing for progressive design and development  \n    - Bailey will coordinate sharing the timeline and team introductions via Slack to facilitate immediate feedback  \n    - This documentation will serve as the foundation for managing client expectations and internal workflows  \n\n- **Bailey will manage ongoing communications and help transition leadership as the original project lead reduces involvement** (15:58)  \n    - The team anticipates smoother progress with more hands involved and clearer accountability  \n    - Emphasis remains on limiting scope creep and ensuring timely delivery of copy, design, and development milestones  \n    - Continuous monitoring of client responsiveness and quality will be necessary to maintain momentum  \n    - The approach aims to deliver the website and ebooks on schedule for the January 12th board meeting with minimal surprises","outline":null,"keywords":["Encamp","website copy","brand guidelines","project timeline","scope management","client communication"],"overview":"- **Project Leadership Updates:** Bailey will be the new account director for better management of the NCAMP website project.\n\n- **Scope Adjustments:** Project scope revised to exclude copywriting and certain design deliverables after discussions on scope creep.\n\n- **Content Deadlines Set:** NCAMP to provide website copy by January 2nd for the January 12th board meeting; current progress is slow.\n\n- **Improved Communication Channels:** A Slack channel will replace email for real-time updates, aiming to speed up feedback loops.\n\n- **Quality Control Measures:** Brand guidelines finalized to avoid delays; AI tools will be used cautiously to maintain quality standards.\n\n- **Actionable Next Steps:** Nina to draft a timeline document for deliverables, with Bailey coordinating ongoing communications for clarity.","action_items":"\n**Nina Belina**\nBuild detailed website project timeline slides including key milestones, assumptions (e.g., revision limits, scope boundaries), and dependencies based on copy delivery by January 2 (00:09)\nUse provided kitchen sink template as a starting point to format timeline and milestone presentation slides (00:25)\nFollow up with Kylie regarding status and delivery plan of copy for second ebook and remaining web pages to confirm drip-feed schedule (00:06)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nSet up Slack channel for Encamp project team and client stakeholders; introduce Bailey and connect agency and client teams for streamlined communications (00:15)\nSend the timeline and assumptions slide deck through Slack to client team once completed (00:17)\nManage scope creep by communicating clearly with client on out-of-scope items such as PowerPoint/social media templates, reinforce brand guidelines finality (00:05)\n\n**Bailey Gunnell**\nEngage closely with Nina and client’s Jenny B. and Kylie for project continuity and account management transition (00:01)\n\n**Nina Belina & Tristan Pelligrino**\nCoordinate with client’s content migration lead (Demir) to plan content export/import for blogs and knowledge articles using programmatic methods, assisted by AI tools (00:12)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"9c2bac9b-d3e2-4cb9-9808-d376a8ccb9d7","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
