-- Meeting: New North x Planon Weekly Meeting (2025-12-18 15:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'ff2ef389-756d-4ece-b525-93fab32170d6',
    '2025-12-18 15:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KCM261TGX3VFMG7BQMMBZKEQ',
    'New North x Planon Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Taylor Doerbaum","Lauren Poirier"}'::text[],
    3064,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1',
    '{"id":"01KCM261TGX3VFMG7BQMMBZKEQ","title":"New North x Planon Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Campaign Performance and Optimization**\n\nThe ABM campaigns are steadily increasing connections, with brand awareness efforts ongoing but requiring more targeted messaging to boost engagement and lead quality (02:06).\n\n- **ABM connections are rising across all categories**, with the strongest performance in two key roles and campaigns, while other segments are catching up gradually (02:06).  \n    - Weekly maintenance ensures campaign delivery is smooth and volumes are optimized without risking LinkedIn account restrictions.  \n    - Three separate email sender domains help speed up outreach and avoid domain blocks, supporting consistent email flow through Lemlist (03:23).  \n    - LinkedIn messaging yields more responses than email, as LinkedIn’s personal approach fosters conversation, while emails mainly drive link clicks without replies (10:31).  \n    - Taylor emphasized caution to avoid blacklisting personal LinkedIn accounts by limiting daily outreach volumes (02:06).  \n\n- **Planned shift from brand awareness to more compelling offer-based messaging** targeted for mid-January aims to increase response rates and lead quality (03:23).  \n    - Taylor proposed evolving messaging from informational to conversational sequences ending in demo scheduling, based on successful tactics used for other clients (04:52).  \n    - Lauren requested examples of offers, highlighting limitations on discounts and preference for consultative or analytical incentives like free system or inventory analyses (05:13).  \n    - Taylor suggested short surveys or quick assessments to stimulate interest without heavy resource demands, aligning with Planon’s capabilities (06:21).  \n    - A separate, smaller campaign for a focused group of 20–50 universities can be created to limit demo requests and manage sales team capacity (07:27).  \n\n- **Audience targeting and messaging need refinement to improve relevance and engagement** (11:28).  \n    - Lauren flagged mismatches such as chief investment officers receiving maintenance-focused messaging, indicating need to adjust targeting or tailor messages per group (11:28).  \n    - Taylor agreed to segment messaging by the five defined audience groups, providing Lauren with detailed sequences for her to customize with Jay’s input (13:42).  \n    - Current broad messaging supports brand awareness but will be supplemented by targeted offer campaigns to re-engage contacts and drive sales conversations (16:48).  \n\n- **Ongoing campaign management includes weekly performance reviews and adaptive messaging adjustments without extra charge to optimize results within the existing 60 point monthly budget** (08:10).  \n    - Taylor assured that changes to messaging and minor interactive elements like surveys fit within current resources and points allocations (08:57).  \n    - The team monitors email open and click rates, acknowledging their limited accuracy but offering to provide these metrics weekly for transparency (21:04).  \n\n## **Lead Generation Goals and Sales Alignment**\n\nThere is a strategic pivot from quantity to quality of leads, with a focus on generating sales-ready leads rather than just brand awareness contacts (24:36).\n\n- **Target lead volume is approximately 50 leads per month, but emphasis is shifting to the number of leads ready for sales conversations** (24:42).  \n    - Lauren stressed the importance of leads that explicitly express interest in speaking with sales, as the sales team discounts low-value actions like content downloads (27:17).  \n    - Taylor proposed defining lead qualification criteria collaboratively, combining response behavior and website engagement metrics to identify sales-ready leads (27:42).  \n    - The team will develop a lead definition document with AND/OR logic to standardize qualification across marketing and sales teams (28:10).  \n\n- **A longer, extended meeting on January 8th will cover goal alignment, metrics, and ABM strategy updates to set clear expectations for the next quarter** (23:03).  \n    - Taylor will prepare recommendations incorporating new ABM approaches influenced by evolving AI and marketing technologies (26:36).  \n    - Lauren committed to sharing internal goals and refining target audiences to support focused outreach (24:36).  \n    - This meeting will enable formalizing a milestone plan aligned with contract timelines and business priorities (22:28).  \n\n## **Contract Extension and Budget Considerations**\n\nThe current ABM contract runs through March with a proposed one-month extension to April, pending internal approval and budget review (29:50).\n\n- **Lauren’s team prefers at least a three-month minimum engagement and hopes to extend one month past March, with cancellation notice due mid-January** (30:22).  \n    - Taylor will escalate the extension request to leadership and provide feedback before the cancellation deadline (31:05).  \n    - The contract extension would support running the refined ABM messaging sequence consistently through the first quarter (31:47).  \n    - Budget constraints are a key factor in finalizing contract length and scope of deliverables (29:50).  \n\n- **Points management is critical for balancing ongoing ABM activities and video production needs within the monthly 60-point budget** (33:16).  \n    - Lauren noted uncertainty about allocating 25 points for final video edits on top of ABM work (33:31).  \n    - Taylor explained that heavy video edits already performed justify the 25-point charge, but further small edits would be included without additional cost (36:17).  \n    - Lauren requested a full cost estimate before approving further video work to avoid budget overruns (40:33).  \n    - Taylor committed to clarifying costs with leadership and ensuring better upfront communication on charges going forward (48:04).  \n\n## **Video Production Status and Next Steps**\n\nVideo production is partially complete with significant storyboard and animation updates done, but final cut delivery is on hold pending budget clarity and approval (33:16).\n\n- **Major edits including color changes and facial animations were completed and represent the primary workload charged at 25 points, currently in progress but not yet finalized** (35:50).  \n    - Taylor clarified that the 25 points cover the entire edit and animation task, not just storyboard revisions (37:04).  \n    - Lauren was surprised by the cost structure and stressed the importance of prior cost estimates for budget management (46:58).  \n    - Taylor acknowledged the need for improved communication and committed to consulting leadership about potentially adjusting the charge or pausing work as requested (48:16).  \n\n- **Lauren has additional feedback on the storyboard but requested no further action until cost and budget are confirmed** (42:11).  \n    - Taylor confirmed no further edits will be made without explicit approval, ensuring budget control (42:15).  \n    - The team will provide a final quote for completing the video project inclusive of remaining requested changes before proceeding (49:41).  \n\n- **The video is intended as a key deliverable to support ABM efforts, and Taylor emphasized willingness to complete it if budget allows** (50:06).  \n    - Taylor plans to share a detailed recap and timeline covering both ABM and video project statuses immediately after the meeting (50:35).  \n\n## **ABM Advertising and Campaign Launch Timing**\n\nABM display ads are undergoing final design updates and will await approval before scheduling launch, likely in early January to align with audience attention patterns (19:30).\n\n- **Designs have been sent to the designer Lou with pending final approval from Roderick, expected by December 23rd** (19:30).  \n    - Launching ads will follow approval and a review by Stella, who is out the first week of January, potentially delaying the live date (20:07).  \n    - Taylor recommended launching the ads in the second week of January, aligning with audience availability post-holidays and maximizing campaign impact (20:25).  \n    - Staggered launch with ongoing email campaigns will maintain brand visibility while introducing new messaging sequences (20:25).","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing (ABM)","Campaign Messaging","Lead Generation","Video Production","Contract Extension","Audience Targeting"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaigns Growing:** Connections increasing across categories, best in key roles, necessitating targeted messaging for better engagement.\n\n- **Message Shift Planned:** Moving to offer-based messaging by mid-January to enhance response rates and lead quality.\n\n- **Refine Audience Targeting:** Adjust messaging for specific roles, improving relevance and maintaining engagement with defined audience groups.\n\n- **Quality Over Quantity:** Focusing on 50 sales-ready leads monthly, developing criteria to identify interested contacts for sales conversations.\n\n- **Contract Extension Proposal:** Seeking one-month extension past March for consistent ABM messaging, dependent on budget review.\n\n- **Video Production Delayed:** Major edits done, final delivery on hold pending budget approval; costs need clarification before proceeding.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nContinue weekly ABM campaign monitoring and update shared documents with new responses (03:00)\nWork with developers to improve email send rates without risking LinkedIn personal account blacklisting (03:00)\nPrepare new ABM messaging campaign options with conversational/offer-style sequences for January presentation (04:30)\nShare detailed ABM messaging sequences organized by audience group with Lauren, including contact lists (14:40)\nCoordinate with designer Lou and submit ABM ads for Roderick''s final approval by December 23, then prepare for Stella''s review (19:30)\nAdd email open and click rate metrics with explanation of data accuracy to weekly reports (21:00)\nExtend January meeting to 1 hour for strategic goal setting and planning (23:30)\nDiscuss lead qualification definitions with Bailey to align on lead handoff criteria and reporting (26:30)\nLiaise with leadership regarding contract extension request to April and communicate response by early January (31:00)\nVerify video project status and point allocations with internal team, delaying further edits until budget approval (42:00)\nSend meeting recap and updated deliverables to Lauren and her team (50:45)\n\n**Lauren Poirier**\nReview shared ABM messaging sequences and collaborate with Jay to refine target audiences and messaging per group (13:50)\nIdentify 20-50 top university targets for a potential limited offer campaign focusing on demos or consultations (16:00)\nShare latest video edits comments with Taylor but hold off on further execution pending budget clarity (41:00)\nDiscuss contract extension and budgeting internally and provide feedback in early January (32:00)\n"},"duration":51.06999969482422,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":1,"name":"Lauren Poirier"}],"sentences":[{"text":"How are you?","index":0,"end_time":1.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Can you hear me all right?","index":1,"end_time":6.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can, yeah.","index":2,"end_time":7.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.4,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":3,"end_time":8.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I didn''t know if it was on my end or not.","index":4,"end_time":11.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":5,"end_time":14.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.52,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"You excited?","index":6,"end_time":15.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":14.64,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m off.","index":7,"end_time":16.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.6,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I am, yeah.","index":8,"end_time":18.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m excited.","index":9,"end_time":18.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"My family''s coming in.","index":10,"end_time":20.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The rest of my family''s coming in tomorrow, so.","index":11,"end_time":22.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Nice.","index":12,"end_time":23.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":22.88,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Have a lot of cleaning to do tonight and just still have so many gifts to wrap.","index":13,"end_time":27.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":23.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just.","index":14,"end_time":28.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I haven''t started rapping.","index":15,"end_time":31.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.38,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":16,"end_time":32.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That makes me feel better.","index":17,"end_time":32.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I feel like some people are really ahead of it.","index":18,"end_time":34.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Usually I''m still buying gifts now and I still have one more, but I''m.","index":19,"end_time":38.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":35.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I feel like it just goes fast.","index":20,"end_time":40.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You think you have a lot of time?","index":21,"end_time":41.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because I feel like Christmas is the last week of the month, but it''s really not.","index":22,"end_time":44.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.939,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s the third week, like, right.","index":23,"end_time":47.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It sneaks up on you.","index":24,"end_time":48.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.54,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Thank you for the reminder.","index":25,"end_time":50.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.98,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I have one more gift to buy too.","index":26,"end_time":51.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":50.18,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And you just remember.","index":27,"end_time":52.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.5,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"There''S one for my brother.","index":28,"end_time":55.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"He wants like a golf glove, but the one like, like sporting good store I went to, like, was sold out.","index":29,"end_time":60.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I have to have my husband try to get it by where he works because I''m like, it''s.","index":30,"end_time":64.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I need that gift because they have their birthday and Christmas together.","index":31,"end_time":67.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''s like extra things I have to buy.","index":32,"end_time":70,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m like, oh my gosh.","index":33,"end_time":70.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"My mother in law is kind of similar.","index":34,"end_time":73.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.52,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Her birthday is the 19th and so it''s like she hates that her birthday is near Christmas.","index":35,"end_time":79.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":73.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So her birthday celebration always has to be separate from Christmas, which I understand completely.","index":36,"end_time":84.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.48,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But it''s like, oh, just another thing.","index":37,"end_time":86.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.72,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like you can''t use Christmas wrapping paper for her gift.","index":38,"end_time":89.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.64,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like, oh, man, that is so funny.","index":39,"end_time":92.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"My husband''s birthday is Christmas Eve, so.","index":40,"end_time":94.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is it really?","index":41,"end_time":95.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.78,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Oh, wow.","index":42,"end_time":96.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s so.","index":43,"end_time":97.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It is frustrating because I feel bad for him because it''s hard to make it special for them.","index":44,"end_time":101.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"He''s very like, I don''t care, give me the Christmas paper.","index":45,"end_time":104.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":102.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I feel like he should have it separate.","index":46,"end_time":106.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":104.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I mean, when it''s Christmas Eve, it''s really hard, so it''s really hard, but.","index":47,"end_time":112.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":106.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Poor guy.","index":48,"end_time":115.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":114.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":49,"end_time":116.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.88,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I feel bad for December.","index":50,"end_time":117.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":116.24,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"December birthdays.","index":51,"end_time":118.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":117.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know.","index":52,"end_time":119.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s a.","index":53,"end_time":120.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s a tricky, tricky one.","index":54,"end_time":121.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Everyone''s just so got a lot going on.","index":55,"end_time":124.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":56,"end_time":125.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":57,"end_time":127.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, well, today I just want to share some updates with you on the ABM updates.","index":58,"end_time":130.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we have those different categories still getting sent out.","index":59,"end_time":134.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":130.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The connections are still rising on all of them with our top ones being these two roles and campaigns currently.","index":60,"end_time":142.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then these ones are starting to catch up now.","index":61,"end_time":145.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we have been keeping note in that document.","index":62,"end_time":149.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Every now and then I see a couple more come in of people that just respond and I know you want to see those, so we''ll continue to update that as those come through.","index":63,"end_time":157.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we did some maintenance yesterday.","index":64,"end_time":159.769,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":157.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We just have a developer look each week to make sure everything is moving correctly and everything is reaching and so everything looked good.","index":65,"end_time":168.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.769,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I worked with him on a couple of things to just see if we can get the amount out a little faster for a couple of the other ones.","index":66,"end_time":176.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":168.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But with the LinkedIn profile, since they''re personal ones, we don''t want to ever get them like blacklisted, especially because they''re personal accounts.","index":67,"end_time":184.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you''ll see the LinkedIn ones may take a little bit more time on a couple of the other ones because it was kind of going down like a, like a trickle effect on the different campaigns.","index":68,"end_time":194.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''re okay with that just because they will get out eventually and we, we don''t want to run the risk of anything happening their accounts because there''s only so many you can send a day.","index":69,"end_time":202.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":194.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, so that looks good.","index":70,"end_time":205.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":203.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And LEM List, those emails are flying out, which is really good too because sometimes Lemlist also has blocks because they have a certain amount of day.","index":71,"end_time":213.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":205.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we''re monitoring that too because we don''t want to lose any of the domains that we''ve purchased.","index":72,"end_time":217.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But having three different senders really does help, like coming from three different people because we were able to purchase I think like three domains per so.","index":73,"end_time":225.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So there''s so many that we can pull from which helps get those emails going out quicker.","index":74,"end_time":230.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, so that''s really great to see.","index":75,"end_time":232.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then just looking, I know we talked through potentially changing up the sequence once we have some more data to make it more of a compelling offer.","index":76,"end_time":243.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So maybe in January, mid January, when we''ve seen some more analytics come through and we''ve seen some responses from people, maybe we can ramp up or change the way we do the messaging just to make it a little bit more compelling as an offer.","index":77,"end_time":256.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because that''s where we''ve noticed the most significant success across different clients campaigns.","index":78,"end_time":260.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can brainstorm some of those ideas.","index":79,"end_time":262.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But is that something you''d still be interested in, is kind of changing up the messaging?","index":80,"end_time":266.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think right now it''s for brand awareness and informational, which is where we started, which is good.","index":81,"end_time":271.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But that doesn''t always yield the most responses because we''re just kind of giving them the link right away, which gives them no reason to Respond.","index":82,"end_time":279.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":83,"end_time":280.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Whereas it''s more of like a compelling conversational piece where ultimately it ends in a demo schedule.","index":84,"end_time":286.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We could kind of wrap it more in that way.","index":85,"end_time":289.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":86,"end_time":290.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"What are your thoughts there?","index":87,"end_time":291.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I think having a more conversational tone would be.","index":88,"end_time":295.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.17,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Would be really great to stimulate more engagement as far as the offer goes.","index":89,"end_time":301.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.33,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"What.","index":90,"end_time":302.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.33,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Do what has worked for you in the past.","index":91,"end_time":305.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Because that''s the piece where I don''t really know what we would offer since we can''t offer like a discount or anything beyond like a demo.","index":92,"end_time":312.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.05,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, it will.","index":93,"end_time":314.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it would.","index":94,"end_time":315.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"A couple of my clients, it''s the same way too.","index":95,"end_time":317.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":315.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"In the industry that everybody''s in, it''s not like you''re like, oh, fill this out and get a gift card, because then you sound desperate.","index":96,"end_time":323.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we don''t ever want that for our clients.","index":97,"end_time":324.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we would work with you to see, like, what kind of things we could do.","index":98,"end_time":328.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So one of my clients, what they started doing is offering a free inventory analysis.","index":99,"end_time":334.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So basically what they would do is have somebody fill out a form and then they would get like a free analysis of their company or their business.","index":100,"end_time":341.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"In return of them doing that, it would be like they would get on a call and jump on a call to go over it.","index":101,"end_time":348.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":342.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so it kind of opens up the door to that conversation, but they get something in return.","index":102,"end_time":352.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":348.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So they''re getting an analysis of how their company is running, how production is going, but in return, they''re getting on a call.","index":103,"end_time":359.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":353.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So the client wins, and they win because they''re both getting something out of it.","index":104,"end_time":363.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s something that we do.","index":105,"end_time":364.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t know if Planon has anything like that.","index":106,"end_time":366.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Can even be like a quick consultation to see how your systems are running or how up to date maybe is your school system like a quick, short form.","index":107,"end_time":377.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or it could even be like five questions where it''s like, is this up to date?","index":108,"end_time":381.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you use any kind of smart technology?","index":109,"end_time":383.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is this something that you''re interested in?","index":110,"end_time":384.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"One of my other clients is also doing a survey right now, and it''s only five questions and we send it out.","index":111,"end_time":390.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it could be something even like that where just getting insights if somebody''s interested, where they''re at with their smart building journey, stuff like that.","index":112,"end_time":399.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So there''s ways around it to make it beneficial for both parties.","index":113,"end_time":402.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But just depending on the kind of things that you guys do, we can kind of coordinate around that.","index":114,"end_time":408.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":404.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If that''s.","index":115,"end_time":408.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.35,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If you guys do anything like that of like a performance analysis and stuff like that, it doesn''t have to Be a heavy lift because we also don''t want you guys wasting time and money if it''s not going to turn into anything.","index":116,"end_time":418.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":408.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just something short that could be made as an offer.","index":117,"end_time":421.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":118,"end_time":423.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I, I love the idea of like a custom, you know, analysis of your systems and how they''re running and if you''re using room booking and yada yada yada.","index":119,"end_time":434.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The problem is I think our demo team is already really short on time so I don''t that we can offer like a face to face meeting.","index":120,"end_time":443.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.35,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":121,"end_time":444.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":443.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Unless it was to like a really specific like 20 universities or like if we really narrow down, I think we could do something like that so that we''re limiting how many people will come.","index":122,"end_time":459.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":447.08,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Back and say yes, yeah, yeah, for sure.","index":123,"end_time":462.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We could create our own audience, build for that particular offer.","index":124,"end_time":467.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we wouldn''t need to necessarily include it within all of these campaigns that we have running as they''re already kind of working through anyway.","index":125,"end_time":474.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We could create a different campaign that could run along simultaneously with a specific audience of like people you would definitely like to work with and then we can send it out to them which would, like you said, limit the amount that could potentially be responding.","index":126,"end_time":490.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":475.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":127,"end_time":491.379,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":490.98,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Points wise, will that be like a significant additional amount of points or is that built into the.","index":128,"end_time":498.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":491.86,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s just part of our abm because that''s like what we''re running for you.","index":129,"end_time":502.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And if that''s what our focus is, we want to continuously manage that.","index":130,"end_time":505.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":502.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that manage ABM campaign, that''s 10 points every week.","index":131,"end_time":509.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We look and we''re like, how is this performing?","index":132,"end_time":511.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":509.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We don''t want to have her be stagnant.","index":133,"end_time":513.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":511.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if we''re like this isn''t performing well, we''re not getting responses, then we''re going to change it and it''s not going to be like, okay, we''re going to charge you to change it.","index":134,"end_time":519.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":513.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we did like a huge overhaul of a ton of things, it might.","index":135,"end_time":523.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But something like this, we want to kind of perfect the offer that we''re doing here and we want to make sure it''s being successful for you.","index":136,"end_time":531.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s why we kind of just adapt and change and that''s what those management tasks are for.","index":137,"end_time":536.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":138,"end_time":537.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Even if you do have to build out like a survey or something a.","index":139,"end_time":540.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537.32,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Little bit interactive, that might be a couple additional things.","index":140,"end_time":543.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I think based on our conversation last week, we have room with the tasks that we normally do.","index":141,"end_time":549.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":543.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s still.","index":142,"end_time":550.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because I think you guys have 60 points a month and if we do some of those things, I think we''re at like 50 something so we would have the additional space.","index":143,"end_time":557.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":144,"end_time":558.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.04,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"To do something like that.","index":145,"end_time":559.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And it''s not like a 30 videos or very high points tasks just because the time intensity.","index":146,"end_time":565.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But something like a survey wouldn''t be as, as crazy.","index":147,"end_time":568.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It would fit more into the to the monthly allotment.","index":148,"end_time":571.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And like I said, we want your ABM campaign to be successful so we''ll definitely work with you to make sure it is.","index":149,"end_time":577.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''re not going to be like, you know, super whatever about that, like a 30 point task and again it goes into the management.","index":150,"end_time":585.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if we see that what we currently are doing isn''t working with this campaign and this audience, we want to change it and make it better.","index":151,"end_time":592.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":586.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":152,"end_time":592.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds good.","index":153,"end_time":594.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":592.9,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Couple clarifying questions on just the performance.","index":154,"end_time":597.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":595.38,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I''m looking at the document you shared with any message replies on LinkedIn.","index":155,"end_time":602.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":598.34,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Are these.","index":156,"end_time":605.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":604.98,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I see like convo started.","index":157,"end_time":607.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.1,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That''s people who accepted the request.","index":158,"end_time":609.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":607.94,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":159,"end_time":611.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So as soon as they accept the connection request then we''re able to send them a message.","index":160,"end_time":615.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":611.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it does it automatically or it waits.","index":161,"end_time":617.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think it waits a three day period before sending a message and then it sends it.","index":162,"end_time":622.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":617.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":163,"end_time":622.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":622.35,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":164,"end_time":624.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":624.11,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So we haven''t had any like productive conversations yet on LinkedIn.","index":165,"end_time":628.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":624.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Have we had any email responses?","index":166,"end_time":630.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"No, and that''s usually typical emails.","index":167,"end_time":634.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We don''t tend to see a lot of responses across the board.","index":168,"end_time":636.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like with my clients, it''s usually LinkedIn.","index":169,"end_time":639.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":636.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"One of my other clients that I''m running right now, a huge ABM campaign, we have been running it for a couple months now and they''ve gotten a lot of good responses off LinkedIn and none on email.","index":170,"end_time":648.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I think people are just.","index":171,"end_time":650.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s a more casual environment.","index":172,"end_time":651.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":650.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think email is more informational so people will just click the link directly from there and not feel the need to respond.","index":173,"end_time":657.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But because on LinkedIn it''s like a personal message, you see somebody''s account pop up.","index":174,"end_time":662.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It kind of makes people like feel like they need to respond more if that makes sense.","index":175,"end_time":666.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because if it''s an email, you just click the link and you go on with your day.","index":176,"end_time":669.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if it''s like a message, it''s almost like thanks for sending.","index":177,"end_time":672.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Kind of like it creates conversation.","index":178,"end_time":674.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":179,"end_time":675.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.31,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So but other, other, other colleagues of mine have had campaigns that do yield email responses.","index":180,"end_time":682.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But Lemlist or payreach is definitely where we see the most come through.","index":181,"end_time":687.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":683.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good to know.","index":182,"end_time":689.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.11,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m seeing one of the responses.","index":183,"end_time":692.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":690.35,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m a chief investment officer managing the endowment fund.","index":184,"end_time":694.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.27,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I Don''t have anything to do with maintenance.","index":185,"end_time":696.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":694.91,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Can we make sure that title is removed from the targeting list?","index":186,"end_time":700.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.39,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":187,"end_time":702.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":701.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So a couple, like in this finance and budgeting stakeholders particular group, I think that we have, you know, people like that in there because that was what we had determined.","index":188,"end_time":714.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We want to separate them all, not just have facilities managers.","index":189,"end_time":718.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that is populating from this group.","index":190,"end_time":722.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is that something that you want to continue or refine to not have?","index":191,"end_time":725.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":722.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because I think with the budgeting and stakeholders of a university, you''re not necessarily always going to have the facilities in the title.","index":192,"end_time":732.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":726.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I.","index":193,"end_time":732.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s where this is pulling from is more titles like that.","index":194,"end_time":735.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So did that change on your end?","index":195,"end_time":737.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":735.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you want to kind of tweak those?","index":196,"end_time":738.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":737.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I think just based on this response that he''s like, this has nothing to do with me.","index":197,"end_time":745.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.62,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think maybe we need to look at that group of people and the messaging that we''re sending.","index":198,"end_time":750.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.94,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It sounds like it''s not resonating.","index":199,"end_time":752.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.86,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I think we should take a look at that.","index":200,"end_time":754.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":752.5,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Let me see if I can.","index":201,"end_time":755.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":754.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we can definitely change a couple of the campaign specifics for the audiences.","index":202,"end_time":765.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let''s see if I can pull up the list.","index":203,"end_time":768.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t know that we broke out messaging for each of those groups.","index":204,"end_time":777.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":770.67,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Can you correct me if I''m wrong?","index":205,"end_time":779.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":777.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"No, we.","index":206,"end_time":780.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"When we originally talked about it, I think you were out that week.","index":207,"end_time":784.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We talked about it, but we were talking to Paula about potentially changing the messaging sequence for each.","index":208,"end_time":789.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we were so behind already.","index":209,"end_time":790.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"She wanted to launch which.","index":210,"end_time":793.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Which was fine because we were going to test how that worked.","index":211,"end_time":795.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And it was.","index":212,"end_time":796.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It was broad enough where it worked for every group because it wasn''t super specific.","index":213,"end_time":801.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":796.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And if you''re involved in higher educational, it''s applicable if you''re making decisions which a lot of these people are making decisions on behalf of, like facilities and things like that.","index":214,"end_time":810.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":801.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But that was one of the ideas that we had started with when building the campaign is making it more niche per group, making the message more applicable kind of across the board.","index":215,"end_time":822.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":810.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we should revisit that.","index":216,"end_time":824.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Able to share like the LinkedIn messaging and the emails that are going out and then, you know, break it down by the.","index":217,"end_time":833.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.67,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The groups.","index":218,"end_time":834.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think there were five different groups.","index":219,"end_time":835.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":834.11,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Right.","index":220,"end_time":835.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":835.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then I can go in and tweak a little bit to try to target more these specific roles.","index":221,"end_time":843.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":836.15,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''ll work with Jay to try to get that a little bit more dialed into what that role does.","index":222,"end_time":848.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":843.11,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":223,"end_time":850.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":849.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And yeah, I just pulled this up so you could see, like we do have those Higher.","index":224,"end_time":854.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like finance.","index":225,"end_time":855.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":854.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":226,"end_time":857.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Groups in here, I think we, I.","index":227,"end_time":862.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Think I''ve talked to Jay about them and I think they''re fine.","index":228,"end_time":865.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.61,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s just a matter of they''re more interested in like it costs.","index":229,"end_time":870.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":865.61,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So that would be how we would tweak that one.","index":230,"end_time":873.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":871.33,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But yeah, if you, if you could share that with me, I think in this case it might be that chief investment officers, maybe we can include them.","index":231,"end_time":882,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":873.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s just tweaking the message to be a little bit less facilities focused.","index":232,"end_time":885.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":882,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":233,"end_time":887.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If you could put everything over to.","index":234,"end_time":890.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":888.88,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"You in a message just so it''s more you probably, it''s probably somewhere, but don''t you have to look back?","index":235,"end_time":894.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":890.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So yeah, I can send this over to you.","index":236,"end_time":895.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And like I said, if we''re wanting to tweak them all individually and kind of think about that offer a little bit more.","index":237,"end_time":904.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":896.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we want to meet.","index":238,"end_time":905.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know next time we''ll meet will be in January.","index":239,"end_time":908.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If you want, Bailey and I, we can brainstorm ahead of time and come up with a couple potential ideas and how that would work.","index":240,"end_time":914.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":908.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we wanted to do the survey route and we could just come prepared and kind of present that to you and see if you like that idea.","index":241,"end_time":921.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, off the top of my head, that''s what I do for other clients.","index":242,"end_time":925.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I can make it more concrete into a presentation to show you how we could facilitate that change.","index":243,"end_time":929.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then we can talk about also the specifics if you want to take a look at it now and see if you want to change things.","index":244,"end_time":935.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if we did do something like an offer style, we could work that.","index":245,"end_time":939.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We would change the messaging here too as well.","index":246,"end_time":942.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Unless that was only a separate group like you''re talking about.","index":247,"end_time":946.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think we would want to do a separate group if it was a survey where we''re not having a face to face meeting as the outcome.","index":248,"end_time":953.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":947.38,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Fine to do it for everybody.","index":249,"end_time":955.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":954.1,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But if we do do an offer like a meeting, we definitely need to break that out and it''s okay.","index":250,"end_time":960.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":955.46,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If it''s like I would say 20 to 50 universities that are like top of the target list, I can identify, you know, for you guys, like which ones we would want to be in that group.","index":251,"end_time":969.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.52,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think that''s a great idea.","index":252,"end_time":972.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":971.08,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I just have to run it by Jay and his team.","index":253,"end_time":974.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":972.28,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":254,"end_time":975.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":974.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":255,"end_time":975.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":975.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we''ll come prepared next time with.","index":256,"end_time":977.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":975.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll build it out into like the deck here.","index":257,"end_time":979.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I can show you.","index":258,"end_time":980.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can bring a couple examples from my other clients too, just to show you how that would work.","index":259,"end_time":984.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, if, if it''s A win win on both sides.","index":260,"end_time":988.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It tends to be more successful.","index":261,"end_time":990.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":988.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I know we were building this originally for brand awareness, which is good because then you have people that can just click the links on their own.","index":262,"end_time":997.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":990.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, so we can definitely do that.","index":263,"end_time":1000.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":998.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then also look at refining a couple of these and all of these are continuing on.","index":264,"end_time":1005.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1000.809,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So the brand awareness is getting to each of these groups, which is good.","index":265,"end_time":1009.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1005.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if we want to refine the messaging to.","index":266,"end_time":1013.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1009.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can always put them into a new campaign with that new messaging and revisit these people again.","index":267,"end_time":1018.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So even if we''ve already sent them these other emails and we decided to change what we''re saying, we can put them into a new campaign that can run simultaneously and it''ll send them additional email, but this time it''ll be a different offer or messaging sequence because we do that too for other clients where we.","index":268,"end_time":1035.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1019.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You can use the same contact groups again.","index":269,"end_time":1037.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1035.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that way they can get the same.","index":270,"end_time":1039.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1038.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The new offer and it''s not like they missed it.","index":271,"end_time":1041.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1039.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we change the messaging sequence, if that makes sense.","index":272,"end_time":1043.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we can continue to run with the brand awareness side, but also we can send them additional emails if we do change it to like an offer style sequence.","index":273,"end_time":1053.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1044.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I think I.","index":274,"end_time":1055.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1054.25,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"At this point, because there are more eyes on this now.","index":275,"end_time":1059.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1055.93,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Brand awareness is great, but I think we do need to start pushing a little bit more for like sales.","index":276,"end_time":1064.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1059.69,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Converse the conversations with sales.","index":277,"end_time":1066.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1064.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":278,"end_time":1066.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1066.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that, that sounds good.","index":279,"end_time":1070.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.12,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think if you put together your plan for some kind of survey for the wide audience, that would be great.","index":280,"end_time":1075.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1070.24,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If you can share the email and like all the messaging sequences.","index":281,"end_time":1079.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1076.08,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It looks like it''s already in one document.","index":282,"end_time":1080.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1079.24,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That''s perfect.","index":283,"end_time":1081.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1080.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You can share that with me.","index":284,"end_time":1083.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1081.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''ll go through that.","index":285,"end_time":1084.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1083.16,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''ll talk to Jay about doing some sort of offer.","index":286,"end_time":1089.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1085.68,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Let me just write this down so I don''t forget.","index":287,"end_time":1092.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1090.79,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then that would be to like.","index":288,"end_time":1097.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1096.23,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"A select group of university targets just.","index":289,"end_time":1102.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"To make sure that we are getting the right message to the right titles.","index":290,"end_time":1106.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1102.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, and it would be a good time to do it too.","index":291,"end_time":1108.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1107.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":292,"end_time":1109.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1108.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"In the new year when everyone''s fresh.","index":293,"end_time":1110.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1109.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''ll be.","index":294,"end_time":1112.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1111.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''ll be good.","index":295,"end_time":1113.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1112.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so can you divide out.","index":296,"end_time":1117.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1114.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So with those five groups of titles, can you divide this out so that we have the messaging sequence for each group and then from there I can tweak it.","index":297,"end_time":1127.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1117.41,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":298,"end_time":1129.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":299,"end_time":1129.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like create a new document or in the same document you just want me to put headings?","index":300,"end_time":1133.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be fine.","index":301,"end_time":1135.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1134.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just so that we have each one for each group of people.","index":302,"end_time":1139.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1135.45,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":303,"end_time":1140.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1139.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This has Been happening to me so much Google, it''s like, I know you''re on a meeting, but guess what?","index":304,"end_time":1146.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1140.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m gonna sign you out of everything anyway.","index":305,"end_time":1150.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But, yes, I can just keep it all in one document.","index":306,"end_time":1153.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1151.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"What I''ll do is I''m gonna actually create a duplicate document so that way we can keep the original sequence somewhere and I''ll create a V2 with a new campaign so that way we don''t.","index":307,"end_time":1163.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1153.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We don''t get rid of the old messaging.","index":308,"end_time":1167.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, I will do that.","index":309,"end_time":1169.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I''ll send that over to you.","index":310,"end_time":1170.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1169.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can send the contact list to you just so that''s fresh in the chat so you can find that.","index":311,"end_time":1176.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1170.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the ABM ads, we''re working on those design updates.","index":312,"end_time":1180.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I sent that over to Lou, our designer.","index":313,"end_time":1182.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1180.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is that the final step, do you think, for those ABM ads?","index":314,"end_time":1186.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or will you send them back to Roderick for final approval?","index":315,"end_time":1189.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1186.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, I just want to make sure that we get those to you and in case you wanted those launched.","index":316,"end_time":1194.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1189.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I will get those to you and then we''ll wait for your approval on those.","index":317,"end_time":1197.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1194.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And yeah, I think Roderick is in until, I want to say, the 23rd.","index":318,"end_time":1202.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1197.53,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So we''re able to get that back to him in time.","index":319,"end_time":1205.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1203.18,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Give him a couple days to review.","index":320,"end_time":1207.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1206.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It, and then I think Stella.","index":321,"end_time":1209.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1207.5,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So once, once he finally approves them, we get them loaded into LinkedIn and then share that with Stella before those go live so she can review.","index":322,"end_time":1217.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.14,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think she is out like the first week of January, so that might be a little bit of a hold up.","index":323,"end_time":1225.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1218.46,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s okay.","index":324,"end_time":1226.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Even if we launch the ABM ads, obviously we like to do them simultaneously when we launch the ABM campaign.","index":325,"end_time":1234.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1227.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I know we''ve had some stop and go, but it''s.","index":326,"end_time":1237.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1234.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It might be better to launch them in the new year anyway because right now everybody''s kind of checking out, right?","index":327,"end_time":1241.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like audiences and stuff.","index":328,"end_time":1243.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1241.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ve noticed just like, even website visits across some of our clients.","index":329,"end_time":1245.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1243.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just it''s that time of year, so that''s okay if we launch it the second week of January.","index":330,"end_time":1250.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, I''ll be here up until the 23rd too.","index":331,"end_time":1253.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1251.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I will be contacting you and messaging you with those updates.","index":332,"end_time":1258.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1253.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And yeah, the video too.","index":333,"end_time":1259.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1258.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you have anything new regarding the video?","index":334,"end_time":1262.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1259.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No.","index":335,"end_time":1263.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So before we get to that, one more thing about abm.","index":336,"end_time":1267.309,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1264.59,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So with these emails, can you share every week?","index":337,"end_time":1271.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1267.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like just the.","index":338,"end_time":1272.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1271.15,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Or maybe in the dashboard?","index":339,"end_time":1273.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1272.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s there and I''m not seeing it.","index":340,"end_time":1275.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1273.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just the open rate for the emails and the click rate.","index":341,"end_time":1277.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1275.11,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Are you tracking that we usually don''t track that because that has been proven to be skewed data and lemless.","index":342,"end_time":1283.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1277.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We have noticed like across the board sometimes that data is not always accurate.","index":343,"end_time":1287.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So our team on our side has encouraged us that that''s not a good metric to go off of.","index":344,"end_time":1292.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1287.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If that''s something you''re interested in, I can pull it.","index":345,"end_time":1294.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1292.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But there is like a margin of error to the open rates now that just the way the links work.","index":346,"end_time":1300.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And when someone opens an email, sometimes that data gets skewed.","index":347,"end_time":1303.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1300.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Bailey knows so much research about that because she has done it, which she''s determined it''s not as great as the statistic.","index":348,"end_time":1309.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1303.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I can share.","index":349,"end_time":1310.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1309.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Have her share that more with you next week.","index":350,"end_time":1312.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1310.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if that''s something you''re interested, I can add it to our deck each week just so you can see it.","index":351,"end_time":1315.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And Bailey can kind of explain that margin of error.","index":352,"end_time":1318.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1315.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, I can provide additional data in the the deck slides and we can review it.","index":353,"end_time":1323.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1318.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":354,"end_time":1325.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1324.37,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just since there''s eyes on this, I want to be able to pull some data about even if it''s not 100% accurate.","index":355,"end_time":1331.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1325.249,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Totally.","index":356,"end_time":1331.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1331.37,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Get wet blog.","index":357,"end_time":1333.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I just.","index":358,"end_time":1333.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, just wanted to give you that disclaimer.","index":359,"end_time":1336.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like, even if you Google it now, they talk about how the click rate has just gotten so skewed with the way that tracking and linking is working.","index":360,"end_time":1344.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But.","index":361,"end_time":1344.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1344.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, I can provide that so you can have additional data.","index":362,"end_time":1348.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1345.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":363,"end_time":1349.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1348.7,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then on that same vein, is it possible.","index":364,"end_time":1355.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1350.94,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I''ve been talking just this morning to my manager about, you know, the contract and all this going on.","index":365,"end_time":1361.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1355.34,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"She is really curious to see some sort of like a delivery plan that includes like goals for lead delivery and just what we have envisioned for the next.","index":366,"end_time":1372.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1362.83,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think the contract is now running through the end of March, so for the next three months.","index":367,"end_time":1377.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1373.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, it could be some kind of like milestone plan that you could provide that would be really helpful to share with her.","index":368,"end_time":1383.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1377.31,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":369,"end_time":1384.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1383.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"What I''m doing with a couple of my clients.","index":370,"end_time":1386.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, just to backtrack, I know we went back and forth on leads and things like that, the four of us, when Paul was here about what would work best.","index":371,"end_time":1393.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1386.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then before we launched a new campaign, we had deposit.","index":372,"end_time":1397.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1393.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I think that.","index":373,"end_time":1398.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1397.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think I put that in my last slide.","index":374,"end_time":1399.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1398.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think it''d be good to align on goals in the specifics.","index":375,"end_time":1402.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1399.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Once we get back together in January, I think it might be beneficial if we extend our meeting to an hour.","index":376,"end_time":1407.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1402.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If that works for you.","index":377,"end_time":1408.859,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t know if you have time after this meeting.","index":378,"end_time":1410.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1408.859,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Typically, we can just keep the same meeting time.","index":379,"end_time":1412.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1410.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m doing that with a couple of my other clients the first week back in January, and we''re extending meeting to an hour to go through goals, what we want to see in the upcoming quarter or year.","index":380,"end_time":1421.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1412.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can definitely do that.","index":381,"end_time":1423,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1421.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll come with some ideas, and then if you have anything additional, we can do that.","index":382,"end_time":1427.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1423.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I can put it into, like, a document for you so you can send it along with your manager.","index":383,"end_time":1432.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1427.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I think that might just be beneficial if we all work together and we''ll come with some things as far as goals and abm.","index":384,"end_time":1437.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1432.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then if you want to share any specific goals, too, for your side and your team, and then we can put it into like a, like, PDF or whatever would be best to share with your boss.","index":385,"end_time":1447.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be great.","index":386,"end_time":1448.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1447.49,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":387,"end_time":1449.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1448.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me just.","index":388,"end_time":1451.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1450.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I logged me out, but I''m just gonna look at this.","index":389,"end_time":1454.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1451.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I think that would be the eighth because the next Thursday.","index":390,"end_time":1459.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1455.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So do you want me to go ahead and extend that meeting to an hour?","index":391,"end_time":1462.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1459.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Would that work?","index":392,"end_time":1463.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1462.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Please do.","index":393,"end_time":1464.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1463.57,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yep.","index":394,"end_time":1464.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1464.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":395,"end_time":1465.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1464.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I will do that after this.","index":396,"end_time":1466.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1465.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can just get some brainstorming.","index":397,"end_time":1468.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1466.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":398,"end_time":1470.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1470.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And get that all together.","index":399,"end_time":1471.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1470.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But definitely would love to align and make sure we''re on the same page going in 2026.","index":400,"end_time":1476.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1471.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":401,"end_time":1477.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1476.85,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And if you guys can share, like, I can kind of share right now what we''re thinking goals wise.","index":402,"end_time":1481.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1477.33,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":403,"end_time":1482.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1481.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think before we had talked about about 50 leads a month, I think was sort of our target.","index":404,"end_time":1488.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1482.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''d love to hear from you guys what you think is realistic in terms of what activity those 50 leads have done.","index":405,"end_time":1496.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1488.85,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know we''re tracking that in our Excel sheet, which is awesome.","index":406,"end_time":1499.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1496.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":407,"end_time":1500.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But, like, how many of those leads will be ready to be passed off to sales in your experience?","index":408,"end_time":1506.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1500.9,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like, based on, you know, the messaging that we have and our tweaking, obviously, so makes it a little more difficult to predict.","index":409,"end_time":1513.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1506.82,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But just what you have seen and what we can expect realistically, just so that I can share that with my manager so that her expectations are set too.","index":410,"end_time":1522.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1513.74,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":411,"end_time":1524.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1523.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I do know that originally in the deck that Tristan had presented when we kicked off together, I think there was one of the goals was to the brand awareness or leads gener or contacts generated was one of the goals that we had shared in that marketing deck.","index":412,"end_time":1541.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1524.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we can also send all of these to before our meeting, so you can review.","index":413,"end_time":1545.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But.","index":414,"end_time":1545.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1545.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I think we talked about with you, Paula and Bailey, we talked about changing that goal to be more lead based generation from the ABM campaign.","index":415,"end_time":1554.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1546.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I definitely do think we need to make it more definitive and I think that''s what we were on track to do and then we had to pause the ABM campaign and change some things.","index":416,"end_time":1561.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1554.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So yes, also something just internally we''ve revamped our ABM process and we''re launching it in January hopefully.","index":417,"end_time":1568.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1561.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we have a couple of new ideas and just with the way that everything is working with AI and tech, the way that we''re doing everything like across marketing, not just here is changing.","index":418,"end_time":1579.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1568.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so we''re trying to keep up to date with how to be most successful in delivery and leads because just now with all the changes to technology, we want to make sure that we''re staying ahead of the curve with different things because the way we did ABM six months ago is different now and we want to always stay ahead of that.","index":419,"end_time":1596.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1579.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So yeah, so there''s a lot of new ideas coming down to me from our management team too on abm.","index":420,"end_time":1601.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1596.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''ll be perfect timing too in January.","index":421,"end_time":1603.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1601.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we''re going to get trained on a couple of new things there but.","index":422,"end_time":1607.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1604.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yes, as far as the goals and things like that.","index":423,"end_time":1610.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1607.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll sync with Bailey.","index":424,"end_time":1611.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1610.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We have a meeting on Monday together and I''m going to bring this up and see what we can come prepared with so we can come with our recommendations while also taking into account what your specific goals are.","index":425,"end_time":1620.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1611.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I think it''d be good to just like you said, put it on paper in a document so we can have it on both ends of what our goal is for the next three months of the running campaign.","index":426,"end_time":1629.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1620.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, absolutely.","index":427,"end_time":1631.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1629.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think for us the ultimate goal.","index":428,"end_time":1633.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631.04,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know we shared before we have like a new names goal.","index":429,"end_time":1635.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1633.04,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":430,"end_time":1637.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1636.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":431,"end_time":1637.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1637.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so right now that was very quantity focused and it''s.","index":432,"end_time":1641.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1637.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"There''s a tide that''s shifting now to being more quality focused, which I am all about.","index":433,"end_time":1646.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1641.61,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think.","index":434,"end_time":1646.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1646.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes, I think we probably all are.","index":435,"end_time":1648.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1646.49,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I think if we can use a goal of more like, like number of leads that are passed off to sales, number of leads that are ready for a conversation with sales, that would be a good metric for us to kind of align on there for a goal.","index":436,"end_time":1662.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1648.49,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":437,"end_time":1663.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1662.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And also what would determine what like data would determine that it was ready to be passed on to your sales team.","index":438,"end_time":1669.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because I know we have that leads dashboard that we''ve created which is tracking like how many sends and replies.","index":439,"end_time":1674.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1669.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can also talk about the quantitative side of things.","index":440,"end_time":1677.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1674.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"What would make it A lead that''s ready to get passed on to sales from your end.","index":441,"end_time":1681.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1677.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Whether it''s just a response or whether it''s certain actions that they''ve taken on the website.","index":442,"end_time":1685.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1682.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we can come with recommendations for those specific analytics too.","index":443,"end_time":1689.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1685.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":444,"end_time":1690.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1689.94,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":445,"end_time":1691.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1690.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So one of my other clients we for.","index":446,"end_time":1693.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1691.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We did the same thing with theirs where we defined what a lead was for them and they use HubSpot.","index":447,"end_time":1698.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1693.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it was like we defined a lead on a document.","index":448,"end_time":1700.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1698.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''s like a definition of a lead.","index":449,"end_time":1702.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1700.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The user takes X amount of actions or they respond to this and it''s like a and or kind of statement thing and then we have the definitive lead in there and so you can kind of add different aspects of it too.","index":450,"end_time":1714.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1702.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''s not just one thing.","index":451,"end_time":1715.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1714.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We want to make sure that there''s and.","index":452,"end_time":1717.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1715.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or.","index":453,"end_time":1717.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1717.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or different qualities too.","index":454,"end_time":1719.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1717.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''s not just if they respond but if it''s a.","index":455,"end_time":1721.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1719.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"They''re interacting with our links a lot and we see that there''s a lot of clicks.","index":456,"end_time":1724.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1721.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So yeah, we can definitely make sure that that''s definitive on both ends.","index":457,"end_time":1728.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1724.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":458,"end_time":1728.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1728.46,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If you guys have recommendations for what that looks like.","index":459,"end_time":1731.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1728.82,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be great to hear.","index":460,"end_time":1732.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1731.02,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"For us, the gold standard is definitely someone who responds and says like I''d love to hear more from a salesperson.","index":461,"end_time":1738.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1733.82,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s the best one.","index":462,"end_time":1741.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1738.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, love to see that one come through.","index":463,"end_time":1744.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Our sales team tends to not take like content downloads very seriously.","index":464,"end_time":1749.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1744.69,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''ll tell them this person downloaded two white papers and they''re like why am I going to spend my time reaching out to that lead?","index":465,"end_time":1754.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1749.05,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":466,"end_time":1755.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1755.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Then it would definitely be beneficial that we update our sequence to make it more like you said, conversational and offer based instead of currently it''s brand awareness.","index":467,"end_time":1764.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1755.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":468,"end_time":1764.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1764.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s where those downloads then you might not be getting the results that we''re trying to.","index":469,"end_time":1768.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1764.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I think it would be beneficial to change that and even better change it according to each audience group that we have.","index":470,"end_time":1775.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1768.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":471,"end_time":1776.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1775.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, but we''ll definitely agreed work that out in our.","index":472,"end_time":1780.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1776.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Our meeting on the.","index":473,"end_time":1781.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1780.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Whatever I just said the 8th or 9th.","index":474,"end_time":1783.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1781.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":475,"end_time":1784.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1783.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you have another meeting right now or are you okay for a few more minutes?","index":476,"end_time":1787.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1784.86,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"No, I''m good actually.","index":477,"end_time":1788.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1787.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I have a couple, couple extra time.","index":478,"end_time":1790.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1788.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":479,"end_time":1791.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.78,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That sounds awesome.","index":480,"end_time":1792.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1791.3,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"For the 8th.","index":481,"end_time":1793.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1792.3,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think that''s a really good plan.","index":482,"end_time":1794.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1793.14,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"1.","index":483,"end_time":1796.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.96,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I have one more thing about the contract.","index":484,"end_time":1798.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1796.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I spoke to my manager this morning.","index":485,"end_time":1801.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1798.84,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know right now we have renewed at 60 points a month through the end of March, which is fine.","index":486,"end_time":1807.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1801.96,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We are considering how long we are able to engage with you guys for?","index":487,"end_time":1814.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1808.6,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just budgetary wise, we don''t want to cut the ABM shorter than any than three months at the very, very least.","index":488,"end_time":1822.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1814.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know that''s what you guys recommended and she totally understands that too.","index":489,"end_time":1825.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1822.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Ideally we would run through the end of April.","index":490,"end_time":1830.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1827.76,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I''m curious to hear from you guys and I know you probably have to discuss this with other people too.","index":491,"end_time":1836.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1831.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But if we could extend the contract for one month past when it''s ending right now and then at that point at the end of April, how difficult would it be to at that point evaluate and say, you know, can we continue at that point the contract will be ended.","index":492,"end_time":1854.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1836.48,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Right, because we wouldn''t have.","index":493,"end_time":1855.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1854.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But at that point can we say like we want to continue for another month, two months, how difficult would that be to arrange?","index":494,"end_time":1864.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1856.52,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll have to take that back to internal team.","index":495,"end_time":1867.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1865,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t do anything with the contracts.","index":496,"end_time":1868.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1867.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m just the account manager for you guys.","index":497,"end_time":1870.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1868.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So and some other of my clients but on the Bailey and our leadership team do all the contract stuff.","index":498,"end_time":1876.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1870.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I will send this over to them and see about those specifics.","index":499,"end_time":1880.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1876.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But on my end I don''t know anything about that.","index":500,"end_time":1882.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1880.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":501,"end_time":1883,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1882.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, yes, I will send the specifics of your request for the extending the contract out for an additional month there.","index":502,"end_time":1889.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1883.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And yeah, if we change the sequence 2 for the ABM campaign, we want to make sure that new sequence can run like you said for those three months from January to March.","index":503,"end_time":1898.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1891.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, I will share that with our internal team and make sure leadership gets it.","index":504,"end_time":1902.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1899.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And yes, is there a definitive time you need an answer back about that?","index":505,"end_time":1906.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1902.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Ideally the second week of January we are drafting the notice of cancellation since I know there is the 45 day leeway that we have to provide that by.","index":506,"end_time":1917.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1907.85,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So we''ll be drafting that to send that out before, before whenever, 45 days before the end of marches just to.","index":507,"end_time":1923.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1917.66,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I got covered.","index":508,"end_time":1925.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1923.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But with that said, ideally we would like to extend for just one more month.","index":509,"end_time":1930.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1926.34,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So.","index":510,"end_time":1930.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1930.26,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, I''ll pass that along to Bailey and the rest of the leadership team too and we''ll get back to when we know that answer but looking forward to to doing more specifics for the ABM campaign since that''s our main focus and it''s good to have to a main focus so we can put all our efforts towards it.","index":511,"end_time":1949.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1930.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I think like you said it''s a good idea to break it up like we originally had planned.","index":512,"end_time":1953.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1949.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I know there''s a couple of bumps in the road.","index":513,"end_time":1956.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1953.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But now that we''re kind of on track, I think it''d be good to reevaluate our messaging sequence and make sure that runs for a good three months solid.","index":514,"end_time":1963.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1956.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Even though this brand awareness one is running right now, it''s a good opportunity still for people to see the name come across their screens.","index":515,"end_time":1969.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1964.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then if they get a new email with a different offer, then they''re already familiar with your brand, which is also a positive.","index":516,"end_time":1975.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1969.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, yes, completely.","index":517,"end_time":1977.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1975.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, on the 8th, we''ll come prepared.","index":518,"end_time":1979.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1978.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''ll be a good meeting and we''ll go over all these things and I''ll send a recap here too, after this to your teams, just so we can keep everything on track.","index":519,"end_time":1987.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1979.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know you''ve been keeping notes, but just.","index":520,"end_time":1989.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1987.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So on our end that we come prepared for the eighth, but that would be great.","index":521,"end_time":1995.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1989.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":522,"end_time":1996.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1995.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":523,"end_time":1996.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1996.17,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And as far as the video goes, I think whether or not we can make the additional changes just depends on next year, like what our points balances that we have.","index":524,"end_time":2008.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1997.17,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know we said like 54 points to run ABM.","index":525,"end_time":2010.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2008.27,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":526,"end_time":2011.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2011.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t really have a good answer for you right now on whether we can continue.","index":527,"end_time":2014.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2011.83,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think it might depend on if we can use some of those points across the three months.","index":528,"end_time":2019.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2015.19,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"This.","index":529,"end_time":2020.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2019.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"What is it, six points per month to put towards that and how that shakes out.","index":530,"end_time":2024.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2020.15,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So you''re talking about the video?","index":531,"end_time":2025.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2024.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, the 25 points we need to make the additional changes.","index":532,"end_time":2031.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2027.37,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, well, the changes are already implemented.","index":533,"end_time":2034.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2031.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s the new version we sent you that we''re waiting on the feedback for.","index":534,"end_time":2040.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2035.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we went through and made all the changes to the colors and the cuts, and that was the most recent one.","index":535,"end_time":2047.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2040.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So there was another round of edits or another round of recommendations from Stan on our design team.","index":536,"end_time":2054.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2048.25,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think I shared those with you guys.","index":537,"end_time":2056.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2055.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And Bailey came back and said to implement these changes would be another 25 points.","index":538,"end_time":2060.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2056.61,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That was after the most recent one we sent.","index":539,"end_time":2063.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2061.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I believe so, yeah.","index":540,"end_time":2065.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2064.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"His feedback came to me on December 4th and he said, I only see plan on brand colors and no natural colors.","index":541,"end_time":2073.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2065.81,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The background is too white and gray.","index":542,"end_time":2077.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2075.81,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Don''t use the green bar as a split screen.","index":543,"end_time":2080.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2078.53,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And remove the arc in the outro and the cta.","index":544,"end_time":2083.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2081.01,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I don''t see that in teams.","index":545,"end_time":2089.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2088.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Was that a.","index":546,"end_time":2089.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2089.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Was that an email?","index":547,"end_time":2090.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2090.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Don''t think so.","index":548,"end_time":2093.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2093.02,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Let me go back and look for it and then I can re.","index":549,"end_time":2096.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2093.94,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know a couple of.","index":550,"end_time":2098.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2097.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like when we originally all sat down and you had said like the natural colors and we moved like a plant and we changed.","index":551,"end_time":2107.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2098.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Remember the guy''s legs were weird.","index":552,"end_time":2108.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2107.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":553,"end_time":2109.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2108.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We made all of those adjustments.","index":554,"end_time":2110.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2109.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know you did.","index":555,"end_time":2111.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2111.19,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And you got back to us with that video.","index":556,"end_time":2113.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2111.87,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And we''ve paid for those changes already, right?","index":557,"end_time":2116.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2113.67,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I believe so.","index":558,"end_time":2117.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2117.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m trying to see if there''s anything, because on December 3, you had said you sent the video to Roderick for review.","index":559,"end_time":2127.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2117.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then after that, I don''t see anything else in here about the video.","index":560,"end_time":2131.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2128.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Maybe it was in a meeting that I shared that with you because it was December 4th that I got the email from the team.","index":561,"end_time":2138.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2132.95,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m not sure because Bailey definitely responded with how many additional points it would be.","index":562,"end_time":2149.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2142.54,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think just so on my end of things, from what I''m getting from this.","index":563,"end_time":2155.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2150.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So the original edits that you had brought us with all those changes, and we were like, I''m not sure if you guys can do this.","index":564,"end_time":2162.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2155.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''re kind of changing the whole design and look.","index":565,"end_time":2165.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2162.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That was what those additional 25 points were.","index":566,"end_time":2167.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2165.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"When we changed the colors and the.","index":567,"end_time":2169.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2167.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We fixed the way the guy was sitting.","index":568,"end_time":2171.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2169.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That was a heavy lift for our team.","index":569,"end_time":2173.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2171.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That was like a couple days worth of work.","index":570,"end_time":2175.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2173.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that was where that 25 points came in.","index":571,"end_time":2177.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2175.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":572,"end_time":2177.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2177.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Because I don''t see anything else because I had.","index":573,"end_time":2180.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2177.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I had sent you that message after that.","index":574,"end_time":2182.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2180.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":575,"end_time":2184.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2183.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I see what you.","index":576,"end_time":2185.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2184.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That was the 25 points.","index":577,"end_time":2186.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2185.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s already, like.","index":578,"end_time":2187.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2186.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If you go into Pulse, you''ll see that the.","index":579,"end_time":2189.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2187.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let see what it''s titled.","index":580,"end_time":2192.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2191,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just so I can tell you.","index":581,"end_time":2193.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2192.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The project is titled Develop final cut of Product Walkthrough Video.","index":582,"end_time":2201.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2194.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you''ll see right now that has the 25 points attached to it.","index":583,"end_time":2205.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2202.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that was for all those edits that we did.","index":584,"end_time":2209.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2205.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Now the new ones you''re talking about, I don''t see in teams or remember that.","index":585,"end_time":2213.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2209.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":586,"end_time":2215.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2214.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that.","index":587,"end_time":2215.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2215.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t think we would have an additional 25 points if there was more edits.","index":588,"end_time":2220.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2215.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because a couple of the ones you just said don''t sound like a complete revamp.","index":589,"end_time":2223.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2220.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":590,"end_time":2224.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2223.73,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And we expected a couple more from the new cut.","index":591,"end_time":2226.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2224.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And that''s just part of like that same 25 point task.","index":592,"end_time":2230.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2227.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''s not like it''ll be additional 25 on top of the 25, if that makes sense.","index":593,"end_time":2234.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2230.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":594,"end_time":2235.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2234.77,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So the 25 points.","index":595,"end_time":2236.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2235.33,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We haven''t incurred that charge yet.","index":596,"end_time":2239.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2237.81,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Because you haven''t built out.","index":597,"end_time":2240.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2239.49,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It was just the storyboard that was built out.","index":598,"end_time":2242.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2240.77,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Right.","index":599,"end_time":2243.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2242.85,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So the 25 points would be to re.","index":600,"end_time":2246.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2243.59,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"To redo the past.","index":601,"end_time":2249.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2246.95,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The storyboard.","index":602,"end_time":2250.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2249.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The final cut, I guess you call it.","index":603,"end_time":2252.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2251.03,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":604,"end_time":2253.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2253.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we on the.","index":605,"end_time":2258.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2254.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me see here.","index":606,"end_time":2260.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2259.349,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"On the 20th of November, I sent it back to our creative director and asked how many of the changes we can implement.","index":607,"end_time":2269.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2262.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because we talked about the colors for the brand, changing the animations.","index":608,"end_time":2275.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2269.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We added the facial expressions because the faces were blank.","index":609,"end_time":2278.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2275.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we did that and then we went ahead and gave that to our team the end of November.","index":610,"end_time":2286.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2278.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So the 28th.","index":611,"end_time":2287.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2286.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then they finished it on the 1st and I sent it over to, I think on the first as well.","index":612,"end_time":2293.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2287.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So those were really heavy edits, which was the 25 points that we charge for those edits.","index":613,"end_time":2300.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2293.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It wasn''t marked delivered yet because that task was technically finished in December.","index":614,"end_time":2305.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2301.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''ll get marked delivered at the end of December.","index":615,"end_time":2308.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2305.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you''ll see that as a delivered task.","index":616,"end_time":2310.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2308.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But when we send edits, we still want to do a final cut for you and leave room for any additional edits.","index":617,"end_time":2318.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2310.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I hope this is making sense, but it''s all one task.","index":618,"end_time":2322.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2319.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So like the 25 points, it''s all part of the task where we made those edits.","index":619,"end_time":2326.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2322.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''re going to make a final audio design master, give you the final cut, implement any additional edits that are needed after this last round.","index":620,"end_time":2333.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2327.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So no additional points will be charged for the final final cut.","index":621,"end_time":2337.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2333.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Any small edits that you have.","index":622,"end_time":2339.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2337.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like you just said, if there''s a couple additional things where colors need to be changed, that''s all part of the same 25 point task because we changed pretty much the entire way that thing looked.","index":623,"end_time":2348.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2339.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s why those 25 points were added.","index":624,"end_time":2350.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2348.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if you have some small additional edits, if you want to send those to me now, I can get them to our team and we can come up with the final video.","index":625,"end_time":2359.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2352.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And that''s all part of that one task.","index":626,"end_time":2361.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2359.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":627,"end_time":2362.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2362.08,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":628,"end_time":2363.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2362.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sorry if it''s kind of all over, but it''s not an additional 25 and then another 25 if you have more edits.","index":629,"end_time":2369.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2364.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":630,"end_time":2370.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2370.08,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I think my.","index":631,"end_time":2372.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2370.68,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":632,"end_time":2373.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2372.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I am surprised because I thought that I had asked how much it would be to change the video before any changes were made.","index":633,"end_time":2385.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2375.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If I had known it would be an additional 25 points just to do the storyboard, I think we would have.","index":634,"end_time":2389.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2385.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Held off for the edits that we just did.","index":635,"end_time":2393.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2389.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":636,"end_time":2394.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2393.69,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We''re talking about the same edits, right?","index":637,"end_time":2395.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2394.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The new version where we change the color and things like that.","index":638,"end_time":2398.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2395.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":639,"end_time":2399.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2398.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yep.","index":640,"end_time":2399.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2399.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":641,"end_time":2400.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2399.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I didn''t.","index":642,"end_time":2401.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2400.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":643,"end_time":2402.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2401.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m not sure as far as communication wise if we can do that.","index":644,"end_time":2407.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2402.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But again, I. I''m not in charge of determining point, so I can send this to Bailey.","index":645,"end_time":2412.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2407.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can Let her know just to look at the transcript here too, and see what we can do.","index":646,"end_time":2416.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2412.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But did you not want those edits made at all?","index":647,"end_time":2418.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2416.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like, did you not want to finish the video?","index":648,"end_time":2422.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2420.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because the.","index":649,"end_time":2422.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2422.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The whole point of this was to give you a good deliverable of a.","index":650,"end_time":2425.589,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2422.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Of a video that you guys could use.","index":651,"end_time":2427.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2425.589,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s why we made the edits, because we weren''t going to not make the edits.","index":652,"end_time":2431.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2428.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I. I think it just totally depends on price.","index":653,"end_time":2436.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2433.31,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So if you had known it would be an additional 2500 to even storyboard it, I think we would have said, like, let''s hold off until we were sure that that could fit into our points budget.","index":654,"end_time":2448.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2436.99,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But now we kind of have to move forward.","index":655,"end_time":2452.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2450.7,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Right.","index":656,"end_time":2452.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2452.38,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Let me.","index":657,"end_time":2453.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2453.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me talk with the leadership team.","index":658,"end_time":2455.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2453.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like I said, I don''t have anything to do with the point specific.","index":659,"end_time":2457.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2455.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if that''s something you''re concerned about and you guys may not want to complete the video, then since we haven''t delivered a final cut yet, I can talk to them about the specifics of that.","index":660,"end_time":2467.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2457.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But the most recent edits were just heavy edits.","index":661,"end_time":2471.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2468.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s why we said, you know, we''re going to do the 25 points charge to complete the project, but I can talk to them about potentially changing that.","index":662,"end_time":2480.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2471.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If you don''t want to complete the project, Obviously we want to complete the project for you, but if that''s something you''re concerned about, I can get with Bailey and we can talk about it.","index":663,"end_time":2487.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2480.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So is that kind of what you''re thinking, that you don''t want us to continue the project or it''s just depending on everything as far as points?","index":664,"end_time":2495.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2488.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And finishing it will completely depend on points.","index":665,"end_time":2498.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2495.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I think ideally, if we could put a pin in those 25 points and moving forward until we''re sure that it fits into our budget for the next three months, that would be ideal.","index":666,"end_time":2508.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2499,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I would love to finish it.","index":667,"end_time":2510.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2508.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I just don''t know whether I can get approval to go above and beyond, you know, our 60 budget.","index":668,"end_time":2516.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2510.28,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":669,"end_time":2518.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2517.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And you said you got edits back from the latest edit we sent the V2?","index":670,"end_time":2522.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2518.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I did, yep.","index":671,"end_time":2523.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2522.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you want to share those with us since I don''t see them in teams, or do you want to hold off on everything until I can share them with you?","index":672,"end_time":2530.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2524.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just as long as.","index":673,"end_time":2532.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2531.86,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just don''t act on them.","index":674,"end_time":2535.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2534.18,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"No.","index":675,"end_time":2536.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2535.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we won''t.","index":676,"end_time":2536.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2536.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We won''t do any more edits until we know.","index":677,"end_time":2538.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2536.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But you don''t even have to share them.","index":678,"end_time":2540.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2538.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m just making sure we''re on the same page because we sent the whole new version with the complete revamp of the video, but I don''t remember getting any edits or see them here additionally.","index":679,"end_time":2549.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2540.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So confusion maybe.","index":680,"end_time":2552.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2550.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I just want to make sure.","index":681,"end_time":2553.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2552.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think when I heard that it was going to be 25 additional points to make the edits, I didn''t share the second round.","index":682,"end_time":2559.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2554.16,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, I think I see your computer.","index":683,"end_time":2561.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2559.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you thought that the edits that we never got would be the 25 points, not the.","index":684,"end_time":2567.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2561.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The revamp that we had already done of the complete overhaul.","index":685,"end_time":2570.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2567.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, I thought.","index":686,"end_time":2572,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2570.96,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I thought to implement the edits in the storyboard into the full video, that would be the 25 points.","index":687,"end_time":2577.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2572,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes, we did do that.","index":688,"end_time":2580.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2579.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We changed the storyboard with the new colors in the storyboard.","index":689,"end_time":2584.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2580.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But you didn''t build out the full video from.","index":690,"end_time":2586.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2584.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That''s what I sent you last.","index":691,"end_time":2588.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2586.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s the frame link, the full video, the new colors and the animations, the facial expressions.","index":692,"end_time":2595.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2588.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We did send that to you.","index":693,"end_time":2596.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2595.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s the frame link, but not the full executed animated video.","index":694,"end_time":2601.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2596.41,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Right.","index":695,"end_time":2601.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2601.21,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That is what the frame link is like in frame.","index":696,"end_time":2606.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2602.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I sent you the animated video.","index":697,"end_time":2607.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2606.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Can you share that again?","index":698,"end_time":2609.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2608.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, Sorry.","index":699,"end_time":2625.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2609.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The markup link.","index":700,"end_time":2626.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2625.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You''re talking about the frame link.","index":701,"end_time":2628.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2626.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":702,"end_time":2630.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2629.96,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Wait a second.","index":703,"end_time":2631.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2630.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Backup.","index":704,"end_time":2631.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2631.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This is so many steps.","index":705,"end_time":2634.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2633.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":706,"end_time":2635.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2634.76,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We did the original animations for the creative graphics, changing the updates, and then we sent you the.","index":707,"end_time":2643.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2635.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The markup link to check to make sure that the project looked good before animation.","index":708,"end_time":2653.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2645.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":709,"end_time":2654.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2653.56,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So that''s what I am surprised about is that that was the 25 points to make the markup changes.","index":710,"end_time":2659.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2654.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes, that''s in the task currently, but it''s not been checked complete.","index":711,"end_time":2665.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2661.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":712,"end_time":2666.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2665.96,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Therefore it''s not been charged.","index":713,"end_time":2667.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2666.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, so the 25 points is creating the full video.","index":714,"end_time":2672.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2668.12,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":715,"end_time":2674.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2673.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":716,"end_time":2675,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2674.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Sorry if that got lost here in translation.","index":717,"end_time":2677,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2675.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The edits that we sent you in the storyboard were done and that was a heavy lift.","index":718,"end_time":2683.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2677.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Now, as far as the actual.","index":719,"end_time":2686.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2683.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Execution of that, we haven''t checked it off yet.","index":720,"end_time":2695.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2691.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Which is why you don''t see the points balance, because it''s still technically in progress.","index":721,"end_time":2699.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2695.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But let me just double check here.","index":722,"end_time":2701.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2700.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thanks for bearing with me.","index":723,"end_time":2705.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2704.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know there''s a lot of steps here.","index":724,"end_time":2706.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2705.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me just double check.","index":725,"end_time":2710.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2708.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":726,"end_time":2726.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2726.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if we.","index":727,"end_time":2727.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2726.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If you wanted to move forward with the animation style, then we would give that full 25 points and execute.","index":728,"end_time":2737.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2727.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And do it.","index":729,"end_time":2738.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2737.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But you''re saying you guys saw the storyboard and have edits to the still images.","index":730,"end_time":2745.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2738.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":731,"end_time":2746.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2745.9,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":732,"end_time":2747.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2746.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":733,"end_time":2748.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2747.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So like I said, we haven''t charged the 25 points yet because it hasn''t been completed.","index":734,"end_time":2752.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2749.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if you.","index":735,"end_time":2753.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2752.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are you saying you don''t like that number necessarily and you wouldn''t want to move forward because it may not fit into the budget.","index":736,"end_time":2759.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2753.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":737,"end_time":2760.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2759.9,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yep.","index":738,"end_time":2761.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2760.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":739,"end_time":2761.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2761.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we.","index":740,"end_time":2761.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2761.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We would just need to.","index":741,"end_time":2762.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2761.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Since we already did the work of changing the animations, I would just have to get with the team and see what they would charge for just those and not implementing them into the final cut, and then we can work from there.","index":742,"end_time":2774.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2762.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I''m not sure what that''ll be.","index":743,"end_time":2777.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2775.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like I said, I don''t determine points, but I can check with Bailey and see, because obviously, since we did all that work, we do want to give you the final deliverable, but I can double check with the team on the specifics.","index":744,"end_time":2790.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2777.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":745,"end_time":2791.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2790.5,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":746,"end_time":2792.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2792.02,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And I think if I had known that this storyboard itself would be.","index":747,"end_time":2796.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2792.42,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"No, that it''s.","index":748,"end_time":2799.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2798.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it''s not just for the storyboard.","index":749,"end_time":2801.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2799.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It would be the whole project.","index":750,"end_time":2802.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2801.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So when you see it, like in Pulse, if you go in the develop final Cut product walkthrough video, the entire task is 25 points.","index":751,"end_time":2809.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2802.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I understand, but what you''re saying that the storyboard itself is still a cost.","index":752,"end_time":2813.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2809.5,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So if I had known that, we might not have moved forward with this.","index":753,"end_time":2816.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2813.42,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I get what you''re saying.","index":754,"end_time":2817.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2816.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":755,"end_time":2818.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2817.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I didn''t realize that that would be the case.","index":756,"end_time":2820.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2818.38,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I thought the storyboard was sort of like the trial to see if we wanted to move forward.","index":757,"end_time":2824.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2820.76,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":758,"end_time":2826,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2825.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The heavy, heaviest lift is actually the storyboard because we create the individual stills.","index":759,"end_time":2831.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2826,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So these.","index":760,"end_time":2833.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2831.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"These here.","index":761,"end_time":2837.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2836.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So these graphics.","index":762,"end_time":2838.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2837.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This is what takes a lot of time, is because the team redid the colors and added the facial expressions change.","index":763,"end_time":2847.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2839.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like.","index":764,"end_time":2848.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2847.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like, this is the hard part, because they basically are working with a template, and then they customize the template.","index":765,"end_time":2853.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2848.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So then when they do the animation, it''s just putting those in or putting those stills into, like, the working file.","index":766,"end_time":2860.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2853.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then they.","index":767,"end_time":2861.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2860.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That also takes a lot of time.","index":768,"end_time":2862.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2861.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But the actual.","index":769,"end_time":2863.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2862.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This is the most important step of any video because we want to make sure that the way it looks is correct before we animate it, because the animation also takes a lot of time.","index":770,"end_time":2872.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2863.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But to make sure the storyboard is approved is, like, number one priority for a video.","index":771,"end_time":2877.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2872.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I hear what you''re saying, and I will get with Bailey and we can.","index":772,"end_time":2881.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2877.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can talk through that.","index":773,"end_time":2882.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2881.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But.","index":774,"end_time":2882.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2882.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But anyway, going forward, if you guys could just let us know what the cost will be for everything we want to do before you execute on it so that we can approve that before you actually do it, that will be really important.","index":775,"end_time":2895.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2884.06,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":776,"end_time":2897.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2896.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":777,"end_time":2898.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2897.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think with this video just, you know, like we did with the original animation, because the original storyboard was approved and we animated it and created a full video.","index":778,"end_time":2909.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2898.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That alone is a.","index":779,"end_time":2910.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2909.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is a heavy project and an expensive project, our video projects.","index":780,"end_time":2914.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2910.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And basically because we redid the entire video, that''s where that cost is coming from, because it''s basically starting new with a new storyboard and everything like that.","index":781,"end_time":2922.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2914.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But, yeah, if there''s any miscommunication on whether or not to execute those, we will.","index":782,"end_time":2928.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2923.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We will make sure in the future.","index":783,"end_time":2929.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2928.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We have, you know, double confirm with you before executing any adjustments.","index":784,"end_time":2933.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2929.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I will get with Bailey on the specifics.","index":785,"end_time":2935.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2933.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so it sounds like from your end, you want to wait to do anything else until you have, like, the number for the whole project of edits.","index":786,"end_time":2945.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2935.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, I can get with her.","index":787,"end_time":2948.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2946.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m going to try to sync with her right after this.","index":788,"end_time":2950.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2949.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think she might have some availability.","index":789,"end_time":2952.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2951.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll check.","index":790,"end_time":2953.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2952.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can get back to you on that, because if.","index":791,"end_time":2955.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2953.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we are able to get that executed, I''d like to try to get that to you as soon as possible just so we can have the final video and the new edits and things like that that we didn''t see come through.","index":792,"end_time":2963.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2955.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I will get with her on that and I''ll get back to you.","index":793,"end_time":2966.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2963.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But, yes, a lot of different steps for this one.","index":794,"end_time":2969.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2967.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So thanks for sticking with me on the specifics, but I know we did a lot of edits and we have all these different tasks open, so I was trying to make sure.","index":795,"end_time":2977.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2969.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I didn''t want to hang up with you.","index":796,"end_time":2979.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2977.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I wanted to try to make sure I understood.","index":797,"end_time":2980.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2979.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":798,"end_time":2981.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2981.14,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":799,"end_time":2982.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2982.18,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"No, I appreciate you looking into that.","index":800,"end_time":2984.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2982.54,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And I know it was a lot of edits on our side, too.","index":801,"end_time":2986.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2984.02,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That was unexpected for all of us.","index":802,"end_time":2988.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2986.1,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I do appreciate you guys looking into, you know, how much that would be.","index":803,"end_time":2993.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2988.26,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So just let me know what the rest of the project will be in total, taking into account that we do have a few more edits to the storyboard.","index":804,"end_time":3001.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2993.54,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If you can let me know the final quote for before we decide whether we can move forward or not, that would be great.","index":805,"end_time":3006.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3001.74,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":806,"end_time":3007.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3006.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":807,"end_time":3008.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3007.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":808,"end_time":3008.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3008.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I appreciate your questions and everything, because ultimately, at the end of the day, we want to be here for you and make your life easier and deliver these things that you can utilize at your company.","index":809,"end_time":3016.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3008.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So however we can make that work, we want to so on.","index":810,"end_time":3020.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3016.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"On the specifics and numbers.","index":811,"end_time":3021.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3020.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s not my area, but I will talk with leadership and get back to you.","index":812,"end_time":3025.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3021.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we definitely want to make it work.","index":813,"end_time":3026.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3025.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think the video looks really cool right now.","index":814,"end_time":3028.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3026.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if we''re able to get it perfect where we need it to be, we want to do that for you.","index":815,"end_time":3032.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3028.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yes.","index":816,"end_time":3034.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3033.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":817,"end_time":3035.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3035.24,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":818,"end_time":3036.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3036.04,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"All right, so you''ll send a recap of everything on your side that you guys are working on right after this call.","index":819,"end_time":3043.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3037.72,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And I will.","index":820,"end_time":3045,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3043.88,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''ll read that and I''ll get back to you on anything you need from me.","index":821,"end_time":3048.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3045.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":822,"end_time":3049.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3048.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thanks, Lauren.","index":823,"end_time":3050.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3049.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And if I don''t talk to you in person again, I hope you have a really great Christmas.","index":824,"end_time":3053.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3050.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You, too.","index":825,"end_time":3054.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3053.48,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":826,"end_time":3054.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3054.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Bye.","index":827,"end_time":3055.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3055.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"See you in a couple of weeks.","index":828,"end_time":3056.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3055.6,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes, I''ll.","index":829,"end_time":3057.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3056.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"dateString":"2025-12-18T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KCM261TGX3VFMG7BQMMBZKEQ","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Proposed refining ABM messaging by role to drive higher-targeted engagement and lead quality.","Agreed to develop a new campaign in January featuring a survey-based offer to stimulate replies.","Taylor confirmed weekly ABM maintenance is on track with rising connection metrics and clean delivery.","Team aligned on goal of 50 qualified leads per month, shifting from content views to sales readiness.","Pending contract extension request through April to support multi-month ABM messaging revisions."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We want your ABM campaign to be successful so we''ll definitely work with you to make sure it is.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"quote":"Brand awareness is great, but I think we do need to start pushing a little bit more for like sales.","speaker":"Lauren Poirier"},{"quote":"We''ll come prepared next time with...examples from my other clients to show how that would work.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"topics":["ABM","delivery","lead_quality","contract","campaigns"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-19T14:38:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Campaign Performance and Optimization**\n\nThe ABM campaigns are steadily increasing connections, with brand awareness efforts ongoing but requiring more targeted messaging to boost engagement and lead quality (02:06).\n\n- **ABM connections are rising across all categories**, with the strongest performance in two key roles and campaigns, while other segments are catching up gradually (02:06).  \n    - Weekly maintenance ensures campaign delivery is smooth and volumes are optimized without risking LinkedIn account restrictions.  \n    - Three separate email sender domains help speed up outreach and avoid domain blocks, supporting consistent email flow through Lemlist (03:23).  \n    - LinkedIn messaging yields more responses than email, as LinkedIn’s personal approach fosters conversation, while emails mainly drive link clicks without replies (10:31).  \n    - Taylor emphasized caution to avoid blacklisting personal LinkedIn accounts by limiting daily outreach volumes (02:06).  \n\n- **Planned shift from brand awareness to more compelling offer-based messaging** targeted for mid-January aims to increase response rates and lead quality (03:23).  \n    - Taylor proposed evolving messaging from informational to conversational sequences ending in demo scheduling, based on successful tactics used for other clients (04:52).  \n    - Lauren requested examples of offers, highlighting limitations on discounts and preference for consultative or analytical incentives like free system or inventory analyses (05:13).  \n    - Taylor suggested short surveys or quick assessments to stimulate interest without heavy resource demands, aligning with Planon’s capabilities (06:21).  \n    - A separate, smaller campaign for a focused group of 20–50 universities can be created to limit demo requests and manage sales team capacity (07:27).  \n\n- **Audience targeting and messaging need refinement to improve relevance and engagement** (11:28).  \n    - Lauren flagged mismatches such as chief investment officers receiving maintenance-focused messaging, indicating need to adjust targeting or tailor messages per group (11:28).  \n    - Taylor agreed to segment messaging by the five defined audience groups, providing Lauren with detailed sequences for her to customize with Jay’s input (13:42).  \n    - Current broad messaging supports brand awareness but will be supplemented by targeted offer campaigns to re-engage contacts and drive sales conversations (16:48).  \n\n- **Ongoing campaign management includes weekly performance reviews and adaptive messaging adjustments without extra charge to optimize results within the existing 60 point monthly budget** (08:10).  \n    - Taylor assured that changes to messaging and minor interactive elements like surveys fit within current resources and points allocations (08:57).  \n    - The team monitors email open and click rates, acknowledging their limited accuracy but offering to provide these metrics weekly for transparency (21:04).  \n\n## **Lead Generation Goals and Sales Alignment**\n\nThere is a strategic pivot from quantity to quality of leads, with a focus on generating sales-ready leads rather than just brand awareness contacts (24:36).\n\n- **Target lead volume is approximately 50 leads per month, but emphasis is shifting to the number of leads ready for sales conversations** (24:42).  \n    - Lauren stressed the importance of leads that explicitly express interest in speaking with sales, as the sales team discounts low-value actions like content downloads (27:17).  \n    - Taylor proposed defining lead qualification criteria collaboratively, combining response behavior and website engagement metrics to identify sales-ready leads (27:42).  \n    - The team will develop a lead definition document with AND/OR logic to standardize qualification across marketing and sales teams (28:10).  \n\n- **A longer, extended meeting on January 8th will cover goal alignment, metrics, and ABM strategy updates to set clear expectations for the next quarter** (23:03).  \n    - Taylor will prepare recommendations incorporating new ABM approaches influenced by evolving AI and marketing technologies (26:36).  \n    - Lauren committed to sharing internal goals and refining target audiences to support focused outreach (24:36).  \n    - This meeting will enable formalizing a milestone plan aligned with contract timelines and business priorities (22:28).  \n\n## **Contract Extension and Budget Considerations**\n\nThe current ABM contract runs through March with a proposed one-month extension to April, pending internal approval and budget review (29:50).\n\n- **Lauren’s team prefers at least a three-month minimum engagement and hopes to extend one month past March, with cancellation notice due mid-January** (30:22).  \n    - Taylor will escalate the extension request to leadership and provide feedback before the cancellation deadline (31:05).  \n    - The contract extension would support running the refined ABM messaging sequence consistently through the first quarter (31:47).  \n    - Budget constraints are a key factor in finalizing contract length and scope of deliverables (29:50).  \n\n- **Points management is critical for balancing ongoing ABM activities and video production needs within the monthly 60-point budget** (33:16).  \n    - Lauren noted uncertainty about allocating 25 points for final video edits on top of ABM work (33:31).  \n    - Taylor explained that heavy video edits already performed justify the 25-point charge, but further small edits would be included without additional cost (36:17).  \n    - Lauren requested a full cost estimate before approving further video work to avoid budget overruns (40:33).  \n    - Taylor committed to clarifying costs with leadership and ensuring better upfront communication on charges going forward (48:04).  \n\n## **Video Production Status and Next Steps**\n\nVideo production is partially complete with significant storyboard and animation updates done, but final cut delivery is on hold pending budget clarity and approval (33:16).\n\n- **Major edits including color changes and facial animations were completed and represent the primary workload charged at 25 points, currently in progress but not yet finalized** (35:50).  \n    - Taylor clarified that the 25 points cover the entire edit and animation task, not just storyboard revisions (37:04).  \n    - Lauren was surprised by the cost structure and stressed the importance of prior cost estimates for budget management (46:58).  \n    - Taylor acknowledged the need for improved communication and committed to consulting leadership about potentially adjusting the charge or pausing work as requested (48:16).  \n\n- **Lauren has additional feedback on the storyboard but requested no further action until cost and budget are confirmed** (42:11).  \n    - Taylor confirmed no further edits will be made without explicit approval, ensuring budget control (42:15).  \n    - The team will provide a final quote for completing the video project inclusive of remaining requested changes before proceeding (49:41).  \n\n- **The video is intended as a key deliverable to support ABM efforts, and Taylor emphasized willingness to complete it if budget allows** (50:06).  \n    - Taylor plans to share a detailed recap and timeline covering both ABM and video project statuses immediately after the meeting (50:35).  \n\n## **ABM Advertising and Campaign Launch Timing**\n\nABM display ads are undergoing final design updates and will await approval before scheduling launch, likely in early January to align with audience attention patterns (19:30).\n\n- **Designs have been sent to the designer Lou with pending final approval from Roderick, expected by December 23rd** (19:30).  \n    - Launching ads will follow approval and a review by Stella, who is out the first week of January, potentially delaying the live date (20:07).  \n    - Taylor recommended launching the ads in the second week of January, aligning with audience availability post-holidays and maximizing campaign impact (20:25).  \n    - Staggered launch with ongoing email campaigns will maintain brand visibility while introducing new messaging sequences (20:25).","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing (ABM)","Campaign Messaging","Lead Generation","Video Production","Contract Extension","Audience Targeting"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaigns Growing:** Connections increasing across categories, best in key roles, necessitating targeted messaging for better engagement.\n\n- **Message Shift Planned:** Moving to offer-based messaging by mid-January to enhance response rates and lead quality.\n\n- **Refine Audience Targeting:** Adjust messaging for specific roles, improving relevance and maintaining engagement with defined audience groups.\n\n- **Quality Over Quantity:** Focusing on 50 sales-ready leads monthly, developing criteria to identify interested contacts for sales conversations.\n\n- **Contract Extension Proposal:** Seeking one-month extension past March for consistent ABM messaging, dependent on budget review.\n\n- **Video Production Delayed:** Major edits done, final delivery on hold pending budget approval; costs need clarification before proceeding.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nContinue weekly ABM campaign monitoring and update shared documents with new responses (03:00)\nWork with developers to improve email send rates without risking LinkedIn personal account blacklisting (03:00)\nPrepare new ABM messaging campaign options with conversational/offer-style sequences for January presentation (04:30)\nShare detailed ABM messaging sequences organized by audience group with Lauren, including contact lists (14:40)\nCoordinate with designer Lou and submit ABM ads for Roderick''s final approval by December 23, then prepare for Stella''s review (19:30)\nAdd email open and click rate metrics with explanation of data accuracy to weekly reports (21:00)\nExtend January meeting to 1 hour for strategic goal setting and planning (23:30)\nDiscuss lead qualification definitions with Bailey to align on lead handoff criteria and reporting (26:30)\nLiaise with leadership regarding contract extension request to April and communicate response by early January (31:00)\nVerify video project status and point allocations with internal team, delaying further edits until budget approval (42:00)\nSend meeting recap and updated deliverables to Lauren and her team (50:45)\n\n**Lauren Poirier**\nReview shared ABM messaging sequences and collaborate with Jay to refine target audiences and messaging per group (13:50)\nIdentify 20-50 top university targets for a potential limited offer campaign focusing on demos or consultations (16:00)\nShare latest video edits comments with Taylor but hold off on further execution pending budget clarity (41:00)\nDiscuss contract extension and budgeting internally and provide feedback in early January (32:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"31c6c4fd-9ca6-4b8c-b236-dccc4410a0a3","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
