WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'bf57e936-b322-4b36-bf32-174d44c65e09',
    '2025-12-19 17:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KC9Y82RC32RF4GSBRB3DAN4G',
    'Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Gab","Baylee Gunnell","Tim Finnigan","Baylee Gunnell","Igor Zagradjanin"}'::text[],
    981,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84384090979?pwd=CWYLaJlFxbjtxp2qyx0nk6skchlVVg.1',
    '{"id":"01KC9Y82RC32RF4GSBRB3DAN4G","title":"Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Marketing Metrics**\n\nThe team is seeing positive early results from targeted campaigns, reinforcing brand positioning and lead generation.\n\n- **The HR 2808 campaign has generated an upsell opportunity and strong search visibility, ranking on page one for related Google searches** (09:34)  \n    - This early traction confirms the campaign is effectively positioning the company ahead of competitors in the HR tech space.  \n    - Gab credited the teams for executing the campaign quickly, which helped seize first-mover advantage.  \n    - The campaign’s SEO strength directly supports lead generation and brand authority.  \n    - Continued focus on keyword targeting and retargeting will likely expand this momentum.\n\n- **The two ebooks collectively produced approximately 170 form fills, with the most recent email driving around 78 new leads** (10:35)  \n    - Tim noted these forms extend brand reach and attract quality prospects, validating the content strategy.  \n    - Gab will coordinate with Shannon to track conversion quality from these leads.  \n    - Email cadence and content are performing well, supporting ongoing nurture efforts.  \n    - This lead volume will inform future content marketing priorities and resource allocation.\n\n## **Podcast Production and Content Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to postpone the planned podcast compilation to ensure a polished, engaging final product that strengthens audience connection.\n\n- **Tim committed to producing a thoughtful 30–35 minute podcast compilation with improved intros and guest acknowledgments, targeting mid-January release** (03:09)  \n    - Tim emphasized quality over speed, aiming to craft a meaningful narrative that highlights recent episodes and guests.  \n    - Gab and Igor supported pausing the quick compilation to allow adequate time for scripting and editing.  \n    - This approach is expected to increase listener engagement and brand loyalty.  \n    - Tim will own the script development and coordinate production with Gab.\n\n- **A note was made to flag Pat Sullivan’s coughing incident during recording for editing, ensuring polished final audio** (11:14)  \n    - Igor confirmed this will be addressed during post-production to maintain professionalism.  \n    - This attention to detail reflects the team’s commitment to quality content.  \n    - Managing such production nuances will improve overall listener experience.  \n    - It also highlights the need for thorough review processes before release.\n\n## **Operational and Process Updates**\n\nThe team is streamlining campaign management and preparing for a quieter end-of-year period while planning for January ramp-up.\n\n- **Business Manager access will be added to the LinkedIn account to simplify ad approvals and speed campaign execution** (07:56)  \n    - Christina volunteered to lead the setup, improving operational efficiency.  \n    - This change will reduce delays caused by manual approval of individual requests.  \n    - It supports scaling paid media efforts with less administrative overhead.  \n    - Igor will provide the necessary Business Manager ID promptly post-meeting.\n\n- **January staffing availability was discussed, with noted overlapping vacation times to maintain coverage** (13:20)  \n    - Baylee and Igor flagged possible meeting reschedules due to planned absences.  \n    - Gab and Tim planned personal time off around January 9th, with backup coverage by Christina and Tim as needed.  \n    - The team will rely more on Slack communication during this period to maintain responsiveness.  \n    - This planning ensures continuity despite reduced capacity.\n\n## **2026 Strategy Planning and Business Vision**\n\nThe team is finalizing the 2026 strategy visualization to align on goals, themes, and engagement plans for the upcoming year.\n\n- **Gab is preparing a chronological, visual PowerPoint deck outlining 2025 metrics, learnings, and 2026 themes to clarify the yearly roadmap** (12:19)  \n    - The deck will help the team and partners align on priorities and timing.  \n    - This visual approach supports clearer communication and planning across stakeholders.  \n    - Baylee expressed eagerness to connect post-holidays to integrate support for new initiatives.  \n    - The strategy emphasizes building on 2025 successes while adapting to evolving market conditions.\n\n- **The team plans to resume active collaboration in mid-January following the holiday break** (12:56)  \n    - Baylee confirmed reconnecting after New Year to kick off new projects and goals.  \n    - This timing aligns with internal goal-setting cycles and resource planning.  \n    - Early visibility into strategy components will guide budget and staffing decisions.  \n    - The approach ensures momentum into 2026 while respecting end-of-year downtime.\n\n## **Technical Preparation and Equipment Setup**\n\nPreparation for upcoming podcast production includes dedicated time for technical training and equipment handling.\n\n- **Gab and Tim will attend a podcast event in Vegas in January to advance production skills and equipment knowledge** (13:51)  \n    - Gab is focusing on learning camera setup with a goal to master it by January 4th.  \n    - Equipment has been shipped and organized for travel, with logistics managed by Becky.  \n    - Baylee offered support for equipment training, enhancing cross-team capabilities.  \n    - This investment in skills development aims to raise production quality and team autonomy.\n\n- **Due to planned absences and new equipment setup, some January meetings may be rescheduled to maintain workflow** (14:00)  \n    - The team will rely on multiple members to cover essential tasks during absences.  \n    - Slack will be the primary communication channel to manage ad hoc needs.  \n    - This flexible approach balances personal time with operational demands.  \n    - It reflects proactive resource management ahead of a busy new year.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast Compilation","Paid Media Campaign","Ebook Marketing","HR 2808 Campaign","LinkedIn Business Manager","2026 Strategy Planning"],"overview":"- **Campaign Success:** HR 2808 campaign gaining traction, ranking on page one of Google, boosting brand positioning and lead generation.\n\n- **Lead Generation Metrics:** Two ebooks produced 170 form fills; latest email generated about 78 leads, validating content strategy.\n\n- **Podcast Quality Focus:** Planning to release a polished 30-35 minute podcast in mid-January, enhancing listener engagement and brand loyalty.\n\n- **Operational Efficiency:** Adding Business Manager access to LinkedIn for streamlined ad approvals, improving campaign execution efficiency.\n\n- **2026 Strategy Preparation:** Gab is developing a visual PowerPoint for 2025 metrics and 2026 themes to align team priorities and goals.\n\n- **Technical Training:** Gab and Tim attending podcast event in Vegas to improve production skills, ensuring high-quality content creation.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nPut a note on Pat Sullivan’s podcast recording about his coughing break to ensure proper editing (11:13)\nCoordinate with the team post-holidays to reconnect and support new goals or initiatives for 2025 and 2026 strategy (11:51)\nAccept Gab''s offer for equipment setup advice and arrange a call for late January (15:15)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nHide the podcast compilation slide from the current agenda and support delaying production to mid-January (04:01)\nEnsure timely sharing of LinkedIn business manager ID with Baylee via Slack immediately after the meeting (15:45)\n\n**Christina Bila**\nLead on adding the business manager to the LinkedIn account for paid campaign simplification and manage approvals (07:45)\n\n**Gabrielle Verzella**\nReview blog banner final assets, provide feedback, and coordinate comments via Slack if necessary (06:27)\nShare 2026 strategic visual once finalized to align on marketing themes and yearly plan (12:19)\nManage scheduling around expected January vacation and ensure coverage by team members or via Slack (13:50)\n\n**Tim Finnigan**\nDevelop more thoughtful podcast compilation with scripted intros, outros, and guest acknowledgments for mid-January release (03:09)\nContinue tracking ebook campaign performance and brand engagement metrics (10:35)\nCommunicate travel plans impacting meetings and support coverage arrangements (13:51)\n"},"duration":16.350000381469727,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Gab"},{"id":1,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":2,"name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":4,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"sentences":[{"text":"The name of this brand?","index":0,"end_time":1.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1,"end_time":1.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.12,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":2,"end_time":3.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My partner''s a firefighter, so they got a uniform.","index":3,"end_time":6.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Volunteer or.","index":4,"end_time":7.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.96,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":5,"end_time":8.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Full time?","index":6,"end_time":9.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Full time.","index":7,"end_time":10.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":8,"end_time":10.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":9,"end_time":11.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":11.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They all wear the same thing.","index":10,"end_time":13.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":11.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bailey, I know what I want for Christmas from you.","index":11,"end_time":16.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":14.32,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"What''s that?","index":12,"end_time":18.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":17.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know what I want from.","index":13,"end_time":19.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":18.72,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"For Christmas from you.","index":14,"end_time":21.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":20,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Are you ready?","index":15,"end_time":21.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":21.16,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":16,"end_time":22.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":21.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My wife is obsessed with Chicago Fire, and there''s this particular firefighter that she loves on the show.","index":17,"end_time":29.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":23.2,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Could you send me, like, firefighter gear?","index":18,"end_time":32.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":30.07,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Oh.","index":19,"end_time":33.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I can dress up as a surpriser.","index":20,"end_time":38.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":34.55,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"This is.","index":21,"end_time":41.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":41.35,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I did do this, so I''m going to be quiet because she''s upstairs.","index":22,"end_time":44.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":41.83,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I was at Target, and I bought her, like, a toy fire truck.","index":23,"end_time":49.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":44.55,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It''s like, this big.","index":24,"end_time":50.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":49.79,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And then I was able on Amazon to find, like, little cutouts of the people from Chicago Fire that I''m going to put in, like, the fire truck.","index":25,"end_time":60.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":51.59,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And she''s going to say, why did you waste money on this present?","index":26,"end_time":64.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":60.91,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"That''s what her reaction is going to be.","index":27,"end_time":66.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":64.35,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"No, you got to do it for the bit.","index":28,"end_time":69.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s amazing.","index":29,"end_time":70.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":69.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":30,"end_time":70.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":70.43,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"You gotta go.","index":31,"end_time":72.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":71.15,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":72.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":72.51,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"You just gotta follow through.","index":33,"end_time":74.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":72.87,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":34,"end_time":74.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, those are my favorite kind of gifts.","index":35,"end_time":77.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m like, wow, you''ll never forget those.","index":36,"end_time":80.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Good to know.","index":37,"end_time":85.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Your wife loves that show, though.","index":38,"end_time":86.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"People just love firefighters.","index":39,"end_time":88.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How can you not save lives?","index":40,"end_time":91.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":88.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They''re just saving lives.","index":41,"end_time":92.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":91.8,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like, that''s what they do.","index":42,"end_time":93.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.68,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":43,"end_time":96.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":95.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If.","index":44,"end_time":97.319,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":96.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"If you mess up in your job.","index":45,"end_time":98.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":97.319,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"No one''s losing their life, Bailey.","index":46,"end_time":100.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":98.8,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like that.","index":47,"end_time":101.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.72,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Except.","index":48,"end_time":102.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Except you, Bailey.","index":49,"end_time":104.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":102.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Just me might lose some money, but it''s not the same.","index":50,"end_time":109.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":107,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":51,"end_time":110.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.45,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s like, we''ll just fix it tomorrow.","index":52,"end_time":112.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":110.65,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":53,"end_time":113.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":112.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":54,"end_time":115.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, they''re the person who everyone wants.","index":55,"end_time":119.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"To talk to at a party.","index":56,"end_time":120.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":119.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nobody cares what I do, but everybody cares what a firefighter does.","index":57,"end_time":125.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":120.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":58,"end_time":126.569,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":126.21,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Your stories can''t even compare.","index":59,"end_time":128.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":126.569,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"No.","index":60,"end_time":128.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":128.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":61,"end_time":129.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":128.61,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"My coolest story is that we launched an awesome ebook.","index":62,"end_time":135.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":131.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s the right answer.","index":63,"end_time":138.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.37,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":64,"end_time":138.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I also put you in a post.","index":65,"end_time":142.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":141.24,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like, that was good.","index":66,"end_time":143.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.76,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"You probably didn''t expect that, did you, Bailey?","index":67,"end_time":145.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":143.88,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I know.","index":68,"end_time":146.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That made me smile.","index":69,"end_time":147.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":146.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I actually forwarded that to the entire team.","index":70,"end_time":149.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":147.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I was like, look how cool we are.","index":71,"end_time":154.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":149.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We did that.","index":72,"end_time":156.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.4,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I went to a Christmas party last night, and some of my friends were like, oh, I saw your post about being number one.","index":73,"end_time":162.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":156.6,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I''m like, it''s not like I wanted whoever did.","index":74,"end_time":165.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":162.16,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It''s not like the Oscars.","index":75,"end_time":167.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.72,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It''s more like a Daytime Emmy.","index":76,"end_time":168.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":167.17,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like, but it''s still.","index":77,"end_time":169.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":168.61,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It''s still good.","index":78,"end_time":170.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":169.73,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like, I''m not complaining about it.","index":79,"end_time":172.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":170.53,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It''s a.","index":80,"end_time":175.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s a big deal in in our niche world.","index":81,"end_time":178.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":175.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Number one, B2C award winning or whatever.","index":82,"end_time":184.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":180.93,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We''re winning.","index":83,"end_time":186.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.97,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"All right.","index":84,"end_time":189.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":189.09,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Do.","index":85,"end_time":189.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":189.53,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Do you want my.","index":86,"end_time":191.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":189.85,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I need to tell you my excuse.","index":87,"end_time":193.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":191.17,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I don''t even have an excuse.","index":88,"end_time":195.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":194.43,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I''m just not doing it.","index":89,"end_time":197.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":195.87,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Okay?","index":90,"end_time":197.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.03,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"This is what happened.","index":91,"end_time":198.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.43,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"The compilation.","index":92,"end_time":201.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":200.51,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"We are going to do it.","index":93,"end_time":202.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":201.75,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"We''re just not going to do it now.","index":94,"end_time":203.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":202.67,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I want to do it right.","index":95,"end_time":205.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":204.67,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I don''t want, like, my whole idea was, let''s do a quick one, 10, 15 minutes.","index":96,"end_time":209.389,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":205.87,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"That''s the wrong idea.","index":97,"end_time":210.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.39,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I need to do a better intro outro and then an intro of each person or each sort of subject matter.","index":98,"end_time":217.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":210.55,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And I want it to be a full blown 30, 35 minute thing.","index":99,"end_time":220.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":217.63,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"That''s just not going to happen before Christmas.","index":100,"end_time":223.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":221.36,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Just.","index":101,"end_time":228.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":227.84,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Just don''t even question it because then I''ll just do that.","index":102,"end_time":232.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":228.24,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Then I''m like, no, okay, I''ll do it today.","index":103,"end_time":234.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":232.88,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I.","index":104,"end_time":235.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":235.04,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"We''re not.","index":105,"end_time":237.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":236.959,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Just leave me alone.","index":106,"end_time":239.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":238.4,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"We''re not doing it.","index":107,"end_time":240.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":239.4,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Let me hide that slide.","index":108,"end_time":242.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":241.36,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Let me hide that slide in the agenda.","index":109,"end_time":246,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":243.76,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Hide the slide.","index":110,"end_time":247.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":246.32,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but.","index":111,"end_time":254.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":253.18,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, Bailey, what do you think then?","index":112,"end_time":255.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":254.18,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So, Tim, if I may jump in.","index":113,"end_time":258.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":255.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So, Bailey, what do you think then about.","index":114,"end_time":261.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":259.02,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So just doing something like extending the script between.","index":115,"end_time":269.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":263.66,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"In between every.","index":116,"end_time":271.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":270.06,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Like something we''re doing for the other client.","index":117,"end_time":274.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":271.42,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":118,"end_time":275.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":274.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think, Tim, you were planning on writing your own script.","index":119,"end_time":278.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":120,"end_time":278.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":278.62,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":121,"end_time":279.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":122,"end_time":280.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":280.14,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":123,"end_time":281.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll.","index":124,"end_time":282.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll just pause then for now.","index":125,"end_time":283.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And yeah, as I''m thinking of it, if we can do this in mid, like have it published in mid January or something, I get it done.","index":126,"end_time":291.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":283.66,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I can do a thoughtful way, I can talk about it because I don''t do a lot of that where I not talk about personal stuff.","index":127,"end_time":300.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":291.18,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"But I don''t go right into the guest.","index":128,"end_time":302.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":300.9,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":129,"end_time":302.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.46,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I want to thank, like, all the guests.","index":130,"end_time":304.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.02,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Hey, we had a great 20, 25.","index":131,"end_time":305.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.66,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"We had all these guests.","index":132,"end_time":306.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":305.98,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"We talked about this.","index":133,"end_time":307.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.86,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I like to thank Gab, who''s the producer, and she really does this.","index":134,"end_time":312.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.17,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like, I want to be thoughtful about it rather than do it.","index":135,"end_time":316.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":312.17,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And I just haven''t had time to put a lot of effort into it.","index":136,"end_time":320.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":316.77,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds great.","index":137,"end_time":323.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":321.93,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s do it that way.","index":138,"end_time":324.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":323.01,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Cool.","index":139,"end_time":325.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":324.97,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay then, so let''s quickly go through everything we have for today.","index":140,"end_time":334.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":327.85,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And it''s.","index":141,"end_time":335.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":334.33,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s not a lot.","index":142,"end_time":336.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":335.56,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s the end of the year.","index":143,"end_time":337.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":336.28,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We''re winding down.","index":144,"end_time":342.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":341.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":145,"end_time":347.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":347.24,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And by the way, we have new design for the weekly agenda.","index":146,"end_time":353.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":348.28,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":147,"end_time":353.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":353.04,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Delivered assets, tofu and mofu designs, and then these blog.","index":148,"end_time":366.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":357.64,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So blog recap and the social posts for that.","index":149,"end_time":371.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":366.01,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And also the, the.","index":150,"end_time":373.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":371.97,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The adored Blog banner and prompting design is right.","index":151,"end_time":380.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":373.61,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Gab, did you.","index":152,"end_time":381.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":380.69,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Did you had the time to look at the blog banner I sent?","index":153,"end_time":385.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":381.57,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"No.","index":154,"end_time":387.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":387.26,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Did that come through this morning?","index":155,"end_time":389.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.74,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think I sent it, but I. I will double check.","index":156,"end_time":393.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":390.38,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, I think I. I just took a chance.","index":157,"end_time":397.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":393.5,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":158,"end_time":397.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":397.58,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":398.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":397.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And it''s only like final assets because it''s basically just the size.","index":160,"end_time":403.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":398.18,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Size change.","index":161,"end_time":404.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":403.5,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":162,"end_time":404.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":404.46,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Compared to the.","index":163,"end_time":406.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":405.5,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The social graphic post.","index":164,"end_time":410.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":408.78,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":165,"end_time":411.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So if you have any feedback, you can just still.","index":166,"end_time":414.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":412.15,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":167,"end_time":415.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":414.79,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Like just comment or in Slack or.","index":168,"end_time":419.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":415.19,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":169,"end_time":419.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":419.11,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay, then we''re working on the two podcast episodes and of course, campaign management.","index":170,"end_time":429.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":421.59,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We are going to go back to the campaign in a couple of slides.","index":171,"end_time":440.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":435.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":172,"end_time":441.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":441.43,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":173,"end_time":441.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":441.59,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The upcoming priorities and deadlines to podcast episodes and regarding the campaign.","index":174,"end_time":450.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":441.95,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So our paid media specialist asked if we could just work on adding our business Manager into your LinkedIn account, if that''s possible.","index":175,"end_time":466.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":451.75,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Because that way it would be easier.","index":176,"end_time":469.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":467.93,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That way you wouldn''t have to approve everyone''s request, if that''s okay with.","index":177,"end_time":478.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":470.09,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So this is the business manager ID and we can send it over.","index":178,"end_time":482.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":478.85,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":179,"end_time":486.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.85,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Christina, do you want to take lead on that?","index":180,"end_time":488.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":486.21,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Sure, I can.","index":181,"end_time":489.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":489.05,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"All right, Cool.","index":182,"end_time":490.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.17,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":183,"end_time":492.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":491.45,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":184,"end_time":492.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":492.09,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And these are some comments for the adroll campaign.","index":185,"end_time":497.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":493.21,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So apart from the one we''re already running, it would be great.","index":186,"end_time":502.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":497.37,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So since the retargeting campaign may take some time to fill up volume, it would be good to add another like ad set to it.","index":187,"end_time":513.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":502.46,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So with.","index":188,"end_time":516.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":514.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"By targeting keywords, basically.","index":189,"end_time":520.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":518.62,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And this works basically if a website where the one of the ads appears is somehow related to the topic of HR and contains some of these keywords like HR 2808 or Home Buyers Privacy Protection act or somewhere along these lines.","index":190,"end_time":539.999,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":520.7,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So it would automatically.","index":191,"end_time":543.079,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":540.959,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The ad will automatically appear there.","index":192,"end_time":546.159,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":543.079,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So that''s another thing we can do to extend the number of people and number of people we can reach, actually.","index":193,"end_time":556.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":546.479,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":194,"end_time":556.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":556.46,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So that''s something we can think about for the campaign.","index":195,"end_time":561.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":556.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":196,"end_time":564.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":564.14,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yeah, that''s it.","index":197,"end_time":567.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":565.26,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It was very quick.","index":198,"end_time":568.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":567.3,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"But if you have any questions.","index":199,"end_time":570.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":568.62,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Shoot.","index":200,"end_time":571.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":570.62,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"No, not a question, but just we have seen some traction for the HR 2808 campaign.","index":201,"end_time":578.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.06,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Like we had an upsell come through on a customer or I think it''s upsell.","index":202,"end_time":583.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.86,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Wow.","index":203,"end_time":583.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And that''s one other opportunity I can''t speak to if it''s related to a targeted ad, but it''s working nice.","index":204,"end_time":594.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.76,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"If you search HR 2808 on Google, we''re like one of the first tech kind of data solution companies that pops up on page one, you know, establishing that we''re ahead of most other competitors.","index":205,"end_time":608.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.44,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So Pat, on the Back for all of the teams involved with telling us to put that out there sooner rather than later.","index":206,"end_time":616.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.59,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, and then also on the ebook front, we sent out our third email, and that got us another 12 form fills.","index":207,"end_time":624.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":617.79,"speaker_nam