-- Meeting: GSS // MID Weekly Meeting (2025-12-17 16:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '6061d0c2-de11-40b9-8824-1ccd80a970d6',
    '2025-12-17 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KC4GPEK7T0T888BJ8AGNZ9YM',
    'GSS // MID Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Baylee Gunnell","Nick S (GSS)","Will Fleming","Guille Santana"}'::text[],
    1544,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83236942727?pwd=NaLGKm3JEGM6umJeSVS9pHPmDfNAYN.1',
    '{"id":"01KC4GPEK7T0T888BJ8AGNZ9YM","title":"GSS // MID Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Production and Campaign Management**\n\nThe team is progressing well with content and has adapted campaign timing to match market rhythm.\n\n- **Two blog posts are in progress, focusing on the CFO talent crisis and cost of CFO turnover, both based on a recent interview with Will Fleming** (00:45)  \n    - One blog post is live, linked to the latest podcast episode with Gary Ma, highlighting audit cost alignment.  \n    - The newsletter is set for review and distribution within this week, maintaining engagement momentum.  \n    - Baylee Gunnell noted no new major issues, indicating steady content flow.\n\n- **New ABM campaigns launched with connection requests sent, but no responses yet, likely due to seasonal slowdowns** (01:49)  \n    - Campaigns will pause Friday before holidays and restart January 2nd to align with typical business cycles.  \n    - Nick S raised concerns about connection targeting accuracy, noting some non-C-suite contacts from previous campaigns.  \n    - Baylee confirmed new campaigns target only C-suite roles; feedback on mismatches will be reviewed and lists adjusted accordingly.  \n    - Nick found value in a corporate trainer response, showing flexibility in engagement beyond strict titles.\n\n- **Client portal shows a positive points balance of 94 with a negative 29 points balance, allowing room for increased activity next year** (05:02)  \n    - This financial health supports continued or expanded content and campaign efforts without immediate resource constraints.\n\n## **Website Traffic and Engagement Metrics**\n\nWebsite traffic has grown significantly this year, driven mainly by direct visits and service-focused content.\n\n- **Overall website sessions increased by 44% to about 8,000 in 2023, with visitors spending the most time on service pages like bank reconciliations for Taco Bell** (06:14)  \n    - Pages about restaurant accounting and global shared services hold engagement times around 90 seconds, signaling strong content relevance.  \n    - Baylee linked October-November traffic spikes directly to ABM outreach, confirming campaign impact on brand recognition.\n\n- **Direct traffic dominates with 6,460 sessions, up 115% year-over-year, indicating strong brand recall and repeat visitors** (08:12)  \n    - Organic traffic fell 42% to 2,100 sessions, reflecting industry-wide decline due to AI tools reducing traditional search visits.  \n    - Referrals, email, and organic social are smaller but growing traffic sources, showing modest diversification in visitor acquisition.\n\n- **Organic traffic favors brand and service pages, with the About Us page leading at 477 visits, while educational blog content saw declines** (10:10)  \n    - This suggests visitors prioritize credibility and core service information over niche educational content.  \n    - Will Fleming confirmed limited opportunity in McDonald''s-related content due to market exclusivity and client restrictions.  \n    - Baylee noted such blog content may be deprioritized or refreshed to regain relevance.\n\n## **Content Effectiveness and Future Strategy**\n\nNew content focused on industry challenges is gaining traction, while multimedia and newsletters show strong engagement needing further development.\n\n- **Top new pages this year include “How GSS approaches the market” with 120 visits and “From labor costs to AI restaurant ROI tactics” with 114 visits, showing demand for strategic insights** (14:30)  \n    - This trend guides future content priorities toward addressing industry challenges and strategic advice.\n\n- **YouTube videos garnered 234 views since launching mid-April, establishing a baseline for growth in video engagement next year** (15:50)  \n    - Podcast downloads are low at 25 since publishing, indicating a need for better promotion on platforms like Spotify and Apple Podcasts.  \n    - Guille Santana suggested prioritizing podcast marketing next year to leverage its lead generation potential.\n\n- **Newsletters outperform industry averages with open rates between 45% and 55%, and the highest click rate at 11.4% in November, signaling strong reader interest** (17:20)  \n    - The upcoming newsletter aims to close the year maintaining these strong engagement metrics.\n\n## **Market Conditions and Sales Engagement Outlook**\n\nDespite strong content engagement, sales conversations remain subdued due to seasonal and cyclical market factors, with cautious optimism for early 2024.\n\n- **Will Fleming highlighted that current engagement is the lowest in company history during what is usually a peak season from September to January** (18:26)  \n    - He expects a potential interest rebound in Q1 2024, driven by anticipated rate cuts and pent-up demand in the restaurant industry.  \n    - Will emphasized the cyclical nature of the market and the importance of investing early in processes to manage downturns effectively.\n\n- **Baylee and Will agreed to explore content focused on tax season as a trigger for client decision-making, while clarifying that tax services are not their core offering** (20:54)  \n    - The content will aim to encourage business reviews and potential service changes without positioning as tax advisors.\n\n- **Will cited a case study with Munson CFO group showing strong business insight improvements, underscoring the value of the service despite current market softness** (21:52)  \n    - This reinforces the messaging that process investment helps clients navigate cyclical downturns with better visibility.\n\n## **Partnership and Team Collaboration**\n\nThe team maintains strong communication and partnership dynamics, preparing for a holiday break with clear next steps.\n\n- **Baylee expressed gratitude for the partnership, emphasizing ongoing support and availability despite upcoming holiday absence** (24:43)  \n    - She encouraged open communication via email for any questions during the break to maintain momentum.  \n    - Will and Nick confirmed holiday schedules and appreciation, reinforcing a positive team culture.","outline":null,"keywords":["Content Strategy","ABM Campaign","Website Traffic","Organic Search","Podcast Promotion","Restaurant Industry Cycles"],"overview":"- **Content Production Progress:** Two blog posts on CFO crises underway; one live, with newsletter distribution this week.  \n- **New ABM Campaigns Launch:** Campaigns paused for holidays, targeting C-suite only; feedback on connection accuracy to be reviewed.  \n- **Strong Website Traffic Growth:** Sessions up 44% to 8,000; direct traffic increased significantly, while organic traffic fell 42%.  \n- **YouTube and Newsletter Engagement:** YouTube videos at 234 views; newsletters show 45-55% open rates, signaling strong interest.  \n- **Sales Engagement Outlook:** Seasonal softness in sales; optimism for Q1 2024 due to expected market improvements and tax season content planned.  \n- **Team Collaboration:** Ongoing support emphasized; holiday communication encouraged to maintain momentum and positive culture.","action_items":"\n**Guille Santana**\nFinalize and send newsletter for review this week (01:49)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell & Guille Santana**\nReview and remove non-target LinkedIn connection requests upon receiving Nick’s feedback links (03:09)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nMonitor and optimize website form fills to improve lead conversion from traffic, discuss further strategies next year (18:26)\nContinue conversation with client about ABM campaign resumption post-holidays and ways to increase engagement and nurture leads (24:00)\n\n**Marketing Team**\nEnhance promotion of podcasts on Spotify and Apple Podcasts to improve downloads and engagement in 2025 (16:50)\n\n**Content Team**\nPlan and produce tax season related content focused on restaurant year-end financial insights without framing as tax preparation (20:54)\n"},"duration":25.739999771118164,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"id":2,"name":"Will Fleming"},{"id":3,"name":"Guille Santana"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Good.","index":0,"end_time":0.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Love to hear it.","index":1,"end_time":1.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we''ve got really exciting things today.","index":2,"end_time":5.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we mentioned last week we''re going to do a 2025 content review, so super excited to go over that, but we''ll wrap up the meeting with that.","index":3,"end_time":16.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so we''ll go over some content updates, your ABM campaign, and then we''ll hop into the content review.","index":4,"end_time":31.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But any.","index":5,"end_time":31.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Anything else you all want to chat about today?","index":6,"end_time":33.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t got anything.","index":7,"end_time":37.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":36.62,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":8,"end_time":38.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":38.3,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":9,"end_time":40.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ll kick it to Guille for this.","index":10,"end_time":44.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All righty.","index":11,"end_time":46.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":45.26,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So some quick content updates.","index":12,"end_time":50.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":46.62,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We currently have two blog posts in progress.","index":13,"end_time":54.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":51.02,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"One focuses on the CFO talent crisis and the other one looks at risk analysis, specifically the cost of CFO turnover.","index":14,"end_time":66.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":54.94,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And we are basing both blog posts of the interview that we did last week with Will.","index":15,"end_time":72.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":66.68,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We also have one block live right now.","index":16,"end_time":79.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":75.16,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s rowing in the same direction how alignment codes, audit costs.","index":17,"end_time":85.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":80.36,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And this one''s based on our latest podcast episode.","index":18,"end_time":88.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":85.32,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That''s the one with Gary Ma.","index":19,"end_time":91.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":89.56,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And we also like.","index":20,"end_time":97.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":94.76,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Lastly, we have our newsletter in progress and we''ll send it out for review next week.","index":21,"end_time":103.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":97.16,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"No, this week, sorry, this week.","index":22,"end_time":106.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":103.48,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Then hopping into abm.","index":23,"end_time":110.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have the new campaigns launched, so we''re sending out connect connections.","index":24,"end_time":116.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":111,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''ve had a couple people accept them also.","index":25,"end_time":119.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":116.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We haven''t had any responses yet, though, and I''m.","index":26,"end_time":123.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I honestly, I''m guessing it''s just this time of year, people are really busy.","index":27,"end_time":127.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":123.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m seeing that across all of our other clients, too, that things are pretty slow.","index":28,"end_time":131.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think we talked about last week.","index":29,"end_time":133.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll pause the campaigns Friday right before the holidays and get them started Back up again January 2nd.","index":30,"end_time":141.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":133.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But any questions or anything else you want to chat about with this.","index":31,"end_time":145.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My, my, this one thing.","index":32,"end_time":153.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":149.7,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So what I''ve noticed is where, where are we finding the connection request list in LinkedIn?","index":33,"end_time":158.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.3,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Because I''ve been going through it and I''m seeing, you know, quite a few people with their titles that might not be.","index":34,"end_time":167.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":159.86,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I mean, they''re connected to a hospitality group, but it''s somebody I wouldn''t target, per se.","index":35,"end_time":172.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.98,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Not that it''s a bad thing, but, like, I''m looking at.","index":36,"end_time":178.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.23,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You know, a.","index":37,"end_time":182.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":181.51,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Few of them and it''s like director of marketing or a catering manager.","index":38,"end_time":186.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.07,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I think those might have been from the previous campaign because this new one should only be.","index":39,"end_time":196.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we only did, like, CEOs, like the C Suite.","index":40,"end_time":202.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But if, if, if you have the links to those that you feel like aren''t a good fit and you want to shoot them over to us.","index":41,"end_time":210.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll look at that and just confirm that that was the previous campaign, but the new one should be all just C suite.","index":42,"end_time":217.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess I couldn''t.","index":43,"end_time":220.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.26,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess I couldn''t.","index":44,"end_time":221.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.3,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I don''t know when these requests went out, when they accepted them.","index":45,"end_time":224.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":221.58,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So that''s a good point.","index":46,"end_time":226.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.5,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I mean, I''m looking at one right now.","index":47,"end_time":228.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.94,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And she responded, which was great.","index":48,"end_time":230.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.3,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"She responded yesterday and will.","index":49,"end_time":232.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":230.66,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It''s actually from Turning Point Restaurants, but it''s.","index":50,"end_time":235.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.98,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"She''s a corporate trainer, which it''s actually okay because her response was, hey, I''m on the corporate training side.","index":51,"end_time":246.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.7,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I love to bounce some ideas about franchise, you know, franchisee and success and financial management.","index":52,"end_time":251.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.18,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Oh, you know, I can.","index":53,"end_time":253.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.5,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":54,"end_time":254.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You know, bend her ear and then talk to her about, you know, what value and things that we provide and we''re an option for their franchisees if needed.","index":55,"end_time":265.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.86,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And if not, they should be looking at these kind of things and just being a resource for them.","index":56,"end_time":270.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.82,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So.","index":57,"end_time":271.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":270.62,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But that''s kind of what I''m seeing.","index":58,"end_time":272.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":271.26,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"But in the next campaign that''s fine.","index":59,"end_time":275.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":273.58,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So that''s good.","index":60,"end_time":276.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.22,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"If they''re the, you know, the C suite level or, you know, the higher level financial management people that are the owners, that''ll be good.","index":61,"end_time":282.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":62,"end_time":284.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":283.57,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"If you see any.","index":63,"end_time":285.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you see any that don''t seem like a good fit, just send us the links to them and like we can pull them out of the campaigns and just keep that in mind for the next list we pull too.","index":64,"end_time":296.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that feedback''s helpful.","index":65,"end_time":298.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But I''m glad you got.","index":66,"end_time":301.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That was a great response though.","index":67,"end_time":303.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":306.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, then we''ll just quickly look into the client portal and then Guille is going to share the content report.","index":69,"end_time":314.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you can see.","index":70,"end_time":315.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Got a lot of stuff currently in progress, newsletter, blog posts, all of our monthly management tasks and then looking really good on points.","index":71,"end_time":327.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":315.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Right now currently have 94 and working with a negative 29 points balance.","index":72,"end_time":332.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that''s a pretty good place to be.","index":73,"end_time":335.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll have room for a lot more stuff next year too.","index":74,"end_time":338.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s a.","index":75,"end_time":340.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":339.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That feels really weird to say so close to the end of the year.","index":76,"end_time":344.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, and then do you want to share your screen?","index":77,"end_time":349.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, One second.","index":78,"end_time":357.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":350.5,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Reset.","index":79,"end_time":363.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":362.58,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"One moment.","index":80,"end_time":367.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":367.07,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Because I''m not finding the.","index":81,"end_time":368.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":367.59,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"If it''s not working, I can also share.","index":82,"end_time":373.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, could you share?","index":83,"end_time":375.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":374.67,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":84,"end_time":382.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":381.95,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right, so I''ll walk us through our content review for 2025.","index":85,"end_time":389.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":383.39,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s basically focused on how the website performed this year compared to last year and what the data is telling us about engagement and interest.","index":86,"end_time":400.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":390.97,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Right.","index":87,"end_time":401.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":400.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So here you can see that our overall traffic was about or is about 8,000 test sessions for this year, which is up 44% compared to last year.","index":88,"end_time":415.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":402.09,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So we are seeing some solid growth there on like overall active users.","index":89,"end_time":420.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":415.41,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And when we look at engagement and how much time people spend on pages, we can see that the bank reconciliations for Taco Bell page leads with just under like two minutes, followed by the restaurant accounting services and then about global shared services page are around a minute and a half.","index":90,"end_time":446.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":421.71,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I would say this tell us that visitors are spending the most time on service focused content, which it''s a good signal for like content relevance and what we''re producing.","index":91,"end_time":461.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":447.17,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So we grew pretty much on active users this year.","index":92,"end_time":466.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":463.41,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":93,"end_time":467.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ll also point out like if you look at this graph, a lot of growth here like starting October to November.","index":94,"end_time":474.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I would probably relate that to our ABM efforts.","index":95,"end_time":477.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":474.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think a lot of that came or you''ll see in the next slide, a lot of that did come from just direct traffic, people coming through our outreach.","index":96,"end_time":486.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":478.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Right.","index":97,"end_time":492.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":492.19,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So this slide shows us our top sources of traffic by sessions.","index":98,"end_time":499.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":492.91,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And sessions means like a visit to a website.","index":99,"end_time":501.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":499.31,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"One person can generate multiple sessions to a website if they come back different times.","index":100,"end_time":510.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":504.11,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Right.","index":101,"end_time":510.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":510.03,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So direct traffic is by far the largest driver with 6,460 sessions.","index":102,"end_time":519.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":511.31,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That''s an increase of 115% for this year.","index":103,"end_time":524.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":519.71,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"This like suggests like brand recognition and returning visitors.","index":104,"end_time":530.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":525.15,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"This is what this is telling us.","index":105,"end_time":532.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":530.43,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Right.","index":106,"end_time":532.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":532.35,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And for organic traffic we can see that we are at 2,100 sessions and this is down by 42% which is something that we want to keep an eye on.","index":107,"end_time":546.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":533.6,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But we also know why this is happening.","index":108,"end_time":548.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":546.28,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And this is happening across all industries.","index":109,"end_time":551.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":548.96,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s been mainly because of large language models like ChatGPT.","index":110,"end_time":556.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":552.32,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"People are in like people aren''t Googling anymore or if they are googling, they can see the snippets before they go to the pages.","index":111,"end_time":566.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":557.68,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So this is why we are also focusing on other sources as well.","index":112,"end_time":572.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":566.66,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Referrals, email and organic social are like smaller contributors, but they are all like trending up and it''s showing like modest growth.","index":113,"end_time":586.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":574.66,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I will say overall we''re seeing strength in direct traffic with opportunities to like rebuild momentum in organic search if we play our cards right this next year.","index":114,"end_time":600.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":586.97,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Right.","index":115,"end_time":604.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":604.09,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And now we can see like how we performed organically.","index":116,"end_time":609.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":604.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We can see on the left table, starting with the top page winners, we''re seeing that the strongest organic traffic came from the About Us page, which leads with 477 visits followed by accounting services, services Partners and the press room, they are all performing well.","index":117,"end_time":633.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":610.98,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And on the other hand we have like the top page losers which are mostly educational content.","index":118,"end_time":639.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":634.26,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"For example, your guide to McDonald''s outsourced accounting or the top mistakes in Restaurant 365 implementation.","index":119,"end_time":651.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":641.94,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Where like the, where we saw like very low organic business here.","index":120,"end_time":656.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":651.86,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But we can see like, or this tell us that organic traffic is currently favoring brand service and credibility and less like blog style educational content and very niche.","index":121,"end_time":672.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":659.22,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So I don''t know if something happened to McDonald''s this year that I don''t know drove.","index":122,"end_time":678.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":672.96,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"People were googling less.","index":123,"end_time":680.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":678.72,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I, I guess or if you did a campaign last year for this content.","index":124,"end_time":685.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":680.6,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But this is what we''re seeing overall with organic traffic.","index":125,"end_time":690.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":685.84,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And this maybe is an opportunity if you, if you feel like these blogs are still important, we can refresh them to try and increase the rankings again.","index":126,"end_time":700.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But they also might not be super relevant anymore.","index":127,"end_time":702.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":128,"end_time":703.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t think McDonald''s, I mean if, even if that was removed, it wouldn''t be.","index":129,"end_time":709.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":705.29,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean we don''t work in McDonald''s.","index":130,"end_time":711.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":709.37,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"McDonald''s is very.","index":131,"end_time":712.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":711.21,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Limited.","index":132,"end_time":717.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":717.21,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean there''s, there''s probably less than five firms that do all the outsourcing work in the United States for them.","index":133,"end_time":726.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":717.85,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So it''s, they''re not, they''re.","index":134,"end_time":729.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":726.22,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They can be hard to penetrate and they don''t like, sometimes they complain if you''re working with other competing brands.","index":135,"end_time":739.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":729.9,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":136,"end_time":739.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":739.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s not uncommon to see one firm and all they do is McDonald''s.","index":137,"end_time":744.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":739.9,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So.","index":138,"end_time":745.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":745.59,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":139,"end_time":746.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":140,"end_time":747.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":747.43,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay.","index":141,"end_time":748.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":748.31,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So then it seems like these are less of a priority.","index":142,"end_time":751.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''m not worried about these.","index":143,"end_time":754.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Overall, we saw almost every single page on your website saw an increase in traffic.","index":144,"end_time":760.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":754.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"These were like very select few that saw decreases.","index":145,"end_time":763.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.309,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And even so, the decreases weren''t that large.","index":146,"end_time":766.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think people are drawn to the site for either just general service service needs for restaurants or brand needs.","index":147,"end_time":779.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":769.03,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then they, they, they check us out.","index":148,"end_time":782.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":780.05,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They.","index":149,"end_time":783.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.01,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay, who''s, who''s the about.","index":150,"end_time":785.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.49,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Who''s in the about page.","index":151,"end_time":787.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":785.65,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And that''s sort of the credibility process that people go through.","index":152,"end_time":790.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":787.17,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yep, that''s what the data seems to be showing.","index":153,"end_time":795.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":154,"end_time":798.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":797.98,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And then this slide is very similar, but this one shows overall traffic.","index":155,"end_time":803.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":798.54,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So this includes all visits to the website that come from direct referrals, email, socials, pretty much everything that organic doesn''t cover.","index":156,"end_time":813.739,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":803.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"On the left we can see if we look at overall traffic, the top pages are more conversion and credibility focused.","index":157,"end_time":823.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":816.14,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So like the let''s talk page about gsl, the pressroom, accounting services and services.","index":158,"end_time":831.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":823.74,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"They are like our core pages and this tells us that our visitors are moving beyond discovery and more into like an evaluation and contact like phase.","index":159,"end_time":846.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":831.67,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So they''re looking at this conversion LED pages and similar to what we saw with organic traffic, the top page losers are like longer form blog contents and very niche like McDonald''s or Restaurant 365.","index":160,"end_time":862.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":846.55,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yep.","index":161,"end_time":868.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And well this slide highlights the top pages that we created this year.","index":162,"end_time":877.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":870.48,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The leading one being how GSS approaches the market with 120 visits followed by from labor costs to AI restaurant Roi Tactics at 114.","index":163,"end_time":892.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":877.84,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And you can see all the other pages and how much traffic they are generating.","index":164,"end_time":900.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":894.36,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I would say these numbers show that the new content that we''re building is gaining traction particularly when it addresses like challenges, challenges and like strategic insights for the industry.","index":165,"end_time":916.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":902.12,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So moving on, I would say we should create content that''s similar to this because we''re seeing this is what''s driving the most traffic.","index":166,"end_time":924.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":917.09,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Your YouTube stats, your videos got 234 views this year.","index":167,"end_time":939.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":932.77,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We didn''t have a YouTube last year so there''s nothing to compare it to.","index":168,"end_time":943.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":939.15,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And while 234I would say it''s a good number.","index":169,"end_time":949.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":945.07,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"If I see we started mid April it will give us a baseline for to measure growth next year and engagement and video content moving forward.","index":170,"end_time":959.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":949.15,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So you''re telling me I''m not a YouTube star?","index":171,"end_time":966.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":964.12,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Not yet.","index":172,"end_time":968.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":967.8,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"You''re setting the foundation.","index":173,"end_time":971.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":970.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then for bus route we only had 25 downloads download.","index":174,"end_time":983.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":978.6,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Since publish like our podcast is performing better on YouTube I will say we need to do a better job promoting Spotify and Apple podcast links.","index":175,"end_time":996.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":983.84,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Maybe this is something that we can talk to maybe next week or for next year.","index":176,"end_time":1003.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":997.75,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But you never know.","index":177,"end_time":1006.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1004.39,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Sometimes podcast can get you a lot of leads if you play your cards right.","index":178,"end_time":1012.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1006.07,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So I would say this is something that we need to focus on next year.","index":179,"end_time":1015.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1012.39,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And for the newsletters stats you can see here that your open rate or the industry average open rate for business and finance is around 25 and 30%.","index":180,"end_time":1038.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1021.33,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And you guys are way above average with 45%, 53%, 55%.","index":181,"end_time":1046.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1038.85,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So that''s a really good open rate.","index":182,"end_time":1048.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1046.5,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It means people are interested in your content and what we''re producing.","index":183,"end_time":1053.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1049.38,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And you can see the newsletter that got the highest click rate was the one you sent out in November with 11.4%.","index":184,"end_time":1066.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1054.58,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That''s the highest of all newsletters shown.","index":185,"end_time":1069.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1066.9,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So we should keep this going.","index":186,"end_time":1073.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1071.41,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We have the newsletter for your review this week so we can close the year with good numbers.","index":187,"end_time":1083.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1073.89,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s Everything, Lots of growth all around and always opportunities to keep improving things.","index":188,"end_time":1096.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1087.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we were pretty happy with how things have been performing so far.","index":189,"end_time":1101.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But did you have any questions or just comments?","index":190,"end_time":1104.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1101.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think the content, the content''s been great.","index":191,"end_time":1109.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1106.47,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I can see that it''s increasing our traffic.","index":192,"end_time":1112.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1109.99,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, hopefully the things will open up a little bit.","index":193,"end_time":1119.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.55,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean we need to figure out how to convert some of the, the growth in engagement to get Nick talking to them because I mean, I know this is what the ABM is all about, but I mean typically between September and January is our highest volume period of time and that''s just not been the case.","index":194,"end_time":1149.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1119.43,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"This is probably the lowest level of engagement we''ve had in the history.","index":195,"end_time":1156.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1150,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s just, I mean it''s, some of it''s just a challenging market and we can see it with our customers.","index":196,"end_time":1165.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1156.37,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But my feeling right now is that there''s going to be a rate cut in the first quarter and that''s going to, and it''s going to help.","index":197,"end_time":1175.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1166.29,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And I think there''s pent up demand.","index":198,"end_time":1178.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1175.73,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we, I think the fact that we''ve got the content, we''ve got the viewers, as you know, it takes time to nurture people and so hopefully that''ll, we can convert some of this in the first quarter into engagement.","index":199,"end_time":1194.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1179.34,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, I completely agree.","index":200,"end_time":1198.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1196.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And things seem to be moving in the right direction and we can, we''ll definitely keep talking about maybe ways we can try and get more form fills because you''re getting a lot of traffic to that page.","index":201,"end_time":1212.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1199.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It just seems like maybe something''s disconnected to, to people actually taking that next step.","index":202,"end_time":1218.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1212.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s just we''ll know more probably in this late January usually takes a little bit of time when the new year comes and then February it should be, we should get some pickup before tax season because I mean what happens is people go through a process either at the end of the year and they''re like I''m not going to do that again and then, or in the first quarter and they want to make a change.","index":203,"end_time":1249.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1221.66,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So hopefully we can see some of that.","index":204,"end_time":1253.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1249.96,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"That would be a good thing to maybe create some content on.","index":205,"end_time":1258.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1254.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"With tax season we could maybe get some specific articles about that.","index":206,"end_time":1264.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1259.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can, we can do that.","index":207,"end_time":1269.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1266.08,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I, We''ve had that kind of stuff before and people think we do taxes so we just.","index":208,"end_time":1275.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1269.16,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay, we need to be quick.","index":209,"end_time":1276.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1275.6,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like the tax, like we''re not, we don''t really care about taxes.","index":210,"end_time":1280.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1276.96,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s, it''s just an event for us.","index":211,"end_time":1282.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1280.72,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s like people, it gets People to make a change, but we don''t want to be the tax change, so to speak.","index":212,"end_time":1293.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1283.8,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":213,"end_time":1295.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But yeah, I mean year end stuff, how did the year turn out and were you up to date?","index":214,"end_time":1306.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1299.24,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Did you know where everything was?","index":215,"end_time":1308.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1306.6,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean just general stuff about.","index":216,"end_time":1309.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1308.28,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"How.","index":217,"end_time":1312.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Organized they are and how much do they know about their business and yeah, I mean we talk about this company Munson, which was this CFO group that we worked with this year and we, I know we did kind of a case study and talked about how much we''ve improved their, helped them improve their business and that stuff is, is very like, was very relevant and this year like we did a very good job.","index":218,"end_time":1343.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1312.49,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But what we''re seeing right now in that business is they''re kind of entering a little bit of a downturn in, but they know exactly what''s going on and they can say oh, we think it''s the snowstorm or the cold weather we''ve had and then we know where they''re missing, where they expected to be.","index":219,"end_time":1366.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1343.85,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I mean the, the restaurant industry is very cyclical.","index":220,"end_time":1370.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1366.76,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So times were great for the last five months and we got kind of our system in place and, and they''re very, they very, they were very well informed and, and they could see the improvements and they were very happy.","index":221,"end_time":1384.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1370.68,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like when we went to the show, they, they talked to other people and had good things to say about us.","index":222,"end_time":1389.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1384.92,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But now they''re not super happy.","index":223,"end_time":1392.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1390.2,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They''re not blaming us.","index":224,"end_time":1393.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1392.04,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, not, yeah, you know, this stuff is, is, is, is very cyclical.","index":225,"end_time":1401.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1393.12,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I mean right now hopefully it, you know, it''s just a holiday thing for them.","index":226,"end_time":1405.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1401.78,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But that''s kind of the nature of, of of the business that we''re in.","index":227,"end_time":1411.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1405.94,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It goes through cycles and I think we''re coming out of a, a downturn and, and, but even, you know, but you know, the sooner they make the change and get invested in processes, the more they can say okay, we know exactly what''s going on and we don''t have to overreact.","index":228,"end_time":1431.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1411.26,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We can see that this is a snow issue or whatever.","index":229,"end_time":1434.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1431.19,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, so, so, so yeah, that, that''s, I think it''s just, you know, with, it''s just I try to remind people that the company that, you know, things are very cyclical and you can''t use the word cyclical if, if you don''t have it moving up when it was moving down.","index":230,"end_time":1456.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1434.39,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we don''t have a permanent downturn so it''s going to improve.","index":231,"end_time":1461.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1456.46,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We just don''t know when.","index":232,"end_time":1462.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1461.5,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely goes through cycles though.","index":233,"end_time":1467.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1464.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I know we were always excited for it to start going back up and definitely see that on the horizon.","index":234,"end_time":1480.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1471.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":235,"end_time":1483.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1482.48,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But, yeah, thanks.","index":236,"end_time":1484.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1483.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thanks for hopping on today.","index":237,"end_time":1485.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1484.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We love working with you.","index":238,"end_time":1488.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1486.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re really grateful for the partnership we have with you.","index":239,"end_time":1492.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1488.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I know we''re not going to see you next week, but if you have questions, just send us a message over email and we''ll be in touch.","index":240,"end_time":1501.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1493.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":241,"end_time":1503.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1502.73,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Happy holidays.","index":242,"end_time":1503.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1503.05,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":243,"end_time":1504.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1503.89,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We''ll see you Christmas, everybody.","index":244,"end_time":1506.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1505.05,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Bye.","index":245,"end_time":1507.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1507.21,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Bye.","index":246,"end_time":1508.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1507.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2025-12-17T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83236942727?pwd=NaLGKm3JEGM6umJeSVS9pHPmDfNAYN.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,nstauff@gsslp.com,wfleming@gsslp.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","nstauff@gsslp.com","wfleming@gsslp.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KC4GPEK7T0T888BJ8AGNZ9YM","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Reported 44% annual growth in website traffic; highest engagement on service-focused pages.","Confirmed newsletter open rates consistently exceed 45%, outperforming 30% industry average.","Flagged drop in organic traffic but attributed trend to industry-wide shift toward AI tools.","Aligned on pausing ABM campaigns over holidays; resuming January 2 to improve engagement.","Identified opportunity to update underperforming blog content or deprioritize where relevance has declined."],"highlights":[{"quote":"The content''s been great. I can see that it''s increasing our traffic.","speaker":"Will Fleming"},{"quote":"We grew pretty much on active users this year.","speaker":"Guille Santana"},{"quote":"Lots of growth all around and always opportunities to keep improving things.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["traffic","content","abm","engagement"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-19T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content Production and Campaign Management**\n\nThe team is progressing well with content and has adapted campaign timing to match market rhythm.\n\n- **Two blog posts are in progress, focusing on the CFO talent crisis and cost of CFO turnover, both based on a recent interview with Will Fleming** (00:45)  \n    - One blog post is live, linked to the latest podcast episode with Gary Ma, highlighting audit cost alignment.  \n    - The newsletter is set for review and distribution within this week, maintaining engagement momentum.  \n    - Baylee Gunnell noted no new major issues, indicating steady content flow.\n\n- **New ABM campaigns launched with connection requests sent, but no responses yet, likely due to seasonal slowdowns** (01:49)  \n    - Campaigns will pause Friday before holidays and restart January 2nd to align with typical business cycles.  \n    - Nick S raised concerns about connection targeting accuracy, noting some non-C-suite contacts from previous campaigns.  \n    - Baylee confirmed new campaigns target only C-suite roles; feedback on mismatches will be reviewed and lists adjusted accordingly.  \n    - Nick found value in a corporate trainer response, showing flexibility in engagement beyond strict titles.\n\n- **Client portal shows a positive points balance of 94 with a negative 29 points balance, allowing room for increased activity next year** (05:02)  \n    - This financial health supports continued or expanded content and campaign efforts without immediate resource constraints.\n\n## **Website Traffic and Engagement Metrics**\n\nWebsite traffic has grown significantly this year, driven mainly by direct visits and service-focused content.\n\n- **Overall website sessions increased by 44% to about 8,000 in 2023, with visitors spending the most time on service pages like bank reconciliations for Taco Bell** (06:14)  \n    - Pages about restaurant accounting and global shared services hold engagement times a